<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<bible xml:lang="bko" backtTranslaltionDefaultLanguage="en" oxes="2.0">
  <book id="MRK" stage="Rev" version="C">
    <Annotation class="History">
      <Message author="JSW" created="2009-10-02 03:43:33Z" when="2009-10-02 03:43:33Z" stage="Draft">Max &amp; June Jacob; C&amp;B Grimes; CCC, CRS, UKAW; Cranfield, Crofts, UBS Handbook, TW resources; Gk comments added Oct 2005; Consultant checked with Gilles Gravelle &amp; 4 UNS's 29 March -- 1 April 1999; Read thru for NT by Chuck, Adriana;</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-02-24 10:38:25Z" when="2014-02-24 10:38:25Z" stage="Consult">Consultant Check: 29 March - 1 April 1999 in Kupang (UKAW?); Consultant: Gilles Gravelle, approved. Report: v2revise.doc; v3revise.doc</Message>
      <Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-07 05:04:16Z" when="2015-01-07 05:04:16Z" stage="Consult">Smoothing read through for Kupang mini-Bible with Chuck, Lena, Oma, Rina, 7 Jan 2015 at UBB. BT adjusted slightly to match.</Message>
    </Annotation>
    <p class="Header" usfm="h">Markus<bt>Markus</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">Tuhan Yesus pung Carita Bae<bt>Lord Yesus' *Gospel1 (Good Story)</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Secondary" usfm="mt2">iko<bt>following/according to</bt></p>
    <p class="Title Main" usfm="mt">Markus<bt>Markus</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="1" />
      <v n="1" />Ini carita bae. Ini, Tuhan Allah pung Ana<bt>This is a good story. It is the story of God's Child.</bt><note reference="1:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Kata &lt;Tuhan Allah pung Ana&gt; sonde ada dalam tulisan asli saparu.<bt>The words &lt;God's child&gt; are not in some original writings.</bt></note>pung carita. Dia pung nama Yesus Kristus, yang Tuhan Allah su tunju memang dari dolu. Dia pung carita mulai bagini:<bt>His name is Yesus *Kristus, whom God had already designated from long ago. His story begins like this: [KEY TERM (Christ): explicated as per TBT article.] [DISCOURSE: (book level structure): Mark lays out his purpose for writing this book here in vs. 1 “I want to present the case that Jesus is the Christ that God has been promising to send.” Note that he does not talk about Jesus' birth, but immediately starts in with John the Baptist—not Jesus. The point he is making to his Jewish audience in vs. 2-8 is: (yes, we all know that Elijah has to come before the Messiah can come); actually Elijah has already come in the form/life of John the Baptist. Look at all these points of comparison. NOTE: header about John the Baptist does not make sense if put before vs. 1.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis tukang sarani buka jalan kasi sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Yohanis, the habitual *Baptizer, opens the way/path for the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 3:1-12; Lukas 3:1-18; Yohanis 1:19-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Yesus balóm mulai Dia pung karjá, te Tuhan Allah su utus satu orang, nama Yohanis. Yohanis musti pi sadia jalan kasi Yesus pung datang. Te dolu-dolu, Tuhan Allah su pake Dia pung jubir satu, nama ba'i Yesaya. Dia su tulis memang bilang:<bt>Yesus had not yet begun His work, (but) God had already sent/commissioned a (certain) person, named Yohanis. Yohanis had to go prepare the path/way for Yesus' coming. Cuz (elaboration) long-long before, God had already used His *prophet1 (spokesperson), named forefather Yesaya. He wrote beforehand (= wrote before the event), saying:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dengar, ó! Beta suru Beta pung orang satu, ko pi buka jalan kasi sang Lu.<bt>&lt;&lt;Listen, ó! I am ordering/commanding a person of Mine, to go open the path/way for You. [EXEG: Gk here is /anggelos/ whose primary and normal sense is 1) ‘human messenger’, not 2) ‘supernatural angel’.]</bt><note reference="1:2" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Maleaki 3:1</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="3" />Itu orang nanti pi tampa sunyi, ko batarea bilang:<bt>That person will go to a place where there are no people, to shout, saying: [NOTE: check that your word for ‘shout’ can include a message, not just noise.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Samua orang siap-siap bekin bae jalan, ko tarima Tuhan pung datang!<bt>&lt;All people/everyone prepare/get ready to make good/fix the way/path, to receive the Lord/Master's coming!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bekin lurus jalan ko sambut sang Dia.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>Make straight the path to greet/welcome Him.&gt;&gt;&gt; [NOTE: ‘straight’ has both physical and moral overtones.] [STYLE: Hebrew poetic parallelisms are nicely mirrored in traditional poetry in lgs around Timor.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bekin rata jalan ko sambut sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Bekin rata jalan ko sambut sang Dia.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:3" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 40:3</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4-6" />Orang biasa pange sang Yohanis, Tukang Sarani. Dia tenga di tampa sunyi. Dia pung pakean bekin dari onta pung bulu. Dia pung ika pinggang bekin dari binatang pung kulit. Dia pung makanan, kalamak deng madu utan. [Yohanis pung cara idop ni, sama ke ba'i Elia dolu-dolu.]<bt>People usually called Yohanis, the habitual *Baptizer. He lived in a lonely place (=no people around). His clothes were made from camel's (loan) fur. His belt was made from animal skin. His food, was grasshoppers and wild/bush honey. [This way of life of Yohanis, was like forefather Elia long ago.] [EXEG: High-level book-level theme from 1:1 (Jesus is the Christ; Elijah will come before the Christ comes) that was obvious to a reasonably informed Jewish audience, but is not accessible or retrievable by Timor audiences.] [DISCOURSE: 4-6 restructured to get chronology and background-foreground info in the right order for RL patterns.]</bt><note reference="1:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Raja-raja dong 1:8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu waktu, banya orang dari kota Yerusalem, deng propinsi Yudea pung isi samua, datang katumu deng Yohanis di dia pung tampa. Dong datang ko mau lia sang Yohanis deng mau dengar dia pung ajaran. Yohanis kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong musti mangaku deng kasi tenga bosong pung sala samua, ko biar Tuhan Allah hapus buang itu sala dong. Ais bosong musti sarani dolo, ko jadi tanda bilang, bosong su babae deng Tuhan.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, many people from Yerusalem city (loan: kota), and all the contents of (=throughout) Yudea province (loan), came to meet with Yohanis at that place of his. [DISCOURSE: Jerusalem-Judea reordered to reflect RL worldview of importance.] They came because they wanted to see Yohanis and wanted to hear his teaching. He told them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl must *confess and leave behind/abandon all your *wrongs, so that *God will *forgive1 (erase throw away) those *wrongs. Then you-pl must get *baptized, as a sign that you are already again RECIP-good (=in a right/proper/good relationship) with the *Lord.&gt;&gt; [KEY TERMS: baptise, repent, forgive, sins. Make sure the term for forgive involves a change of heart, not merely a social act.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangaku sala has element of both"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">mangaku sala has element of both confess and stop doing; po'a buang (focus on inside); angka buang</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pantes: not necessarily every last person,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">pantes: not necessarily every last person, but lots, by a hyperbole common in Greek. Could be "plenny plenny," but "all" is OK.</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-06-20 08:03:32Z">[</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00296C.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Yohanis, Tukang Sarani<bt>Yohanis, the Habitual Baptizer</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dengar abis bagitu, ju dong mangaku sala, ais dia sarani sang dong di kali Yarden.<bt>After they *confessed their *sins, then he *baptised them in the Yarden stream/river.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="calop ko sarani ; sunge (implies"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">calop ko sarani ; sunge (implies always water) vs. kali (can have water or be just the bed) &gt; kali mati and parigi mati = dry</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti ada satu Orang yang lebe hebat dari beta mau datang. Biar cuma jadi Dia pung tukang suru-suru sa ju, beta sonde pantas.<bt>He told them saying, &lt;&lt;Later there is a (certain) Person who is more amazing/noteworthy than me going to come. Even to just be his *slave (person who is habitually ordered about), I'm not fitting/appropriate. [EXEG: removed figure of metaphor and kept grounds for comparison.]</bt><note reference="1:7" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani asli tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;tondo ko buka dia pung tali sapatu sa ju beta sonde pantas.&gt;&gt; Dia pung arti bilang, Yohanis cuma orang kici sa, biar jadi Tuhan Yesus pung tukang suru-suru sa ju, dia sonde pantas.<bt>The original Greek language writings, says, &lt;to just bow down in order to undo his shoe strap, it's not fitting/appropriate for me.&gt; It's meaning is Yohanis was just a little person (=low social status), even if he just became the Lord Yesus' *slave/servant, he wasn't fitting/appropriate.</bt></note><v n="8" />Beta cuma bisa sarani sang bosong pake aer sa, ma nanti Dia bekin lebe dari beta, te Dia bekin ponu bosong pung hati deng Tuhan pung Roh yang Barisi.&gt;&gt;<bt>I'm only able to *baptize you with water, but later He will do more than me, cuz (elaboration) He will make your-pl *livers full with God2's *Holy Spirit (=clean, free from impurities, undefiled, holy).&gt;&gt; [NOTE: literal ‘baptise with the HS’ is nonsensical in most languages. If we try to force the same parallel construction, people just guess vaguely.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rasuk: evil spirits control supernaturally, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">rasuk: evil spirits control supernaturally, but negative or destructive associations; topang (BI) = senda (KM) -support; setan naik; takana setan; Rote/Timor-sumanak/smanan; baras barisi/ hati barisi</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Collocation of &quot;baptize&quot; and &quot;Spirit&quot; is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">Collocation of "baptize" and "Spirit" is opaque; spelled out here.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yohanis sarani sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Yohanis *baptizes *Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 3:13-17; Lukas 3:21-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Itu waktu, Yesus datang dari kampong Nasaret di propinsi Galilea ko katumu sang Yohanis. Ju Yohanis sarani sang Dia di kali Yarden.<bt>At that time, Yesus came from the Nasaret village in Galilea province in order to meet Yohanis. Then Yohanis *baptized Him in the Yarden river. [KT: distinguish lake Galilee from the province of Galilee throughout, as per RL referent tracking for places. Don't be lazy and just say ‘Galilee’ like the English does.] [KT: while the Gk baptizw has the sense of ‘dip in and out’ as dunking a piece of white cloth into dye and having it come out with a new identity, as early as Acts, the METHOD is not in focus, but rather the symbol of a public ritual leaving behind the OLD and committing to a NEW identity, affiliation, orientation. Note that doctrinally, Jesus would not have been baptized for repentence, but rather beginning His public ministry.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kai egeneto: scene setting best expressed"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">kai egeneto: scene setting best expressed by a comma after "time"</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-06-25 00:16:22Z">L</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Waktu Yesus kaluar dari aer, takuju ju, dapa lia langit tabuka. Ais ju Tuhan pung Roh turun pi Dia, sama ke burung pompa.<bt>As Yesus came out of the water, suddenly, the sky was seen opened. Then the Lord's *Spirit descended to Him, like a dove. [EXEG: different gospels handle this phrasing differently, so preserve Mark's way of describing it here. #1 The ‘sky was opened’ has no Actor. Can your language do this? What do they visualise? Clouds separating? A hole appearing? A window opening? They need to be able to visualise something that makes sense and is not wacko. #2 ‘the Spirit descending like a dove’ in the form of a dove? in the manner of a dove? (The Gk doesn't specify, so leave both open if possible.) #3 ‘descended to Him’ did it land on his head? on his shoulder? or just descend toward him? (Again, the Gk in Mark allows all these possibilities, so don't be more specific if you can preserve the ambiguities.)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="takuju sa - tiba-tiba, satu peristiwa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">takuju sa - tiba-tiba, satu peristiwa kejutan; kantara - dapa lia, terlihat, kelihatan</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ju dapa dengar Tuhan Allah pung suara dari langit bilang,<bt>And also was heard *God's voice from the sky saying, [EXEG: Mark doesn't specify who heard this. Jesus? John? Can you preserve both possibilities?]</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Lu ni, Beta pung Ana sayang.<bt>"You-sg here, are My dear Child.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Lu salalu bekin sanáng sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>You always make Me happy.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paling cocok deng --tetap ; (selalu)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">paling cocok deng --tetap ; (selalu) beking senang beta pung hati (can be occasional). Beta sanang deng Lu.</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 22:2, Lagu Puji dong 2:7, Yesaya 42:1, Mateos 3:17, 12:18, Markus 9:7, Lukas 3:22</note></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01656b.tif" rtfFormat="width:9.0cm">Yohanis su sarani abis sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Yohanis has finished baptising the Lord Yesus</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Setan dong pung bos goda Tuhan Yesus di tampa sunyi<bt>*Satan (=evil spirits boss) *tempts the Lord Yesus in a lonely place</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 4:1-11; Lukas 4:1-13)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais itu, Tuhan pung Roh hela bawa sang Yesus pi tampa kosong yang sunyi.<bt>After that, the *Lord's *Spirit dragged off Yesus to an empty place that was lonely. [EXEG: Gk verb here is fairly forceful ‘drove, compelled’.] [KT: wilderness]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tola bawa - implies forced against"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">tola bawa - implies forced against will; angka bawa can be understood like Wiro Sableng flying</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Di situ ju ada binatang utan dong. Yesus tenga di itu tampa ampa pulu hari. Di situ, setan dong pung bos datang goda sang Yesus ko iko sang dia, ma tar ontong. Ais itu ju, Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga datang urus sang Dia.<bt>There, there were also wild animals. Yesus stayed in that place forty days. There, *Satan *tempted Yesus to follow him, but he didn't accomplish.his.purpose. After that, *angels (God's underlings from heaven) came to arrange/ take care of Him. [NOTE: continuing background from vs.12] [KT: several. Here ‘tempt, test’ is about testing character, in this case seeing how committed Jesus is to obeying God in all things.] [DISCOURSE: (implicit to explicit): the devil tested Jesus, but did not succeed in making him fall/follow him.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***tweaked background-foreground like HCE setan dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">***tweaked background-foreground like HCE setan dong pung Kapala Besar - Iblis; fafudi sang Dia (Kupang Rote, but Sabu fafudik = babusa 'foam') - goda, buju; kakoe = buju (to do s.t. pos); buju (neutral); Tuhan Allah pung ana bua dari sorga = angel; kapala besar can = kapala batu; setan dong pung Kapala Paling Besar (can be thought of as having replaced another; Setan Tua (precedence) , but ambiguous with age; utan = wild, bush, does not imply 'rainforest'<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaa: da Devil &quot;Wild animals&quot; is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">Satanaa: da Devil "Wild animals" is part of the setting for Pidgin, so moved to connect with "boonies".<span class="Italic">(13) (13) </span>Implicit "come" to get them on site. Not "take care Jesus," because the reference is clear from the cast of characters and the semantics. In this case the pronoun works.<span class="Italic">(13)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia tenga di itu tampa ampa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Dia tenga di itu tampa ampa pulu hari sama-sama deng binatang utan dong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pi Galilea ko kasi tunju Tuhan Allah pung jalan<bt>*Lord Yesus goes to Galilea to show God's path</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 4:12-17; Lukas 4:14-15)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Tempo hari, dong kasi maso sang Yohanis tukang sarani pi dalam bui abis, ju Yesus pi propinsi Galilea, ko kasi tau Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae di sana.<bt>One day, after they had put Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer in jail, then Yesus went to Galilea province to (purpose) tell *God's Good News (*gospel2) there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Tukang Sarani&quot; from the first section."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">"Tukang Sarani" from the first section.</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Dia omong bilang,<bt>He spoke saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;Dengar, ó! Sakarang Tuhan pung waktu su sampe!<bt>Listen, ó! Now the *Lord's time has arrived!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Sakarang samua orang dapa tau bilang, Tuhan Allah ada pegang parenta.<bt>Now all people can know that *God is holding authority (to rule). [EXEG: Gk ‘time is fulfilled’ Willard points out = already available.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan Allah su pegang parenta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Tuhan Allah su pegang parenta</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia ko bosong musti barenti suda deng bosong pung putar-balek,<bt>That is why you-pl must stop your deceitfulness (*repent1 -phase 1)!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">ko bale iko sang Tuhan.<bt>to turn back and follow/obey God2 (=repent, phase 2).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Ais ju parcaya sang Dia pung Kabar Bae ni, suda.&gt;&gt;<bt>And then believe in the *Lord's Good News [+imperative].&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi bosong musti buang bosong pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Jadi bosong musti buang bosong pung jalan bengko-bengko suda! sala - jalan bengko-bengko, pakane'o; bosong musti brenti deng bosong pung jalan pakane'o suda; musti ~ musi *** path --Good News</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis ju, iko Tuhan pung Kabar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Abis ju, iko Tuhan pung Kabar Bae suda</Message></Annotation><note reference="1:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 3:2</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pange nalayan ko iko sang Dia<bt>Lord Yesus calls fishermen to follow Him</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ana bua = followers, hanger-arounders, those"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">ana bua = followers, hanger-arounders, those who follow and subscribe to the boss's views, those who do what the boss wants/needs done; (Yoel Jacob) 'berkonotasi komando, kaki-tangan'</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 4:18-22; Lukas 5:1-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Satu hari, Yesus jalan iko dano Galilea pung pinggir. Dia dapa lia satu orang, nama Simon, deng dia pung adi, nama Anderias. Dong dua ada jala ikan. Itu dong pung karjá hari-hari.<bt>One day, Yesus went along the edge of Lake Galilea. He saw a person, named Simon, with his younger sibling (ss), named Anderias. The two of them were cast-netting fish. That was their daily work. [EXEG: cast-net here different from drag-net below. Cast-net is round with lead weights on the edges. Thrown from shore, a rock, or standing up to waist deep. These fishermen were poorer than those below who let down a drag-net from a boat.]</bt><v n="17" />Yesus pange sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Mari ko iko sang Beta suda! Bosong biasa cari ikan, ma sakarang Beta mau bekin sang bosong jadi tukang cari jiwa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus called them saying, &lt;&lt;We! Come.here in order to follow Me [+imperative]. You-pl customarily hunt fish, but now I'm going to make you become people who habitually hunt *souls.&gt;&gt; [NOTE: don't force ‘fisher of men’. That is a collocational clash that does not work in most languages unless you have hundreds of years of teaching in the church. Also be careful that phrases like ‘gathering souls’ ‘hunting men’ isn't associated with sorcery.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kumpul orang - rapat; tangkap jiwa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">kumpul orang - rapat; tangkap jiwa - sihir; hoi dan he lebe kasar dari hei; le'o-le'o = jimat, ilmu, obat, magic</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-06-25 00:39:27Z">fi</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="problem with suanggi - tangkap jiwa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">problem with suanggi - tangkap jiwa</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Dengar abis bagitu ju, dong dua kasi tenga itu jala, ko pi iko memang sang Dia.<bt>After hearing that, then the two of them left that net behind, to immediately go follow Him.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01682b.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ais itu, Yesus jalan tarús sadiki lai, ju Dia dapa lia Sabadeus pung ana-ana dong. Yang kaka pung nama Yakobis, deng dia pung adi, nama Yohanis. Dong dua ada ator bekin bae pukat dalam parahu.<bt>After that, Yesus walked a little bit more, then He saw Sabadius' children. The elder sibling's name was Yakobis, and his younger sibling's name was Yohanis. The two of them were arranging fixing their drag-net in a boat. [EXEG: Contra Sunday school teaching, fishermen tell us that you don't ‘mend’ torn nets on a boat, but rather hang them from a tree or pole on land to repair them. On the boat you ‘arrange, prepare’ them carefully so they can be clean and folded to let down over the side the next time without snagging. It turns out the Gk is a better match with ‘arrange’ than with ‘mend’.]</bt><v n="20" />Yesus pange sang dong dua bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Mari ko iko sang Beta.&gt;&gt; Jadi dong dua jalan kasi tenga dong pung papa deng dong pung orang karjá dong di atas parahu. Ju dong pi iko sang Dia.<bt>Yesus called them two saying, &lt;&lt;We! [+attention] Come here in order to (purpose) follow Me.&gt;&gt; So (consequently), the two of them went leaving behind their father and their working people on the boat. And they went following Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ju berfungsi 'jadi' dan 'lalu'"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">ju berfungsi 'jadi' dan 'lalu'</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus usir kasi kaluar setan dari satu orang di kota Kapernaum<bt>Lord Yesus expels making go out *evil spirit/s from a person in Kapernaum city</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 4:31-37)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais Yesus deng itu ampa orang yang iko sang Dia, sampe di kota Kapernaum. Waktu orang Yahudi dong pung hari sambayang,<bt>Then Yesus with those four people who were following Him, arrived at Kapernaum city. On the *Sabbath (Yahudi people's (collective) worshipping day),</bt><note reference="1:21" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Orang Yahudi pung hari sambayang, hari istirahat, ko, hari barenti karjá, dong bilang &lt;Hari Sabat&gt;.<bt>Yahudi people's worshipping day, rest day, or day of stopping work, they call &lt;Sabat Day&gt;.</bt></note>ju Yesus maso pi dalam ruma sambayang ko mangajar di situ.<bt>then Yesus went into the *synagogue (=worship-service house) to teach there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hari bae -- Sundays, birthdays, holidays,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">hari bae -- Sundays, birthdays, holidays, feast days</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Dengar Dia pung omong, samua orang dong taheran-heran, te Dia tau batúl itu ajaran pung isi. Itu beda deng orang Yahudi pung guru agama dong.<bt>Hearing His talk/hearing what He was saying, all the people were *amazed1, cuz (elaboration) He truly knew the contents of that teaching. That was different than the Yahudi people's religious teachers. [EXEG: think through carefully what ‘taught with authority’ really means. The Gk has a sense of ‘legitimacy’ built into it. It does not mean ‘forceful manner’ like a passionate preacher. Most people can remember teachers they have had who really understood what they were teaching AND could also explain the implications when questions were asked. Vs. other teachers who were shallow.]</bt><note reference="1:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 7:28-29</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Itu waktu, ada satu orang yang takaná setan. Dia ju iko maso dalam ruma sambayang, ais itu setan di dalam itu orang batarea<bt>At that time, there was a person who was adversely affected by (=*possessed) an *evil spirit. He also followed entering into the *synagogue, and then that evil spirit inside that person shouted [NOTE: AGNT has “and cried out” in vs. 23. Some translations put it in vs. 24 without explanation. In Gk. quote margin is in 24.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="setan -- can occasionally act gentle"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">setan -- can occasionally act gentle and nice, even though</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="en: &quot;take ova&quot; and &quot;let go&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">en: "take ova" and "let go" is the culturally appropriate way to talk about a person being under the control of an outside power. "In" and "go out" or "throw out" doesn't make a lot of sense. At least two of the translators have had first hand experience with this kind of situation.</Message></Annotation><v n="24" />bilang, &lt;&lt;Woi! Yesus, orang Nasaret! Lu ada pung urusan apa deng botong! Lu datang ko mau bekin ancor sang botong, ko? Botong kanál sang Lu. Lu ni, Orang yang dolu Tuhan Allah janji ko mau kirim datang. Lu ni, Tuhan pung Orang Barisi yang sonde ada pung sala.&gt;&gt;<bt>saying, &lt;&lt;Woi! [+challenge] Yesus, the Nasaret person! What business do you-sg have with us-exc! You come because you want to destroy us-exc, ko [+tag]? We-exc know/recognise You. You here are the *Messiah (the Person that long ago God promised that he wanted to send). You here, are God2's *Clean/Holy Person who doesn't have any *sin1.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ma Yesus masparak sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Tutu lu pung mulu! Kaluar dari itu orang!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus spoke angrily to/scolded/rebuked him saying, &lt;&lt;Shut your mouth! Get out of that person!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paróp! - Belanda &quot;cork it!&quot;; masparak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">paróp! - Belanda "cork it!"; masparak bicara secara kasar, keras</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ju itu setan bekin ame itu orang pung badan batahela karás-karás. Ju dia kaluar dari itu orang deng batarea kuat-kuat.<bt>Then that *evil spirit made that person's body to be yanked repeatedly hard-hard. And then he came out of that person with a very loud shout. [EXEG: convulsion, like an epyleptic fit. After discussing (without showing what you means), have them demonstrate their word.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="batahela karás-karás"><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-06 07:14:21Z" status="Anyone">batakincang ??</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Ais ju samua orang dalam itu ruma sambayang tanganga. Ju dong samua ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Ini apa ni? Dia parenta setan dong ko kaluar, ju dong iko Dia pung mau. Ini ajaran baru, ko? Bapatua pung omong, hebat, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then all the people in that *synagogue were *amazed (open-mouthed). And they all spoke to each other saying, &lt;&lt;We [+attention]! What's this! He commands *evil spirits to go out, and they follow/obey His will. Is this a new teaching, ko [+tag]? Elder Father's [term of respect] talking, is really exceptional, ó!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia parenta ame setan dong kaluar,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Dia parenta ame setan dong kaluar,</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Several people have remarked on the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">Several people have remarked on the inadequacy of just "?" and "!" for Pidgin. The combination "?!" is what they suggest for something that sounds like a question but which is really a surprised exclamation. kat' exousian: could go either with "teaching" or with "tell". This kind of sits on the fence.<span class="Italic">(27)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ju orang dong mulai bacarita kuliling dari mulu pi mulu, tasiar sampe di samua kampong di propinsi Galilea.<bt>Then the people began to tell the story all over the place from mouth to mouth, spreading to all the villages in Galilea province.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae Petrus pung mama mantu, deng banya orang dong<bt>Lord Yesus *heals Petrus mother-in-law and many other people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 8:14-17; Lukas 4:38-41)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Waktu dong kaluar dari itu ruma sambayang ju, Yesus pi di Simon deng Anderias pung ruma. Yakobis deng Yohanis pi sama-sama deng dong.<bt>As they were coming out of the *synagogue, then Yesus went to Simon and Anderias' house. Yakobis and Yohanis went with them.</bt><v n="30" />Simon pung mama mantu ada saki damám, ko ada tidor di koi. Jadi waktu Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong maso di itu ruma, ju orang datang kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Mamatua ada saki damám.&gt;&gt;<bt>Simon's mother-in-law was fever sick, and so was sleeping on the bed. So (consequently), when Yesus with his *disciples entered that house, then someone came telling saying, &lt;&lt;Elder mother [term of respect] is fever sick.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: in some RL lgs mo-in-law = FZ; in the Gk this is mo-in-law.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="koi -dari kayu; bale-bale - dari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">koi -dari kayu; bale-bale - dari bambu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais itu, Yesus pi lia mamatua, ju pegang dia pung tangan, ko tolong kasi bangun sang dia. Ju dia pung damám ilang memang. Ais ju mamatua kaluar pi urus sang dong.<bt>After that, Yesus went to see elder mother, and held her hand, to help get her up. Then her fever immediately disappeared. After that elder mother went out, to go arrange/take.care of them. [EXEG: this ‘serve/minister to’ is about food and drink, not church activities.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="She couldn't cook because it was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">She couldn't cook because it was Sabbath.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Waktu matahari mulai tanggalám, orang dong datang bawa dong pung orang saki, deng dong pung orang yang takaná setan dong. Dong bawa pi Yesus ko minta tolong.<bt>When the sun was beginning to sink/drown, people came bringing their sick people, and their people who were adversely affected by *evil spirits. They brought them to Yesus to request help. [EXEG: two categories of people in need.]</bt><v n="33" />Sampe manusia satu kota pung isi datang makarubu di muka itu ruma.<bt>To the point that the humans filling up an entire city, came crowding around the front of that house. [EXEG: hyperbole, not literal. Check how best to communicate this.]</bt><v n="34" />Itu orang dong pung panyaki macam-macam, ma Yesus bekin bae samua. Deng Dia usir kasi kaluar setan jahat pung banya lai. Ma Dia sonde kasi loos itu setan dong ba'omong, te dong ju ada kanál sang Dia na.<bt>Those people had various sorts of sicknesses, but Yesus *healed them all. And he expelled making leave ever so many evil *evil spirits. But He didn't give opportunity/permission for those *evil spirits to talk, cuz (elaboration) they knew Him [+emphatic].</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kuliling di kampong laen dong, ko kasi tau Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae<bt>Lord Yesus goes around other villages, to tell the Good News *gospel2 from/about God</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 4:42-44)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Dia pung beso amper siang, masi galáp buta, Yesus su bangun ko jalan kaluar dari itu ruma. Dia pi satu tampa sunyi ko sambayang, ba'omong deng Tuhan Allah.<bt>The next morning almost daylight, still totally dark, Yesus had already gotten up to walk out of that house. He went to a lonely place to *pray, RECIP-talking with God. [NOTE: double-barrelled here, to kick people out of thinking of prayer as a ceremonial or liturgical ritual—it's about relationships.]</bt><v n="36" />Waktu Simon dong bangun, sonde dapa lia sang Yesus, ju dong pi cari sang Dia.<bt>When Simon (coll) (=collective/associative plural) woke up, they couldn't see Yesus, so they went to look for Him.</bt><v n="37" />Waktu dong dapa katumu sang Dia, ju dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa, banya orang ada cari sang Papa.&gt;&gt;<bt>When they found Him, then they said, &lt;&lt;Papa [+affection], many people are looking for Papa  (=you).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Papa - voc; can be used"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Papa - voc; can be used outside family, akrab dan hormat</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ma Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu ju bae. Ma lebe bae kotong pi kampong-kampong laen dolo, yang deka-deka di sini. Te Beta mau kasi tau Kabar Bae sang dong ju. Ko itu Beta pung tugas na.&gt;&gt;<bt>But He responded/answered saying, &lt;&lt;That's good. But it's better for us-inc to go first to other villages, that are close by here. Cuz (elaboration) I want to tell them the *Gospel (Good News) too. Cuz (elaboration) that is my work, [+emphatic].&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: Gk is so stark it appears in some translations that he is ignoring them. Structured for he is not being rude in RL cultures, but is still telling them he wants to focus on something else.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ais ju Dia jalan kuliling itu propinsi Galilea, ko kasi tau Kabar Bae dari Allah di dong pung ruma-ruma sambayang. Deng Dia ju usir kasi kaluar setan dari orang dong.<bt>After that, He went walking all around that Galilea province to tell the *Gospel from *God2 at their various *synagogues. And He expelled making leave *evil spirits from people. [NOTE to daughter translations: make sure they understand this to be 1) throughout, not 2) around (the outside)]</bt><note reference="1:39" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 4:23, 9:35</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae satu orang panyaki kusta<bt>Lord Yesus *heals a person with leprosy (loan)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 8:1-4; Lukas 5:12-16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Itu waktu, ada satu orang panyaki kusta datang sang Yesus. Ju dia tikam lutut ko minta tolong sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa, é! Tolong beta dolo! Te beta tau, Papa bisa kasi ilang beta pung panyaki ni, ko biar orang jang noju lai sang beta. Asal Papa mau.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, there was a person with leprosy, who came to Yesus. Then he knelt (lit: pierce knees) to request help from Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Papa! Help me now! Cuz (elaboration) I know, Papa can make this illness of mine disappear, so that people no longer are grossed out/avoid me. As long as you want to.&gt;&gt; [KT: check with male and female, old and young, to ensure that your term for *leprosy evokes some sort of skin disease that visibly and socially grosses people out.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tikam lutut = spontan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">tikam lutut = spontan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lepros: probably not a Hansen's disease"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">lepros: probably not a Hansen's disease patient, but someone suffering from a skin disease that made him ritually unfit for worship. But with so many people here having relatives who were (or are) in the Kalaupapa leper colony, "lepa" has instant recognition, and a strong emotional reaction as serious. Ideas of "ritually impure" are not, on the other hand, common in the culture. katharisai: "cleanse" in the ritual sense, "make me so I can worship with the rest again"<span class="Italic">(40)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ais ju Yesus jato kasian itu orang, ju Dia sorong tangan ko raba sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang, Beta mau! Naa, lu bae suda!&gt;&gt;<bt>So then Yesus dropped love/pity (toward) that person, and He stretched out his hand to touch him, and said, &lt;&lt;Certainly, I want to! Naa [+shift] you're now healed!&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="42" />Takuju sa, itu orang pung panyaki ilang. Ais ju dia bae memang.<bt>Unexpectedly/immediately, that person's disease disappeared. And so (consequently) result), he was immediately well. [EXEG: Gk indicates two separate things: 1) the disease left, and 2) he was made clean/restored. For leprosy, which leaves one without noses and fingers, this is significant.]</bt><v n="43" />Ju Yesus suru itu orang ko pulang, deng kasi inga sang dia<bt>Then Yesus told that person to go home, and reminded/warned him, [NOTE to daughter translations: In the Gk, the quote margin is in vs.44. Some translations are not careful here.]</bt><v n="44" />bilang, &lt;&lt;Inga bae-bae! Lu su bae, ma sonde bole kasi tau sapa-sapa, é! Lu musti iko ba'i Musa pung parenta dolu. Jadi pi di kapala agama dolo, ko dia pareksa sang lu pung badan, ko lia lu pung panyaki ilang batúl, ko sonde. Ais itu, lu musti kasi persembahan tanda tarima kasi, ko orang samua tau bilang, lu su bae batúl.&gt;&gt;<bt>saying, &lt;&lt;Remember this well (=take note of this)! You are now healed, but you may not tell anyone, é! You must follow/obey forefather Musa's command from long ago. So (consequently) go first/now to the *priest (=head of religion), in order that (purpose) he examine your body, to see if your illness is really disappeared/gone, or not. Then you must give an *offering as a sign of thanks, so that (purpose) all people know that you are truly healed.&gt;&gt; [KT: offering: if there is no obvious term, it is good if you have something that indicates that this ‘gift’ is associated with religious or ceremony or sacrificial things.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="embrimeesamenos ... exebalen: Jesus was very"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">embrimeesamenos ... exebalen: Jesus was very abrupt with the man, and practically pushed him out the door. Two senses of "now": admonition with "no foget", and time with "stay good." No clash.<span class="Italic">(44)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="1:44" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 14:1-32</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Ma itu orang kaluar abis ju, dia pi bacarita kuliling di mana-mana. Ais ju orang banya cari ko katumu sang Yesus, sampe-sampe Dia sonde bisa tunju muka di kota. Jadi Dia tenga di tampa-tampa sunyi di luar kota sa. Ma dari mana-mana, orang maen malele datang tarús, ko mau katumu sang Dia.<bt>But after that person went out, he narrated all around everywhere/wherever. And then many people searched to meet Yesus, to the point that He couldn't show his face in the city. So (consequently), He just stayed in lonely places outside the city. But from everywhere, people kept flowing coming continually, wanting to meet Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maen malele datang; po'a datang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">maen malele datang; po'a datang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae orang lumpu<bt>The Lord Yesus heals a *paralyzed person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 9:1-8; Lukas 5:17-26)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="2" />
      <v n="1" />Lewat barapa hari ju, Yesus pi ulang lai di Kapernaum. Ju orang kasi tau di mana-mana bilang, Dia su ada di ruma.<bt>After passing several days, Yesus then went again to Kapernaum. And people (non-referential/impersonal construction) told everywhere that He was already at the house.</bt><v n="2" />Ais orang dong datang dari mana-mana, ju dong makarubu sampe basesak dalam ruma. Di muka pintu ju, basesak. Ais itu, Yesus kasi tau sang dong Tuhan Allah pung mau.<bt>So/then people came from everywhere. They crowded around until they were crowded-tight in the house. To the point that in front of the door (=yard) also was already crowded-tight. Then Yesus told them God's will. [EXEG: Gk here is "word, message" which we take to not be talking about cereal at the supermarket; so "talking about God's will" is a very broad way of saying "talk about the things of God".]</bt></p>
    <fig path="Art-Read\thruRoof.jpg" rtfFormat="textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Yesus masi ba'omong, ju ada ampa orang dorok bawa satu orang lumpu ko pi Dia.<bt>While He was still talking, there were four people carrying a *paralysed person to go to Yesus. [EXEG: Gk ‘paralyzed, lame, unable to walk’.]</bt><v n="4" />Ma tagal su talalu banya orang, andia ko dong sonde bisa bawa itu orang sampe di Yesus pung muka. Ju dong nae pi atas ruma, ko bongkar atap pas di atas Yesus pung kapala. Waktu atap tabuka, ju dong kasi turun sang itu orang lumpu deng dia pung tikar.<bt>But because there were already too many people, that is why they could not bring that person in front of Yesus. Then they went up to the top of the house, to tear apart the roof right/exactly above Yesus' head. When the roof was open, then they lowered him with his mat. [EXEG: discuss houses with flat roofs made from hard material, and stairs along the outside. Socialising was done on the roofs, not on terraces/porches. What verb is appropriate for making a hole in hard material? If you use a term for (pandanus) sleeping mat, will people be worried about it not being strong enough material? Avoid the TB problem of using a term for ‘bed’ that evokes a large heavy ironwood frame. It should be commonly used for carrying sick people.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="krabatton: The mat was the sick"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">krabatton: The mat was the sick man's, not a mat that happened to be in front of Jesus.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:4" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dong pung tikar, dong bekin dari bahan yang kuat.<bt>Their mat, they made from strong material.</bt></note><v n="5" />Waktu Yesus lia sang dong, Dia tau dong parcaya batúl-batúl sang Dia. Ju Dia kasi tau sang itu orang lumpu bilang, &lt;&lt;Ana, é! Beta su kasi ampon lu pung sala dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus saw them, He knew they really *believed in Him. Then He told that paralysed person saying, &lt;&lt;Child [+affection]! I have already *forgiven2 your *sins!&gt;&gt; [NOTE: don't force the vocative. Use something that is socially appropriate. Cook pictures show an older man, although we don't really know.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="complement clause with no complementiser"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">complement clause with no complementiser</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ma di situ ada dudu barapa orang guru agama Yahudi. Waktu dong dengar Yesus pung omong tu, dong rasa tar enak dalam hati.<bt>But there were sitting several Yahudi religious teachers there. When they heard what Yesus had said, they felt not satisfied/happy inside their hearts (livers). [=disturbed, to them this was wrong]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;in their hearts&quot; would be overkill"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">"in their hearts" would be overkill for Pidgin, though it's sayable</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-06-25 05:01:34Z" /></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong batanya dalam hati,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Dong batanya dalam hati,</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Ais dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ko ini orang pung barani omong bagitu lai! Cuma Tuhan Allah sa, yang bisa kasi ampon orang dong pung sala. Ma ini orang pung omong tu, bekin diri sama ke dia Tuhan Allah sa. Dia su hojat tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>So then they said to each other saying, &lt;&lt;Ko [+indignation], this person is very bold/brave talking like that! It is only just God, who can *forgive2 people/s *sin1. But what this person has said, just makes himself the same as if he is God. He has *slandered/blasphemed like that!&gt;&gt; [KT forgive: here may use a term that focuses on social interaction ‘grant forgiveness’, since they are not thinking that any change really happens.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hojat = hujat, fitnah, slander, blaspheme"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">hojat = hujat, fitnah, slander, blaspheme</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01689b.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.5cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Ma Yesus su tau memang dong pung hati. Ais Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong jang pikir bagitu!<bt>But Yesus already knew [+certainty] their hearts (livers). Then He talked saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl shouldn't think like that!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pneumati: could say &quot;inside his spirit&quot;,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">pneumati: could say "inside his spirit", but it isn't as meaningful as "inside". Same thing for "inside yoa heart".</Message></Annotation><v n="9-10" />Mana lebe gampang? Kalo Beta kasi tau sang ini orang lumpu bilang, &lt;Lu pung sala su dapa ampon,&gt; bosong sonde tau kalo jadi bagitu, ko sonde. Ma kalo Beta bilang, &lt;Bangun suda! Angka lu pung tikar ko pulang.&gt; Kalo dia bangun memang, bosong baru dapa lia bukti bilang, Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Deng Beta ada pung kuasa deng hak ko kasi ampon orang pung sala.&gt;&gt;<bt>Which is easier? If I say to this paralysed person saying, &lt;Your-sg *sin/s1 are already *forgiven2&gt;, you-pl don't know if that happens like that, or not. But if I say, &lt;Get.up [imperative]! Pick up your mat to go home! If he gets up immediately, only then will you-pl be able to see evidence that I here, am *Ideal/Prototype Human. And I have *power and *right to *forgive2 people's *sins1.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: restructured with several consultants and testing with UNSs in several languages, until we got something that people could follow. Gk has embedded speech, RQ, and implied propositions. Other constructions are possible, but check carefully that all the logic is there.] [KT: see discussion of *Son of Man at Mark 9:1.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais itu ju, Yesus kasi tau sang itu orang lumpu bilang,<bt>After that also, Yesus told that paralysed person saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="compare Matthew 9:5-6."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">compare Matthew 9:5-6.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />&lt;&lt;Lu dengar, é! Sakarang lu su bae! Jadi bangun, angka tikar ko pulang su, é.&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;You-sg listen, é! Now you are *healed! So (consequently), get up, pick up mat to go home [+imperative], é.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Dengar bagitu, ju itu orang bangun memang. Ais dia angka dia pung tikar, ju jalan kaluar. Samua orang di situ lia deng dong pung mata biji. Ju dong samua tanganga, ko bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Botong baru parná lia yang bagini, ó! Tuhan Allah memang pung hebat lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing that, the person got up straight away. And he picked up his mat and walked out. All the people there saw with their very own eyeballs. And they all were amazed (open-mouthed) saying, &lt;&lt;Awii [+positive amazement]! Only now have we-exc ever seen anything like this, ó! God is truly incredible [+positive]! [KT: Gk has ‘glorified God’, which some other lgs have better terms for than Kupang.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dengar bagitu, ju itu orang takuju"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Dengar bagitu, ju itu orang takuju bangun.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pange sang Lewi ko iko sang Dia<bt>Lord Yesus calls/summons Lewi to follow Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 9:9-13; Lukas 5:27-32)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais itu ju, Yesus pi ulang lai di dano Galilea pung pinggir. Banya orang datang katumu sang Dia, ju Dia kasi tau sang dong Tuhan Allah pung mau.<bt>And so after that, Yesus went again to the edge/shore of Galilea lake. Many people came to meet Him, and He told/explained to them God's will (=the things of God). [EXEG: Gk ‘taught them’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="se'ok = skim off the top,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">se'ok = skim off the top, pungut liar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00309C.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left">Orang ame doi bea<bt>A person collecting taxes</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Di situ, ada satu orang, nama Lewi, Alpius pung ana. Dia karjá di tampa bayar bea kasi sang pamarenta Roma. Pas Yesus jalan lewat di situ, Dia dapa lia sang Lewi. Ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Mari ko iko sang Beta!&gt;&gt;<bt>At that place, there was a person named Lewi, Alpius' child. He worked at a place for paying *tax (assimilated loan) to the Roma government. Just as Yesus walked by there, He saw Lewi. And he said, &lt;&lt;We [+attention]! Come to follow Me!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dengar Yesus bilang bagitu ju, Lewi bangun ko iko memang sang Dia.<bt>Hearing Yesus say like that, then Lewi got up to follow Him straight away.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais itu ju, Yesus dong ada dudu makan di Lewi pung ruma, sama-sama deng Lewi pung tamán tukang tagi bea dong. Ada orang laen ju, yang orang Yahudi anggap orang tar bae dong, iko makan deng dong. Dari itu orang yang dudu makan dong, ada banya yang suka dengar sang Yesus.<bt>After that, Yesus (collective) were sitting eating at Lewi's house, together with Lewi's friends who habitually collected tax. There were also other people, whom the Yahudi people considered not good people, eating with them. From/among those people who sat eating, there were many who liked to listen to Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teloonai kai hamartooloi: sinners in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">teloonai kai hamartooloi: sinners in the eyes of the pharisaical. Even in Galilee of the Gentiles, people who associated with non-Jews were considered second class Jews. It isn't a matter of them actually sinning or being bad people; they were just religious outcasts as the religious leaders defined it. Verse 16 mentions them too, and 17 mentions the outcasts. eekolouthoun: they were tagging along (not "plenny peopo" but a crowd of the wrong kind of people who were curious about Jesus and wanted to see more).<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Itu waktu, ada guru agama dari partei Farisi barapa orang, dapa lia Yesus dudu makan deng tukang tagi bea, deng itu orang sonde bae dong. Ju dong tanya sang Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko bosong pung Guru dudu makan deng itu orang tukang tagi bea, deng itu orang tar bae dong?&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, there were several religion teachers from the Farisi party, able to see Yesus sitting eating with those who habitually collect tax, and those people who were not good. Then they asked his *disciples/underlings saying, &lt;&lt;Why is your-pl Teacher sitting eating with those people who habitually collect tax, and with those no-gooders?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;odda kine peopo jalike dem&quot; in"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">"odda kine peopo jalike dem" in Matthew. "Bad name jalike dem" may be better, since it is judgmental and reflects the Pharisees' viewpoint. It also leads into Verse 17 better, which the neutral term used in Matthew doesn't do. Matthew has "fo da odda kine peopo" in 9:13. Change?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pangkotor; kamomos 'filthy'; tar laku-laku dong;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">pangkotor; kamomos 'filthy'; tar laku-laku dong; sampa masarakat; harba-biruk 'sembarangan'</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ma Yesus dapa dengar dong batanya bagitu, ju Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang saki memang parlú dokter, ma orang su bae sonde parlú. Beta datang ko urus orang yang tar bae dong. Ma sonde datang ko urus orang yang su rasa diri batúl dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus heard them asking each other like that, and He responded saying, &lt;&lt;Sick people truly need a doctor, but healed people don't need. I came to take care of/arrange those no-gooders people. But not come to take care of/arrange/deal with issues of people who already feel themselves correct.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: restructured to reflect RL logical relations. Explicate ellipted info.] [EXEG: the “righteous” is talking about “the attitude of the Pharisees towards themselves” TH. “who think they are already righteous” TN. Also TRT.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orang yang su rasa diri batul"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">orang yang su rasa diri batul dong. ma orang-orang yang bosong anggap hina." mati mampos; grammar = no subject = SS.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung ajaran baru, laen dari orang Farisi dong pung ajaran<bt>The Lord Yesus' new teachings are different from the Farisi people's teachings</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 9:14-17; Lukas 5:33-39)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Satu kali, orang dari partei agama Farisi dong ada puasa. Dong lia Yohanis tukang sarani pung ana bua dong ju ada puasa. Ma dong sonde lia Yesus pung ana bua dong puasa sama ke dong. Ais dong pung orang datang katumu deng Yesus ko batanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa. Botong ada puasa. Yohanis pung orang dong ju puasa. Ma, akurang ko Papa pung ana bua dong sonde puasa?&gt;&gt;<bt>One time, people from the Farisi religious party were *fasting. They saw the *disciples/underlings of Yohanis the Habitual Baptizer were also fasting. But they didn't see Yesus' *disciples fasting like them. Then their people came to meet with Yesus to ask saying, &lt;&lt;Father. We-exc are fasting. Yohanis' people also fast. But, why aren't/don't Father's/your *disciples fasting?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang bosong su tau, kalo ada pesta kawin, tamu dong sonde puasa, ma dong makan sampe kinyang. Kalo baroit laki-laki masi ada di situ, tantu dong samua makan rame-rame.<bt>And Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;Obviously you-pl already know, that if there's a marriage feast, the guests don't fast, but they eat until satisfied/full. If the groom is still there, of course they all eat together festively.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="baroit laki-laki"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">baroit laki-laki</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ma nanti satu kali, kalo orang laen tangkap bawa itu baroit laki-laki dolo, dia pung tamán dong rasa susa, baru dong puasa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But later at some time, if another person/people arrest/kidnap that groom, his friends will feel difficulty, only then will they will fast.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk ‘sons of bridgegroom’ is idiom for ‘wedding guests’. See NRSV, NLT. Since marriage is traditionally a long process involving many steps, RL worldview does not find it strange for a groom to have several children by the time he gets around to having a church ‘wedding’. So don't go literal to the words here = wrong meaning. Further complicated by groom = Messiah.] [EXEG: happy/feasting while groom is still with them; sad/fasting later when the groom is taken away/kidnapped (can also mean ‘killed’) by others. He doesn't just leave. TN, TRT, TH.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais ju Yesus tamba satu umpama bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang sonde tempel ko jaet kaen baru di baju lama. Te nanti kalo cuci, itu kaen baru takundur, ko bekin tamba tarobe lai itu baju lama.<bt>Then Yesus added a *parable (example story) saying, &lt;&lt;People don't patch and sew new cloth on old shirt. Cuz (elaboration) later when it's washed, that new cloth will shrink and so make that old shirt tear even more. [NOTE to daughter translations: Ask a woman if this makes sense.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="takundur = shrink"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">takundur = shrink</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Sama ju, ke orang sonde isi tuak baru pi dalam haik yang su lapuk. Te nanti itu haik pica, ju itu tuak malele buang. Jadi tuak baru musti po'a pi dalam haik yang baru.&gt;&gt;<bt>Similarly, like people don't fill new palmwine in a fragile/decayed traditional palmwine leaf bucket. Cuz (elaboration) later that pail will break, and that palmwine seep out wasted. So (consequently), new palmwine must be poured into a pail that is new.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="2:22" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;jang isi aer anggor yang baru pi dalam tas kulit yang lama, ko jang sampe dia pica ko tarobe.&gt;&gt;<bt>Original Greek language writings say don't fill grape juice that is new in a skin bag that is old, so that it doen't get.to-point-that it breaks and.so tears.</bt></note>[Deng bagitu, Yesus ajar sang dong bilang, Dia pung ajaran baru, jang kasi campor deng orang Farisi dong pung ajaran lama.]<bt>[Like that Yesus taught them saying his new teaching, shouldn't be mixed with the Farisi people's old teaching.] [NOTE: square brackets to indicate we know this is not in the Gk. Explicated under consultant supervision after UNSs in several lgs could not get the point of these two examples.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lapuk = fragile/old/decayed (also checked with"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">lapuk = fragile/old/decayed (also checked with Yanto); puruk = (more generic) rotten</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung ana bua dong ketu ame padi-gandum pas deng hari barenti karjá<bt>Lord Yesus' *disciples pick wheat grain on the *Sabbath2 (stop work day/day of rest)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hari faré-faré = free day (no"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">hari faré-faré = free day (no other activities)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 12:1-8; Lukas 6:1-5)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Satu kali, pas deng orang Yahudi pung hari sambayang, Yesus ada jalan lewat iko kabón. Ju Dia pung ana bua dong ketu ame padi-gandum ko makan.<bt>One time, exactly on the *Sabbath1 (Yahudi people's worship day), Yesus was walking on the path through/by the gardens. And His *disciples were breaking.off wheat grain to eat. [EXEG: they were passing between fields (=allowed), not entering through them (=stealing); picking grain hanging over the trail was allowed if hungry. Ripe wheat can be rolled between the hands to husk, and the grain chewed raw. Rice cannot.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ketu ame padi gandum pung pulek;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">ketu ame padi gandum pung pulek; pulek: head plus stalk to which attached; koru = harvest, strip off just the seeds; ketu pick, snap off; \va puler</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-06-25 05:40:06Z">in</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 23:25</note><v n="24" />Ma orang Farisi dong dapa lia, ais ju dong kasi tau sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko lu pung ana bua dong langgar kotong pung atoran agama? Dong ada ketu padi-gandum pas deng hari barenti karjá! Bosong sonde bole bekin bagitu!&gt;&gt;<bt>But the Farisi people saw it, then they told Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Why are your-sg disciples violating our-inc religious teaching? They are breaking.off wheat grain exactly on the *Sabbath2 (work stop day)! You-pl may not do like that!&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: should be worded as a general prohibition. Use the appropriate pronoun for that genre in your lg: we-inc, they, you-pl.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hari barenti karjá = hari frei"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">hari barenti karjá = hari frei</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00099C.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right">Padi gandum<bt>Gandum grain</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25-26" />Dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana, ó? Bosong sonde inga ba'i Daud pung carita tu. Itu waktu, bapatua Abiatar jadi kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos bésar. Ba'i Daud deng dia pung ana bua dong pung parú su karoncong sampe lapar mau mati. Ju dong maso pi dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tenda Sambayang, ko ame itu roti yang kapala agama dong su kasi sang Tuhan, ko dong makan. Padahal cuma kapala agama dong sa yang bole makan, ma orang laen sonde bole. Ais ba'i Daud dong makan, ma sonde ada orang kasi sala sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>He replied saying, &lt;&lt;How is it, ó? (It seems) you-pl don't remember that story about forefather Daud. At that time, Old Man Abiatar was the *high priest (biggest boss of the Yahudi priests). Forefather Daud and his follower's stomachs were strumming (with hunger like a musical instrument) to the point that they were exceedingly hungry. Then they entered into *God's *tabernacle (Worship Tent), in order to take that bread that the *priests had already given to Lord, so that they could eat [it]. However it was only just the priests who were allowed to eat [it], but other people were not allowed. Then forefather Daud (collective) ate, but there was no one who *accused/condemned them.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: restructured to get RL background-foreground right.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parut karoncong - stomach growling from"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">parut karoncong - stomach growling from hunger, like a strumming instrument</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="The point is not just that"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">The point is not just that David and his ate the special bread, but that the action is not condemned by Scripture even though it broke the letter of the law.</Message></Annotation><note reference="2:25-26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Samuel 21:1-6; Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 24:9</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ju Yesus kasi tau tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong jang lupa bilang, Tuhan Allah bekin hari barenti karjá ko jadi berkat, ko tolong kotong manusia. Ma Dia sonde bekin kotong manusia ko cuma iko hari barenti karjá pung atoran sa.<bt>And Yesus told them further saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl shouldn't forget that God made the *Sabbath2 (work stop day) to be a *blessing, to help us-inc humans. But He didn't make us-inc humans in order to (purpose) only just follow the regulations of the *Sabbath2.</bt><v n="28" />Jadi Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Beta yang ada pung hak ko bilang manusia bole, ko, sonde bole bekin apa-apa pas deng hari barenti karjá.&gt;&gt;<bt>So I here, am the *Ideal/Prototype Human. I am the one who has the right to say humans may or may not do whatever on the *Sabbath2.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho hyios tou anthroopou: Jesus is"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">ho hyios tou anthroopou: Jesus is talking about himself. Is this clear? "Lord" is a relation to people, not to a time period. The relation to the day has to be spelled out more, because "Boss" does not collocate that way.<span class="Italic">(28)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae orang, pas deng hari barenti karjá<bt>Lord Yesus heals a person on the *Sabbath2 (work stop day)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 12:9-14; Lukas 6:6-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="3" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu ju, Yesus kambali lai pi ruma sambayang. Di situ Dia lia ada satu orang yang dia pung tangan mati sablá.<bt>And so after that, Yesus returned again to the *synagogue (worship house). There He saw a person whose arm on one side was dead (not functional).</bt><v n="2" />Di situ ju, ada barapa orang yang cari-cari jalan ko mau kasi sala sang Yesus. Jadi dong tarús lur-lur sang Dia, ko mau tau Dia mau bekin bae itu orang, pas deng hari barenti karjá, ko sonde.<bt>There, there were also several people who kept looking for a way to *accuse/condemn Yesus. So (consequently), they continually scrutinized him, because they wanted to know if He would heal that person exactly on the *Sabbath2, or not.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangadu = menggugat, bawa ke hakim;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">mangadu = menggugat, bawa ke hakim; = kalak (KM) 'tell on'; lur-lur = scrutinize (also checked with Yanto)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ju Yesus pange sang itu orang yang tangan mati sablá bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari ko lu badiri di muka sini.&gt;&gt;<bt>And Yesus called that person who had the dead arm on one side saying, &lt;&lt;Come here so you-sg to stand in front here.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ju Dia tanya sang itu orang dong samua bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo iko kotong pung atoran agama, kotong bole bekin apa, pas deng hari barenti karjá? Kotong bekin bae, ko sonde? Kotong bekin bae orang, ko, bunu bekin mati?&gt;&gt; Ma dong samua diam sa.<bt>And He asked all those people saying, &lt;&lt;If [we] follow/obey our-inc religious regulations, what may we-inc do just on the *Sabbath? [May] we-inc do good, or not? [May] we heal people or, murder [them]?&gt;&gt; But they were all just quiet. [DISCOURSE: paragraph above due to change of audience, rather than normal change of speaker.] [EXEG: vs. 3 Gk “in the middle” in the way synagogues tended to be laid out, puts them in front of everybody, not just the Pharisees. So “them” in vs. 4 is ambiguous, as a) just the Pharisees (TN), or b) everybody present including the Pharisees (favoured by context; Jesus was constantly doing things so the crowds would see the true nature of the bad guys in positions of authority.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Tarús ju Yesus pung hati talalu susa, tagal dong lebe pusing dong pung atoran, ma sonde toe deng itu orang yang tangan mati sablá. Ju Dia mara ko pe'e mata lia kuliling sang dong. Ais ju Dia kasi tau itu orang bilang, &lt;&lt;Sorong lu pung tangan suda!&gt;&gt; Itu orang sorong dia pung tangan, ju takuju sa, dia pung tangan bae memang.<bt>So then Yesus' liver was very troubled/difficult/upset, because they were more occupied with/focused on their regulations, but they didn't care about that person whose arm one side was dead. So he got angry and glared all around at them. And then He told that person saying, &lt;&lt;Stretch out your-sg arm (imperative)!&gt;&gt; That person stuck out his arm, and suddenly/unexpectedly his arm was immediately well.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pe'e mata = stare, glare"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">pe'e mata = stare, glare</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ekteinin: may imply trying to stretch"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">ekteinin: may imply trying to stretch out the paralyzed fingers, or just extending the hand and arm.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais ju itu orang Farisi dong kaluar kasi tenga itu ruma sambayang. Ju dong pi basakongkol deng orang dari partei politik Herodes, ko cari jalan mau bunu mati sang Yesus.<bt>After that, those Farisi people went outside leaving that worship house. And they plotted with people from the political party of Herodes, to find a way to murder killing Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sakongkol - seek accord, satu hati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">sakongkol - seek accord, satu hati</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Healing itself was not the issue;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">Healing itself was not the issue; details of the Law were. This is implicit in the Greek, but not accessible in Pidgin. The "Herodians" were a political group. Herod was a very unpopular king, but some people backed him because he was generally a winner.<span class="Italic">(6)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae banya orang di dano pung pinggir<bt>Lord Yesus heals many people at the edge of the lake</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7-8" />Satu kali, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong ondor pi dano Galilea pung pinggir. Ma tagal orang banya su dengar apa yang Dia su bekin, andia ko dong samua datang dari kampong-kampong ko iko sang Dia. Dong datang dari propinsi Galilea, propinsi Yudea, deng propinsi Idumea. Ada orang laen ju datang dari kota Yerusalem, kota Sidon, deng kota Tirus. Deng ada yang laen ju datang dari kali Yarden pung sablá matahari nae. Dong samua cari ko bakatumu deng Dia.<bt>One time, Yesus and His *disciples/underlings retreated to lake Galilea's edge/shore. But because so many people had already heard what he had done, that is why they came from various villages to follow Him. They came from Galilea province, Yudea province, and Idumea province. There were other people who also came from Yerusalem city, Sidon city, and Tirus city. And there were also other people who came from the east side of the Yarden river. They all were seeking to RECIP-meet with Him. [DISCOURSE: RL background-foreground, chronology, RL provinces together, then cities together.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eekoloutheesen: not necessarily &quot;followed by boat.&quot;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">eekoloutheesen: not necessarily "followed by boat." The place all these people ended up was "by the lake," however they got there</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-06-25 06:29:40Z">[</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satu kali, Yesus deng Dia pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Satu kali, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong ondor pi di dano Galilea pung pinggir. Ma, tagal orang banya su dengar apa yang Dia su bekin, andia ko dong samua datang dari kampong-kampong di propinsi Galilea, ko iko sang Dia. Ada banya orang ju datang dari propinsi Yudea, dari kota Yerusalem, dari propinsi Idumea, dari kali Yarden pung sablá, deng dari kota Sidon deng kota Tirus. Dong samua cari ko bakatumu deng Dia.</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-01-07 01:02:55Z">yang</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Tagal orang dong bagitu banya, sampe Yesus suru Dia pung ana bua dong ko sadia kasi sang Dia satu parahu. Dia mau ba'omong di atas parahu, ko dong samua dapa dengar, deng Dia sonde tapele.<bt>Because there were so many people, to the point that Yesus ordered His *disciples to prepare a boat for Him. He wanted to talk from on top of the boat, so they all could hear and He wouldn't get blocked [by people]. [EXEG: Gk word can be ‘crushed’ or ‘crowd around, press around’; we take the latter for contextual reasons.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gepe = pinch, grap; pele ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">gepe = pinch, grap; pele = block</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Dolu Dia parná bekin bae banya orang saki. Andia ko sakarang samua orang saki dong datang baseti ko mau raba sang Dia.<bt>Before, He had healed many sick people. That is why now all the sick people came elbowing/pushing their way forward wanting to touch Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="baseti = fah-fiku, push their way"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">baseti = fah-fiku, push their way forward (e.g. to buy cheap fish); raba = touch</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="etherapeusen: aorist covers the whole occasion;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">etherapeusen: aorist covers the whole occasion; it's not a perfect, so "befo time" is probably wrong.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:9-10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 4:1, Lukas 5:1-3</note><v n="11" />Waktu orang yang setan su maso dong dapa lia sang Dia, tarús dong jato sampe muka kaná tana di Yesus pung muka. Ais ju dong batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu ni, memang Tuhan Allah pung Ana!&gt;&gt;<bt>When the people whom the *evil spirits had entered saw Him, straight away they fell down until their faces were on the ground in front of Yesus. And then they shouted saying, &lt;&lt;You here are indeed God's Child!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jato matono = (prostrate? to minta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">jato matono = (prostrate? to minta ampun); soya</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ma Dia larang karás sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong jang kasi tau orang bilang, Beta ni sapa!&gt;&gt;<bt>But he strongly forbade them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl don't tell people who I am!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pili ame dua blas orang jadi Dia pung ana bua<bt>Lord Yesus chooses twelve people to be his *disciples</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 10:1-4; Lukas 6:12-16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais ju Yesus nae pi atas satu gunung. Dia pange ame barapa orang yang kaná deng Dia pung hati. Ju dong datang sang Dia.<bt>And then Yesus went up a mountain. He called several people who fit/were appropriate/matched his liver. And they came to Him.</bt><v n="14" />Tarús Dia tunju ame dua blas orang. Dia bilang sang dong, &lt;&lt;Beta pili sang bosong ko iko tarús sang Beta, ko jadi Beta pung utusan. Beta ju mau suru sang bosong ko pi kasi tau Tuhan Allah pung pasán di samua orang.<bt>Then he designated twelve people. He said to them, &lt;&lt;I choose you-pl to follow Me continually, becoming My *apostles (sent ones/commissioned ones/emmisaries). I also want to order/send you to go tell God's message/instructions to all people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="quote margin no bilang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">quote margin no bilang</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Deng Beta mau kasi kuasa sang bosong, ko bosong bisa usir setan dari orang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>And I will give *power/authority to you-pl, so that you are able to expel/kick out *evil spirits from people.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16-19" />Itu dua blas orang dong pung nama, andia:<bt>Those twelve people's names are like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Simon (yang Yesus ju kasi nama, Petrus),<bt>Simon (who Yesus also gave the name Petrus),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yakobis,<bt>Yakobis,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yohanis, (Yakobis deng dia pung adi Yohanis ni, dong dua, Sabadeus pung ana. Yesus kasi nama sang dong dua &lt;Boanerges&gt;, dia pung arti &lt;sama ke guntur&gt;.)<bt>Yohanis, (this Yakobis and his younger sibling Yohanis, these two, are Sabadeus' children. Yesus gave a name to the two of them &lt;Boanerges&gt;, its meaning &lt;like thunder&gt;.)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="violent disposition, bombastic, calling down fire"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">violent disposition, bombastic, calling down fire on people (which fortunately God didn't send)</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:16-19a" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani ada tulis bilang, &lt;guntur pung ana&gt;, deng dia pung arti &lt;sifat sama ke guntur&gt;. Barapa orang yang pintar dong basangka bilang, ini Yakobis deng Yohanis dong pung suara karás sama ke guntur, ko, dong suka masparak sama ke guntur na.<bt>The Greek writing says &lt;thunder's child&gt;, and its meaning &lt;characteristic like thunder.&gt; Several knowledgable/clever people think that this Yakobis and Yohanis their voices were loud like thunder, or, they liked to talk-angrily like thunder.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Anderias,<bt>Anderias,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Filipus,<bt>Felipus,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Felipus = Pelipus = Ipu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Felipus = Pelipus = Ipu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Bartolomeos,<bt>Bartolemeos,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Mateos,<bt>Mateos,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tomas,<bt>Tomas,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Yakobis (Alpius pung ana),<bt>Yakobis (Alpius' child),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tadius,<bt>Tadius,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Simon (yang iko partei politik Selot),<bt>Simon (who followed the political Selot party),</bt><note reference="3:16-19b" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Partei Selot ni cari jalan ko dong mardeka dari Roma pung pamarenta. Dong ju kasi nama ini partei bilang, &lt;Patriot&gt;.<bt>This Selot party sought a way for them to be independent from Roma's government. And they also called this party saying, &lt;Patriot&gt;.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng Yudas Iskariot (dia ni yang nanti jual buang sang Yesus).<bt>and Yudas Iskariot (he is the one who later *betrayed (sold away) Yesus).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kosi = tendang, sepak; bale tumit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">kosi = tendang, sepak; bale tumit ko kosi; buka kartu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Guru agama dong kasi sala sang Tuhan Yesus bilang, itu setan dong pung bos yang kasi kuasa sang Dia<bt>The religious teachers *accuse the Lord Yesus saying it's *Satan who has given *power/authority to Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 12:22-32; Lukas 11:14-23, 12:10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais itu, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong turun kambali dari itu gunung. Ju dong maso pi dalam ruma. Ma orang banya datang makarubu lai sang Yesus, sampe dong su sonde sampat makan lai.<bt>After that, Yesus and his *disciples/underlings went down again from that mountain. And they entered a house. But many people came crowding-around Him again, until Yesus (collective) no longer had time/opportunity to eat.</bt><v n="21" />Lia bagitu ju, orang bilang, &lt;&lt;Coba lia sang Yesus dolo. Dia su lupa urus diri.&gt;&gt; Tagal Dia pung kelu dong su dengar orang ba'omong bagitu, andia ko dong datang mau ame bawa sang Dia.<bt>Seeing that, people said, &lt;&lt;Have a look at Yesus. He's forgotten to take care of himself.&gt;&gt; Because His family heard people talking like that, that is why they came wanting to take Him away.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="krateisai: sieze, restrain It's unclear whether"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">krateisai: sieze, restrain It's unclear whether it was Jesus' family saying he was nuts, or if it was other people were saying it. It doesn't sound, however, as if it were the other people, who were quite enthusiastic about him. It was probably his family who were shamed by his being so prominent. There are other indications the family were upset, as in John when Jesus' brothers did not believe in him.<span class="Italic">(21)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Itu waktu, guru agama dong dari Yerusalem datang ko kasi tau orang di situ bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Bosong jang iko-iko sang itu Yesus. Te Dia bisa usir setan bagitu, tagal Dia dapa kuasa dari setan dong pung bos, yang orang biasa pange Balsebul.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time religious teachers from Yerusalem came to tell people there saying, &lt;&lt;Weh [+negative attitude]! You-pl don't go following/obeying that Yesus. Cuz (elaboration) He can cast out evil spirits like that, because He gets power/authority from *Satan (boss of evil spirits), whom people usually call Balsebul.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Te setan dong pung Bos, yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Te setan dong pung Bos, yang orang biasa pange Balsebul, su maso di Dia, deng su kasi kuasa ko bisa usir setan.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 9:34, 10:25</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Yesus dengar bagitu, ju Dia pange ame sang dong samua, ko bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde maso akal! Karmana ko setan dong pung bos bisa usir dia pung diri sandiri? Sonde bisa!<bt>Yesus heard that, and He called/summoned all those people, to say, &lt;&lt;That doesn't make sense (lit: enter into the idea)! How can *Satan be able to expel his own self!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parabolee: here Jesus is not telling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">parabolee: here Jesus is not telling stories, but using concise examples to make a point. Stick with the intent to teach, not the means used to do it. "Satan" doesn't fly as a name. After discussion it always comes back to "Devil."<span class="Italic">(23)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="24" />Kalo dalam satu karaja'an, dia pung rakyat dong baku hantam, karmana ko itu karaja'an masi bisa batahan? Sonde bisa!<bt>If in a kingdom (loan), its citizens beat up on each other, how can that kingdom still last/endure!</bt><v n="25" />Deng kalo isi ruma dong satu bara'u deng satu, karmana ko dong masi bisa batahan? Sonde bisa!<bt>And if the people of a household (=contents of a house) are gouging each other, how can they still last/endure!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bara'u = bertengkar, scoop up"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">bara'u = bertengkar, scoop up</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Bagitu ju kalo setan dong satu bamusu deng satu, pasti dong tapica-pica. Kalo bagitu, na, dong ancor-ancor!<bt>It's like that also, if evil spirits are RECIP-enemies with each other, surely they will break up [into all sorts of factions]. And if that's the case, na [+break up complex information load], they are completely destroyed!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaas: da Devil Not the destruction"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">Satanaas: da Devil Not the destruction of the Devil, but the demise of his organization.<span class="Italic">(26) (26) </span>"going" is not the future auxiliary "goin", but the main verb "go gains" 'oppose' in the progressive.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Kalo orang mau datang rampok barang di satu orang kuat pung ruma, dia musti ika mati itu tuan ruma dolo. Abis, baru dia bisa rampok itu orang pung barang.<bt>If a person comes to rob things from a strong person's house, he must first tie up completely that person. Only after that can he rob that person's things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ika rorobi = ikat badan entero"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">ika rorobi = ikat badan entero (kaki tangan); ika fafeu (Rote) = lilit tarus, wind; ika kuat-kuat</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="alla: alternative way of thinking about"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">alla: alternative way of thinking about it. The rhetorical question has to be set up so the answer is clear, so the "no good" is needed to provide the context.</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:27" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Deng bagitu, Yesus kasi tau bilang, Dia lebe kuat dari setan dong pung bos, yang dong biasa pange deng nama &lt;Balsebul&gt;.<bt>In that way, Yesus told that He was stronger than *Satan, who they (impersonal) usually call with the name &lt;Balsebul&gt;.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Jadi Beta kasi tau memang sang bosong: Tuhan Allah su sadia hapus buang orang dong pung sala. Deng kalo orang omong tar bae-bae so'al orang laen, Tuhan Allah masi sadia kasi ampon sang dia.<bt>So (consequently), I'm telling you-pl directly: God is prepared to *forgive1 (wipe away) people's *wrongs. And if a person speaks not well about other people, God still can *forgive2 (social action) him.</bt><v n="29" />Ma kalo ada orang yang barani omong tar bae-bae kasi Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi, Tuhan Allah sonde kasi ampon lai dia pung sala tu, sampe kiamat ju!&gt;&gt;<bt>But if there is a person who dares to speak not well about that *Holy Spirit of God's, God will not *forgive2 that wrong of his, even until the end (of the world)!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kiamat = forever, not stop"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">kiamat = forever, not stop</Message></Annotation><note reference="3:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 12:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Yesus bilang bagitu, tagal dong su cap ame sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu Orang su kaná setan!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus said that, because they had already stamped/branded (=characterized) Him saying, &lt;&lt;That Person has already been afflicted by *evil spirit/s!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang yang iko Tuhan Allah pung mau, dong tu, batúl-batúl Tuhan Yesus pung kelu<bt>The people who obey God's will, they are the Lord Yesus' true family</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 12:46-50; Lukas 8:19-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais ju Yesus pung mama deng Dia pung adi dong datang pi itu ruma, ko mau katumu deng Dia. Di sana dong badiri sa di luar ruma ko suru orang pange sang Dia.<bt>After that, Yesus' mother and His younger siblings came to that house, wanting to meet with Him. There they just stood outside the house and told/ordered someone to go call/summon Him.</bt><v n="32" />Itu waktu, Yesus ada dudu ba'omong deng banya orang. Ju orang datang kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa, ó! Papa pung mama deng adi-adi dong ada di luar. Dong mau katumu deng Papa.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, Yesus was sitting talking with many people. Then someone came telling that, &lt;&lt;Father, ó! Father's/your mother and younger siblings are outside. They want to meet with Father/you.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung mama deng Beta pung sodara yang batúl tu, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus responded/replied saying, &lt;&lt;Those who are My real mother and My siblings, are who?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ais Dia lia pi itu orang yang dudu kuliling sang Dia. Ju Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong samua ni, Beta pung mama deng Beta pung sodara yang batúl.<bt>Then He looked at those people who were sitting all around Him. And He spoke saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl all here, are My real mother and My siblings (same generation kin).</bt><v n="35" />Te sapa yang bekin iko Tuhan Allah pung mau, na, dong tu, batúl-batúl Beta pung kelu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) whoever follows/obeys God's will, na, those ones are truly-truly My family.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al bibit di macam-macam tana<bt>Tuhan Yesus tells a *parable (example) about seed in different kinds of soil</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:1-9; Lukas 8:4-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="4" />
      <v n="1" />Satu kali, Yesus pi lai di dano Galilea. Ju orang banya sakali datang makarubu sang Dia. Ais Dia nae pi dudu di atas satu parahu yang ada balabu di situ, ko mangajar. Itu orang di darat dong samua dengar sang Dia.<bt>One time, Yesus went again to lake Galilea. And very many people came crowding around Him. So He went up to go sit on top of a boat that was tied up there, in order to teach. Those people on the land could all hear Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="orang mal'unuk = gobs of people"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">orang mal'unuk = gobs of people</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 5:1-3</note><v n="2" />Ju Dia ajar bam-banya sang dong pake umpama bilang,<bt>Then He told lots and lots to them using *parables (examples) saying, [NOTE: in spite of English translations and Sunday school lessons, this story is not about the sower.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />&lt;&lt;Bosong dengar bae-bae, ó! Ada satu orang pi siram bibit di dia pung kabón.<bt>&lt;&lt;You-pl listen up (well)! There was a person who went to sprinkle/broadcast seed in his garden/field. [NOTE: many RL lgs have a different word for seed for planting/reproduction ‘bibit/benih’ in contrast to seeds in which planting is not intended or not in focus. These are seeds for planting (grain, not mango).]</bt><v n="4" />Waktu dia siram itu bibit dong, ada yang jato di jalan. Ju burung-burung dong datang ko toto bekin abis itu bibit.<bt>While he sprinkled those seeds, there were some that fell on the path. Then birds came and pecked making all gone that seed/s.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="toto = peck"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">toto = peck</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ma ada bibit saparu jato kaná di tana babatu. Itu bibit banupuk capát. Ma tagal itu tana tipis,<bt>But there was some seed/s that fell hitting the rocky soil. That seed sprouted fast. But because the soil was thin,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="banupuk = sprout; Should this final"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">banupuk = sprout; Should this final ko be a te or a tagal?</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />waktu matahari nae, ju itu nupuk dong mamalek ko mati karíng. Te dong pung akar sonde maso sampe dalam na.<bt>when the sun came up, then those sprouts withered and died dry. Cuz (elaboration) their roots couldn't enter until deep, [+emphatic].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="nupuk-nupuk = ; mamalek = layu,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">nupuk-nupuk = ; mamalek = layu, wither</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="Art-Read\sower.jpg" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ada bibit saparu lai jato di tenga rumput baduri. Ju itu rumput baduri dong gepe bekin mati itu nupuk, sampe sonde bisa babua.<bt>There was some other seed that fell in the midst of thorny grass. Then those thorny grasses grabbed tight/squeezed killing those sprouts, to the point that they were not able to have fruit/yield. [NOTE: word for ‘fruit’ should collocate with grain.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gepe = grab, squeeze; baboa ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">gepe = grab, squeeze; baboa = bear fruit (what is Engl</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="akanthoon: available varieties of thorns are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">akanthoon: available varieties of thorns are more like cockleburrs, and wouldn't grow up over a wheat stalk or stunt its growth. There are, however, several imported plants that take over native growth and strangle it ("choke" is used in discussions of this), and some can be referred to as "weeds."</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ma ada bibit saparu lai jato kaná di tana isi. Itu bibit dong banupuk, abis ju dong jadi bésar sampe babua. Ada yang kasi bale hasil tiga pulu kali, ada yang anam pulu kali, deng ada yang sampe saratus kali.<bt>But there was some other seed that fell hitting good soil (lit. soil contents-no rocks, etc). Those seeds sprouted, after then they grew until they had fruit. There were some which returned back a profit of 30 times, there some 60 times, and there were some that even reached 100 times. [NOTE: check with local farmers, how they talk about planting corn, peanuts, etc. and getting x-fold return.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Jadi bosong sapa yang ada talinga na, dengar babae, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently), you-pl who have ears listen carefully, ó!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Akurang ko Tuhan Yesus ba'omong pake umpama<bt>Why the Lord Yesus speaks using examples [not question]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:10-17; Lukas 8:9-10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ais ju waktu Yesus su sandiri, Dia pung ana bua dua blas orang, deng barapa orang laen yang su dengar Dia pung ajaran tu, dong datang katumu sang Dia. Dong minta Dia kasi tau itu umpama pung arti.<bt>Later on, when Yesus was alone, those 12 disciples/underlings of His, with several other people who had already heard that teaching of His, they came to meet Him. They asked Him to tell/explain the meaning of that parable/example.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="umpama = ande-ande"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">umpama = ande-ande</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Tagal bosong mau tau batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung parenta, andia ko Beta kasi tau memang itu umpama pung arti. Ma kalo orang laen, na, Beta ajar deng umpama sa.<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;Because you-pl really want to know/understand God's command/rule/governing, that is why I'll actually tell/explain that parable's meaning. But as for other people, na, I teach with *parables only.</bt><v n="12" />Itu orang laen dong sama ke yang Tuhan Allah pung jubir su tulis memang bilang,<bt>Those other people are like what God's *prophet1 (spokesperson) wrote beforehand saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Dong su lia, ma sonde mau mangarti.<bt>&lt;They have seen, but don't want to understand.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde mangarti = sonde hasek, sonde"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">sonde mangarti = sonde hasek, sonde toe</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong su dengar, ma sonde mau tau.<bt>They have heard, but don't want to know.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Biar ko dong sonde usa parcaya sang Tuhan,<bt>Leave them/let them be so that they don't need to believe the Lord (=so they don't believe the Lord),</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ko Tuhan sonde parlú kasi ampon sang dong lai.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>so that the Lord doesn't need to *forgive them anymore (=so the Lord doesn't forgive them anymore).&gt;&gt;&gt; [EXEG: The Gk uses ‘lest’ that is poorly reflected in some English translations, and missed by several.] [DISCOURSE: this is irony/sarcasm. If they are willful about not understanding, then it is appropriate that God not waste his time trying to save them.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hina: Implies that Jesus expected a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">hina: Implies that Jesus expected a negative outcome when he told stories to some people.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 6:9-10</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau itu umpama bibit pung arti<bt>Lord Yesus tells that seed *parable's meaning</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:18-23; Lukas 8:11-15)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais ju Yesus kasi tau sang dong itu umpama pung arti bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bosong balóm tangkap ame ini umpama pung arti na, karmana ko bosong bisa tangkap umpama yang laen dong pung arti?<bt>Then Yesus told them that *parable's/example's meaning saying, &lt;&lt;If you-pl still don't catch this parable's meaning, na, how are you-pl going to be able to catch the meaning of other parables?</bt><v n="14" />Jadi dia pung arti, bagini: itu orang yang siram bibit tu, andia sama ke orang yang ba'omong Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata.<bt>So (consequently) it's meaning is like this: that person who sprinkled those seeds, he's like a person who tells God's *Word/s/Sayings/Message.</bt><v n="15" />Deng itu bibit yang jato di jalan sampe burung makan abis, sama ke orang yang dengar Tuhan Allah pung Kata-kata. Ma sonde lama ju, setan dong pung bos datang ko angka bawa itu Kata-kata dari itu orang pung hati.<bt>And that seed that fell on the path to the point that the birds ate it all gone, is like a person who hears God's Word/s. But not long after (=soon) then *Satan (boss of evil spirits) comes to pick up carry away those Word/Message from that person's liver.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaas: da Devil The figure of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">Satanaas: da Devil The figure of "take away the seed" loses the thread of the meaning. What the Devil is doing is not taking away seeds, he is removing the ability to assimilate the Word.<span class="Italic">(15)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Bibit yang jato kaná di tana babatu tu, sama ke orang yang su dengar deng tarima itu Kata-kata deng sanáng hati.<bt>The seed that fell hitting that rocky soil, is like a person who hears and receives/accepts that Word/Message with a happy liver.</bt><v n="17" />Ma itu Kata-kata sonde ba'akar. Andia ko dia sonde tasimpan lama di itu orang pung hati. Waktu orang laen bekin susa tagal dia tarima itu Kata-kata, dia langsung lapás buang itu Kata-kata.<bt>But that Word/Message doesn't take root. That is why it is not stored long in that person's liver. When other people make things difficult [for him], because he received/accepted that Word, he straight away lets go throws away that Word/Message.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="de = sehingga; when te and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">de = sehingga; when te and when karna;</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Deng bibit yang jato di tenga rumput baduri tu, sama ke orang yang su dengar itu Kata-kata.<bt>And the seed that fell in that thorny grass, is like a person who hears that Word/Message.</bt><v n="19" />Ma dia talalu barepot deng macam-macam urusan ko bisa idop ena-ena sa. Ju itu urusan dong samua, seti buang itu Kata-kata dari dia pung hati, sampe sonde ada hasil apa-apa lai.<bt>But he is too busy with various sorts of arrangements in order to just live well off. And all those arrangements, push aside that Word/Message from his liver, to the point that it no longer has any result/fruit/yield. [NOTE: if the word used in 4:7-8 cannot be used figuratively for results of labour, don't force the same word here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="seti = push aside; de (Rote)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">seti = push aside; de (Rote)</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-06-25 07:31:33Z">us</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="guna lai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">guna lai</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ma bibit yang jato kaná di tana isi, sama ke orang yang pasang talinga ko tarima itu Kata-kata, deng iko Tuhan pung mau. Ais dia bekin hal-hal yang bae sa, sama ke bibit yang babua tu. Ada yang babua tiga pulu kali lipat, ada yang anam pulu, deng ada yang sampe saratus kali.&gt;&gt;<bt>But that seed that fell in the good soil, is like a person who fastens/attaches his ears (listens well) to receive/accept that Word/Message, and follow's the Lord's will. After that he just does (various) good things, like that seed that had fruit. There are some who have fruit 30 times over, some that 60, and some that are even 100 times.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="What it is that is being"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">What it is that is being multiplied by 30, 60, and 100 isn't clear, and perhaps doesn't need to be.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang tutu lampu te'oek deng bakul<bt>Don't cover a (wick) lamp with a basket</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 8:16-18)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Yesus omong tarús dari atas itu parahu. Dia kasi tamba lai satu umpama bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana! Bosong parná ko sonde, lia orang pake lampu te'oek, ais tutu sang dia dalam bakul! Ko, taro sang dia di kolong tampa tidor! Sonde, to? Kalo taro bagitu, na, dia sonde taráng lai. Orang musti taro itu lampu di tampa yang tinggi ko taráng.<bt>Yesus continued to speak from on top of that boat. He added another *parable saying, &lt;&lt;How is it! [STYLE: Discourse opener, not question, but setting up a RQ.] Have you ever or not, seen a person use a (wick) lamp, and then cover it in a tightly woven basket (no specific size)! Or, put it underneath a/the bed! No, right? If it's placed like that, na, it's no longer bright/gives light. People must/should put that lamp in a high place so that it's bright/give light.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lampu ti'oek ~ te'oek = pelita"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">lampu ti'oek ~ te'oek = pelita ; te'oek is duri babi, sea urchin = sea urchin lamp; kumbang = basin, clay jug; ba can be reciprocal; soke = tempurung kelapa; koi = tampa tidor ; bakul ~ karanjang (loose weave) ~ sapai/sapa'i (?) (tight weave ~ lapneuk (Rote)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko here = supaya, sehingga"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">ko here = supaya, sehingga</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:15, Lukas 11:33</note><v n="22" />Jadi barang yang tasambunyi sakarang, nanti dapa lia. Apa yang orang sonde tau sakarang, nanti dapa tau.<bt>So (consequently), things which are hidden now, later will be able to be seen. What people don't know now, later will be known.</bt><note reference="4:22" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:26, Lukas 12:2</note><v n="23" />Jadi sapa yang ada pung talinga, na, dengar bae-bae.<bt>So (consequently), whoever has ears, na, listen carefully/carefully.</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00148C.tif" rtfFormat="width:5.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:right" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Naa, pikir bae-bae! Kalo bosong ukur orang laen pung bekin, orang ju ukur bosong bagitu. Tuhan Allah ju ukur bale sang bosong bagitu. Ma Dia pung ukuran lebe barát lai.<bt>Naa [+shift], think carefully! If you measure another person's deed/s, people will also measure you-pl like that. God will also measure you-pl like that in turn. But His measuring is even more heavy/severe. [EXEG: CEV, TEV, LN note, Carlton note.] [DISCOURSE: RL do not like quote margin for same speaker continuing. Most quote margins imply change of speaker. (Can get away with it across pericopes.)]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dacing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">dacing</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 7:2, Lukas 6:38</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Naa, kalo orang mau cari tau batúl-batúl Tuhan pung mau, dia tamba pintar. Ma kalo orang sonde pusing deng Tuhan pung mau, dia tamba bodo.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [+shift], if a person wants to really know the Lord's will, he'll get smarter. But if a person isn't at all concerned with the Lord's will, he'll get dumber.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: several sources point out this is not a general state of affairs, but in the context of talking about understanding and wisdom, beginning from 4:10ff.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="toe = pusing"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">toe = pusing</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 13:12, 25:29, Lukas 19:26</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al bibit yang idop sandiri<bt>The Lord Yesus gives a *parable about seed that lives by itself</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ais ju Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuhan Allah pung karaja'an tamba bésar sama ke bibit yang orang siram di dia pung kabón.<bt>And then Yesus spoke further saying, &lt;&lt;God's *kingdom1 (loan) grows like a planting.seed someone sprinkles/broadcasts in his field/food.garden. [NOTE to daughter translations: God's rule...grows bigger, or God's people...increase in number, can also work in this context.]</bt><v n="27" />Biar itu orang pulang, tidor-bangun, sonde inga itu bibit lai, ma itu bibit banupuk deng tamba bésar tarús.<bt>Even if that person goes home, sleeps-gets up (repeatedly), doesn't remember/think about that seed anymore, nevertheless that seed continues to sprout and grow.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tarus ~ trus; tidor-bangun ~ makan-tidor"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">tarus ~ trus; tidor-bangun ~ makan-tidor</Message></Annotation><v n="28" />Te itu bibit idop sandiri di tana, mulai batangke, babunga, sampe ba'isi.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) that seed lives by itself in the soil, starts to grow a stalk, flower, to the point that it has contents (fruit, grain).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="batangke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">batangke</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Kalo padi su kuning, na, tuan kabón tau datang ko koru sa. Tuhan Allah pung karaja'an ju bagitu. Samua tu, Tuhan yang karjá.&gt;&gt;<bt>If the grain is already ripe, na, the garden master/owner just knows to come to strip the grainheads (term for how rice is harvested). God's kingdom1 is also like that. All that, it is the Lord who does the work.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="koru = strip off rice; ketu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">koru = strip off rice; ketu = pick, break off.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="From higher level context."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">From higher level context.</Message></Annotation><note reference="4:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yoel 3:13</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi umpama so'al biji yang paling kici<bt>Lord Yesus gives a *parable about the seed that is so very small/smallest</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:31-32, 34; Lukas 13:18-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ais itu, Yesus omong sambung lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta tamba satu umpama lai, bagini: bosong bisa banding Tuhan Allah pung orang dong. Dong mulai deng sadiki sa, ma tamba lama, dong tamba banya.<bt>After that, Yesus continued speaking saying, &lt;&lt;I'll add another *parable again like this: you-pl can compare God's *kingdom2 (people). They begin with just a few (in number), but adding long time, they add many (in number).</bt><v n="31" />Itu tingka ke biji yang paling kici ana.<bt>That is like a seed that is most teeny-tiny.</bt><v n="32" />Ma kalo kotong su tanam itu biji, dia idop jadi pohon yang paling bésar. Ju burung-burung datang cari sombar ko basarang di situ.&gt;&gt;<bt>But (contrary to expectation) if/when we-inc have planted that seed, it lives to become the biggest tree. And birds come seek shade and make (their) nests there.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="basarang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">basarang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Yesus pung cara ajar sang dong iko dong pung mangarti.<bt>Yesus' way to teach them was following/according to their understanding.</bt><v n="34" />Dia biasa pake umpama kalo ajar sang orang dong. Ma kalo deng Dia pung ana bua dong, Dia kasi tau itu umpama pung arti samua.<bt>He usually used *parables/examples if/when he taught them. But if/when with His *disciples, He told them the full/entire meaning of that parable.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin tadó angin ribut<bt>Lord Yesus calms a storm/noisy wind</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 8:23-27; Lukas 8:22-25)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Dia pung sore, Yesus masi di atas parahu. Ju Dia suru Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari kotong balayar pi sablá.&gt;&gt;<bt>When it was late afternoon, Yesus was still on the boat. Then he told/ordered his *disciples/underlings saying, &lt;&lt;Let us-inc go by boat/sail to the other side [of the lake].&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ais dong nae parahu sama-sama deng Yesus. Ju dong balayar kasi tenga itu orang banya dong di situ. Ma ada yang iko nae parahu laen.<bt>After that they got into the boat together with Yesus. And they went by boat/sailed leaving those many people there. But there were some who got into other boats.</bt><v n="37-38" />Itu waktu, Yesus alas Dia pung kapala di bantal ko tidor sonu di balakang. Sonde lama ju angin ribut datang. Galombang puku kasi maso aer di Yesus dong pung parahu, sampe amper ponu. Jadi ana bua dong taku mau mati. Ju dong datang kasi bangun sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Bangun dolo! Kotong su mau calaka ni! Ma Papa sonde toe sang botong!&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time Yesus supported his head on a pillow and slept soundly in the back. Not much later then a storm/noisy wind came. Waves hit making water enter Yesus (coll.-pl) boat, to the point that it was almost full. So (consequently) the *disciples were scared to death. Then they came to wake Him up saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Wake/get up! We're about to have a disaster here! But Father/you don't care about us-ex!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: check to make sure he is in the back of the boat, not behind the boat.] [DISCOURSE: restructured for RL background-foreground, chronology.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="buritan = balakang parahu ; toe"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">buritan = balakang parahu ; toe = pusing</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sonde lama ju angin ribut datang."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Sonde lama ju angin ribut datang. Ombak puku kasi maso aer di Yesus dong pung parahu, sampe amper ponu. Jadi ana bua dong taku mo mati. Itu waktu Yesus alas Dia pung kapala di bantal ko tidor sonu di balakang. Ju dong datang kasi bangun sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Bangun dolo! Kotong su mau calaka ni! Ma Papa sonde toe sang botong!&gt;&gt;<span class="Italic">(37)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus bangun ko togor itu angin bilang, &lt;&lt;Diam!&gt;&gt; Ais Dia parenta itu dano bilang, &lt;&lt;Tadó suda!&gt;&gt; Itu angin langsung barenti, deng dano ju tadó memang.<bt>Hearing that, then Yesus woke/got up to scold/rebuke that wind saying, &lt;&lt;Quiet!&gt;&gt; After that He commanded that lake saying, &lt;&lt;Be calm!&gt;&gt; That wind straight away stopped, and the sea also was truly calm. [EXEG: Gk has two commands and repetition, addressing the wind (a) and the waves (b) separately marking discourse peak: aa bb ab ab. It is best not to conflate them like TEV and CEV do. Keeping them separate can raise their significance in the discourse.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="togor = 1) scold, rebuke 2)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">togor = 1) scold, rebuke 2) greet, sapa ; laut tado =  \ant laut mangamok</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-06-25 08:15:18Z">and</Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Ais Yesus togor Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko bosong samua taku bagitu? Bosong sonde parcaya sang Beta, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>After that Yesus scolded/rebuked His *disciples saying, &lt;&lt;Why were you all afraid like that? You-pl don't *believe in Me, ko [+tag]?&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: RQ purpose = rebuke.] [DISCOURSE: Change of audience, so could make separate paragraph.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Dong samua taku deng heran, ju dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia ni sapa, é? Sampe angin deng galombang ju dengar sang Dia, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>They were all afraid and amazed, also they spoke to each other saying, &lt;&lt;Him here, who is he? Even wind and waves also listen/obey him, ó!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk word has both aspects of ‘fear’ and ‘awe/respect/reverence’ LN. Compare also NRSV ‘great awe’ vs. NLT ‘terrified’.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae orang yang takaná banya setan<bt>Lord Yesus makes well a person afflicted with very many *evil spirits</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 8:28-34; Lukas 8:26-39)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="5" />
      <v n="1" />Ais ju Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong sampe di dano Galilea pung sablá, di satu tampa nama Gerasa.<bt>Then Yesus with his *disciples arrived at lake Galilea's other side, at a place named Gerasa.</bt><v n="2-6" />Di situ ada satu orang laki-laki yang takaná setan sampe gila. Dia tenga di kuburan. Siang-malam dia tapaleuk kuliling bukit-bukit di situ deng talanjang bulat ko batarea tarús-tarús. Dia puku bekin luka dia pung badan deng batu. Ma dia kuat mati pung. Sonde ada orang yang bisa ika sang dia, biar deng rante besi ju. Orang dong su ulang kali ika dia pung kaki-tangan deng rante besi, ma dia bekin putus itu rante deng kasi pata buang besi dari dia pung kaki. Dia talalu kuat sampe sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa tahan sang dia.<bt>There there was a male person who was afflicted by *evil spirit/s until he was crazy/insane. He lived in the graveyard. Night-day he meandered all around those hills stark naked yelling out over and over. And he beat wounding his body with rocks. But he was really really strong (lit. strong wanting to die = strong to the superlative degree). There was no one who could tie him up, even with iron chains. People had already repeatedly tied his hands feet with iron chain, but he severed that chain and broke threw.away iron from his feet. He was too strong, to-point-that there was no one else who could stand up to him. [DISCOURSE: repackaged for RL background-foreground info sorted out to relieve confusion between vs.2 and 6.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kuburan = kerkof (Du, archaic); tapaleuk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">kuburan = kerkof (Du, archaic); tapaleuk = wander around</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00303C.tif" rtfFormat="width:10cm;textWrapping:none">Orang gila yang takaná setan<bt>A crazy man afflicted by evil spirits</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Waktu Yesus dong turun dari parahu ko inja kaki di darat, ju itu orang gila dapa lia sang dong dari jao. Ais dia kaluar dari itu kuburan, ju dia lari pi ko tikam lutut di Yesus pung muka.<bt>When Yesus (collective) got down from the boat to step feet on the land, then that crazy person saw them from far. Then he exited from that graveyard, and he ran to kneel in front of Yesus' face.</bt><v n="7-8" />Lia itu orang pung muka bagitu, ju Yesus omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoi! Setan jahat! Lu kaluar dari ini orang su!&gt;&gt;<bt>Seeing that person's face like that, then Yesus spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Hoi! [+reprimand] Evil spirit! You-sg come out of this person!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="iskarobis ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">iskarobis ;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais, itu orang batarea karás-karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Lu mau bekin apa sang beta! Beta tau Lu ni, memang Yesus, Tuhan Allah yang paling kuasa pung Ana. Beta minta ko Lu jang siksa sang beta!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that person yelled loudly saying, &lt;&lt;Hee! [+objection] You want what with me! I know you-sg here are really Yesus, the Child of God who has the most *power/authority. I request that You don't make things hard for me! [DISCOURSE: 7-8 reordered to get chronology sorted out.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ju Yesus tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu pung nama sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus asked him saying, &lt;&lt;What's your-sg name?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu orang manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung nama <span class="Italic">Legion,</span> te botong ni, banya sakali, tingka ke banya batalyon!&gt;&gt;<bt>That person replied saying, &lt;&lt;My name is <span class="Italic">Legion,</span> cuz (elaboration) we-exc here, are very many, like many batalyons!&gt;&gt; [NOTE: name plus meaning for churched audiences.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ais setan dong pake itu orang ko minta Yesus jang suru sang dong kaluar dari itu da'era.<bt>Then the evil spirits used that person to request that Yesus not order them to leave that region. [NOTE to daughter translations: check if your language prefers this to be made direct speech &lt;&lt;Don't send us away from this region.&gt;&gt;]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Sonde jao dari situ ada barapa orang yang jaga babi satu kandang. Itu babi dong samua kira-kira ada dua ribu ekor. Dong ada cari-cari makan di pinggir gunung.<bt>Not far from there were several people who watched one pen (counter for group of pigs) of pigs. Approximately those pigs are all 2000 tails. They were busy hunting/foraging for food on the side of the mountain. [DISCOURSE: number of pigs from vs. 13 in Gk. RL requires this background info here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pinggir gunung/gunung pung pinggir = lereng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">pinggir gunung/gunung pung pinggir = lereng</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Kira-kira dong samua ada dua ribu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Kira-kira dong samua ada dua ribu ekor.</Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Ais ju itu setan dong minta sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Suru sang botong ko pi maso di itu babi dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then those evil spirits requested Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Order us-ex to go enter in those pigs.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus satuju. Ju itu setan dong lari kaluar dari itu orang ko maso pi dalam itu babi dong. Ju babi yang dua ribu ekor tu, dong balari harba-biruk turun iko gunung pung pinggir pi dalam dano, ju dong samua mati tanggalám di situ.<bt>Hearing that, then Yesus agreed. Then those evil spirits ran exiting from that person to enter into those pigs. Then those pigs which were 2000 tails, they ran and ran falling.over.each.other.in.confusion down the side of the mountain into the lake, then they all died drowning there. [NOTE to daughter translations: OV /jurang/ here was vague, ranging from cliff to steep slope, but defaulting to cliff. There is no cliff around Galilee, so make sure your word matches steep slope /pinggir gunung/ if /jurang/ creates too much noise.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="harba-biruk = all directions, confused, falling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">harba-biruk = all directions, confused, falling over each other; kiri-kanan ~ muka-balakang ~ bata-siram ; lari fuik = liar</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis ju, dong balompa iko pinggir"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Abis ju, dong balompa iko pinggir jurang pi dalam dano,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Dapa lia bagitu, ju orang yang jaga itu babi dong samua jadi taku mau mati. Ais dong lari pi bakastau orang kuliling kampong-kampong di situ. Ju banya orang kaluar datang ko mau pi lia apa yang su jadi.<bt>Seeing that, then those people who were watching those pigs were all scared to death. Then they ran to tell people all around the different villages there. Then many people exited coming because they wanted to go see what had happened.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ephugon: flee, escape from danger, run"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">ephugon: flee, escape from danger, run out of fear, seek safety, shun, avoid</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Dong datang katumu sang Yesus, ju dong dapa lia itu orang yang takaná setan ada dudu di situ. Dia pung pikiran su jadi bae, deng dia su pake pakean. Lia bagitu ju, itu orang dong samua taku, tagal dong tau, sapa yang bisa usir kasi kaluar banya setan dari itu orang, na, dia memang batúl-batúl orang hebat.<bt>They came meeting Yesus, and they saw that person who had been afflicted by evil spirits was sitting there. His thinking was now well/good, and he now wore clothing. Seeing like that, then those people all were afraid, because they knew, whoever could expel driving out many evil spirits from this person, na, he really truly was an amazing/extraordinary person. [DISCOURSE: mind and clothes reordered to fit RL logic.] [EXEG: reason for fear explicated under consultant supervision, because of UNS confusion &amp; wrong answers. See also TRT note.]</bt><v n="16" />Ais dong samua bakastau kuliling bilang, dong su lia deng mata biji sandiri itu orang gila su bae, deng itu babi dong yang su mati tanggalám.<bt>Then they all tell all around that they had seen with their own eyeballs that crazy person healed/now well, and those pigs which had died drowning.</bt><v n="17" />Ju itu orang kampong di situ dong datang minta ko Yesus kasi tenga dong pung tampa.<bt>Then those village people there came asking so that Yesus leave their place.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Waktu Yesus mau nae pi dalam parahu, ju itu orang yang tadi takaná setan datang minta sang Dia ko dia ju mau iko.<bt>When Yesus wanted/was.about.to go.up into the boat then that person who had just previously been afflicted by evil spirits came requesting Him so that he could also follow/go.along.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ma Yesus sonde mau. Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Lebe bae lu pulang ko kasi tau lu pung kelu samua, apa yang Tuhan Allah su bekin kasi sang lu. Deng bilang Tuhan Allah talalu sayang sang lu.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus didn't want that. He spoke saying, &lt;&lt;It's better that you go home to tell all your family, what God has done for you. And that God loves/has.pity.on you very much.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk: mercy]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="stok lama = older generation"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">stok lama = older generation</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais ju itu orang pulang ko pi kuliling satu da'era deng sapulu kota yang dong biasa subu bilang, &lt;Dekapolis&gt;. Dia bacarita apa yang Yesus su bekin kasi sang dia. Samua orang yang dengar dia pung carita tu, dong heran mau mati bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang batúl, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>And then that person went home and went all around a region with ten cities which is usually called &lt;Dekapolis&gt;. He narrated what Yesus had done for him. All the people who heard that story of his, they were amazed [to the superlative degree] saying, &lt;&lt;That's really true, ó!&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: direct speech as RL pattern.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi idop kambali Yairus pung ana. Deng parampuan saki dara loos yang sonto Tuhan Yesus pung baju<bt>Tuhan Yesus makes Yairus' child live again. And a woman sick with uncontrolled blood who touches Yesus' shirt/dress [ALT: a woman touches Jesus clothes]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 9:18-26; Lukas 8:40-56)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais ju Yesus dong balayar pulang pi dano pung sablá. Waktu dong turun dari parahu, orang banya sakali datang makarubu sang Dia.<bt>And then Yesus (collective) sailed going back to the lake's other side. As they got down from the boat, very many people came crowding around Him. [DISCOURSE: 5:18 is about to get into the boat (but hadn't yet); TEV, CEV, and NLT in 5:21 say ‘again’ in with reference to 5:1, (ignoring 5:18), but UNSs read that as Jesus getting into the boat twice. He didn't. So structure this sequence carefully for the RL.]</bt><v n="22" />Di situ ju ada satu orang nama Yairus. Dia tu, kapala ruma sambayang di itu kota. Waktu dia lia sang Yesus, ju dia tikam lutut di Dia pung muka<bt>There there was also a person named Yairus. That him (=I'm going to tell you about him) head of *synagogue (worship house) in that city. When he saw Yesus, then he knelt at His face</bt><v n="23" />ko kokoe bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa, é! Beta pung ana nona baru umur dua blas taon, ada saki amper mati. Papa tolong datang ko bekin bae sang dia dolo.&gt;&gt;<bt>to beg saying, &lt;&lt;Papa, é! My girl child who is just 12 years old, is sick almost to die. Papa please come to heal her now.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: age of girl from vs.42, put here for RL background-foreground patterns.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="taru tangan generally implies kasi berkat,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">taru tangan generally implies kasi berkat, not normally assoc with healing (forced); datang sambayang &gt; heal</Message></Annotation><note reference="5:23" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa tolong datang ko taro tangan sang dia, ko biar dia bae kambali, ju idop.&gt;&gt; Di sana, &lt;&lt;minta taro tangan&gt;&gt; pung arti &lt;&lt;tolong bekin bae&gt;&gt;. Itu nona pung umur tu, bahasa Yunani tulis di ayat 42.<bt>The Yunani language Bible writes saying, &lt;&lt;Papa please come to put your hand on her, so that she is well again, and lives.&gt;&gt; There, &lt;&lt;request to put hands on” meant “please heal”. That young-girl's age, in the Yunani language is written in verse 42.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ju Yesus iko sang Yairus ko pi dia pung ruma.<bt>Then Yesus followed Yairus to go to his house.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma waktu dong mulai jalan, banya orang iko sang Dia sampe dong seti-seti sang Dia dari kiri-kanan.<bt>But while they were walking, many people followed Him to-point-that they shoved Him left-right (=all over the place). [NOTE: commentators agree that this sentence transitions setting up the next story. Many combine it with the next paragraph. Others argue it stands between the two.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="datang bulan (n) = mens"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">datang bulan (n) = mens</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Di itu orang banya dong pung teng-tenga, ada satu parampuan yang dia pung datang bulan sonde barenti batúl su dua blas taon.<bt>In the middle of that crowd, there was a woman whose monthly period hadn't stopped correctly for 12 years.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Di tenga itu orang dong samua,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Di tenga itu orang dong samua,</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Dia su kasi abis dia pung doi deng harta dong ko pake bayar dokter dong. Sonde ada yang bisa bekin bae sang dia. Ma dia pung panyaki tu, foe tarús.<bt>She had spent all her money and all her possessions to use them pay for various doctors. But none of them could heal her. But that sickness of hers continued to get worse.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="foe = jalan, continue, increase"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">foe = jalan, continue, increase</Message></Annotation><v n="27-29" />Itu parampuan su dengar banya, so'al Yesus. Jadi dia baseti di tenga orang banya tu, ko mau datang deka-deka sang Yesus dari Dia pung balakang. Dia ada pikir di dia pung hati bilang, &lt;&lt;Asal beta bisa raba Yesus pung baju sa, pasti beta bae!&gt;&gt;<bt>That woman had heard alot about Yesus. So (consequently), she was elbowing/pushing through in the middle of those many people because she wanted to come very close to Yesus from His back/behind. She had thought in her heart (liver) saying, &lt;&lt;If only I can just touch his shirt/dress, I surely will be healed!&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: Repackaged to get chronology right for RL.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="baseti = makaseti = baku seti;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">baseti = makaseti = baku seti; palang-palang</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-06-05 01:37:41Z">E</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00310C.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Waktu dia sonto Yesus pung baju ju, takuju sa, dia pung dara loos tu, barenti memang. Dia rasa dia su bae batúl.<bt>Just as she touched Yesus' shirt/dress, then just suddenly/unexpectedly, that uncontrolled blood of hers really stopped. She felt she was truly healed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Pas itu waktu ju, Yesus rasa ada tanaga yang kaluar dari Dia pung badan. Ju Dia bale balakang ko lia itu orang banya dong. Ais Dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong sapa yang ada sonto Beta pung baju, é?&gt;&gt;<bt>Exactly at the time also, Yesus felt there was force that exited from His body. Then He turned back to see those many people. Then He asked saying, &lt;&lt;Which one of you-pl touch My shirt/dress, é?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="collocational clash - tanaga doesn't malele"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">collocational clash - tanaga doesn't malele</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Dia pung ana bua dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa lia sandiri sa. Ko orang bagini banya dong baseti satu deng yang laen na. Ais Papa tanya bilang, &lt;Sapa yang sonto Beta pung baju?&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>His *disciples replied saying, &lt;&lt;Papa just look for yourself. This many people are obviously pushing.and.shoving each other [+obvious]. Then Papa asks saying, &lt;Who touched My shirt/dress.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ma Yesus maen lia kuliling, ko mau cari tau sapa yang tadi ada sonto sang Dia.<bt>But Yesus kept on looking all around because he wanted to find out who it was who had just previously touched Him.</bt><v n="33" />Dengar Yesus tanya bagitu, ju itu parampuan su taku mau mati. Ais dia tikam lutut di Yesus pung muka ko mangaku samua bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Beta yang sonto Papa pung baju.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Yesus ask like that, then that woman was scared to death. Then she knelt at Yesus' face to *confess all saying, &lt;&lt;Papa! I'm the one who touched Papa's shirt/dress.&gt;&gt; [NOTE: ‘tremble’ undertranslated here. Don't force a heavy information load if it is implied by ‘scared to death’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="element of trembling explic &gt; implic"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">element of trembling explic &gt; implic</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ju Yesus manyao sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Tagal mama parcaya batúl-batúl sang Beta, andia ko mama su bae. Sakarang mama pulang ruma deng hati tanáng suda, te mama pung susa su abis.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus responded to her saying, &lt;&lt;Because mama truly-truly *believes in Me, that is why mama is healed. Now mama go home with a calm liver [+polite imperative], cuz (elaboration) mama's troubles are over.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk here is ‘in peace’. ‘Troubles are over’ NLT.] [NOTE to daughter translations: be careful of “pulang deng hati tenáng”, cuz that is an idiomatic phrase meaning “now you can die in peace”. So make “pulang ruma” explicit here.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Yesus masi ba'omong bagitu, ju ada orang datang dari Yairus pung ruma, ko kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Kasian é, ana nona su mati. Jadi jang bekin cape sang Bapa Guru lai. Dia sonde usa pi lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus was still talking like that, then a person/people came from Yairus' house, to tell saying, &lt;&lt;So.sorry/sad, the girl child is dead. So (consequently) don't make tired/bother for Father Teacher anymore. It isn't neccessary for Him to go anymore (=don't go).&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk has PL people coming and speaking. Ex. Summ. notes “‘they come’ is an impersonal plural form...” Multiple MTT teams and UNSs say culturally only one (designated) person would speak here with this kind of phrasing. In Kupang, we can make this sentence unmarked for number and keep it vague in both clauses. Not all lgs can do that. If not, I suggest, PL in first clause and SG in second clause. . “Then people came from Yairus' house and (one) told him saying,...” Scenario: a rombongan comes; a jubir delivers the message on behalf of them all. LJ. Aug 2017.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ma Yesus sonde ame pusing itu orang pung omong. Jadi Dia bilang sang Yairus, &lt;&lt;Lu sonde usa taku, é! Parcaya sang Tuhan sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus didn't take concern (pay attention) to that person's talk. So (consequently), He said to Yairus, &lt;&lt;You don't need to be afraid, é! Just believe in God2.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: see discussion in TH re: AGNT, LN 1) ‘ignoring that message’ (supported by 14 authorities plus ftn in several translations), 2) ‘overhearing’, rather than TexRec (diff Gk word) ‘overhearing that message’. TB also follows ‘ignore’.]</bt><v n="37" />Ju Yesus jalan kasi tenga dia pung ana bua laen dong. Ma Dia bawa sang Petrus, Yakobis deng dia pung adi Yohanis, ko dong jalan tarús.<bt>Then Yesus walked leaving his other *disciples. But He brought Petrus, Yakobis and Yohanis, and so they continued walking.</bt><v n="38" />Waktu dong sampe di Yairus pung ruma, dong lia orang banya dong batasibu, deng dengar dong ada manangis makarereu.<bt>When they got to Yairus' house, they saw many people being busy-bodies, and heard them crying wailing in grief.</bt><v n="39" />Yesus maso pi dalam, ais Dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko bosong tasibu deng manangis makarereu bagini? Ini ana sonde mati. Dia cuma tidor sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus went inside, then He asked them saying, &lt;&lt;Why are busy and crying wailing in grief like this? This child isn't dead. She's only just sleeping.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makarereu = wailing in grief, long"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">makarereu = wailing in grief, long wails, as opposed to short sobs (diff word)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40" />Dong dengar Yesus pung omong bagitu, ju dong samua katawa olok-olok sang Dia.<bt>They heard Yesus' talk like that, then they all laughed ridiculing Him. [EXEG: Gk here is ‘make fun of or ridicule by laughing at’ (LN), so just ‘laugh at’ might not carry the sense. Without the explication, one group of UNSs said “They were laughing because they were happy that Jesus had come.”—which made sense to the RC who highly revere everything about Jesus—but that's not what the Gk says.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais Dia suru sang dong samua kaluar. Ju Dia pange ame itu ana pung papa deng mama, deng Dia pung ana bua tiga orang, ko dong samua maso pi dalam itu ana pung kamar.<bt>Then He ordered them all to exit. And He called that child's father and mother, and His 3 disciples, so that they all enter into that child's room.</bt><v n="41" />Ju Yesus pegang itu ana pung tangan, ais Dia pake dong pung bahasa Aram ko omong sang itu ana bilang, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Talita kum!&gt;&gt;</span> (Dia pung arti bilang, &lt;&lt;Nona! Bangun suda!&gt;&gt;)<bt>Then Yesus held that child's hand, then He used their Aram language to speak to her saying, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Talita kum!&gt;&gt;</span> (It's meaning says &lt;&lt;Girl! Get.up!&gt;&gt;) [NOTE to daughter translations: Bahasa Yunani tulis, bilang, /talitha koum/ yang mencerminkan bhs Aram /telitha’ qum/. NRSV, CEV, TB2, dll. samua tulis, bilang, /talitha kum/ ~ /talitha cum/ ~ /talitha koum/ Jadi, kalo TB ju bilang /talitha kum/ akurang ko orang Kristen di Indonesia banya tegas, bilang /talita kumi/?? Dia pung masala bagini: Jaman antoni dong dolu, terjemahan bhs Eropa dong pake naskah Yunani dari kumpulan Beza (andia Textus Receptus) yang kurang tua, deng sonde langkáp. Textus Receptus tu, tulis pake bentuk feminine, andia: /talitha kumi/. Ma samua naskah yg lebe tua, yang lebe langkáp, deng yang lebe dapat diandalkan pake bentuk masculine, andia: /talitha kum/. Bentuk masculine ni, yang samua terjemahan moderen pake tagal dong anggap itu yang sebenarnya. Bentuk masculine ni, yang samua Ahli Biblika moderen pake tagal dong anggap ini yang sebenarnya. Jadi, PB Yunani UBS edisi ke-4 (text yang kita pake di UBB-GMIT), deng Nestle-Aland edisi ke-27 pake /talitha kum/. Cuma Textus Receptus (taon 1519) sa yang pake /talita kumi/. Ma terjemahan Leijdekker, Klinkert, Bode, TL samua iko Textus Receptus, tagal waktu dong ada karjá, Cuma itu sa yang ada. Andia ko secara populer, orang Kristen di Indonesia pertahankan bentuk /talita kumi/. Dari beta, sonde usa diperkarakan. Ma dlm Alkitab bhs Kupang, kotong pake /talita kum/ sa.]</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01713b.tif" rtfFormat="width:8.5cm;textWrapping:none" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42-43" />Takuju sa, itu nona bangun ko mulai bajalan. Ais Yesus suru dia pung mama bilang, &lt;&lt;Kasi ini ana makan suda!&gt;&gt;<bt>Just unexpectedly, that girl got.up to start walking.around. Then Yesus ordered her mother saying, &lt;&lt;Give this child something to eat!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Samua orang yang lia apa yang su jadi tu, dong taheran-heran. Ma Yesus larang karás sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong jang kasi tau sapa-sapa bilang, Beta su kasi idop kambali sang dia!&gt;&gt;<bt>All the people who saw that that happen, they were very amazed-amazed. But Yesus strictly forbade them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl don't tell anyone that I have made her to live again!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Nasaret dong tola sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>The Nasaret people push.aside the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 13:53-58; Lukas 4:16-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="6" />
      <v n="1" />Ais ju Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong samua pulang pi Dia pung kampong Nasaret.<bt>And then Yesus and all His *disciple went.home to His village Nasaret. [DISCOURSE: (referent tracking): ‘all’ here, because previous paragraph only had Peter, James, and John. Consider adding ‘left Capernaum’ for tracking location.]</bt><v n="2" />Pas kaná deng orang Yahudi pung hari sambayang, Yesus maso pi ruma sambayang ko mangajar. Itu hari, ada banya orang yang pi sambayang. Waktu dong dengar Dia pung ajaran, dong taheran-heran, ko bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang pung pintar lai! Dia ju ada pung kuasa na! Karmana ko Dia bisa bagitu?<bt>Exactly at the time it was the Yahudi people's *Sabbath1 (worship day), Yesus entered into the *synagogue (worship house) to teach. That day there were many people who went to worship. As they heard His teaching, they were amazed-amazed, and.so said, &lt;&lt;This person's knowledge is extraordinary! He also obviously has *power! How can it be that He can be like that?</bt><v n="3" />Padahal Dia cuma tukang kayu sa. Kotong kanál Dia pung mama Maria; deng Dia pung adi-adi dong, andia Yakobis, Yoses, Yudas deng Simon. Dia ju ada pung adi parampuan barapa orang. Kotong samua tenga satu kampong na!&gt;&gt; Andia ko dong camburu sampe dong su sonde mau dengar sang Dia lai.<bt>However He is only a carpenter. We know his mama Maria; and his younger siblings, that is Yakobis, Yoses, Yudas and Simon. He also has several female younger siblings. We-inc all live together in one village obviously!&gt;&gt; That is why they were jealous to-point-that they didn't want to hear him anymore.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="camburu = cemburu; jealous"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">camburu = cemburu; jealous</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ju Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang batúl! Orang lebe suka kasi hormat sang Tuhan Allah pung jubir dari tampa laen. Ma di dia pung kampong sandiri, orang sonde kasi hormat sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus told saying, &lt;&lt;It really is true! People like to give respect to God's *prophet (spokesperson) from other places. But in his own village, people don't respect him/her.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang lebe suka kasi hormat sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Orang lebe suka kasi hormat sang Tuhan Allah pung utusan dari tampa laen, daripada di kampong sandiri.</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 4:44</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5-6a" />Ma itu orang dong pung hati karás mau mati, sampe dong sonde mau parcaya sang Yesus. Andia ko Dia heran, ais Dia sonde pake Dia pung kuasa lai di situ. Dia cuma bekin bae satu-dua orang saki sa.<bt>But those people's livers were extremely hard to-point-that they didn't want to believe in Yesus anymore. This.is.the.reason He was surprised/amazed, and didn't use His *power anymore there. He only just healed one two sick people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus utus Dia pung ana bua dua blas orang<bt>Lord Yesus commissions His twelve *disciples</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 10:5-15; Lukas 9:1-6)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6b" />Ais ju Yesus pi kuliling di kampong-kampong yang badeka, ko ajar orang dong Tuhan Allah pung mau.<bt>Then Yesus went all around the different.villages that were close to teach people God's will.</bt><v n="7" />Dia pange ame Dia pung ana bua dua blas orang ko suru dong jalan dua-dua orang pi kasi tau Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae. Dia ju kasi kuasa sang dong ko usir setan.<bt>He called his twelve *disciples to command them to travel in pairs to go tell God's Good News. He also gave them *power to expel *evil spirits.</bt><v n="8-9" />Dia parenta sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong sonde usa bawa bam-banya di jalan, te nanti Tuhan yang ator. Sonde usa bawa bakál, doi, deng tas. Ma bawa tongkat deng sandal di kaki, deng baju satu potong sa.<bt>He commanded them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl don't need to bring alot on the road, cuz (elaboration) God2 will arrange/take care of it. It's not neccessary to bring trip.food, money, and bag. (= don't bring). Bring walking.stick and sandals on feet, and just one shirt/dress. [EXEG: elaboration of reason: high-level context and SEV.] [DISCOURSE: Gk order is mixed; RL order sorted into don't take 1,2,3, just take 4,5,6]</bt><v n="10" />Kalo ada orang tarima sang bosong di dong pung ruma, na, bosong musti tenga di situ sampe bosong barangkat lai.<bt>If people receive you-pl in their house, na, you-pl must stay there until you leave again.</bt><v n="11" />Ma kalo sampe di satu tampa, abis orang di situ dong sonde mau tarima, deng sonde mau dengar sang bosong, na, angka kaki dari situ. Ais kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;Bosong sonde mau dengar na. Jadi biar bosong pikol tanggong-jawab sandiri!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>But if it.comes.to-point-that in one place, then the people there don't want to receive [you], and obviously don't want to hear you, na, pick.up your feet from there. Then tell them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl obviously don't want to listen. So let it be that you (shoulder) carry the responsibility yourselves!&gt;&gt; [STYLE: meaning of symbolic action, worded like a warning.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added 1st sentence to ftn, on"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">***added 1st sentence to ftn, on literal "brush dust off feet"</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:8-11" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dalam Alkitab bahasa Yunani ada tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;kabás buang abu dari dong pung kaki&gt;&gt;. Di sana waktu itu, orang biasa kabás buang abu dari dong pung kaki ko jadi tanda bilang, orang yang sonde mau dengar, na, pikol tanggong-jawab sandiri. Lia ju <span class="Italic">Lukas</span> 10:4-11; <span class="Italic">Utusan dong pung Carita</span> 13:51.<bt>In the Yunani language Bible it is written saying, “brush off the dust from their feet”. There at that time, people would brush off dust from their feet as a sign that people who didn't want to listen/obey, they must shoulder-carry the consequences. Also see Luke 10:4-11; Acts 13:51.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais ju dong pi ko kasi tau itu Kabar Bae. Dong bilang samua orang musti barenti suda dari dong pung sala-sala, ais bale ko idop iko Tuhan pung mau-mau.<bt>And then they went to tell that Good News. They said everyone must stop their wrongs/sins, and/then turn to live following/obeying God's will (=ways of God).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***undertranslated &quot;repent&quot;?"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">***undertranslated "repent"?</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Dong ju usir kasi kaluar setan dong. Ais itu, dong taro minya di orang saki dong pung kapala, ko sambayang bekin bae sang dong. Ju dong bae memang.<bt>And they expelled sending out *evil spirits. After that, they put oil on sick people's heads, in order to pray heal them. So they got well.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="foo = menggembalakan; sapu minya"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">foo = menggembalakan; sapu minya</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="on head??"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">on head??</Message></Annotation><note reference="6:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yakobis 5:14</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong potong bekin mati sang Yohanis tukang sarani<bt>They cut killing Yohanis the One who habitually Baptizes</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 14:1-12; Lukas 9:7-9)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Itu waktu, orang di mana-mana su kanál sang Yesus. Carita so'al Dia pung kuasa tu, ju su sampe di raja Herodes pung talinga. Ada orang bilang, &lt;&lt;Yohanis tukang sarani tu, su idop kambali di Yesus pung diri! Andia ko Dia bisa bekin itu tanda heran dong samua.&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time people everywhere already knew about/recognised Yesus. Stories about that power of His, also had arrived at raja Herodes' ears. There were people who said, &lt;&lt;That Yohanis who habitually Baptizes, lives again in Yesus' self. That is why He can make all those *miracles (amazing signs).&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ma ada orang laen yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Ini Elia yang su idop ulang di Dia pung diri.&gt;&gt; Ada laen lai yang bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia tu, Tuhan Allah pung jubir yang laen dari dolu dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>But there were other people who said, &lt;&lt;No! It's Elia who lives again in His self.&gt;&gt; Still others said, &lt;&lt;He is one of God's other *prophets (spokesperson) from long ago.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk has 2 groups speaking here.] [DISCOURSE: low prominence in the higher level structure, so no paragraph break needed.]</bt><note reference="6:14-15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 16:14, Markus 8:28, Lukas 9:19</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ma waktu raja Herodes dengar dong omong ame Yesus bagitu ju, dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini tantu Yohanis tukang sarani yang tempo hari beta suru potong ame dia pung kapala. Sakarang dia su idop kambali lai, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>But when raja Herodes heard them talking about Yesus like that, then he replied saying, &lt;&lt;This is certainly Yohanis who habitally Baptizes whom at a previous time I ordered that they cut off his head. Now he lives again, ó!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17-18" />Raja Herodes suru bagitu, tagal dia ada parkara bésar deng Yohanis. Dia pung carita bagini: raja Herodes su kawin ame sang dia pung adi Filipus pung maitua, nama Herodias. Padahal Filipus deng Herodias balóm bacere. Andia ko Yohanis togor ulang-ulang bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa raja sonde bole ba'ame deng papa pung adi pung bini. Te itu su langgar kotong pung adat Yahudi na!&gt;&gt; Biar bagitu, ma Herodes kawin deng itu parampuan ju. Ais ju dia suru orang dong pi tangkap ame sang Yohanis ko kasi maso pi bui.<bt>Raja Herodes ordered like that, because he had a big dispute with Yohanis. The story is like this: raja Herodes had married-taken (serial vb) his younger sibling Filipus' wife, named Herodias. However Filipus and Herodias were not yet divorced. That is why Yohanis scolded him over and over saying, &lt;&lt;Papa Raja can't be recip-taking (=marry) papa's younger sibling's wife. Cuz (elaboration) that violates our-inc Yahudi custom!&gt;&gt; But Herodes married that woman anyway. Then he ordered people to go capture Yohanis to put him in jail. [DISCOURSE: restructured to get the flashback and background laid out for RL.] [EXEGESIS: the problem is not just marrying yBW, but that the yB is still alive, and they are not divorced. See France. Jewish law prohitibed marrying yBW (Lev. 18:16; 20:21), whereas RL cultures allow it as long as he is dead or they are divorced.]</bt><note reference="6:17-18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 3:19-20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Tagal Yohanis su togor ulang-ulang bagitu, andia ko itu parampuan simpan hati ko mau bunu bekin mati sang dia sa. Ma balóm sampat, te Herodes su tahan ame sang dia di bui.<bt>Because Yohanes had scolded over and over like that, therefore that woman held.a.grudge (stored her liver) because she just wanted to murder him. But there was not yet the opportunity, cuz (elaboration) Herodes kept him in jail.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="saki hati / simpan hati /"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">saki hati / simpan hati / binci (mau dendam); sampat = salák (Du? slack?)</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ju dia suru tantara dong ko jaga bae-bae sang Yohanis.<bt>And he told the soldiers to guard him well. [EXEG: Gk ‘protect’]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Memang Herodes eleng sang Yohanis. Dia tau bilang, Yohanis tu, Tuhan Allah yang kirim sang dia. Deng dia tu, orang bae. Herodes memang suka dengar Yohanis pung omong. Ma satu-satu kali, dia pung hati tar enak dengar Yohanis pung omong.<bt>It's true that Herodes was really in awe/fear of Yohanis. He knew that that Yohanis, God who sent him. And he was a good person. Herodes actually liked to hear Yohanis' talk. But sometimes, his liver didn't feel good hearing Yohanis' talk. [EXEG: Gk ‘holy’ in this verse focuses on someone who works for/belongs to God, rather than focuses on being clean/sinless (TN, TRT). Gk ‘fear’ here has both the sense of ‘fear’ AND ‘respect/awe’. See LN. Compare NRSV and NLT.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="eleng = segan dan takut, was-was"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">eleng = segan dan takut, was-was ; hati kici = takut; soldadu ~ sardadu ~ askár ~ tantara</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais itu, ju satu hari, mama Herodias dapa sampat ko balas dia pung saki hati. Itu hari, dong ada bekin raja Herodes pung hari jadi. Dong undang orang-orang bésar ko dong datang makan hari jadi. Yang datang tu, orang pamarenta, tantara pung kapala dong, deng tua-tua adat Galilea dong.<bt>And so after that, one day, mama Herodias got an opportunity to revenge her sick liver. That day they were making raja Herodes' birthday. They invited all the big (important) people to come eat birthday (= eat at the birthday party). Those who came, government people, the soldiers heads, and the traditional leaders of Galilea. [EXEG: the ‘opportune time’ is for Herodias, not Herod. See NLT, NRSV, CEV, TRT.]</bt><v n="22" />Di teng-tenga pesta, ju mama Herodias pung ana nona maso pi baronggeng. Dia pung ronggeng talalu bagus, sampe bekin sanáng Herodes deng dia pung tamu dong. Ju Herodes pange sang dia ko tanya, &lt;&lt;Lu mau minta apa sang beta, na, kasi tau sa! Nanti beta kasi.<bt>In the middle of the feast, then mama Herodias' girl child went in to dance. Her dancing was very good, to-point-that it made Herodes happy and all his guests. Then Herodes called her to say, &lt;&lt;You-sg want whatever from me, na, just tell [it]! I'll give it to you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ronggeng = menari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">ronggeng = menari</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Biar lu minta bagi dua beta pung karaja'an ju, beta kasi. Beta sumpa deng Tuhan Allah pung nama!&gt;&gt;<bt>Even if you also ask divide in two my kingdom (loan), I'll give it. I swear with God's name!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk term is a strong kind of oath that calls upon deity as witness, and to punish if the promise is not fulfilled. Some RL languages classify this as a ‘death oath’. See LN, TH, TRT.] [DISCOURSE: extra quote margin in Gk for same speaker removed, since quote margins signal a change of speaker in RL lgs.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ju itu nona pi ko tanya dia pung mama bilang, &lt;&lt;Mama! Mama kira beta minta apa yang paling bae sang papa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that girl went to ask her mother saying, &lt;&lt;Mama! What does mama think would be the best think for me to ask from papa?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dia pung mama manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Naaa! Pi ko minta ame itu Yohanis pung kapala.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then her mama replied saying, &lt;&lt;Naaa [+satisfaction]! Go ask for that Yohanis' head.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais, itu nona datang sang Herodes capát-capát, ko pasán bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Beta minta ko bawa kasi sang beta Yohanis pung kapala taro dalam dulang. Sakarang ju!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that girl went to Herodes hurriedly to instruct saying, &lt;&lt;Papa! I request so that bring give to me Yohanis' head placed on a tray. And now!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis, itu nona datang sang Herodes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Abis, itu nona datang sang Herodes ko bilang,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Herodes dengar ame bagitu, ju dia pung hati ilang memang. Ma dia su sonde bisa hela kambali dia pung sumpa, te samua orang su dengar na.<bt>Herodes heard that, then his liver disappeared. But he couldn't yank back his oath, cuz (elaboration) obviously all the people had already heard [it].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati ilang = discouraged, putus asa,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">hati ilang = discouraged, putus asa, bingung, takuju; hela collocates w/sumpa</Message></Annotation><v n="27" />Ais ju dia parenta satu komandán ko pi potong ame sang Yohanis pung kapala dari dalam bui.<bt>Then he commanded a commander to go cut off Yohanis head from within the jail. [EXEG: Gk is ‘1) soldier-executioner; 2) soldier-trusted official courier’; RL worldview is that Herod would not interact directly with a common soldier, but with someone of status, so the two converge. Many English versions are undertranslated here.]</bt><v n="28" />Ju dong potong ame Yohanis pung kapala, ais taro dalam dulang, ko pi kasi sang itu nona. Dia tarima ame itu dulang, ju dia koko bawa pi kasi sang dia pung mama.<bt>Then they cut Yohanis' head, next placed it on a tray, to go give it to that girl. She accepted that tray, then she carried taking it to give to her mama.</bt><v n="29" />Waktu Yohanis pung ana bua dong dengar bilang, dong su angka bawa Yohanis pung kapala, ju dong datang ame dia pung mayat, ko pi kubur sang dia.<bt>When Yohanis' *disciples heard that they (=Herod &amp; co.) had lifted taking (svc euphemism indicating ‘cut off’) Yohanis' head, then they came took his corpse, to go bury it.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Bagitu sa, carita Yohanis pung mati.<bt>It's just like that, the story of Yohanis' death. [DISCOURSE: natural RL closure to end the flashback and resume Jesus' story. ALT: That is why Herod thought that John had come back to life in Jesus' body.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="carita mati = carita sia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">carita mati = carita sia</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi makan lima ribu orang lebe<bt>Lord Yesus feeds more than five thousand people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 14:13-21; Lukas 9:10-17; Yohanis 6:1-14)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Satu waktu, ana bua yang Yesus su utus tu, dong pulang samua ko bakumpul ulang lai deng Dia. Dong kasi tau samua yang dong su bekin, deng apa yang dong su ajar sang orang dong.<bt>One time, those *disciples/underlings that Yesus had sent/ commissioned, they all came home to gather once again with Him. They told all they they had done, and what they had taught to people. [EXEG: Gk here is literally ‘apostles’, but it is used in it's literal sense (not its sense in Acts) referring to “the ones who had been sent out” (in Mrk 6:7, 12). So make that the verb, and use ‘disciples’ for referent tracking.]</bt><v n="31" />Ma itu waktu, talalu banya orang bajalan pi-datang ko cari sang Yesus. Sampe-sampe Dia deng Dia pung ana bua dong sonde bisa makan lai. Ju Yesus kasi tau Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Mari ko kotong pi cari tampa sunyi, ko kotong bisa barenti cape ame sadiki doo.&gt;&gt;<bt>But at that time very many people were travelling going to find Yesus. To the point that He and His *disciples couldn't eat anymore. Then Yesus told his disciples saying, &lt;&lt;Let us-inc go find a lonely place, so that (purpose) we-inc can stop our tiredness a bit first (idiom = rest).&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cape = léla"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">cape = léla</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Jadi dong samua nae pi dalam parahu ko pi cari tampa sunyi yang jao dari kampong.<bt>So (consequently) they all climbed/embarked in a boat to (purpose) seek a lonely place that was far from the village/s (generic).</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ma itu orang banya dong dapa lia Yesus dong pung parahu pi iko-iko dano pung pinggir. Ais dong kaluar kampong iko jalan darat, ju dong sampe lebe dolo dari Yesus dong.<bt>But those many people saw Yesus them's boat going along that lake's edge. Then they exited the village following a land path, then2 they arrived ahead of Yesus (collective).</bt><v n="34" />Waktu Yesus turun dari parahu, ju Dia dapa lia orang banya su tunggu sang Dia. Ais ju Dia jato kasian sang dong, tagal dong samua sonde tau mau bekin apa, sama ke domba yang sonde ada pung gambala. Ais Dia ajar sang dong Tuhan Allah pung mau<bt>As Yesus was getting down from the boat, then2 he saw the many people waiting for Him. And then He dropped pity/love on them (=had compassion), because (reason) they all did not know what/how they should be doing, same as sheep that doesn't have a shepherd. Then He taught them God's will (= things/ways of God)</bt><note reference="6:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daftar Sensus 27:17, 1 Raja-raja dong 22:17, 2 Sajara Isra'el deng Yahuda 18:16, Yeskial 34:5, Sakaria 10:2, Mateos 9:36</note><v n="35-36" />dari siang sampe sore. Ju Dia pung ana bua dong kasi tau sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Lebe bae Papa suru ini orang dong samua ko dong pi béli makan di kampong-kampong badeka di sini. Te ini su sore ni, deng sonde ada makanan di sini.&gt;&gt;<bt>from mid-day to late afternoon. Then His *disciples told Him saying, &lt;&lt;Papa! It would be good if Papa  (=you) told all these people to go buy food in the nearby villages. Cuz (elaboration) this is already late afternoon now, and there is no food here.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde usa! Bosong sa yang kasi makan sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;It's not necessary = No! You-pl just feed them.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma dong bale tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Awe'! Kalo botong kasi makan orang bagini banya, na, botong musti kasi kaluar doi banya mau mati! Sama ke satu tukang pung gaji satu taon!<bt>But they responded asking saying, &lt;&lt;Awee [+dismay]! If we-exc feed as many people as this, na, we-exc will have to give out an incredible amount of money! Same as a craftsman's entire year wage (loan)!</bt><note reference="6:37" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani asli tulis bilang, &lt;&lt;dua ratus <span class="Italic">denari</span> uang perak&gt;&gt;. Satu <span class="Italic">denari</span> uang perak jaman dolu, sama ke tukang pung gaji karjá satu hari.<bt>The original Greek language Bible writes saying, &lt;&lt;two hundred <span class="Italic">denari</span> silver money. One <span class="Italic">denari</span> silver money in the old times, is the same as a laborer's wage for one day's work.</bt></note>Mana bisa botong dapa doi banya bagitu!&gt;&gt;<bt>How can we-exc (possibly) get that much money!&gt;&gt; [RQ: = we can't]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="awe = dismay"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">awe = dismay</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pi cari tau dolo, sapa yang ada bawa bakál.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl go find out, who has brought travel food.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais ju dong pi cari tau, ju dong kambali kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada roti lima bua, deng ikan dua ekor sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>So then they went to find out, then they returned to tell saying, &lt;&lt;There's just 5 fruit (counter) of bread, and 2 tails of fish.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00155C.tif" rtfFormat="width:4.0cm;textWrapping:around;horizontalPosition:left" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ais Yesus suru itu orang samua ko dudu bakumpul di atas rumput.<bt>Then Yesus ordered all those people to sit in groups on the grass. [EXEG: feeding 5,000 = sitting on grass; feeding 4,000 = sit on ground]</bt><v n="40" />Ju dong pi dudu bakumpul. Ada yang bakumpul saratus-saratus orang, deng ada yang lima-lima pulu orang.<bt>Then they went to sit in groups. There were those in groups of 100-100 people, and those of 50-50 people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="should this be lima pulu -"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">should this be lima pulu - lima pulu ; grammar</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ais ju Yesus ame itu roti lima bua, deng itu ikan dua ekor. Ju Dia mangada pi langit ko minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Ais itu, Dia kasi pica-pica itu roti, ju sorong kasi pi Dia pung ana bua, ko dong pi bagi-bagi kasi sang itu orang dong samua. Itu ikan dua ekor ju Dia bagi-bagi kasi.<bt>So then Yeus took those 5 fruit of bread and those two tails of fish. Then2 he faced up to the sky to give thanks (assimilated loan) to God. After that He broke-broke that bread, then stretched out his hand giving them to his *disciples so that (purpose) they go divide-divide them to all those people. Those two tails of fish also He divided out [among them].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pe'e roti = open (but balom"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">pe'e roti = open (but balom tantu putus)</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Ais ju dong samua makan sampe kinyang.<bt>And then they all ate until satisfied.</bt><v n="43" />Makan abis ju, itu ana bua dong pi kumpul ame itu makanan yang lebe dong, ponu dua blas bakul.<bt>After eating, then those *disciples went to collect that food that was extra, 12 full baskets. [EXEG: Gk in Mrk uses different words for ‘12 baskets’ with feeding 5,000 vs. ‘7 baskets2’ with feeding 4,000. Both should be common baskets with a tight enough weave that smallish pieces of bread aren't going to fall through. And they need to be a size that can be picked up (i.e. not the giant rice storage baskets). Use terms for two different kinds of baskets in these two stories if you lg can do that naturally. But don't force it or overtranslate. Some scholars think the 7 baskets with feeding the 4,000 is a slightly larger size.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="both bakul (BI) and karanjang are"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">both bakul (BI) and karanjang are context dependent as to size; ko'e = karanjang (not widely known); sapai = closely woven; karanjang = open weave</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="44" />Itu orang dong kira-kira ada lima ribu orang. Itu baru itong laki-laki yang makan sa. Balóm reken tamba parampuan deng ana-ana.<bt>They approximately were 5000 people. That's just the males who ate. Not yet counting adding the women and children.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="itong = reken"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">itong = reken</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang laki-laki sa yang iko makan,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Orang laki-laki sa yang iko makan, dong pung banya kira-kira ada lima ribu orang. Balóm itong tamba parampuan deng ana-ana.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus jalan di atas aer<bt>Lord Yesus walks on top of the water</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 14:22-33; Yohanis 6:16-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Ais itu, Yesus suru Dia pung ana bua dong pi nae parahu ko pi lebe dolo di kampong Betsaida di dano pung sablá. Ma Dia masi tenga di situ, ko suru itu orang banya dong pulang.<bt>After that, Yesus ordered His *disciples/underlings to get.into the boat to go ahead to the village Betsaida on that lake's other side. But He still stayed there, to order those many people to return home.</bt><v n="46" />Waktu dong samua pulang, ju Dia nae pi gunung satu ko sambayang.<bt>When they had all gone home, then He went up a mountain to *pray1/worship.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47-50" />Waktu su malam ju, Yesus turun kambali. Dia su dapa lia ana bua dong pung parahu su sampe di teng-tenga dano. Ma dong ada badayong satenga mati, tagal parahu balayar lawan angin muka na. Waktu amper siang ju, Yesus pi iko sang dong. Ma Dia jalan sa di atas aer. Waktu Dia su mau lewat itu parahu, ju dong dapa lia sang Dia. Dong takuju mau mati. Tarús dong batanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Hee! Apa ni? Setan, ko apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>When it was dark/night, then Yesus went down again. He had seen his disciples' boat had already arrived in the middle of the lake. But they were paddling very, very hard, because (reason) that boat was sailing opposing the front wind [+emphatic]. When it was almost morning/daylight, then Yesus went following them. But He just walked on top of the water. When He was about to pass by the boat, then they saw Him. They were extremely afraid. Straight away they asked.each.other saying, &lt;&lt;Hee! [+confusion] What's this? And *evil spirit, or what?&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE (tracking time): See NLT and BAGD, plus vs. 35-36 followed by series of events listed; i.e. late afternoon (feed, send home, send across lake, go up mountain); during the night (come down mountain [required by target language discourse patterns], see disciples--independent, not sequential) juxtaposition of "land" and "sea/lake" also taken as "shore" and "water"; 4th watch of the night = around 3-4am; check that "on the water" in the title and in text is feet touching the water, not hovering/flying "over/above" the water.] [EXEG: Gk is ‘wanted/about to pass by them’; some people erroneously assume he was coming to get into the boat.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="group#1 = hantu is in the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">group#1 = hantu is in the utan, not laut; group #2 = there are hantu laut; but both groups, when you see s.t. you call it 'setan'. Air Mata talk about bunti-ana (female). suanggi</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-06-20 03:20:02Z">a</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma Yesus langsung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Woe! Bosong jang taku, ó! Ini Beta ni.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus immediately talked saying, &lt;&lt;Woe! [+attract attention] You-pl don't be afraid, ó! It's Me here.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Waktu Yesus nae pi dalam parahu, ju itu angin tadó memang. Dia pung ana bua dong samua heran tar abis-abis.<bt>When Yesus got into the boat, then that wind was really calm. His disciples all were amazed limitlessly.</bt><v n="52" />Dong baru lia Yesus pake Dia pung kuasa ko kasi makan lima ribu orang lebe. Ma dong balóm mangarti batúl Dia pung kuasa, tagal dong pung hati karás.<bt>They had just seen Yesus use His *power to feed more than 5000 people. But they still didn't truly understand His power, because their hearts were hard. [EXEG: Gk ‘concerning the loaves’ seen as representing the whole event. TH, TN, TEV, TRT]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang saki di Genesaret dong rame-rame pi di Tuhan Yesus<bt>Sick people at Genesaret are busy going to Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 14:34-36)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="53" />Waktu dong sampe di dano pung sablá, ju dong balabu di kota Genesaret pung pante.<bt>When they arrived at the lake's other side, then they anchored at Genasaret city's beach.</bt><v n="54" />Waktu dong turun dari parahu, orang banya su dapa lia sang dong. Ju dong batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Yesus su datang ni!&gt;&gt;<bt>When they got down from the boat, many people had already seen them. And they shouted saying, &lt;&lt;We! [+attention!] Yesus has come, ó!&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="55-56" />Dong samua lari pi bakastau kuliling, ju orang dong pikol bawa datang orang-orang saki dong.<bt>They all ran to go tell all around, then people shoulder carried bringing sick people.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Pokonya, asal dong dengar bilang, Yesus ada di satu tampa, dong rame-rame pikol bawa orang saki, ko kasi tidor sang dong di tana lapang. Dong pikir kata, &lt;&lt;Asal itu orang saki dong sonto ame Yesus pung ujung baju sa, tantu dong bae.&gt;&gt; Sonto bagitu, ju dong bae memang.<bt>The important thing was as long as they heard that Yesus was at a place, they enthusiastically (lots of people) shoulder carried sick people. to lay them on the flat land/area/open field. They thought saying, &lt;&lt;If only those sick people just touch the edge of Yesus' shirt/dress, then they'll be truly healed.&gt;&gt; When they touched (His clothes), they were healed straight away. [DISCOURSE: made direct speech following good RL patterns.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pokoknya = \va poknya; tana lapang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">pokoknya = \va poknya; tana lapang = rata, luas, lapangan</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Manusia pung atoran jang ganti buang Tuhan Allah pung parenta<bt>Human's regulations shouldn't replace God's commands</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 15:1-9)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="7" />
      <v n="1" />Ada satu rombongan orang Farisi deng barapa guru agama datang dari Yerusalem ko katumu sang Yesus.<bt>There was a (travelling)group/delegation of Farisi people and several *religious teachers who came from Yerusalem to meet with Yesus.</bt><v n="2-5" />Itu orang Farisi dong pegang karás dong pung adat Yahudi. Umpama, kalo orang mau makan, musti cuci tangan iko adat pung mau. Bagitu ju, kalo pulang pasar, dong musti mandi dolo. Sampe-sampe dong pung barang dapur sandiri, sama ke pareu, piring, galás, cerek, samua musti cuci iko adat pung mau, baru bole pake makan.<bt>Those Farisi people hold tight their Yahudi customs/law. For example, if/when a person wants to eat, they must wash hands according to the will/ways of custom/law. Like that also, if return home from market, they must bathe first (=before doing anything else). To the point that their very own kitchen things, like cooking pots, dishes, glasses, pitchers, all must wash following the will/ways of custom/law, only then is it allowable to use them to eat. [BACKGROUND: this is not about washing for cleanliness, but washing for ritual/ceremonial purposes following prescribed methods and sequences. Watch the M's on Friday washing ritualistically before entering the mosque. The Talmud and Mishnah give details of how it should be done.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Kalo ada orang Yahudi laen yang sonde iko itu adat, orang Farisi dong mara.<bt>If there are other Yahudi people who don't follow that custom/law, the Farisi people get angry.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Andia ko, dong mara waktu dong dapa lia Yesus pung ana bua dong makan sonde cuci tangan iko adat pung mau. Ais dong datang ko kasi sala sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko lu pung ana bua dong makan, ma sonde cuci tangan dolo? Itu, dong su malawan kotong pung adat dari nene-moyang!&gt;&gt;<bt>That is why they got angry when they saw Yesus's *disciples eating without washing hands according to the will/ways of custom/law. Then they came to accuse Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Why do your *disciples/underlings eat, but they don't wash hands first/beforehand? That (means) they've already violated/opposed our-inc customs/law from ancestors!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6-7" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong ni, memang orang yang omong laen bekin laen! Dari dolu ba'i Yesaya su tulis Tuhan Allah pung pasán bilang,<bt>But Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl here are truly people who say other, do other (say one thing, and do the other). From long ago forefather Yesaya wrote God's message saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Ini orang dong puji sang Beta,<bt>&lt;These people *praise Me,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">cuma deng mulu sa, ma sonde deng hati.<bt>only just with mouth, but not with liver (seat of emotions).</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Dong bekin bagitu, ju parcuma sa.<bt>They do like that, and its just fruitless/no results/pointless.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dong angka manusia pung atoran,<bt>They elevate humans' laws/regulations,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">sama ke itu atoran turun dari Beta.<bt>just like/as if that law/regulation has beend handed down from Me.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Padahal bukan Beta yang bekin itu atoran.&gt;<bt>Whereas in fact it was not Me who made that law/regulation.&gt; [EXEG: They teach their human laws as if they were God's laws. AGNT, NLT, NRSV, TRT.]</bt><note reference="7:6-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 29:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Bosong ju sama deng itu.<bt>You-pl also are like that. [NOTE: UNSs could not connect the OT quote to the story without making this explicit (under consultant guidance).]</bt><v n="8-9" />Bosong su kasi tenga Tuhan Allah pung parenta, ko mau iko manusia pung adat sa. Bosong memang pintar sakali bekin bagitu!<bt>You have left behind/abandoned God's command/s/laws, just wanting to follow humans' custom/law2. You are really very clever/skilled at doing like that! [STYLE: Gk uses irony/cynicism here. Very difficult to translate. Jesus is NOT praising them! Discuss carefully. Check carefully. Restructure if needed.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Dolu-dolu ba'i Musa su kasi tau Tuhan Allah pung parenta bilang, &lt;Kasi hormat sang bosong pung mama deng papa.&gt; Deng tamba lai bilang, &lt;Kalo satu orang maki dia pung mama ko papa, musti hukum kasi mati sang dia.&gt;<bt>Long ago forefather Musa told God's command saying, &lt;Give honour to your-pl father and mother.&gt; And adding further saying, &lt;If a person curses/swears at his mother or father, must judge/punish killing him/her.&gt; [DISCOURSE: M and F reordered for RL naturalness.]</bt><note reference="7:10" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:12, 21:17, Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 20:9, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 5:16</note><v n="11-12" />Tuhan Allah ajar bagitu, ma bosong ajar laen lai. Bosong bilang, &lt;Kalo orang janji mau kasi satu barang sang Tuhan Allah, biar dia pung mama deng papa sangsara mau mati, ma itu barang sonde bole pake ko bantu dong, te su janji nanti mau kasi sang Tuhan Allah na.&gt;<bt>God taught like that, but you-pl teach something different again. You-pl say, &lt;If a person promises to give a thing to God, even if/though his mother and father are in extreme suffering, nevertheless/but that thing cannot be used to help them, cuz (elaboration) it has been promised that it will be given to God.&gt; [DISCOURSE: restructured background-foreground so the point gets across. Needs to be clear that this thing has been promised, but not delivered. The person still has it.]</bt><v n="13" />Andia ko Beta su bilang tadi, bosong su buang Tuhan Allah pung mau, ko bosong ganti deng atoran baru. Ada banya atoran yang bosong su ganti bagitu.&gt;&gt;<bt>That is why I said earlier, you-pl have thrown away God's will/ways, and so you have exchanged/replaced [it] with a new regulation/law. There are many regulations which you have exchanged/replaced like that.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Parkara jahat yang kaluar dari orang pung hati<bt>Evil matters/issues which come out from people's liver</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin kamomos"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">bekin kamomos</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 15:10-20)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais ju Yesus pange orang laen dong di situ, ko bilang, &lt;&lt;Pasang talinga dolo, ko bosong mangarti.<bt>After that, Yesus called other people there, and said, &lt;&lt;Attach your ears, so that you-pl understand.</bt><v n="15" />Apa yang maso pi dalam parú, itu sonde bekin kamomos orang. Ma apa yang kaluar, itu yang bekin kamomos.<bt>What enters into the stomach, that doesn't make people dirty/defiled. But what exits/comes out, that is what makes dirty/defiled.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kamomos = kotor; (dodolek), daki;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">kamomos = kotor; (dodolek), daki;</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />[Naa, sapa yang ada talinga, dengar bae-bae, ó!]&gt;&gt;<bt>[Naa [+shift], whoever has ears, listen carefully/carefully, ó!]&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="taru kira = pay attention!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">taru kira = pay attention!</Message></Annotation><note reference="7:16" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani asli yang lebe tua, sonde tulis ini ayat 16.<bt>Original Greek language writings which are older don't write this verse 16.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong jalan kasi tenga itu orang dong, ko maso pi dalam satu ruma. Ju Dia pung ana bua tanya itu umpama pung arti.<bt>Then Yesus with His *disciples/underlings they went leaving behind those people, to enter a house. Then His *disciples asked that *parable/example's meaning.</bt><v n="18-19" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong ju sonde mangarti, ko? Dia pung maksud bagini: apa yang orang makan, itu bae. Ma yang kaluar tu, tar bae. Apa yang kotong makan, maso di parú, abis kaluar ulang lai. (Tuhan Yesus pung maksud bilang, orang bole makan apa sa. Sonde larang.)<bt>Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl also don't understand, ko [+tag]? It's meaning is like this: what people eat, that is good. But that which comes out, is not good. What we-inc eat, enters the stomach, and then comes out again. (The Lord Yesus' meaning that people can eat whatever. There is no prohibition.) [EXEG: Gk uses ‘latrine/sewer’ here, so check that it is clear this bit is talking (acceptably) about feces.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ma apa yang kaluar dari orang pung hati, itu yang bekin kamomos sampe Tuhan Allah noju sang dia, deng sonde mau bagabung deng dia.<bt>But what comes out of a person's liver (fig: seat of character and emotions), that's what makes (him/her) dirty/defiled to the point that God is repulsed/abhorred with/by him/her and doesn't want to join/be together with him/her.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="noju = najis, be repulsed, emgihik,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">noju = najis, be repulsed, emgihik, menjijikan; ngeri</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Te banya parkara jahat kaluar dari orang pung hati! Sama ke: pikir jahat, maen serong deng orang yang bukan dia pung laki ko dia pung bini, mancuri, bunu orang,<bt>Cuz (elaboration) many evil matters/things (abstract) come out of people's liver [general state of affairs]. Like/for example: thinking evil, play off-track (sexually) with a person who is not his/her husband or wife [KT: better match for broad Gk /porneia/], stealing, killing people,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cabul"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">cabul</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />balalas, barsina, jahat, putar-balek, iko nafsu, iri hati, omong kasi jato orang, sombong, kurang ajar, deng kapala batu.<bt>greedy, adultery (one member married), evil (broad), lying/deception, following own desire/lust, jealousy, talking to make people fall (talk bad about people), arrogance, rude/impolite/disrespectful, stubbornness. [NOTE to daughter translations: Careful. /iri hati/ can mean 1) angry, or 2) jealous. We're looking for the second. Using /camburu/ and loan /jelus/ may help narrow down what we're looking for here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bacabul = adultery, zina; ho-hongge ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">bacabul = adultery, zina; ho-hongge = main-main perempuan dan laki-laki galoju, = parakus, greedy, glutton; (UNS: galoju not known); saraka = rakus, mau dia sa, selfish, greedy (more in relation to barang, but can be food); rakus more collocates with food; balalas = perakus, loba (BI)<span class="Italic">(22)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Naa, samua yang jahat bagitu tu, kaluar dari orang pung hati. Itu yang bekin rusak sang dia. Tuhan Allah ju noju sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [+shift to conclusion], all that is evil like that, come out of a person's liver. That is what makes him ruined/broken/defiled. God also is repulsed/abhorred at him.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bantu satu mama yang bukan orang Yahudi<bt>Yesus helps a woman who is not a Yahudi person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 15:21-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ais ju Yesus dong kasi tenga itu tampa, ko pi satu kota nama Tirus. Sampe di situ, tarús dong maso pi dalam satu ruma, tagal Yesus sonde mau ada orang tau Dia ada di situ. Ma Dia sonde bisa sambunyi.<bt>After that, Yesus (collective) left that place, to go to a city named Tirus. Arriving there, straight away they went into a house, because Yesus didn't want anyone to know He was there. But He couldn't hide/conceal.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lantaran = tagal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">lantaran = tagal</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25-26" />Di situ ada satu mama yang bukan orang Yahudi. Dia lahir di da'era Fenisia di propinsi Siria sana. Waktu dia dengar Yesus datang, dia pi minta Yesus ko usir kasi kaluar setan dari dia pung ana parampuan.<bt>There there was a mama who was not a Yahudi person. She was born in the Fenisia area of Siria province over there [+remote]. When she heard that Yesus had come, she went ask Yesus to expel exiting an *evil spirit from her daughter. [DISCOURSE: restructured for RL background-foreground.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Dogs&quot; implicit to make the word"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">"Dogs" implicit to make the word play make sense.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="foo - menggembalakan, menggiring; soya 'bow"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">foo - menggembalakan, menggiring; soya 'bow with respect', tunduk dgn hormat (can be mocking); noki = minta secara mendesak (kasar)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ma Yesus buang bahasa bilang, &lt;&lt;Ana-ana dong musti makan lebe dolo, baru buang dia pung sisa kasi anjing.&gt;&gt; [Deng maksud tasambunyi, Yesus musti bantu Dia pung orang Yahudi dolu, baru bisa bantu orang laen.]<bt>But Yesus threw out language (=riddle/indirect speech) saying, &lt;&lt;The children must eat first, only then throw away its leftovers to give the dog/s. [With a hidden meaning, (that) Yesus must help His Yahudi people first, only then can he help other people.] [EXEG: Many people do not know that ‘dog’ was a code word used by the Jews about Gentiles. This is a key point to this passage. For lg after lg we have had to make the meaning explicit—using square brackets to flag that we know it is not words from the Gk text.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="buang bahasa = omong laen, maksud"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">buang bahasa = omong laen, maksud laen (arti tasambunyi); lia = look after</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ma itu mama balas bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, Papa! Ma itu anjing ada di kolong meja. Dia ju makan yang jato dari itu ana pung piring.&gt;&gt; [Deng maksud bilang, waktu ana-ana makan, anjing ju dapa makan. Biar Yesus bantu Dia pung orang, ma Dia musti lia orang laen ju.]<bt>But that mama responded saying, &lt;&lt;True, Papa! But that dog is underneath the table. S/he also eats what falls from that child's plate.&gt;&gt; [With meaning that, when children eat, dog/s also eat. Even though Yesus helps His (own) people, nevertheless He must also look after other people too.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Dengar bagitu, Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Mama su omong batúl! Jadi mama pulang suda, te itu setan su kaluar dari mama pung ana.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing like that, Yesus told saying, &lt;&lt;Awii [+impressed!] Mama has spoken very true/correctly! So (consequently) mama go on home [light imperative], cuz (elaboration) that *evil spirit has already come out of mama's child.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ais, itu mama pulang. Sampe di ruma, dia pung ana ada tidor sonu. Itu setan memang su kaluar.<bt>Then that mama went home. Arriving at the house, her child was sleeping soundly. That *evil spirit had really already come out.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae satu orang bisu deng tuli<bt>Lord Yesus heals a person dumb and deaf</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais itu, ju Yesus dong kasi tenga itu kota Tirus, iko jalan pante lewat kota Sidon. Dari situ, dong jalan tarús sampe di dano Galilea. Ais dong jalan pi satu da'era deng sapulu kota yang dong biasa subu bilang, &lt;Dekapolis&gt;.<bt>After that, Yesus left that city Tirus, following the road along the coast going by Sidon city. From there, they continued walking to Galilea lake. Then they went to a region with ten cities which they usually refer to as &lt;Dekapolis&gt;.</bt><v n="32" />Di situ ada satu orang yang bisu deng tuli. Dia pung kawan dong bawa sang dia pi Yesus. Dong minta ko Yesus taro tangan di itu orang, ko bekin bae sang dia.<bt>There, there was a person who was dumb and deaf. His friends brought him to Yesus. They asked Yesus to put hands on that person to heal him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bisu ; tuli"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">bisu ; tuli</Message></Annotation><v n="33" />Ju Yesus kasi tenga itu orang banya ko pi sandiri deng itu orang. Yesus kasi maso jari pi dalam itu orang pung talinga dua-dua. Ais ju Dia taro luda di jari, ju raba itu orang pung lida.<bt>Then Yesus left those many people to go alone with that person. Yesus put his finger/s in both of that person's ears. Then He put spittle on finger, then touched that person's tongue.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="raba = touch, sentuh"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">raba = touch, sentuh</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Yesus mangada pi langit, hela napas panjang, ais parenta pake dong pung bahasa bilang, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Efata!&gt;&gt;</span> (Dia pung arti bilang, &lt;&lt;Tabuka suda!&gt;&gt;)<bt>Yesus faced up to the sky, drew a long breath, then commanded using their language saying, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Efata!&gt;&gt;</span> (Its meaning says &lt;&lt;Open (imperative)!&gt;&gt;)</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangada ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">mangada =</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Dia bilang bagitu sa, ju itu orang pung talinga dapa dengar memang. Itu orang pung lida yang kaku tu, noe memang, sampe dia mulai ba'omong ena-ena.<bt>He spoke like that, then that person's ears could really hear. That person's tongue that was akward/stiff, became really soft/pliable, to the point that he started talking in a satifying/pleasing manner.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="noe = lembut ; one UNS"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">noe = lembut ; one UNS says lombo pairs w/kaku and noe pairs w/karas ; another says neither collocate with tongue, but linca does. noe-na'u =</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ais ju dong dua kambali pi orang banya. Yesus larang sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar, ó! Bosong jang kasi tau orang bilang, Beta su bekin bae ini orang.&gt;&gt; Biar Yesus larang karás, ma dong bacarita rame di mana-mana.<bt>Then they two returned to the many people. Yesus forbade them saying, &lt;&lt;Listen, ó! You-pl don't tell people that I have healed this person.&gt;&gt; Even though Yesus strictly forbade, nevertheless they enthusiastically told the story all over the place.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hebo"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">hebo</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Orang yang dengar itu carita, dong heran mau mati. Ju dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Talalu hebat! Ini Orang bekin samua jadi bae. Orang tuli dapa dengar. Orang bisu bisa ba'omong.&gt;&gt;<bt>People who heard that story, they were amazed to extreme degree. And they talked among themselves/with each other saying, &lt;&lt;It's excredibly extraordinary/amazing! This Person makes everything become well/good. Deaf people can hear. Dumb people can talk.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi makan ampa ribu orang<bt>Lord Yesus feeds four thousand people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 15:32-39)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="8" />
      <v n="1-3" />Satu kali, ju ada orang banya datang bakumpul ko dengar sang Yesus. Dong su iko sang Dia sampe tiga hari, andia ko dong su sonde ada makanan lai. Ju Yesus pange ame Dia pung ana bua dong, ko bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta su rasa kasian sang ini orang banya dong. Ada yang su datang dari jao, baru dong bakumpul su tiga hari, sampe su sonde ada makanan lai ni. Lebe bae dong jang pulang deng parú kosong dolo. Jang sampe dong samaput di tenga jalan.&gt;&gt;<bt>One time, then many people came gathering to hear Yesus. They had already been following him for three days, so that is why they had no more food. So Yesus called His *disciples/underlings to say, &lt;&lt;I feel love/pity toward these many people. There are those who came from far, furthermore they have already gathered for three days, to the point that there is no food anymore. It's better if they don't go home with empty stomachs. Don't let it get to the point that they faint/collapse in the middle of the road/journey.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: reordered for chronology and RL background-foreground.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tenga2 ; mangkali; makanan = dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">tenga2 ; mangkali; makanan = dong pung bakal; samaput = faint</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Yesus pung ana bua dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa. Ini tampa su jao dari kampong. Jadi sonde mungkin kotong bisa kasi makan orang bagini banya!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus' *disciples replied saying, &lt;&lt;Papa. This place is far from a village. So (consequently) it's impossible for us-inc to be able to feed as many people as this!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma Yesus tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pung roti, ada barapa banya?&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus asked them saying, &lt;&lt;Your-pl bread, how much is there?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa. Botong ada simpan roti cuma tuju bua sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>They replied saying, &lt;&lt;Papa. We-exc have stored/saved/kept just seven fruits (counter) of bread.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais Yesus suru itu orang dong samua ko dudu di tana. Ju Dia ame itu roti tuju bua, ko minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Ais Dia bekin pica-pica itu roti deng Dia pung tangan ko kasi pi Dia pung ana bua dong. Ju dong pi babagi kasi itu orang dong samua.<bt>Then Yesus ordered all those people to sit on the earth/ground. Then he took those seven fruit of bread, and gave thanks to God. Then he broke (into small pieces) that bread with His hands to give it to his *disciples. Then they went dividing it up giving it to all the people. [EXEG: feed 5,000 = sit on grass; feed 4,000 = sit on ground.]</bt><v n="7" />Dong ju dapa ikan barapa ekor. Ais Yesus minta tarima kasi lai sang Tuhan Allah buat itu ikan dong. Tarús Dia suru Dia pung ana bua dong ko pi babagi ame kasi itu orang dong lai.<bt>They also had a few tails (counter) of fish. Then Yesus gave thanks again to God for that fish. Then2 He ordered His *disciples to go divide give again to those people.</bt><v n="8-9" />Dong samua kira-kira ada ampa ribu orang. Dong makan sampe kinyang. Makan abis, ju ana bua dong pi kumpul makanan yang tasisa dong, ponu tuju bakul. Ais itu, Yesus suru dong samua pulang.<bt>They all were approximately 4000 people. They ate until they were full. After finishing eating, then the disciples went collecting the leftover food, full 7 baskets. After that, Yesus ordered them all to go home. [DISCOURSE: reordered so the background info highlights the significance of them all being full.] [EXEG: Gk in Mrk uses different words for ‘12 baskets’ with feeding 5,000 vs. ‘7 baskets2’ with feeding 4,000. Both should be common baskets with a tight enough weave that smallish pieces of bread aren't going to fall through. And they need to be a size that can be picked up (i.e. not the giant rice storage baskets). Use terms for two different kinds of baskets in these two stories if your lg can do that naturally. But don't force it or overtranslate. Some scholars think the 7 baskets with feeding the 4,000 is a slightly larger size.]</bt><v n="10" />Waktu dong pulang, ju Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong nae pi dalam parahu, ko pi satu tampa, nama Dalmanuta.<bt>When they had gone home, then Yesus and his *disciples got into the boat to go to a place named Dalmanuta.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Farisi mau kasi jato Tuhan Yesus<bt>Farisi people want to bring down the Lord Yesus (socially, morally, politially)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 16:1-4)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Waktu Yesus dong sampe di Dalmanuta, ju ada barapa orang dari partei agama Farisi datang katumu sang Dia. Dong baso'al-jawab deng Dia ko mau hiki sang Dia. Dong minta sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa! Kasi tunju tanda heran ko jadi bukti bilang, Bapa memang dapa kuasa dari Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus (collective) arrived at Dalmanuta, then there were several people from the Farisi religious group/party came to meet Him. They debated (lit: problem-answer) with Him in order to (purpose) trap Him. They requested of Him saying, &lt;&lt;Papa! Show *miracles as evidence that You really have gotten your *power/authority from God.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk ‘trying to test (character/abilities), LN. Needs to be clear these religious leaders are scheming, not coming with good will. Readers need to know who the bad guys arein this story.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hiki = jerat, entrap ensare"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">hiki = jerat, entrap ensare</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:38, Lukas 11:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Yesus hela napas panjang bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo Beta dengar bosong omong bagitu, Beta manyasal! Akurang ko bosong minta tanda heran? Jang bagitu! Tanda heran memang ada, ma Beta sonde bekin kasi bosong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus drew a long breath saying, &lt;&lt;If/when I hear you-pl talk like that, I feel regret! Why are you requesting *miracles? Don't do like that! There really are *miracles, but I won't make/do them for you.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="8:12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:39, Lukas 11:29</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais ju Yesus jalan kasi tenga sang dong ko pi nae kambali dalam parahu deng Dia pung ana bua dong. Ju dong barangkat pi dano pung sablá.<bt>After that, Yesus went leaving them to go get back in the boat with his *disciples. Then they left to go the lake's other side.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ajar bilang, ati-ati deng orang Farisi dong pung pangaru<bt>Lord Yesus teaches saying watch out for/be careful of the Farisi people's influence</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 16:5-12)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Waktu Yesus dong sampe di tenga dano, baru ana bua dong inga yang dong lupa bawa bakál. Dong cuma bawa roti satu bua sa.<bt>When Yesus (collective) arrived in the middle of the lake, only then the *disciples/underlings remembered that they forgot to bring trip food. They had only brought one fruit (counter) of bread.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="use of yang here??"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">use of yang here??</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Dengar dong omong roti, Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong musti ati-ati! Jang bosong takaná raja Herodes deng orang Farisi dong pung pangaru jahat. Dong pung pangaru sama ke bibit roti yang orang campor ko bekin reis roti.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing them talk about bread, Yesus said, &lt;&lt;You-pl must be careful! Don't you be affected/hit by king Herodes and the Farisi people's bad/evil influence. Their influence is like *yeast (bread seed) which people mix in to make bread rise.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mur1 = dregs of laru, ampas;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">mur1 = dregs of laru, ampas; mur2 = nut (from bolt); PROBLEM: omong roti deng mur, the UNS can think of bread and drink, not bread and the stuff that makes it rise. bibit roti = yeast, ragi, mur</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 12:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Dengar Dia omong bagitu, ju Dia pung ana bua dong bingung. Ju dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapatua omong apa tu? Mangkali Dia omong bagitu, tagal botong sonde bawa roti, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Him talk like that, then His *disciples were confused. Then they talked to each other saying, &lt;&lt;What is that Old Man [term of respect] saying? Probably/perhaps He is talking like that, because (reason) we-exc [+obviously] forgot to bring bread.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ma Yesus tau dong pung pikiran. Jadi Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko bosong cuma omong roti sa! Bosong sonde tangkap Beta pung maksud, ko? Bosong pung otak memang tumpul talalu!<bt>But Yesus knew their thinking. So (consequently) he spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Why are you-pl only just talking about bread! You don't catch My meaning, do you, ko [+tag]? Your brains are really exceedingly dull/not sharp!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tumpul = dull, dense ; masparak"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">tumpul = dull, dense ; masparak</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Bosong su lia deng bosong pung mata biji sandiri, ma sonde tau dia pung arti! Sama ke sonde lia sa! Bosong dengar deng talinga sandiri, ma sonde mangarti apa-apa. Sama ke bosong sonde bisa dengar! Bosong su lupa<bt>You have seen with your very own eyes, but you don't know its meaning! That is the same as if you never saw! You hear with your very own ears, but you don't understand anything. That is the same as if you don't know how to hear/listen! You have forgotten</bt><note reference="8:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yeremia 5:21, Yeskial 12:2, Markus 4:12</note><v n="19" />itu roti lima bua yang Beta bekin pica-pica ko kasi makan itu lima ribu orang dong, ko? Tempo hari bosong kumpul ame itu roti pung sisa barapa bakul?&gt;&gt;<bt>those 5 fruits (counter) of bread that I broke (into small pieces) to feed those 5000 people, ko [+tag]? That previous day you gathered that bread's leftovers how many baskets?&gt;&gt; [EXEG: compare with 6:34 and 8:8-9 to use the same words for the two kinds of baskets.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sapai =like bakul, karanjang has loose"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">sapai =like bakul, karanjang has loose weave, sapaik has close weave; all three, size is ambiguous, but canNOT very small</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Dua blas bakul, Papa.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered saying, &lt;&lt;12 baskets, Papa.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Yesus tanya lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong masi inga tempo hari Beta bekin pica-pica itu roti tuju bua ko kasi makan itu ampa ribu orang, ko? Bosong kumpul ame sisa dong barapa bakul?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus asked again saying, &lt;&lt;You still remember that time I broke those 7 loaves of bread to feed those 4000 people, ko [+tag]? You gathered leftovers how many baskets?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***added 7 loaves"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">***added 7 loaves</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Tuju, Papa!&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered saying, &lt;&lt;7, Papa!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ju Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang batúl! Bosong su lia deng mata kapala sandiri, ma akurang ko bosong masi balóm mangarti Beta pung kuasa datang dari mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus said, &lt;&lt;That's correct! You have already seen with the eyes on your very own heads, but why do you still not yet understand where my *power/authority comes from?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae orang buta di Betsaida<bt>Lord Yesus *heals a blind person at Betsaida</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ais itu, Yesus dong sampe di kampong Betsaida. Di situ orang dong antar bawa satu orang buta pi sang Dia. Dong minta Yesus sonto bekin bae itu orang buta.<bt>After that, Yesus (collective) arrived at Betsaida village. There people brought a blind person to Him. They requested Yesus touch heal that blind person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonto = touch (generic)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">sonto = touch (generic)</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Ais Yesus pegang ame itu orang pung tangan ko bawa sang dia pi luar kampong. Ju Dia sumbur luda pi itu orang pung mata, ais Dia raba itu mata. Dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana? Lu su bisa dapa lia, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus took/held that person's hand to take him outside the village. Then He spit spittle into that person's eyes, then He touched those eyes. He asked saying, &lt;&lt;How is it? You can see now, ko [+tag]?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sumbur = blow out wad (of"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">sumbur = blow out wad (of spit)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Itu orang angka muka ko lia kiri-kanan, ais dia manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoo! Beta lia orang bajalan. Ma tingka ke lia pohon yang bajalan!&gt;&gt;<bt>That person lifted his face to look left-right, then he answered saying, &lt;&lt;Hoo [+affirm]! I see people walking, but it's like I see trees that are walking!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tingka ke = sama ke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">tingka ke = sama ke</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Ais Yesus taro lai Dia pung tangan pi itu orang pung mata. Ju itu orang coba lia ulang, tau-tau te dia pung mata su bae batúl. Sakarang dia su dapa lia deng taráng.<bt>Then Yesus again put His hand on that person's eyes. Then that person tried/strained to look again, know-know [idiom: contrary to expectation], his eyes were truly good/healed. Now he could see clearly. [EXEG: Gk word here is ‘look intently, look deliberately, strain to look’. It is not the common word for look/see. Try to reflect that in your translation. LN, NRSV, TRT, TH. TN.]</bt><v n="26" />Ju Yesus suru itu orang pulang, ais kasi inga sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu pulang suda, ma iko jalan laen! Jang bale lai pi Betsaida.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus ordered that person to go home, then he reminded him saying, &lt;&lt;You-sg go home (+imperative), but follow/go by a different path/road! Don't return again to Betsaida.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk ‘the village’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ais ~ as"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">ais ~ as</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus kasi tau bilang, Yesus tu, Kristus, andia Orang yang Tuhan Allah su tunju memang dari dolu<bt>Petrus declares that Yesus is Kristus, that is, the Person whom God had already designated from long ago</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 16:13-20; Lukas 9:18-21)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ais itu ju, Yesus dong jalan kuliling kampong-kampong di Kaisarea Filipi. Di tenga jalan Yesus tanya sang Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo iko orang dong pung carita, dong bilang Beta ni, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>And after that, Yesus (collective) traveled all around various villages of Kaisaria Filipi. In the middle of the road/journey Yesus asked His *disciples/underlings saying, &lt;&lt;If you follow people's story, they say that I here, am who?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada yang bilang &lt;Yohanis tukang sarani&gt;. Ada yang bilang &lt;ba'i Elia&gt;, Tuhan pung jubir dolu tu. Ada laen bilang Papa ni, satu dari Tuhan Allah pung jubir dolu-dolu yang laen dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>They responded saying, &lt;&lt;There are those who say &lt;Yohanis the habitual Baptizer&gt;. There are those who say &lt;forefather Elia&gt;, God2's spokesperson from long ago. There are others who say Papa here is one of God's other *prophets1 (spokesperson) from long-long ago.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="8:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Markus 6:14-15, Lukas 9:7-8</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ju Yesus tanya lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Ma, bosong sandiri bilang Beta ni, sapa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus asked again saying, &lt;&lt;But you-pl yourself say that I here, am who?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Petrus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa ni, Kristus! Yang Tuhan Allah su tunju memang dari dolu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Petrus responded saying, &lt;&lt;Papa here, is Kristus! The one God has designated from before.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Christ is not a name, but a rank/title. Explicated following suggestions in TBT article on where to explicate meaning of ‘Christ’.]</bt><note reference="8:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 6:68-69</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ma Yesus larang sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong jang kasi tau sapa-sapa, é!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus forbade them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl don't tell anyone, é!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau memang Dia pung sangsara deng Dia pung mati<bt>Lord Yesus tells/reveals beforehand His suffering and His death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 16:21-28; Lukas 9:22-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais itu, Yesus mulai kasi tau Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Nanti Beta dapa sangsara bam-banya, tagal tua-tua adat, kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos, deng guru agama dong samua tola buang sang Beta. Nanti dong bunu bekin mati sang Beta, ma pas deng dia pung lusa,<bt>After that, Yesus began to tell His *disciples/underlings saying, &lt;&lt;I here, am the *Ideal/Prototype Human. Later I will get/experience much suffering, because the *traditional elders, the *chief priests (bosses of Yahudi priests), and the *religious teachers all will push away/reject Me. Later they will kill Me dead, but exactly on the day after next,</bt><note reference="8:31" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dalam bahasa Yunani, dong mulai itong dari: ini hari (= 1), beso (= 2), lusa (= 3), tula (= 4). Jadi dalam bahasa Yunani, μετὰ τρεῖς ἡμέρας <span class="Italic">(meta treis hēmeras)</span> &lt;&lt;di hari yang katiga&gt;&gt; pung maksud dalam bahasa Kupang, andia &lt;&lt;dia pung lusa&gt;&gt;. Inga te, Tuhan Yesus mati hari jum'at (itong satu). Dia pung beso, andia hari sabtu (itong dua), Tuhan Yesus ada dalam kubur. Dia pung lusa, andia hari minggu (itong tiga), Tuhan Yesus idop kambali. Jadi iko kotong pung cara itong hari, na, Dia mati dua malam, ais Dia idop kambali.<bt>In the Yunani/Greek language, they begin counting from today (= 1), tomorrow (= 2), day after tomorrow (=3), day three (= 4). So (consequently), in the Yunani language, μετὰ τρεῖς ἡμέρας <span class="Italic">(meta treis hēmeras)</span> “on the third day” means in the Kupang language, “the day after (tomorrow, next)”. Remember that, the Lord Yesus died on Friday (count one). Tomorrow/the next day, that is Saturday (count two), the Lord Yesus was in the grave. The day after (tomorrow/next), that is Sunday (count three), the Lord Jesus lived again/came back to life. So (consequently) according to the way that we-inc count days, na, He was dead for two nights, and then He came back to life.</bt></note>Beta idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>I will live again/come back to life. [KT: see end of this section for expanded note on *Son of Man.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="te here = ? ; tola"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">te here = ? ; tola buang = sonde tarima; on Wed, dia pung tiga hari = Fri</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="apodokimastheenai: be evaluated and found inadequate"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">apodokimastheenai: be evaluated and found inadequate and rejected</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Yesus kasi tau tarús taráng bagitu, ju Petrus hela ame sang Dia pi pinggir ko togor bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa jang omong bagitu! Beta sonde kasi tenga dong nae tangan sang Papa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus revealed/told forthrightly/clearly like that, then Petrus pulled Him to the side to scold saying, &lt;&lt;Papa don't/shouldn't talk like that! I won't allow them to raise their hand (idiom: do violence) against Papa.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="togor = rebuke; raba tangan ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">togor = rebuke; raba tangan = touch; nae tangan sang = raise hand against</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ma Petrus omong bagitu, bukan iko Tuhan pung mau. Ju Yesus bale ko lia Dia pung ana bua laen dong. Ais Dia togor sang Petrus deng karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Itu setan dong pung bos pung omong! Iskarobis dari sini! Lu cuma pikir manusia pung mau sa, bukan Tuhan pung mau!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petrus' talk like that, wasn't according to God2's will. Then Yesus turned to look at his other *disciples. Then he harshly scolded Petrus saying, &lt;&lt;Hee [+rebuke]! That's *Satan's (boss of the evil spirits) speaking! Get out of here! You-sg only just think (according to) human's will, not God2's will.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk here is ‘turn around, turn body’, not ‘turn and look over shoulder’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="iskarobis = heka; Yesus bale balakang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">iskarobis = heka; Yesus bale balakang sang dia, ko lia Diang ana murid dong; penggoda?; suggestion to use Lusifer.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Satanaa: Devil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">Satanaa: Devil</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ais ju Yesus pange orang laen dong ko datang bakumpul deng Dia pung ana bua dong. Ais Dia ajar sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sapa yang mau iko sang Beta, dia musti batahan iko tarús tiap hari! Dia musti lupa buang dia pung mau-mau sandiri, ko iko Tuhan pung mau sa. Biar orang mau bunu sang dia, dia musti iko tarús sa, sama ke orang pikol dia pung kayu palang ko pi mati.<bt>And then Yesus called/summoned other people to come gather with His *disciples. Then He taught them saying, &lt;&lt;Whoever wants to follow Me, he must endure following continually every single day! He must completely forget his own will/desires, to just follow God2's will. Even if someone wants to kill him/her, s/he must just keep following, just like someone shoulder carries his/her *cross (crossed wood) to go die/on their way to die. [NOTE: this took several versions and the help of several consultants before this difficult verse worked consistently.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Biar mati ju bae! Sama ke"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Biar mati ju bae! Sama ke pikol kasyu palang sampe mati ju bae.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tendes = press down; dia musti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">tendes = press down; dia musti lupa buang dia pung diri puing parlu-parlu dong,??</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:38, Lukas 9:23, 14:27</note><v n="35" />Te orang yang cuma mau idop buat dia pung diri sandiri sa, nanti dia pung idop tu, ilang bagitu sa! Ma orang yang sadia mati tagal dia iko sang Beta deng kasi tau Tuhan pung jalan idop, nanti dia dapa idop tarús deng Tuhan.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) a/the person who only wants to live just for his own self, later that life of his/her will disappear just like that! But the person who is ready to die because he follows Me and tell God2's life path/way, later s/he will be able to live continually with the God2. [EXEG: the connectors are of critical importance here. Gk ‘lose their life for my sake’= lose their life because they follow/belong to me.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ilang buang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">ilang buang</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="TERMS: Mt 16:21-28, Lk 9:22-27"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">TERMS: Mt 16:21-28, Lk 9:22-27</Message></Annotation><note reference="8:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:39, Lukas 17:33, Yohanis 12:25</note><v n="36" />Dengar, é! Kalo lu dapa dunya pung isi samua, ma Tuhan Allah tola buang sang lu, lu ontong apa?<bt>Listen, é! If you-sg get the world's entire contents, but God throws you away/rejects you, what have you gained?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="psykhees: this is not eternal life,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">psykhees: this is not eternal life, the life characteristic of the age to come; it's life as a person has it right now</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />Biar lu pikol bawa dunya pung isi samua ju, lu sonde bisa tukar deng lu pung jiwa!<bt>Even if you also shoulder carry away the world's entire contents, you can't exchange/replace it with your *soul!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="antallagma tees psykhees autou: something you"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">antallagma tees psykhees autou: something you pay to get back something in exchange (for your life): there is nothing that would compensate you for such a loss.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Inga, é! Orang di ini dunya sakarang pung jahat macam-macam. Dong sonde toe iko sang Tuhan. Jadi sapa yang malu iko sang Beta, ko malu pegang Beta pung ajaran, Beta ju nanti malu mangaku sang dia di Tuhan Allah pung muka. Te Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, nanti Beta datang kambali dari sorga. Deng Tuhan pung ana bua dari sorga dong, iko sama-sama deng Beta ju. Botong turun dari sorga deng Bapa pung kuasa yang hebat, baru orang tau Beta ni, sapa.<bt>Remember, é! People in this world now have/do all sorts of evil. They don't care about following the Lord. So (consequently), whoever is embarrassed to follow Me, or embarrassed to hold My teachings, I also will be embarrassed/shy to acknowledge/confess him at God's face/in front of God. Cuz (elaboration) I, *Ideal/Prototype Human here, I will come back from *heaven2. And God2's *angels (workers/underlings from heaven) also will follow together/accompany with Me. We-exc will come down from heaven with Father's extraordinary power, only then will people know who I here am. [EXEG: Gk is *glory here.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="9" />
      <v n="1" />Bosong jang lupa Beta pung omong ni. Ada yang dari bosong samua ni, yang balóm mati, ma nanti dapa lia Tuhan Allah ada pegang parenta deng kuasa bésar.&gt;&gt;<bt>You-pl don't/shouldn't forget this talk of Mine/what I say here. There are those from among you all here, who have not yet died, but later will be able to see God's *governing/rule with great power/authority.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk ‘taste’ = experience] [KEY TERM (8:31): Manusia Tulen (*Son of Man; Authentic/Ideal/Prototypical Human). Daniel 7; Markus 2:9-10, 28; 8:31, 38; 9:9, 12, 31; 10:33, 45; 13:23, 26; 14:21, 41, 62; etc. Before Christ was born into this world, God had already shown beforehand to one of His spokesman/prophets, named Daniel, many things that would happen later. Daniel saw (a vision) as if in a dream, there was a Person who descended from the clouds with amazing power/ authority. God gave that Person the right and power/authority to govern all countries and all races/ethnic groups on earth. His rule would never end. But Daniel did not know who this Person was. So he wrote saying, even though He descended from heaven, nevertheless He was like a “child of humans/ity” or an “authentic/ideal/prototypical human”. He meant that this Person was truly human, not a deity. In the books of the New Testament, the Lord Jesus likes to refer to himself with the title/rank of “Authentic/Ideal/Prototypical Human”. In that way He reveals/acknowledges that He is that Person whom Daniel had written about beforehand from long ago. The Lord Jesus says Manusia Tulen has the power/authority to heal the sick, He has the right and power/authority to wipe away/forgive people's wrongs, He has the power/authority to make dead people live again, and that later the leaders of the Jewish people would catch/arrest Him, beat Him, kill Him dead, and then, the day after next, He would come back to life from His death. NOTE: The Greek language Bible writes saying, ὁ υἱὸς τοῦ ἀνθρώπου (ho huios tou anthropou), which translates literally as “child of humans/ity (male)”. But what does it mean? The Jewish people liked to show respect for God, so that is why they would not mention His name. Even today they more often use indirect words. For example: kingdom of heaven (rather than kingdom of God), The Most High (that is, God), etc. So (consequently), they did not like to say “Son of God”, so one way around this was to say “Son of Man”. We have already seen above that this Person had various sorts of power/authority, the same as God's power/authority. But we must also look at the grammar of the Greek. There are two patterns: 1) “child of [a person's name]”. For example: child of Alpheus, children of Zebedeus, etc. But the second pattern is different. That is: 2) “child of [not a person's name]”. In this second pattern there is no connection with “child” in the meaning, and there is no connection with people. Cuz (elaboration) this is their way to lift/focus on a characteristic/attribute (just like the Kupang language says “grandfather of lazy!” not talking about a person's grandfather, but talking about a person's characteristic/ attribute/quality). For example: “You-pl are children of vipers”. That means “your-pl character is like the characteristics we associate with vipers”, that is “you are very clever and deceptive.” “Children of thunder” (naa, [+shift to background explanation] Thunder here is not a person's name, but the sound associated with lightning). [NOTE to CR: This elaboration was necessary because ‘Thunder/Guntur’ is a person's name in Indonesia, and many readers of the Indo Bible assume that is the pattern here—because it is literal-CEG.] It's meaning is, Zebedeus' two children have the character quality “like the characteristic commonly associated with thunder”, so some experts think perhaps “they had loud/booming voices” or, “they often blurted out angrily” There are many examples of this type/pattern. Naa [+shift], let's return to “child of humans/ity”. This is not the name of a person, so it does not follow the first pattern, but it follows the second pattern, that is talking about a characteristic, not about a person's child. For the Jewish people, “human” is paired with/evokes the counterpart “God”. But in our-inc region it is different. Cuz (elaboration) “human” is paired with/evokes the counterpart “animal”. So (consequently), if someone is cursing us saying, we are like some animal [NOTE: usually pigs or dogs-CEG], we-inc protest back saying, “I here am also (a child of) humans, just like you-sg!” Whereas in fact, from the second pattern earlier, the element of “child of” is not important. That is why the Kupang language Bible uses “Authentic/Ideal/Prototype Human”, cuz (elaboration) its meaning is the same as the meaning of the Greek, ὁ υἱὸς τοῦ ἀνθρώπου (ho huios tou anthropou).]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus jadi laen, deng Dia pung pakean mangkilat di atas gunung<bt>Lord Yesus' changes/becomes different, and His clothes shine/flash on a mountain</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 17:1-13; Lukas 9:28-36)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Abis anam hari ju, Yesus minta sang Petrus, Yakobis, deng Yohanis, ko dong sama-sama pi nae di atas satu gunung tinggi yang sonde ada orang. Waktu dong sampe di atas, dong lia Yesus su jadi laen.<bt>After six days, then Yesus requested Petrus, Yakobis and Yohanis, in order that they together go up a tall mountain that did not have people. When they got to the top, they saw Yesus' had become different.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deng dia = dengan dia; sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">deng dia = dengan dia; sang dia = kepada dia; bacaya = shine</Message></Annotation><v n="3" />Deng Dia pung pakean su jadi puti mangkilat. Di ini dunya sonde ada barang yang lebe puti dari Dia pung pakean tu.<bt>And His clothes had become shining/flashing/bright white. In this world there is no thing that is whiter that those clothes of His.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="binatu = penatu?? laundress, dry cleaner"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">binatu = penatu?? laundress, dry cleaner</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Takuju sa, ju dong dapa lia Yesus ada ba'omong deng ba'i Elia deng ba'i Musa.<bt>Suddenly/unexpectedly, they saw Yesus talking with Gf/Ff Elia and gf/ff Musa. [NOTE: can be used to indicate a figure of historical significance.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5-6" />Petrus dong taku mau mati. Ju Petrus su bingung sa, sampe dia omong sambarang. Ais dia kasi tau sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Botong enak di sini, é! Jadi lebe bae botong bekin tiga lopo. Satu kasi sang Papa, satu kasi ba'i Musa, deng satu lai kasi ba'i Elia.&gt;&gt;<bt>The Peter them (collective) were really frightened. And Petrus was just confused, to the point that he spoke randomly/pointlessly like that. So he told Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Papa! We-exc are feeling good here, é! So (consequently) it would be a good idea if we-exc made three open.huts. One for Papa, one for gf/ff Musa, and one more for gf/ff Elia.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: combined and reordered for chronology, cause-effect, and to avoid the confusion that CEV and NLT work themselves into. See TN discussion at 6b, and CONNOT, plus NIV parentheses.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="teng = orang pesta nikah canopy;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">teng = orang pesta nikah canopy; last sentence is backgrounded explanation; is ju or ais appropriate?? or s.t. else; omong kosong is intentional; omong sambarang is thoughtlessly</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-08-07 06:16:39Z" /></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Ais itu, ju awan turun datang ko tutu ame sang dong. Ju dong dengar suara kaluar dari itu awan bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar, ó! Yesus ni, Beta pung Ana sayang. Bosong dengar bae-bae sang Dia sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, a cloud come down to cover them up. Then they heard a voice come out of that cloud saying, &lt;&lt;Listen, ó! This Yesus, is My beloved Child. You-pl just listen carefully to Him!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="taru talinga = pasang talinga; awan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">taru talinga = pasang talinga; awan gumpal = taboa, group of clouds, satu kumpulan awan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis itu awan satu gumpal turun"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Abis itu awan satu gumpal turun datang ko tutu ame sang dong, ... Bosong taro talinga ko dengar sang Dia.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:2-7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">2 Petrus 1:17-18; Mateos 3:17, Markus 1:11, Lukas 3:22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Waktu Petrus dong dengar itu suara, dong lia kuliling, ma takuju dong sonde dapa lia orang laen lai. Cuma Yesus sandiri sa.<bt>When Petrus (coll) heard that voice, they looked all around, but unexpectedly they could not see the other people anymore. Only just Yesus himself.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bagitu Petrus dong dengar itu suara,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Bagitu Petrus dong dengar itu suara, ma Takuju sa</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais itu, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong jalan turun dari itu gunung. Ju Yesus pasán sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Apa yang bosong baru lia tadi tu, bosong jang kasi tau sapa-sapa. Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Beta musti mati dolo. Ais nanti kalo Beta su idop kambali, baru bosong bole kasi tau orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus and his *disciples started walking down that mountain. Then Yesus instructed them saying, &lt;&lt;What you saw just now, you-pl don't tell anyone at all. I here, am *Ideal/Prototype Human. I must die first. Then when I already live again, only then may you tell people.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Dong pegang bae-bae Yesus pung pasán tu, ju dong sonde kasi tau orang. Ma dong tiga mulai batanya sandiri bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia pung maksud apa bilang, Dia mau &lt;idop kambali dari Dia pung mati&gt; tu? Karmana, é?&gt;&gt;<bt>They held well that instruction of Yesus, and they didn't tell people. But they three began to ask each other themselves saying, &lt;&lt;What did He mean, saying that He will &lt;live again from His death&gt;? How's that?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ju dong tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Guru agama dong bilang, &lt;Ba'i Elia musti datang dolo, baru Kristus datang.&gt; Ma iko Papa, karmana?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they asked Him saying, &lt;&lt;Religion teachers say &lt;Forefather Elia must come first, only then Kristus comes.&gt; But according to Papa  (=you), how is it?&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="9:11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Maleaki 4:5, Mateos 11:14</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang batúl. Ba'i Elia musti datang dolo ko buka jalan kasi Kristus, itu Orang yang Tuhan Allah su tunju dari dolu. Ma karmana? Bosong balóm mangarti apa yang dong su tulis di Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi so'al itu Manusia Tulen, ko? Te dong su tulis memang bilang, nanti kalo Dia su datang, na, orang bekin susa sampe dong mau bunu mati sang Dia.<bt>Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;That's true! Forefather Elia must come first to open the path for Kristus, that Person that God has designated from long ago. But how is it? You-pl don't yet understand what they (impersonal) have written in God's book about that *Ideal/Prototype Human, do you? Cuz (elaboration) they have written that when He actually comes, na, people will cause difficulty to the point that they murder kill Him.</bt><v n="13" />Ma bosong musti pasang talinga bae-bae, ó! Itu ba'i Elia memang su datang. Ma orang bekin susa sang dia iko dong pung mau. Itu ju pas deng apa yang ba'i-ba'i dong su tulis memang dari dolu.&gt;&gt;<bt>But you must fasten your ears carefully. That forefather Elia has actually already come. But people made difficulty for him following their own will. And that also was exactly like what the (various) forefathers had written long ago.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae ana yang takaná setan<bt>Lord Yesus heals a child afflicted with a *evil spirit</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jahanam = jahat sakali"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">jahanam = jahat sakali</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 17:14-21; Lukas 9:37-43a)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Waktu Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua tiga orang tu, bakatumu kambali deng ana bua laen, dong dapa lia orang banya ada bakumpul. Itu orang banya dong ada datang ko lia Yesus pung ana bua laen bakanjar deng guru agama dong.<bt>When Yesus and those three *disciples of His met again with the other disciples, they could see many people gathered. Those many people had come to see Yesus' other disciples debate/argue with the religion teachers.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bakanjar = bertengkar, argue, debate, berdebat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">bakanjar = bertengkar, argue, debate, berdebat</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Waktu orang banya dong dapa lia sang Yesus, dong takuju, te dong kira Dia masi ada di atas gunung. Ais dong lari pi katumu deng Dia.<bt>When those many people saw Yesus, they were surprised, cuz (elaboration) they thought He was still up on the mountain. Then they ran to meet Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ju Yesus tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong ada bakanjar apa di sini?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then2 Yesus asked them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl are debating/arguing what here?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ada satu orang datang bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa, dengar dolo! Beta ada bawa beta pung ana laki-laki, ko Papa bekin bae sang dia. Dia bisu, sonde bisa ba'omong, te dia takaná setan.<bt>There was a person who came saying, &lt;&lt;Papa listen please! I have brought my boy child, so that Papa (=you) can heal him. He is dumb, can't talk, cuz (elaboration) he is afflicted by *evil spirit/s.</bt><v n="18" />Kalo itu setan su maso, na, dia banting-banting ini ana pung badan di tana. Ais, itu ana pung mulu babusa, deng dia makan gigi. Ais dia pung badan bakaku sama ke kayu. Beta su minta Papa pung ana bua dong, ko tolong usir itu setan. Ma dong sonde bisa apa-apa.&gt;&gt;<bt>If/when that evil spirit has entered, na, he keeps banging/throwing down this child's body on the ground. After that, the child's mouth foams, and he eats his teeth (=grinds molars). Then his body is stiff like wood. I have requested Your disciples to help/please expel that evil spirit. But they can't do anything.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mulu babusa = foaming at the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">mulu babusa = foaming at the mouth; kaku = stiff, tidak bisa bergerak seperti biasa; makan gigi = grind teeth</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Dengar bagitu, ju Yesus masparak sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Bosong ni, su talalu! Beta su ajar ulang-ulang sang bosong, ma bosong sonde mangarti bae-bae. Deng bosong sonde parcaya batúl-batúl sang Beta! Beta musti sabar sang bosong sampe kapan? Mari bawa itu ana datang di sini!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing that, then Yesus got angry at them saying, &lt;&lt;Heeh [+negative]! You-pl are just too much! [+exasperation] I have taught you over and over, but you don't understand well. And you don't truly believe in Me! I must be patient with you until when? [RQ] Come [+hort] bring (generic) that child here!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sampe kapan tempo ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">sampe kapan tempo =</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Ais dong koko bawa itu ana datang sang Yesus. Ma waktu itu setan dapa lia sang Yesus, ju dia banting itu ana sampe jato taguling-guling di tana, deng dia pung mulu babusa.<bt>Then they carry (LEX: as in carry a child) brought that child to Yesus. But when that evil spirit saw Yesus, then he threw down that child until he fell rolling around on the ground, and his mouth was foaming.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="koko hela stepis = kejang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">koko hela stepis = kejang</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bagitu itu setan dapa lia sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Bagitu itu setan dapa lia sang Tuhan Yesus ju dia bekin ame itu ana hela stepis sampe itu ana jato taguling di tana. Dia pung mulu babusa.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Ais ju Yesus tanya itu ana pung papa bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu pung ana jadi bagini ni, su dari kapan tempo?&gt;&gt;<bt>And then Yesus asked that child's father saying, &lt;&lt;Your-sg child has been like this here, for how long?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dia pung papa manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Su dari kici.<bt>His papa answered saying, &lt;&lt;Already since he was little.</bt><v n="22" />Itu setan su lama mau kasi mati sang ini ana. Dia kasi jato beta pung ana ulang-ulang pi dalam api, deng kasi tanggalám pi dalam aer. Jadi Papa tolong dolo! Kalo bisa, Papa kasian sang botong ko bekin bae ini ana dolo.&gt;&gt;<bt>That evil spirit for a long time has wanted to kill this child. He makes my child fall over and over into the fire, and makes him submerge/drown in water. So (consequently) You please help! If possible, You have pity on us and so heal this child.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko lu bilang &lt;kalo bisa&gt;? Beta memang bisa bekin samua, asal orang parcaya dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;Why do you-sg say &lt;if possible&gt;? I really/actually can do all, as.long as people believe first!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ais itu, bapatua manyao deng mau manangis sa bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Memang beta su parcaya. Ma tolong ko beta pung parcaya jadi lebe kuat lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, elderfather answered and just was about to cry saying, &lt;&lt;Papa! Indeed I believe. But help so that my believe is even stronger!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deng mau manangis sa = minta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">deng mau manangis sa = minta dengan sungguh-sungguh; maskakeduk = crying with short sobs, sobbing</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Itu waktu, Yesus lia banya orang su mulai datang makarubu di situ. Ais Dia parenta itu setan bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh, setan jahat! Lu kaluar suda dari ini ana, ko dia dapa dengar, deng dia dapa ba'omong. Lu jang maso ulang lai sang dia!&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, Yesus saw many people already come crowding around there. Then He commanded that evil spirit saying, &lt;&lt;Heeh, evil2 evil1 spirit! You-sg get out of this child (imperative), so that he can hear, and he can talk. You don't enter him again!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jahanam = jahat nakal, terkutuk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">jahanam = jahat nakal, terkutuk</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Dengar Yesus omong bagitu ju, itu setan batarea karás-karás. Dia bekin itu ana jato tahela-hela, baru kaluar kasi tenga sang dia. Ju itu ana faraku sama ke su mati sa. Sampe orang dong di situ ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa! Dia su mati!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing Yesus talk like that, then that evil spirit yelled loudly. He made that child fall yank-yank, only then exited leaving him. Then that child fainted just like he was already dead. To the point that people there talked saying, &lt;&lt;Naa! He's dead!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="faraku = samaput (KM-checks out by"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">faraku = samaput (KM-checks out by UNS's), collapse, faint, pingsan (not widely known); faruju = berkarat, rust</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ma Yesus pegang ame itu ana pung tangan ko tarek kasi bangun sang dia. Ju dia bangun memang.<bt>But Yesus held that child's hand to help get him up. Then that child actually got up.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ais Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong kasi tenga itu tampa, ko maso pi dalam satu ruma. Di situ dong sandiri tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Akurang ko tadi botong sonde bisa usir itu setan?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then2 Yesus and his disciples left that place to enter into a house. There they were alone and asked Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Papa! Why is it that earlier couldn't we-exc expel that evil spirit?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ais Yesus kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar bae-bae! Setan dong memang jahat. Jadi kalo bosong sonde sambayang minta tolong sang Tuhan, na, bosong sonde ontong usir setan macam bagitu dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus told saying, &lt;&lt;Listen carefully! Evil spirits are indeed evil. So (consequently) if you-pl don't pray requesting help from the Lord, na, you will not succeed expelling an evil spirit of that type.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sambayang = vt pray (thanks for"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">sambayang = vt pray (thanks for food, sick, exorcise)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau ulang lai Dia pung mati<bt>Lord Yesus tells once again His death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 17:22-23; Lukas 9:43b-45)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Ais itu, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong kasi tenga itu tampa, ko maso pi propinsi Galilea. Itu waktu, Yesus sonde mau ada orang yang tau Dia ada di situ,<bt>After that, Yesus and His disciples left that place, to enter Galilea province. That time, Yesus did not want people to know He was there,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="complement clause with no complementiser"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">complement clause with no complementiser</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />te Dia cuma mau ajar sang Dia pung ana bua sa. Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde lama lai, te dong mau jual sang Beta pi orang laen. Ais dong bunu bekin mati sang Beta, Manusia Tulen ni. Memang Beta mati, ma nanti dia pung lusa, Beta idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>cuz (elaboration) He wanted only to teach just His disciples. He told them saying, &lt;&lt;Not much longer (=soon), they (non-referential) want to *betray (sell) Me to other people/foreigners. Then they will kill Me, this *Ideal/Prototype Human. I'll actually die, but later on the day after next/tomorrow, I'll live again.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi pi = serahkan; jual ..."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">kasi pi = serahkan; jual ... pi = betray ; kombali ~ kambali</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:31" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dalam bahasa Yunani, dong mulai itong dari: ini hari (= 1), beso (= 2), lusa (= 3), tula (= 4). Jadi dalam bahasa Yunani, μετὰ τρεῖς ἡμέρας<span class="Italic"> (meta treis hēmeras)</span> &lt;di hari yang katiga&gt; pung maksud dalam bahasa Kupang, andia &lt;dia pung lusa&gt;. Inga te, Tuhan Yesus mati hari jum'at (itong satu). Dia pung beso, andia hari sabtu, Tuhan Yesus ada dalam kubur (itong dua). Dia pung lusa, andia hari minggu, Tuhan Yesus idop kambali (itong tiga). Jadi iko kotong pung cara itong hari, na, Dia mati dua malam, ais Dia idop kambali.<bt>In the Yunani language, they begin counting from today (= 1), tomorrow (= 2), day after tomorrow (=3), day three (= 4). So (consequently), in the Yunani language, μετὰ τρεῖς ἡμέρας <span class="Italic">(meta treis hēmeras)</span> &lt;on the third day&gt; means in the Kupang language, &lt;the day after (tomorrow, next)&gt;. Remember that, the Lord Yesus died on Friday (count one). Tomorrow/the next day, that is Saturday, the Lord Yesus was in the grave (count two). The day after (tomorrow/next), that is Sunday, the Lord Jesus lived again/came back to life (count three). So (consequently) according to the way that we-inc count days, na, He was dead for two nights, and then He came back to life.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Yesus kasi tau bagitu, ma Dia pung ana bua dong babingung. Dong sonde barani tanya lai Yesus pung maksud tu, apa.<bt>Yesus told like that, but His disciples were confused. They didn't dare ask again what Yesus' intention was.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung ana bua dong bakanjar bilang, sapa yang paling bésar<bt>Lord Yesus' disciples debate about who is biggest (most important)</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 18:1-5; Lukas 9:46-48)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ais itu, ju Yesus dong jalan sampe di Kapernaum. Waktu dong maso pi dalam ruma, ju Yesus tanya sang Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tadi bosong bakanjar apa di jalan tu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then after that, Yesus (collective) went/travelled until Kapernaum. When they entered into a house, then Yesus asked His *disciples saying, &lt;&lt;Earlier you-pl were debating what on that road?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Ma sonde ada yang barani manyao, te tadi di tenga jalan dong ada basambung mulu bilang, sapa yang paling bésar dari dong samua.<bt>But there was not anyone brave to reply, cuz (elaboration) in the middle of the road/trip they had been arguing (connecting mouths) about who was the biggest/greatest from them all.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="basambung mulu = bakanjar, bertengkar, berkelahi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">basambung mulu = bakanjar, bertengkar, berkelahi</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 22:24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ais Yesus dudu ko ajar sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Sapa yang mau jadi orang bésar, dia pung idop musti batúl-batúl jadi sama ke orang kici ko layani samua orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus sat to teach them saying, &lt;&lt;Whoever want to be a big/important person, his life must really-really become like that of a small/insignificant person to serve all people.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Sapa yang mau jadi orang nomer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">"Sapa yang mau jadi orang nomer satu, dia musti lebe dolo jadi orang yang paling kakorek, deng dia musti jadi pelayan ko melayani samua orang laen dong!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kakorek = paling belakang, nilai paling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">kakorek = paling belakang, nilai paling rendah; juara kakorek, sonde ada hak,</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:35" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 20:26-27, 23:11, Markus 10:43-44, Lukas 22:26</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Ais Yesus koko ame satu ana kici di situ, ko Dia kambali pi dong pung teng-tenga. Ju Dia omong bilang,<bt>Then Yesus cuddled a small child there, and.so He returned to their middle. Then He talked saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paloo ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">paloo =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis ju Tuhan Yesus hela ame"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Abis ju Tuhan Yesus hela ame ana kici satu ko kasi badiri sang dia di dong samua pung muka. Tuhan Yesus palo itu ana abis omong kasi Dia pung ana murid dong bilang,</Message></Annotation><v n="37" />&lt;&lt;Sapa yang iko Beta ko layani orang kici sama ke ini ana, dia pung arti, itu orang ju ada layani sang Beta. Deng dia ju ada layani sang Beta pung Papa yang utus sang Beta datang di ini dunya.&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;Whoever follows Me to serve small/insignificant people like this child, its meaning, that person also is serving Me. And he also is serving My Papa who commissioned Me to come to this world.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: /orang kici/ here is ‘person of low/insignificant status’. Try to avoid the general principle being restricted to people of young age.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="possible alternatives for welcome: tarima-ame/sayang/lia/melayani/sambut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">possible alternatives for welcome: tarima-ame/sayang/lia/melayani/sambut</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:37" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:40, Lukas 10:16, Yohanis 13:20</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Sapa yang jadi kotong pung orang?<bt>Who is our-inc person?</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 9:49-50)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Ais itu, Yesus pung ana bua Yohanis kalák bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Satu kali botong lia ada satu orang pake Papa pung nama ko usir setan. Ma botong larang sang dia, te dia bukan kotong pung orang na.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus' disciple Yohanes protested saying, &lt;&lt;Papa! One time we-e saw a person using Your name to expel spirit/s. But we-e forbade him, cuz (elaboration) he was [+obviously] not one of our-inc people.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalák = protes"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">kalák = protes</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis ju Yohanis lapor sang Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Abis ju Yohanis lapor sang Tuhan Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Kotong ada lia satu orang usir setan pake Bapa pung nama. Kotong larang sang dia ko jang bekin bagitu te dia bukan kotong pung partei.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Bosong jang larang sang dia. Te sapa yang pake Beta pung nama ko bekin tanda heran, dia sonde akan omong bekin busuk Beta pung nama.<bt>But Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;Hee! [+rebuke] You-pl don't/shouldn't forbid him. Cuz (elaboration) whoever uses My name to do *amazing signs (miracles), he is not going to speak making My name rotten (talk bad about/slander).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="omong bekin busuk ; omong bekin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">omong bekin busuk ; omong bekin malu; akan lebih yakin/pasti dari mau</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma Tuhan Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Ma Tuhan Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong jang larang sang dia, te sonde ada satu orang juga yang bisa bekin tanda ajaib pake Beta pung nama na artinya dia bekin jelek Beta pung nama.</Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Kalo dia sonde malawan sang kotong, artinya dia ju kotong pung orang.<bt>If he is not opposing us-inc, that means he is also our-inc person.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu orang toh sonde malawan sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Itu orang toh sonde malawan sang kotong, bukan? Artinya dia itu kotong pung partei.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:40" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 12:30, Lukas 11:23</note><v n="41" />Naa, inga bae-bae, ó! Kalo ada orang yang tau bilang, bosong iko sang Kristus, ais dia tolong sang bosong, tantu Tuhan Allah sonde lupa itu orang pung cape. Biar dia cuma kasi minum aer puti satu galás sa, ju Tuhan Allah sonde lupa sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [+shift to summary/conclusion], remember this well, ó! If there is person who knows that you-pl follow Kristus, then they help you, surely the Lord God is not going to forget that person's tiredness/effort. Even if he only just gives one glass of white (=drinking) water, the Lord God will not forget him.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cape lela = cape (lelah) but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">cape lela = cape (lelah) but forced phrase; galas = mok (galas implies material is glass, but mok is neutral to bahan)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Inga bae-bae! Orang yang sang kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Inga bae-bae! Orang yang sang kasi sang bosong minum karna bosong itu iko sang Juruslamat, itu orang pasti tarima ame dia pung capa lela pung upah.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:41" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:42</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Jang maen-maen deng dosa!<bt>Don't play around with sin2!</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 18:6-9; Lukas 17:1-2)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42" />Ais Yesus kasi tau lai sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo ada orang yang bekin satu ana kici iko jalan idop yang sala, sampe itu ana sonde parcaya lai sang Beta, awas, ó! Lebe bae kasi itu orang, kalo ame batu bésar satu,<bt>Then Yesus told again to them saying, &lt;&lt;If there is a person who makes a small child follow the wrong life way, to the point that that child doesn't believe anymore in Me, watch out, ó! It's better for that person if [GRAM: subjectless] take a big rock,</bt><note reference="9:42" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;batu giling&gt; yang dong pake ko mol padi-gandum.<bt>The Yunani language Bible writes saying &lt;stone for milling&gt; that they use to mill grain-wheat.</bt></note>ika di dia pung batang leher, ko kasi tanggalám di tenga laut.<bt>tie it to his neck post, in order to submerge/drown [him] in the middle of the sea.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Sapa yang bekin gara-gara kasi ini"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">"Sapa yang bekin gara-gara kasi ini ana-ana kici dong sampe dong sonde parcaya lai sang Beta, lebe bae ame batu bésar satu ko ika di dia pung leher, abis angka buang sang dia pi dalam laut.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bekin gara-gara = cari alasan untuk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">bekin gara-gara = cari alasan untuk mau ganggu; ko ika pi di itu orang pung leher; batu penggilingan = batu giling; mol vt = grind, hancur</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="This verse caused confusion to the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">This verse caused confusion to the UNS's!!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Kalo lu bekin sala pake lu pung tangan, potong buang itu tangan sa! Te lebe bae lu maso sorga biar bawa tangan sablá sa, ko biar dong jang buang sang lu pi api naraka deng lu pung tangan dua-dua.<bt>If you-sg do wrong using your hand, just cut off that hand! Cuz (elaboration) it's better that you enter heaven even if only bring just one(side) hand, rather than they throw you away into the fire of *hell with both your hands.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Lu orang jahat, na lu naraka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Lu orang jahat, na lu naraka pung orang. Lu beking sala, nanti lu maso naraka. Lebe bae A, daripada B (in Pos Kupang)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalo lu pung tangan satu bekin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">kalo lu pung tangan satu bekin sang lu bardosa, potong buang itu tangan! Te lebe bae lu idop deng Tuhan Allah deng tangan sablá, daripada lu lu maso pi dalam naraka deng lu pung tangan dua-dua.</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:43" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:30</note><v n="44" />[Naraka tu, memang tampa sangsara. Dia pung api sonde tau mati-mati. Deng ulat-ulat di situ dong ju sonde barenti bekin busuk.]<bt>[That hell, indeed is a place of suffering. Its fire doesn't know how to go out. And the worms there they also don't stop making [things] rotten.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sonde tau mati = permanence. beking"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">sonde tau mati = permanence. beking jijik = sonde suka, feeling of repulsion</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Naraka pung api itu sonde bisa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Naraka pung api itu sonde bisa mati, deng ulat yang maso di situ ju sonde bisa mati].</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:44" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani asli yang lebe tua, sonde tulis ini ayat 44.<bt>Original Greek language writings which are older don't write this verse 44.</bt></note><v n="45" />Kalo lu bekin sala pake lu pung kaki, potong buang itu kaki sa. Te lebe bae lu maso sorga bawa lu pung kaki sablá sa, ko biar dong jang buang sang lu pi api naraka deng lu pung kaki dua-dua.<bt>If you-sg do wrong using your foot, just cut off that foot. Cuz (elaboration) its better you enter heaven bringing your foot on just one side, than they throw you away in the fire of hell with both of your two feet.</bt><v n="46" />[Naraka tu, memang tampa sangsara. Dia pung api sonde tau mati-mati. Deng ulat-ulat di situ dong ju sonde barenti bekin busuk.]<bt>[That hell, indeed is a place of suffering. Its fire doesn't know how to go out. And the worms there they also don't stop making [things] rotten.]</bt><note reference="9:46" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani asli yang lebe tua, sonde tulis ini ayat 46.<bt>Original Greek language writings which are older don't write this verse 46.</bt></note><v n="47" />Kalo lu bekin sala pake lu pung mata, do'i buang lu pung mata sa! Te lebe bae lu maso pi sorga deng mata sablá sa, ko biar dong jang buang sang lu pi api naraka deng lu pung mata dua-dua.<bt>If you-sg do wrong using your eye, just gouge it out throw away that eye! Cuz (elaboration) its better that you enter heaven with an eye on one side, than they throw you away in the fire of hell with both of your eyes.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="do'i buang = cungkil; siwa, dig"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">do'i buang = cungkil; siwa, dig out</Message></Annotation><note reference="9:47" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:29</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="48" />&lt;Naraka tu, memang tampa sangsara.<bt>&lt;That hell, indeed is a place of suffering.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Dia pung api sonde tau mati-mati.<bt>Its fire clearly doesn't know how to go out.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng ulat-ulat di situ dong ju sonde barenti bekin busuk.&gt;<bt>And the worms there they also don't stop making [things] rotten.&gt;</bt><note reference="9:48" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 66:24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Beta pung ajaran ni, memang barát. Jadi sapa yang mau iko sang Beta, dia musti batahan iko tarús, sama ke daging yang orang taro garam ko se'i, ko biar itu daging batahan lama.<bt>This teaching of Mine is indeed heavy/difficult. So (consequently) whoever wants to follow Me, he must continually endure following, like meat which people place salt to smoke.meat with fire, so that that meat can endure/last a long time. [EXEG: Gk ‘everyone will be salted by fire.’ NOT and TN note 15 different interpetations for this verse. 1. ‘everyone’ here we take as ‘everyone who follows Christ’; 2. Gk ‘fire’ is bridging backwards; ‘salted’ bridges forwards, but ‘salt’ as a verb is not actually in focus in this verse. Fire is. See discussion in TRT and CONNOT. Could alternatively follow ‘test’ like NLT. Sets up conversation ahead in 10:35-45. Other than late textual additions I see ZERO contextual support for linking this verse with sacrifices. We follow ‘preserve’ and ‘live in love’, as in TN, CONNOT looking at higher context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="api sufu = ; awet ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">api sufu = ; awet = ; se'i = smoke (meat) se'i daging (vt) / daging se'i (adj); barat (west) vs. barát (heavy)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tiap orang pasti jalan lewat api"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Tiap orang pasti jalan lewat api sufu, sama ke dong bekin awet daging korban pake garam.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Garam tu, bae. Kotong pake ko bekin enak makanan. Ma kalo itu garam sonde asin lai, dia pung guna apa? Kotong buang sa. Bosong ju musti jadi sama ke garam, ko idop basayang deng samua orang.<bt>Salt is good. We-inc use it to make food taste good. But if salt isn't salty anymore, what is it good for? We-inc just throw it away. You-pl also must become like salt, to live reciprocally loving all people. [EXEG: CONNOT.]</bt><note reference="9:50" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:13, Lukas 14:34-35</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Naa! Bosong barenti bakanjar bilang, sapa bésar, sapa kici!&gt;&gt;<bt>So here's how it is! You-pl stop fighting about who's big/important, who's little/insignificant!&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: closure to higher level theme. M. Crofts.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Garam itu bae. Ma kalo garam"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Garam itu bae. Ma kalo garam pung asin ilang, mau bekin asin ulang karmana sang dia? Jadi, bosong samua musti jadi sama ke garam, - idop sama ke orang basudara yang basayang satu deng satu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang Farisi cari jalan ko hiki sang Tuhan Yesus deng so'al kawin-cere<bt>Farisi people look for way to trap Lord Yesus with the marry-divorce matter/problem</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 19:1-12; Lukas 16:18)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="10" />
      <v n="1" />Ais ju Yesus dong pi propinsi Yudea deng tampa-tampa laen di kali Yarden pung sablá matahari nae. Di mana-mana orang banya datang makarubu sang Dia. Ais Yesus ajar sang dong sama ke biasa.<bt>Then Yesus (collective) went to Yudea province and other places on the Yarden river's east side (sun rise side). Everywhere many people came crowding around Him. So Yesus taught them as usual.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="makarubu kuliling"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">makarubu kuliling</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ada barapa orang Farisi yang datang ko mau hiki kasi jato sang Dia. Dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Iko kotong pung atoran agama, kalo laki-laki su kawin, dia bole bacere, ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>There were several Farisi people who came wanting/intending to trap making Him fall (socially, morally). They asked saying, &lt;&lt;According to our-inc religious regulations, if a man has married, can he divorce, or not?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cere"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">cere</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="exestin: is it permitted"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">exestin: is it permitted</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ada barapa orang dari partei Farisi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Ada barapa orang dari partei Farisi yang iko datang, ma dong mau hiki sang Dia. Dong tanya, bilang, &lt;&lt;Iko kotong pung agama pung atoran, laki-laki yang su kaweng, ma bacere deng dia pung bini/maitua, bole ko sonde?&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Inga dolo! Atoran laki-bini yang ba'i Musa kasi sang kotong bilang, karmana?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;Think about it [+idiomatic]! Husband-wife regulations that forefather Musa gave to us say what?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ba'i Musa pung atoran bilang, orang bole bacere, asal kasi surat cere sang dia pung bini dolo.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered saying, &lt;&lt;Forefather Musa's regulation/s say, a person may divorce, as.long as (he) first gives a divorce letter to his wife.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Musa kasi isin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Dong manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Musa kasi isin ko orang bole cere deng dia pung bini.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:4" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 24:1-4, Mateos 5:31</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Yesus balas bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Dengar, é! Tagal bosong pung kapala batu, andia ko ba'i Musa tulis bagitu!<bt>Yesus responded/retorted saying, &lt;&lt;Hee [+problem, objection]! Listen, é! Because your-pl heads are stone (=stubborn), that is why forefather Musa wrote like that!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tagal ... andia ko. = karena"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">tagal ... andia ko. = karena a... therefore b</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tuhan Yesus tarangkan kasi sang dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Tuhan Yesus tarangkan kasi sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Musa tulis ame itu parenta sebab bosong pung hati karás sampe su sonde bisa ajar lai sang bosong.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Jang bosong lupa itu carita mula-mula waktu Tuhan bekin langit deng bumi! Ada tatulis bilang,<bt>Don't you-pl forget that story of the beginning when the Lord made heaven and earth! It is written that,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Tuhan Allah bekin manusia, laki-laki deng parampuan.<bt>&lt;God1 made humans, male and female.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma dari dolu kala waktu Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Ma dari dolu kala waktu Tuhan Allah bekin sang manusia, ada kasi tau, bilang, Dia bekin sang dong laki-laki deng parampuan.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:6" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 1:27, 5:2</note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">
      <v n="7" />Andia ko laki-laki kasi tenga dia pung mama deng papa,<bt>That is why a male leaves his mother and father,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">pi idop satu hati deng dia pung bini,<bt>go live one livered (Idiom=common purpose and looking out for each other) with his wife,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">
      <v n="8" />te dong dua su jadi satu.&gt;<bt>cuz (elaboration) they two have become one.&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Check against 1 Cor 6:16 and"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">Check against 1 Cor 6:16 and other parallels.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:7-8" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Mula-mula 2:24</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Kalo Tuhan Allah sandiri su bekin dong dua jadi satu, manusia jang kasi cere lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>If God himself has made them two become one, humans don't/shouldn't make separate/divorce again!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ais itu, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong sandiri maso pi dalam satu ruma. Di situ dong tanya Yesus pung ajaran tadi.<bt>After that, Yesus and His *disciples entered a house alone. There they asked (about) Yesus' teaching earlier.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais ju, Yesus dong kasi tenga"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Ais ju, Yesus dong kasi tenga itu orang banya dong, ju maso pi dalam satu ruma. Ju Dia pung ana murid dong tanya cari tau sang Dia kaná Dia pung ajaran itu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sapa yang cere buang dia pung bini, ais kawin lai, itu su barsina!<bt>Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;Whoever divorces throw away his wife, then marries again, that's already (classified as) adultery!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ho-hongge (Rote) = promiscuous ; bini"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">ho-hongge (Rote) = promiscuous ; bini buang (yg diceraikan)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju Yesus kasi tau, bilang, &lt;&lt;Sapa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Ju Yesus kasi tau, bilang, &lt;&lt;Sapa yang cere buang dia pung bini, abis kaweng lai deng parampuan laen, itu sama ke dia su maen parampuan, bekin sala kaná deng dia pung bini asli itu, Ju Yesus kasi tau, bilang, &lt;&lt;Sapa yang cere buang dia pung bini, abis kaweng lai deng parampuan laen, dia berzina terhadap dia pung bini pertama.<span class="Italic">(11)</span></Message></Annotation><v n="12" />Parampuan ju bagitu! Kalo dia su cere buang dia pung laki, ais kawin lai, itu ju barsina!&gt;&gt;<bt>Women are also like that! If she divorces throws away her husband, then marries again, that's also (classified as) adultery!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bagitu lai, kalo parampuan su cere"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Bagitu lai, kalo parampuan su cere buang sang dia pung laki, abis dia kaweng lai deng laki-laki laen, sama ke dia su barzina maen di luar, bekin sala kaná deng dia pung laki asli itu.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:11-12" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 5:32, 1 Korintus 7:10-11</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus omong kasi berkat sang ana-ana<bt>Lord Yesus speaks giving *blessing to the children</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 19:13-15; Lukas 18:15-17)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Satu waktu, ada orang bawa dong pung ana-ana pi sang Yesus, ko minta Dia taro tangan kasi berkat sang dong. Ma Yesus pung ana bua togor itu orang dong.<bt>One time, people brought their children to Yesus, to request that He place hands giving *blessing to them. But Yesus' *disciples scolded those people. [KT: Make sure your word for ‘blessing’ does not evoke only materials things, but can be oral—asking God to do good things to someone.] [DISCOURSE: See if you should go with direct speech here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="togor = scold, larang, forbid, prevent"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">togor = scold, larang, forbid, prevent</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Yesus dapa lia bagitu, ju Dia mara Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kasi tenga itu ana dong datang di Beta! Sonde usa larang! Te orang yang sama ke dong ni, yang Tuhan Allah pung orang.<bt>Yesus saw like that, and He got angry at His disciples saying, &lt;&lt;Allow those children come to Me! You don't need to/shouldn't forbid (them)! Cuz (elaboration) it is people like these here, who are God's people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi tenga = biar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">kasi tenga = biar</Message></Annotation><v n="15" />Bosong inga bae-bae! Sapa yang mau datang mangada sang Tuhan Allah, dong musti rindu sang Dia, sama ke ana-ana rindu dong pung mama deng papa. Kalo sonde bagitu, dong sonde pantas jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>You-pl must remember well! Whoever wants to come front up before (see, come face to face with) God, they must desire/yearn for Him like these children desire their mama and papa. [DISCOURSE: RL order] If not like that, they are not appropriate to become God's people.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangada = bertemu, menghadap Should it"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">mangada = bertemu, menghadap Should it be deng dong pung mama</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 18:3</note><v n="16" />Ais itu, Yesus paló ame itu ana dong, deng taro tangan di dong satu-satu, ko kasi berkat.<bt>After that, Yesus hugged/cuddled those children, and put his hands on their heads one by one, to give blessing. [NOTE: to daughter translations: make sure your word for “lay hands on” reflects the Gk by 1) actually touching the body, and 2) is not restricted to the head. Some church practices are skewed from the meaning of the Gk words.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi berkat = minta berkat, omong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">kasi berkat = minta berkat, omong kasi bae sang dong; bantal palo = Dutch wife</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang kaya cari jalan ko idop tarús deng Tuhan Allah<bt>A rich person looks for a way to live continually with God</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="angka-angka diri = sombong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">angka-angka diri = sombong</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 19:16-30; Lukas 18:18-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Waktu Yesus dong mau barangkat, ju ada satu orang kaya lari-lari datang ko mau katumu sang Dia. Dia tondo di Yesus pung muka, ais dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru yang terhormat! Beta mau tanya sadiki. Bagini, Bapa. Beta musti bekin karmana, ko biar beta tau parsís beta bisa maso sorga ko idop tarús sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah?&gt;&gt;<bt>When Yesus (collective) were about to leave, then a rich person came running wanting to meet with Him. He bowed.slightly (sign of respect) at Yesus' face, then he asked saying, &lt;&lt;Most honoured Teacher! I want to ask a little. It's like this, Father/sir. I must do what, in order that I know with full assurance, I can enter heaven to live continually together with God?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kaya from vs 22ff.-- following theme."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">kaya from vs 22ff.-- following theme. Good as a vocative?; tondo = slight bow, sign of respect</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko lu bilang sang Beta, &lt;terhormat&gt;? Sonde ada satu orang yang terhormat, kecuali Tuhan Allah sa.<bt>Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;Why do you-sg say to Me, &lt;most honoured&gt;? There is no one who is most honoured, except only God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kecuali doesn't sound like KM. -&gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">kecuali doesn't sound like KM. -&gt; cuma Tuhan Allah sandiri sa yang bae.</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Lu su tau Tuhan Allah pung parenta dari dolu dong bilang,<bt>You already know God's commands from before saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;Jang bunu orang;<bt>&lt;Don't murder people;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jang barsina;<bt>Don't commit adultery;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jang mancuri;<bt>Don't steal;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jang jadi saksi putar-balek;<bt>Don't become a lying witness;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Jang tipu orang ko ame dong pung barang;<bt>Don't deceive people in order to take their things;</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Deng kasi hormat sang lu pung mama deng papa.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>And put honour on your-sg mother and father.&gt;&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: RL order.]</bt><note reference="10:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 20:12-16, Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 5:16-20</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Itu orang manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl, Bapa Guru! Mulai dari muda, beta su iko itu parenta samua.&gt;&gt;<bt>That person answered saying, &lt;&lt;True, Father Teacher! Starting from (my) youth, I have followed/obeyed all those commands.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kici = ; muda = remaja"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">kici = ; muda = remaja</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Yesus kasian itu orang. Ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl! Ma masi ada lai satu hal. Sakarang lu pulang ko jual bekin abis lu pung harta dong samua. Dia pung doi, lu pi bagi-bagi kasi orang susa dong. Ais itu, lu datang ko iko sang Beta suda. Nanti Tuhan Allah balas kasi sang lu deng harta laen di sorga.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus loved/pitied that person. Then He said, &lt;&lt;True! But there is still one more thing. Now you must go home to sell off (completely sell) all your possessions/wealth. Its money, you go divide giving to the poor people (lit: people in difficulty). After that, you come to follow Me (imperative). Later God will reciprocate giving you other possessions/wealth in heaven.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mata kasian = ; malarat ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">mata kasian = ; malarat = paling miskin (BI); orang kaya can be susa, but cannot be 'orang susa'</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Itu orang dengar ame Yesus pung omong bagitu, ju dia pung hati ancor. Ais dia pulang deng hati susa mau mati, tagal dia talalu kaya na.<bt>That person heard Yesus' talk like that, then his liver was destroyed (=discouraged, disappointed, depressed). So he went home with his liver in an extreme state of difficulty, because he was truly rich.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hati jato = kasian, pity;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">hati jato = kasian, pity;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="the feeling of 'face fell' (try"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">the feeling of 'face fell' (try for an idiom) should come before he goes home</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu orang dengar ame Yesus pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Itu orang dengar ame Yesus pung omong bagitu, ju dia rasa susa [hati barát] mo mati. Ais dia pi/jalan kasi tenga itu tampa [deng hati susa], tagal dia memang kaya sakali.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ju Yesus lia pi-datang, deng omong sang Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar, é! Orang kaya memang paling susa maso sorga!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus looked around (lit. going-coming), and spoke to His *disciples saying, &lt;&lt;Listen, é! Rich people really are the most difficult to enter heaven!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00038C.tif" rtfFormat="width:8.0cm;textWrapping:none">Binatang onta<bt>Onta (camel) animal</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Dengar Dia omong bagitu, ju ana bua dong bingung. Ma Yesus tamba lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Dengar bae-bae! Mau jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang tu, talalu susa! Jang pikir itu gampang sa.<bt>Hearing Him talk like that, then the disciples were confused. But Yesus added more saying, &lt;&lt;Listen carefully! Wanting to become a person of (belonging to) God's, is very extremely difficult! Don't think it's just easy.</bt><v n="25" />Ko orang kaya maso sorga jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang, itu sama susa ke binatang onta bésar satu, maso pi dia pung kandang lewat jarom pung lobang.&gt;&gt;<bt>For a rich person to enter heaven becoming God's person, that is the same difficulty as a large camel animal entering into its pen through a sewing-needle hole.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: the literal picture carries the sense of ‘impossible, extremely difficult, unlikely’, without having to do gymnastics over the more speculative and more complicated idea of a short gate named ‘eye of needle’. It's a metaphor!]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Yesus pung omong tu, bekin dong samua tamba bingung lai. Ju dong batanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo memang batúl bagitu, sapa yang bisa dapa salamat, é?&gt;&gt;<bt>What Yesus was saying made them all even more confused. Then they asked each other saying, &lt;&lt;If that's really true like that, who can get *salvation, é?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Yesus lia sang dong satu-satu, ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Buat manusia, memang sonde mungkin. Ma jang lupa: buat Tuhan Allah, samua bisa jadi!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus looked at each one of them, then He said, &lt;&lt;For humans, it really is not possible/not likely. But don't forget: for God, all/everything can happen/come into being.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Ais ju Petrus angka omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa. Botong su kasi tenga botong pung samua-samua, ko iko sang Papa. Ma botong dapa apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>And then Petrus started to talk saying, &lt;&lt;Papa. We-exc have already left our everything, to follow Papa. But what do we get?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="angka omong = begin speaking"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">angka omong = begin speaking</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29-30" />Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta mau kasi tau sang bosong bagini: orang yang iko sang Beta, deng jalan kasi tenga dia pung mama-papa, dia pung adi-kaka, dia pung ana-ana dong, dia pung kabón, dia pung karjá, deng dia pung isi ruma samua, ko pi kasi tau orang di mana-mana Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae, nanti dia tarima bale sampe saratus kali lipat. Samua hal yang dia su kasi tenga tu, nanti dia tarima kambali balipa-ganda. Deng dia ju nanti kaná siksa tagal dia iko sang Beta. Ma nanti kalo ini dunya kiamat, dia akan idop tarús sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah. Itu dia pung balasan!<bt>Yesus said, &lt;&lt;I want to tell you-pl like this: a/the person follows Me, and goes/travels leaving behind his mother-father, his elder-younger siblings, his children, his fields, his work, and all his household (=contents &amp; associated people), to go/travel telling people everywhere God's *Good News, later he will receive in reciprocation up to 100 times. Everything that he has left behind, he will later receive back in abundance. And he will also be afflicted with/experience torture because he follows Me. But later when it's the end of the world, he will live continually together with God. That's his reciprocation/reward! [EXEG: careful. I've noticed several teams put in the torture/persecution clause, but omit the critically important reason clause “because he follows me”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta mau kasi tau"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta mau kasi tau sang bosong bagini: Sapa yang su jalan kasi tenga dia pung kelu, deng dia pung karjá, ko iko sang Beta pi kuliling kasi tau orang Tuhan Allah pung Kabar Bae, nanti dia tarima bale sampe saratus kali lipat. Orang yang su jalan kasi tenga dia pung isi ruma, dia pung mama-papa, dia pung kaka-adi, dia pung ana-ana, dia pung kabón, sampe-sampe kaná siksa, tagal iko sang Beta, nanti sampe hari kiamat, dia maso sorga ko idop tarús sama-sama deng Tuhan Allah. Itu dia pung balasan!</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="isi ruma = people &amp; things"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">isi ruma = people &amp; things</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Inga, é! Orang yang bekin-bekin diri bésar, iko Tuhan Allah pung pikir, nanti dia jadi orang yang paling kici. Ma orang yang anggap diri kici, iko Tuhan Allah pung pikir, dia yang nanti jadi orang bésar.&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember, é! A person who keeps trying to make himself big/important, according to God's thinking, later he will be the smallest/most insignificant person. But a person who considers himself small/insignificant, according to God's thinking, he will later be/become a big/important person.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="10:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 20:16, Lukas 13:30</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Ini su tiga kali Tuhan Yesus kasi tau Dia pung mati<bt>This is already third time Lord Yesus tells about His death</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 20:17-19; Lukas 18:31-34)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Itu waktu, Yesus dong jalan pi Yerusalem. Yesus jalan paling muka. Dia pung ana bua dua blas orang deng orang laen dong iko sang Dia. Dong ada inga apa yang Dia omong dolu bilang, orang mau bunu sang Dia di Yerusalem. Tagal itu, ju dong jadi bingung, deng taku. Dengar bagitu, ais Yesus pange ame Dia pung ana bua sandiri, ko kasi tau lai apa yang orang mau bekin sang Dia di Yerusalem.<bt>At that time, Yesus (coll-pl) was traveling to Yerusalem. Yesus was walking at the front. His disciples and other people were following Him. They were remembering what He said before, that people would kill Him in Yerusalem. Because of that, they became confused, and afraid. Hearing that, then Yesus called his disciples by themselves, to tell again what people would do to Him in Yerusalem.</bt><v n="33" />Dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dengar, é! Kotong sakarang mau pi Yerusalem. Beta ni, Manusia Tulen. Ma di sana dong jual sang Beta, kasi pi di kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos, deng guru agama dong. Ais dong kasi hukum mati sang Beta. Ju dong lapás buang sang Beta pi orang laen yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>He talked saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl listen! We now are goint to Yerusalem. I here, am Ideal/Prototype Human. But there they will *betray (sell) me, give to the *chief priests and the religion teachers. Then they will give me a death sentence. Then they will let.go throw away Me to the other people who don't know God.</bt><v n="34" />Ais dong omong bekin malu sang Beta. Dong buang luda sang Beta. Dong firuk kasi ancor-ancor Beta pung badan. Ais baru dong bunu bekin mati sang Beta. Memang Beta mati batúl. Ma dia pung lusa, Beta idop kambali.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they will shame Me. They will throw spit at Me. They will swing.a.whip destroying my body. Then after.that they will murder kill Me. I will indeed truly die. But its day day.after.the.following.day, I will live again.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Afta three days&quot; is not the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z" status="Information">"Afta three days" is not the same as "Day numba three." In Jewish counting, today is the day 1, tomorrow is day 2, day after is day 3. "Afta three days" could be day 4. CHECK.</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko dong inga Yesus su carita"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">ko dong inga Yesus su carita bilang orang dong mau beking susa sang Dia di Yerusalem. = best exegesis as to why they were afraid. ; olok-olok = beking malu ; po-poko = beat with stick rotan/kayu; firuk = swing, whip</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:34" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dalam bahasa Yunani, dong mulai itong dari: ini hari (= 1), beso (= 2), lusa (= 3), tula (= 4). Jadi dalam bahasa Yunani, μετὰ τρεῖς ἡμέρας <span class="Italic">(meta treis hēmeras) </span>&lt;&lt;di hari yang katiga&gt;&gt; pung maksud dalam bahasa Kupang, andia &lt;&lt;dia pung lusa&gt;&gt;. Inga te, Tuhan Yesus mati hari jum'at (itong satu). Dia pung beso, andia hari sabtu (itong dua), Tuhan Yesus ada dalam kubur. Dia pung lusa, andia hari minggu (itong tiga), Tuhan Yesus idop kambali. Jadi iko kotong pung cara itong hari, na, Dia mati dua malam, ais Dia idop kambali.<bt>In the Yunani language, they begin counting from today (= 1), tomorrow (= 2), day.after.tomorrow (=3), day three (= 4). So (consequently), in the Yunani language, μετὰ τρεῖς ἡμέρας <span class="Italic">(meta treis hēmeras)</span> “on the third day” means in the Kupang language, “the day after (tomorrow, next)”. Remember that, the Lord Yesus died on Friday (count one). Tomorrow/the next day, that is Saturday (count two), the Lord Yesus was in the grave. The day after(tomorrow/next), that is Sunday (count three), the Lord Jesus lived again/came back to life. So (consequently)according to the way that we-inc count days, na, He was dead for two nights, and then He came back to life.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yakobis deng Yohanis minta jadi orang bésar<bt>Yakobis and Yohanis request to become big/important people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 20:20-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ais ju Yakobis deng Yohanis, andia Sabadeus pung ana dong, datang sang Yesus. Dong minta sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa Guru! Botong ada parlú.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yakobis and Yohanis, that is Sabadeus' children, came to Yesus. They requested of Him saying, &lt;&lt;Father Teacher! We have a need (to talk with you).&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="36" />Yesus tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong parlú apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus asked them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl need what?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini, Papa! Nanti kalo Papa su dudu pegang parenta deng hebat, na, botong minta ko Papa kasi dudu sang botong, satu di Papa pung sablá kanan, satu di sablá kiri, ko botong ju pegang parenta.&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered saying, &lt;&lt;It's like this, Father! Later if/when You are already sitting holding rule/government with amazingness/glory, na, we-exc request that You seat us, one on Your right side, one on (Your) left side, so we also hold rule.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk: glory here]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dua ni sonde mangarti apa yang bosong minta. Beta ni, nanti dapa sangsara banya. Jadi karmana? Bosong kira bosong ju mampu pikol itu sangsara sama-sama deng Beta sampe mati, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl two here don't understand what you are asking. I here, later will get/experience much suffering. So (consequently) how about it? Do you-pl think you also are able to shoulder.carry that suffering together with Me to the point of death, ko [+tag]?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mok = galas batu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">mok = galas batu</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 12:50</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong bisa, Papa!&gt;&gt;<bt>They answered saying, &lt;&lt;We can, Father!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus balas lai sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang, bosong ju nanti pikol itu sangsara sama ke Beta.<bt>Yesus responded again to them saying, &lt;&lt;Indeed, you also later will shoulder.carry that suffering like Me.</bt><v n="40" />Ma sapa yang nanti dudu di Beta pung kanan deng kiri, itu bukan Beta yang putus. Itu Tuhan Allah pung hak putus. Dia su putus memang, sapa-sapa yang dudu di itu tampa.&gt;&gt;<bt>But who it is who later sits on My right and left, that is not Me who decides. That is the Lord God who has the right to decide. (And) He has already decided beforehand, who it is that sits in those places.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Waktu ana bua yang laen dong dengar Yakobis deng Yohanis pung minta bagitu, ju dong mara.<bt>When the other disciples heard Yakobis and Yohanis' request like that, then they were angry.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***deleted &quot;extremely&quot; (angry)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:33Z">***deleted "extremely" (angry)</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Ais Yesus pange ame sang dong samua, ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bagini! Bosong su tau, to? Orang bésar yang pegang parenta biasa tendes dong pung rakyat, sampe dong sonde bisa bagarák. Deng kapala-kapala dari bangsa yang sonde kanál sang Tuhan Allah, dong kasi parenta lebe-lebe, sampe dong pung rakyat sonde bisa angka kapala.<bt>So Yesus called them all together, and He said, &lt;&lt;It's like this! You know this, to [+tag; expect affirmation]? The big/important people who hold government (who rule) often press.down on their citizens, to the point that they can't move. And heads/leaders from races/peoples that don't know God, they give excessive commands, to the point that their citizens are not able to lift their heads.</bt><v n="43" />Ma bosong sonde bole bekin bagitu! Naa, sapa dari bosong yang mau jadi orang bésar, dia musti jadi sama ke tukang suru-suru ko layani orang laen.<bt>But you-pl may not/aren't permitted to do like that! Naa [+shift to conclusion], whoever from you who wants to be/become a big/important person, he must become the same as the (lowly) servant1 to serve other people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="jongos = pelayan paling rendah (laki-laki)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">jongos = pelayan paling rendah (laki-laki) ; babu (parempuan) koko ana, satrika, pel lantai</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Naa, sapa dari bosong yang mau"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Naa, sapa dari bosong yang mau jadi orang bésar, dia musti jadi sama ke jongos ko layani orang laen.</Message></Annotation><note reference="10:42-43" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 22:25-26</note><v n="44" />Deng orang yang mau jadi kapala, dia musti bekin diri sama ke jongos.<bt>And whoever wants to be/become a head/leader, he must make himself like a lowly servant2.</bt><note reference="10:43-44" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 23:11, Markus 9:35, Lukas 22:26</note><v n="45" />Te Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, bukan datang ko orang layani sang Beta. Ma Beta datang ko layani banya orang. Beta datang kasi Beta pung idop anteru-anteru ko tabús ame banya orang dari dong pung sala-sala.&gt;&gt;<bt>Cuz (elaboration) I, this *Ideal/Prototype Human here, didn't come in order that people serve Me, but I came to serve many people. I came to give my whole-complete life to redeem many people from their sins.&gt;&gt; [KT: ransom, redeem, release. Many are familiar with how pawnshops work. Check the vocabulary.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Beta datang kasi Beta pung idop"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Beta datang kasi Beta pung idop anteru-anteru ko kasi bebas orang banya dari dong pung sala.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bekin bae orang buta<bt>Lord Yesus heals a blind person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 20:29-34; Lukas 18:35-43)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua, deng orang bam-banya sampe di kota Yeriko. Waktu dong mau jalan tarús, te ada satu orang buta yang dudu minta-minta di pinggir jalan. Dia pung nama Bartimeos, papa Timeos pung ana.<bt>Yesus and His *disciples, and very many people arrived at Yeriko city. When they wanted to continue on, there was a blind man who sat begging at the sit of the road. His name Bartimeos, father Timeos' child. [EXEG: Gk ‘large crowd’.]</bt><v n="47" />Waktu dia dengar bilang, yang lewat tu, Yesus dari Nasaret, ju dia batarea karás-karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus! Daud pung turunan, é! Botong su tunggu-tunggu lama sang Papa! Kasian sang beta dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>When he heard that the one who was passing by was Yesus from Nasaret, then he yelled loudly saying, &lt;&lt;Yesus! Daud's descendant, é! We-inc have been waiting a long time for You! Love/Pity me!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: 1) ‘son of David’ is not a difference of one generation, but of many-many generations, so most lgs have to say ‘descendant’. 2) ‘son of David’ is a messianic title that all Jews would recognise. Therefore this blind man is saying Jesus is the long awaited messiah.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="48" />Dengar dia batarea bagitu, ju orang dong togor sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Diam!&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing him yell like that, then people scolded him saying, &lt;&lt;Heeh [+rebuke]! Be quiet!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma dia batarea lebe karás lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Yesus! Daud pung turunan, é! Kasian sang beta doo!&gt;&gt;<bt>But he yelled even more loudly saying, &lt;&lt;Yesus! Daud's descendant, é! Love/Pity me!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="49" />Ais Yesus barenti. Ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong bawa sang dia datang di sini!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus stopped. And He said, &lt;&lt;You-pl bring him here!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dong pi sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu diam suda! Papa Guru ada pange sang lu. Mari suda!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they went to him saying, &lt;&lt;You-sg be quiet now! Father Teacher is calling/summoning you. Come on!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="(al) Lu tanáng sa!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">(al) Lu tanáng sa!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Dengar bagitu, Bartimeos lempar buang dia pung salimut, ju dia badiri capát-capát ko pi katumu sang Yesus.<bt>Hearing that, Bartimeos jumped throwing.off his blanket (man's sarong/outer garmet), and he stood up rapidly to go meet Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Yesus tanya sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu mau apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus asked him saying, &lt;&lt;You want what?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu orang buta manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa, é! Beta minta ko beta bisa dapa lia.&gt;&gt;<bt>That blind person answered saying, &lt;&lt;Father, é! I request that I can be able to see.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="52" />Yesus bilang lai sang dia, &lt;&lt;Tagal lu parcaya bilang, Beta bisa bekin bae sang lu, sakarang ju lu su bae! Pi suda!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus spoke again to him, &lt;&lt;Because you-sg believe that I can heal you, now you're already well/healed! Go on now (imperative)!</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Bartimeos pung mata langsung bae memang. Ais itu, dia pi iko antar sang Yesus.<bt>And Bartimeos' eyes straight away were indeed good/well. After that, he accompanied escorting Yesus.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus dong maso pi Yerusalem, deng banya orang puji-puji sang Dia, sama ke orang bésar<bt>Lord Yesus (coll) enter Yerusalem, and many people praise Him, like a big/important person</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:1-11; Lukas 19:28-40; Yohanis 12:12-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="11" />
      <v n="1" />Waktu dong su deka deng kota Yerusalem, dong sampe di dua kampong, Betfage deng Betania, di gunung Saitun pung pinggir.<bt>When they were already close to Yerusalem city, they arrived at two villages, Betfage and Betania, on the slope of Saitun mountain.</bt><note reference="11:1" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dong kasi nama &lt;Saitun&gt; di itu gunung, tagal di sana ada banya kabón pohon saitun, ko dong parés ame dia pung minya dari itu pohon pung bua. Itu gunung Saitun kira-kira satu kilo dari kota Yerusalem.<bt>They gave the name &lt;Saitun (olive)&gt; to that mountain, because there are many saitun tree groves, so they could press oil from that tree's fruit. That Saitun mountain is approximately one kilo from Yerusalem city.</bt></note>Dari situ Yesus dong barenti tahan. Ais Dia kirim Dia pung ana bua dua orang ko pi lebe dolo.<bt>From there Yesus (collective) waited awhile. Then He sent two of His disciples to go on ahead.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="lereng (BI) = kaki"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">lereng (BI) = kaki</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Dia pasán bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dua pi lebe dolo di itu kampong sana. Kalo bosong maso, nanti bosong dapa lia binatang keledai pung ana satu, ada ta'ika di situ. Orang balóm parná nae coba sang dia. Bosong pi buka dia pung tali ko hela bawa sang dia datang sini.<bt>He instructed saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl two go ahead to that village yonder. As you enter, you will see a donkey (loan) animal's offspring, tied there. People have not yet ever tried to mount/ride on him. You go open/undo his rope to pull bringing him here.</bt><v n="3" />Ma kalo ada orang tanya sang bosong bilang, &lt;Akurang ko bosong lapás bawa itu keledai?&gt; Naa, bosong manyao bilang, &lt;Botong pung Bos mau pake sang dia. Kalo su pake abis, nanti Dia kirim pulang memang.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>But if someone asks you saying, &lt;Why are you releasing taking that donkey?&gt; Naa, you answer saying, &lt;Our-exc Bos wants to use him. If/When finished using, then He will send [him] back straight away.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00033C.tif" rtfFormat="width:9.5cm;textWrapping:none">Binatang keledai<bt>Keledei (donkey) animal</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais, itu dua orang dong pi, ju dong dapa lia itu keledai pung ana ada ta'ika di muka satu ruma di pinggir jalan. Ju dong lapás ko bawa sang dia.<bt>Then those two people went, and they saw that donkey's offspring tied up in front of a house on the side of the road. Then they untied to bring it.</bt><v n="5" />Ma orang yang ada badiri di situ dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoi! Akurang ko bosong lapás ame orang pung keledai?&gt;&gt;<bt>But people who were standing there asked saying, &lt;&lt;Hoi! [+reprimand] Why are you-pl releasing that donkey of someone (=that someone else owns)?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ais dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong pung Bos mau pake sang dia. Kalo su pake abis, nanti botong bawa pulang memang.&gt;&gt; Ju itu orang dong kasi tenga sang dong ko hela bawa itu keledai.<bt>Then they answered saying, &lt;&lt;Our-inc Bos wants to use it. When finished using, we-exc will bring it back straight away.&gt;&gt; Then that person let them pull take away that donkey.</bt><v n="7" />Dong hela bawa pi Yesus. Ais dong taro dong pung salimut di atas itu keledai, ju Yesus nae.<bt>They pulled taking it to Yesus. Then they put their blankets (male sarong) on top of that donkey, and Yesus got up/mounted it.</bt></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00315C.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none">Tuhan Yesus maso pi dalam kota Yerusalem<bt>Lord Yesus enters the city of Yerusalem</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Waktu dong mau maso pi dalam kota, ju ada banya orang yang ame dong pung salimut, deng dong pung salendang, ko taro di jalan. Ada ju yang pi potong ame daon-daon palam<bt>As they were about to enter the city, then there were many people who took their blankets (male sarong) and shawls (female salendang) to place on the road. There were also those who went cutting palam</bt><note reference="11:8" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Markus pung tulisan asli tulis bilang, &lt;cabang dong&gt;. Ma kotong su tau dari Yohanis 12:13 bilang, dong tu, daon-daon palam.<bt>Markus' original writing said &lt;branches&gt;. But we know from Yohanis 12:13 that they were like palam/cycad leaves/fronds (not wood).</bt></note>di pinggir jalan ko dong buka-buka di tenga jalan. Deng bagitu, dong bekin tanda bilang, dong sambut sang Tuhan Yesus deng hormat. Sama ke dong biasa tarima orang-orang bésar.<bt>leaves along the side of the road so they could open/spread them in middle of the road. In that way, they make a sign saying they welcomed/received2 the Lord Yesus with respect. Like they usually received1 big/important people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="salendang ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">salendang =</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Ju ada orang saparu pi bajalan lebe dolo di muka Yesus, deng ada yang iko dari balakang. Dong mulai ba'eki bilang,<bt>Then some people went walking in front of Yesus and some followed from behind. They begin shouting (message happily) saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ba'eki = sorak-sorak, shouting greeting (happy),"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">ba'eki = sorak-sorak, shouting greeting (happy), calling</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;&lt;<span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> Kotong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah!<bt><span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Hosana! </span>We-inc keep praising God!</bt><note reference="11:9" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Dong pung bahasa Aram bilang, <span class="Italic">&lt;Hosana&gt;</span>. Dia pung arti dolu-dolu bilang, &lt;dia kasi salamat&gt;. Ma di Tuhan Yesus pung jaman, dong biasa pake itu kata ko puji sang Tuhan Allah sa.<bt>Their Aram language said <span class="Italic">&lt;Hosana&gt;.</span> Its meaning long ago was &lt;he saves&gt;. But in the Lord Yesus' time/age/era, they usually used that word to just praise God.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tuhan kasi berkat sang orang yang datang pake Tuhan pung nama,<bt>The Lord gives blessing to the person who comes using the Lord's name,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">tagal Tuhan su utus sang Dia!<bt>because the Lord has commissioned Him!</bt><note reference="11:9" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 118:26</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="10" />
      <span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> Kotong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah!<bt><span class="Italic">Hosana! </span>We keep praising God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal Tuhan mau kasi bangun kambali raja Daud pung parenta!<bt>Because the Lord is going to rebuild king Daud's rule/governing!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> Kotong puji-puji sang Tuhan Allah!<bt><span class="Italic">Hosana!</span> We keep praising God!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal Tuhan su dudu parenta di langit yang paling tinggi!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because the Lord sits ruling/governing in the highest sky!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Sampe dalam kota, ais Yesus dong pi maso di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung kintal. Ju Yesus lia bae-bae kuliling itu kompleks. Ma tagal su sonde ada waktu lai, ju dong pulang kambali pi kampong Betania.<bt>Arriving in the city, then Yesus (collective) entered into the *Temple (God's Main Worship House)'s yard. And Yesus looked carefully all around that complex. But because there was no more time (=late), they returned again to Betania village. [KT: Most people don't realise the temple was a collection of walled in buildings, and that most of the events recorded in the gospels in relation to the temple happened in the temple courtyard, not inside a big church.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="buang dia pung mata kuliling ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">buang dia pung mata kuliling =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Di situ Yesus buang Dia pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Di situ Yesus buang Dia pung mata kuliling. Abis hari su mulai glap ju Dia deng ...</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00250C.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none">Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat deng dia pung kintal<bt>God's *Temple and its yard</bt></fig>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus parenta satu pohon ko dia sonde bisa babua lai<bt>Lord Yesus commands a tree so that it can no longer have fruit</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:18-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Dia pung beso papagi, dong jalan kaluar dari Betania ko maso kambali di kota Yerusalem. Ma di tenga jalan, Yesus su rasa lapar.<bt>Very early the next morning, they went out from Betania to enter again Yerusalem city. But in the middle of the road/journey, Yesus felt hungry.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="beso papagi ; dia pung paru"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">beso papagi ; dia pung paru su kete = parut su pedis (idiom)</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Dia dapa lia satu pohon di pinggir jalan. Orang biasa makan dia pung bua.<bt>He saw a tree on the side of the road. People usually eat its fruit.</bt><note reference="11:13" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Bahasa Indonesia pake kata &lt;pohon ara&gt; dari istila bahasa Yunani <span class="Italic">sukē. </span>Ma Alkitab kasi tunju satu pohon di sana yang orang biasa tanam, deng makan dia pung bua. Di Indonesia sablá timur, orang sonde tanam deng sonde makan &lt;pohon ara&gt; pung bua. Jadi &lt;pohon ara&gt; di Alkitab sonde sama ke kotong pung pohon ara di sini.<bt>Indonesian uses the word &lt;pohon ara&gt; from the Yunani/Greek language term <span class="Italic">sukē.</span> But the Bible designates a tree from there (remote) which people usually plant, and eat its fruit. In eastern Indonesia, people do not plant and do not eat &lt;ara&gt; tree's fruit. So (consequently) &lt;ara tree&gt; in the Bible is not the same as our-inc ara tree here.</bt></note>Jadi Yesus pi deka-deka itu pohon ko mau lia coba ada bua, ko sonde. Ma waktu Dia sampe di itu pohon, Dia sonde dapa lia apa-apa. Ko memang bukan dia pung musim babua na. Dia baru mulai badaon sa.<bt>So (consequently) Yesus approached that tree wanting to try and see if there was fruit or not. But when he arrived at that tree, He didn't see anything. Cuz [+emphatic] it really wasn't its fruiting season. It had only just started to put out leaves/buds.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dia pung daon garui sakali ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">dia pung daon garui sakali = thick &amp; luxurious; subur, lebat</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ju Yesus omong kasi itu pohon bilang, &lt;&lt;Tagal lu sonde kasi lu pung bua sang Beta, jadi mulai dari sakarang, lu sonde bisa kasi lu pung bua sang orang laen lai!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus spoke to that tree saying, &lt;&lt;Because you don't give your fruit to Me, so (consequently) starting from now, you will not be able to give your fruit to other people anymore/either!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dia pung ana bua dong dengar Dia pung omong karás bagitu.<bt>His disciples heard him talk severely like that. [EXEG: Gk does not use the word ‘curse’ here, so avoid it. Peter uses ‘curse’ in vs. 21 to describe this event.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus maso pi Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Ais Dia bongkar buang pasar di situ<bt>Lord Yesus enters the *Temple. Then he dismantles getting rid of the market there</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:12-17; Lukas 19:45-48; Yohanis 2:13-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ais dong jalan tarús, sampe di Yerusalem, ju Yesus pi maso lai di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Di itu Ruma Sambayang pung kintal, orang su bekin jadi pasar ko dong bajual burung pompa yang orang pake buat korban sambayang. Lia bagitu, ju Yesus pi usir kasi kaluar sang dong. Dia banting kasi talempar meja-meja yang dong pake tukar doi, deng banting kasi tabale bangku-bangku yang dong pake bajual itu burung dong.<bt>Then they continued walking, arriving at Yerusalem, and Yesus went again into the *Temple (Main House of Prayer/Worship). In that Temple's yard, people had made it into a market for them to sell doves that people used for *worship *sacrifices. Seeing that, Yesus went expelling sending them out. He threw.down making the tables thrown.about which they used to exchange money, and threw.down making upside.down the benches which they used to sell those birds.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tukar doi ; banting ; talempar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">tukar doi ; banting ; talempar ; tabale ; burung pompa</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia mulai usir kasi kaluar samua"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Dia mulai usir kasi kaluar samua orang yang ada pasang jualan di itu tampa.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Dia ju larang samua orang ko sonde bole bawa ame dong pung barang ko jalan potong lewat itu kintal lai.<bt>He also forbade all the people in order that they not bring their things to take a short-cut through that yard any more. [EXEG: see discussion in TN, CONNOT, TRT note, France. This is an additional group of people using the temple for a shortcut, perhaps to get to their gardens in Kidron valley or the mount of Olives. Carson notes that 20 years later or so, even the Jewish religious leaders realised this was inappropriately defiling a sacred place and posted the same ban.]</bt><v n="17" />Ju Dia ajar sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong su tau memang apa yang Tuhan pung jubir su tulis bilang, &lt;Beta kasi bangun Beta pung Ruma ni, ko orang dari samua suku-bangsa datang sambayang di sini.&gt; Ma bosong su bekin ini Ruma jadi parampok dong pung tampa bakumpul!&gt;&gt;<bt>And He taught them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl already actually know what the Lord's spokesperson wrote saying, &lt;I build this House of Mine, so that people from all peoples/races/nations come worship here.&gt; But you-pl have made this House become thieves gathering place!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Buku Itam = Alkitab, Buku"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Buku Itam = Alkitab, Buku</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:17" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 56:7, Yeremia 7:11</note></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01787b.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Waktu kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos deng guru agama dong dengar Yesus su bekin bagitu, ju dong jengkel sang Dia. Ais dong mulai cari jalan ko mau bunu bekin mati sang Dia. Ma dong ju eleng, tagal banya orang talalu suka Dia pung ajaran.<bt>When the *chief priests and the religious teachers heard Yesus had done like that, they were very upset toward Him. Then they began to look for a way to murder kill Him. But they also were afraid/in.awe because many people liked very.much His teaching/s.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="chief priests ; mara is a"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">chief priests ; mara is a speech act verb; jengkel = makan hati (KM), hate, binci; eleng = segan ; bos ; tua-tua adat ; naton = keep track of faults (?)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Waktu matahari su mulai tanggalám, ju Yesus dong kaluar dari kota Yerusalem, ko dong kambali pi tidor di kampong Betania.<bt>When the sun was beginning to sink, then Yesus (collective) went out of Yerusalem city, to return to sleep in Betania village.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bagitu mulai malam ju Yesus deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Bagitu mulai malam ju Yesus deng</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kalo kotong parcaya batúl-batúl sang Tuhan, nanti Dia kasi apa yang kotong minta<bt>If we truly believe in God, He will give what we ask</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:20-22)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20-21" />Dia pung beso papagi, dong kambali lai pi Yerusalem. Di tenga jalan, dong lewat itu pohon yang kamaren Yesus omong kasi dia. Dia pung ana bua dong taheran-heran, tagal itu pohon su mati karíng sampe dia pung akar-akar. Ju Petrus inga Yesus pung omong yang kamaren tu. Ais dia kasi tau bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Lia coba! Itu pohon yang kamaren Papa kasi kutuk tu, su mati!&gt;&gt;<bt>Very early the next morning, they returned again to Yerusalem. In the middle of the road/journey, they passed.by that tree which yesterday Yesus spoke to it. His disciples were amazed, because that tree was already dead dry all the way to its roots. Then Petrus remembered what Yesus had said yesterday. Then he told saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Have a look! That tree which yesterday You cursed there, is already dead!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Ju Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang batúl! Asal bosong ju parcaya sang Tuhan Allah bagitu.<bt>Then Yesus answered/responded saying, &lt;&lt;That's right! If only you-pl would also believe in God like that.</bt><v n="23" />Kalo bosong parcaya batúl-batúl, bosong bisa suru gunung satu ko ta'angka pi laut. Ju Tuhan Allah kasi pinda itu gunung, asal bosong jang parcaya satenga-satenga! Bosong musti parcaya batúl-batúl sang Tuhan Allah.<bt>If you-pl truly believe, you can order a mountain to be lifted up going into the ocean. And God will move that mountain, as long as you don't believe half-half! You must truly believe in God.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="taangka; parcaya satenga-satenga = parcaya satenga"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">taangka; parcaya satenga-satenga = parcaya satenga hati</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:23" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 17:20, 1 Korintus 13:2</note><v n="24" />Naa! Jang lupa, ó! Asal bosong parcaya batúl-batúl bilang, Tuhan Allah mampu kasi apa yang bosong minta, pasti Dia bekin kasi bosong!<bt>Naa [+shift]! Don't forget! As long as you truly believe that God is capable to give what you ask, surely He will give it to you!</bt><v n="25" />Ma kalo ada yang sambayang, padahal dia pung hati ada batar-enak deng orang laen, dia musti babae deng itu orang dolo. Bagitu, baru bosong pung Papa di sorga mau hapus buang bosong pung sala-sala.<bt>But if/when there's someone praying, however his liver is not satisfactory with another person, he musti become in right relationship with that person first. Like that, only then your-pl Father in heaven is going/wants to *forgive your *wrongs.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="batar-enak ; bekin bae 1) heal,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">batar-enak ; bekin bae 1) heal, 2) straighten out, make things right ; sambayang putus kayu batu (id)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="abis dia inga bilang dia pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">abis dia inga bilang dia pung hati batar-enak deng orang laen, // Bagitu, baru bosong pung Papa di sorga mau bekin beres bosong pung sala.</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />[Kalo ada dari bosong yang simpan hati, deng sonde mau kasi ampon orang, tantu bosong pung Papa di sorga ju sonde mau lupa bosong pung sala-sala dong.&gt;&gt;]<bt>[If there are those among you-pl who hate (stores his liver), and doesn't want to forgive people, surely your Father in heaven also won't want to completely forget your wrongs.&gt;&gt;] [NOTE: In Timor area, "forgive" is simply a social action of granting forgiveness, but one can still be seething and planning to kill the guy in one's heart. This rendering gives both the action, and the meaning.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tantu ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">tantu =</Message></Annotation><note reference="11:26" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani asli yang lebe tua sonde tulis ini ayat 26.<bt>Original Yunani writings which are older don't write this verse 26.</bt></note><note reference="11:25-26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 6:14-15</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong baso'al Tuhan Yesus pung hak<bt>They question/challenge Lord Yesus' authority</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:23-27; Lukas 20:1-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Ais ju dong jalan tarús. Sampe di Yerusalem, dong maso kambali lai pi Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Waktu dong maso di kintal, kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, guru agama dong, deng tua-tua adat Yahudi datang,<bt>After that, they continued walking. Arriving in Yerusalem, they entered again into the *Temple. When they entered the yard, the *chief priests, the religious teachers, and the traditional Yahudi elders came, [KT: three levels, priests, chief priests, high priest. Do it as a set. Be consistent from now till the end of the book. Chief priests are always plural. Analogy: minister, head of prebytery, synod moderator.]</bt><v n="28" />ko baso'al deng Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Sapa suru lu datang bekin kaco di sini kamaren? Sapa yang kasi lu hak!&gt;&gt;<bt>to take issue with/challenge Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Who ordered you to come make chaos here yesterday? Who was it that gave you authority!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="so'al (vt)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">so'al (vt)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ma Yesus tau dong ada cari jalan ko mau kasi jato sang Dia. Ais Dia balas bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ju mau tanya sang bosong. Bosong manyao sang Beta dolo, baru Beta manyao sang bosong.<bt>But Yesus knew they were seeking a way to make Him fall (socially, morally, politically). Then He responded/reciprocated saying, &lt;&lt;I also want to ask you-pl. You answer Me first, only then will I answer you.</bt><v n="30" />Beta mau tanya bagini: bosong samua kanál sang Yohanis, Tukang Sarani tu, to? Naa, sapa yang suru sang dia ko pi sarani orang? Tuhan Allah ko, manusia?&gt;&gt;<bt>I want to ask like this: you all know Yohanis, that One.who.habitually Baptized, to [+tag; expecting affirmation]? Naa, who was it who ordered him to go *baptize people? God, or humans?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ais dong bapikir pi-datang, deng barunding bilang, &lt;&lt;Awe'! Kotong su kaná! Kalo kotong manyao bilang, &lt;Tuhan Allah yang suru&gt;, nanti dia balas bilang, &lt;Kalo bagitu, akurang ko bosong sonde parcaya sang Yohanis!&gt;<bt>Then they thought going-coming and consulted among themselves saying, &lt;&lt;Awee! [+uh-oh!] We-inc been hit (we're caught/trapped -idiomatic). If we answer saying, &lt;It was God who commanded&gt;, then he'll respond saying, &lt;If so, why didn't you believe in Yohanis!&gt;</bt><v n="32" />Ma kotong ju sonde bisa bilang, &lt;Manusia yang suru.&gt; Te nanti orang dong samua mangamok. Tagal dong parcaya bilang, Yohanis tu, Tuhan Allah pung jubir.&gt;&gt;<bt>But we also can't say, &lt;It was humans who commanded.&gt; Cuz (elaboration) all the people will go.beserk/riot. Because they believe that Yohanis, is God's *spokesperson.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangamok = mara; mulai bimbang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">mangamok = mara; mulai bimbang</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ais dong manyao sa bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong sonde tau!&gt;&gt;<bt>So they just answered saying, &lt;&lt;We-exc don't know!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju Yesus bale manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa! Kalo bagitu, Beta ju sonde mau kasi tau bilang, sapa yang suru sang Beta.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus responded answered saying, &lt;&lt;Naa! If it's like that, I also won't tell saying, who it was who commanded Me.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus carita umpama so'al orang karjá kabón anggor<bt>Lord Yesus tells *parable/allegory/example about the person/s who works a grape garden/orchard</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 21:33-46; Lukas 20:9-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="12" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, Yesus omong lai deng itu kapala agama Yahudi pung bos-bos, guru agama dong, deng tua-tua adat Yahudi dong. Dia pake umpama bilang, &lt;&lt;Ada satu orang pi buka kabón ko mau tanam pohon anggor di dia pung tana sapo'ong. Ais dia bekin pagar kuliling. Deng dia bekin bak ko mau tada bua anggor pung aer. Ju dia kasi badiri satu tampa jaga yang tinggi. Ais dia kasi sewa itu kabón pi orang laen, ko dong karjá bagi hasil deng dia. Tarús dia barangkat pi luar negrí.<bt>After that, Yesus talked again with the *chief priests, the religion teachers, and the traditional Yahudi elders. He used a *parable saying, &lt;&lt;There was a person who went to open a garden wanting to plant grape trees/plants on a piece of his land. [NOTE: ‘open a garden’ indicates first time cutting out of virgin forest.] Then he made a fence around, and he made a tank (loan) to store.the.liquid of the grape fruit. Also he built a guard place that was high. Then he rented out that garden to other people for them to work dividing the results with him. Then he left to go out of the country. [NOTE to daughter translations: in some RL, there is a difference between /sewa/ ‘rent (for money)’ and share cropping (dividing the yield). Check that there isn't a clash.] [NOTE: lex choice: stone fence to match middle east and picture, if there is a lexical distinction, as in some Timor lgs. Guarding place is like a house on a tower or on stilts. Some have a functional equivalent, and some don't.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tukang garap (mengolah) kabón = ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">tukang garap (mengolah) kabón = ; pares = squeeze w/hand; tada = cistern, store liquid, collect liquid</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 5:1-2</note></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00103C.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none">Kabon bua anggor, ruma jaga yang tinggi, deng bak inja bua anggor ko ame dia pung aer<bt>Field of anggor fruit, high guard house, and stepping tank for collecting grape juice inside it</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Sampe musim ketu bua anggor, ju itu tuan tana suru dia pung orang karjá satu pi di itu tukang garap dong, ko minta dia pung bagian.<bt>When the season for picking grapes arrived, then that landlord order one of his workers to go to those share-croppers, to request his share.</bt><v n="3" />Ma waktu dia pung sampe, itu tukang garap dong tangkap ame sang dia, ju dong papoko sang dia. Ais dong suru sang dia ko pulang deng tangan kosong.<bt>When he arrived, those share-croppers captured him, then they beat him up. Then they ordered him to return home with empty hands.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="beat up ?; papoko = pukul"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">beat up ?; papoko = pukul ulang-ulang (one-sided) bapukul/bakalai (reciprocal)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais, itu tuan tana kirim dia pung orang karjá satu lai. Ma itu tukang garap dong papoko sang dia pung kapala sampe luka-luka. Ais dong bekin malu, deng dong iskarobis sang dia.<bt>Then that landlord sent another worker. But those share-croppers beat his head until there were many wounds. Then they shamed him, and they shooed/ordered him out of there. [EXEG: Gk word and grammar for ‘beat on the head’ implies repeated and severe, not just bopped him on the head one time.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="beat over head? ; treat shamefully"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">beat over head? ; treat shamefully ; cuci-maki = curse, swear at in a way so as to shame; kadeluk (one person says flick on forehead); one feels that iskarobis isn't widely known</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ais, itu tuan tana kirim ulang dia pung orang karjá laen lai. Ma dong bunu sang dia. Biar dong bekin karmana ju, ma itu tuan tana maen kirim tarús dia pung orang karjá. Ma itu tukang garap dong papoko saparu, deng bunu saparu.<bt>Then that landlord sent once again another worker. But they killed him. Even though they did whatever (No matter what they did), nevertheless that landlord kept sending his workers. But those share-croppers beat some, and killed some.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maen = repeated aspect"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">maen = repeated aspect</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Sakarang cuma tenga lai satu orang sa. Andia tuan tana pung ana laki-laki satu biji yang dia paling sayang. Tagal sonde ada jalan laen lai, jadi dia kirim itu ana sa. Dia pikir bilang, &lt;Kalo beta kirim beta pung ana sandiri, pasti dong tarima bae-bae, deng dong dengar sang dia.&gt;<bt>Now there was only left just one person. That is the landlord's one and only male child whom he loves very much. Because there was no other way, so (consequently) he just sent that child. He thought saying, &lt;If I send my own child, surely they will receive him well, and they will listen to/obey him.&gt; [EXEG: Gk ‘finally’ conveying a sense of last resort.] [EXEG: Gk ‘respect’ taken to imply that the share-croppers should also respond with the desired behaviour.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="satu biji = one and only"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">satu biji = one and only</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="7" />Jadi dia kirim dia pung ana pi sana. Ma waktu tukang garap dong dapa lia itu ana datang, ju dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;We! Bosong lia dolo! Bapatua su kirim datang dia pung ana sandiri! Kalo bapatua mati, dia ni yang nanti tarima itu pusaka samua. Mari kotong bunu itu ana, ko biar kotong yang soa dia pung pusaka ni!&gt;<bt>So (consequently), he sent his child there. But when those share-croppers saw that child coming, then they spoke to each other saying, &lt;We [+attention]! You-pl look there! Elderfather has sent his own child. If/when elderfather dies, this one here is the one who will receive all that inheritance (loan). Let's kill that child, so that (purpose) we-inc are the ones who obtain/keep this inheritance of his!&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="soa = dapat, memperoleh, miliki; pusaka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">soa = dapat, memperoleh, miliki; pusaka = land, rumah, harta, ternak, kabón</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bakastau satu deng satu bilang, &lt;&lt;Yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">bakastau satu deng satu bilang, &lt;&lt;Yang datang ini bapatua pung ahli waris.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Ais dong rame-rame tangkap, ju dong bunu sang dia. Tarús dong lempar buang dia pung mayat pi balakang kabón. Itu umpama sampe di situ sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they enthusiastically captured him, and they killed him. Then they threw away his corpse in the back of/behind the garden. That's the end of that parable.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: there is an implied shift here between telling the end of the main story in vs.8, and shifting to ask/challenge the leaders with a question in vs. 9. Cf. CEV formatting. RL natural discourse closure for this genre made explicit for marking the end of the main story.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais ju Yesus tanya sang orang bésar dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Iko bosong pung pikiran, kira-kira itu tuan tana mau bekin karmana sang itu tukang garap dong? Iko Beta, su tantu dia datang ko bunu bekin abis itu tukang garap dong samua. Ais itu, dia kasi sewa itu kabón anggor pi orang laen.<bt>And then Yesus asked the big/important people saying, &lt;&lt;According to you-pl thinking, probably what is that landlord going to do to those share-croppers? According to Me, it's already obvious he will come to kill off all of those share-croppers. After that, he will rent out that grape garden to other person/s. [DISCOURSE: Paragraph and quote margin added to signal major shift in discourse. See note above.] [DISCOURSE: 3 categories of leaders in 11:27 and 12:1 conflated to lighten the information load.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Kotong samua su dapa baca dari Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>We-inc all have already read in God's *Scriptures saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Ada satu batu yang tukang dong su angka buang.<bt>&lt;There is one stone that the craftsmen have picked.up getting.rid.of.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Ma sakarang itu batu su jadi batu alas.<bt>But now that stone has already become a foundation/undergirding stone.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="11" />Tuhan Allah sandiri yang pili ame, ju kasi dudu itu batu.<bt>God himself chose/retrieved and placed that stone.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Andia ko kotong lia dia pung bagus lai!&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>That is why we-inc see it is so good/beautiful!&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Andia ko kotong lia ame dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Andia ko kotong lia ame dia pung bagus lai!&gt;"</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:10-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 118:22-23</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Itu orang bésar dong langsung mangarti bilang, Yesus ada ser sang dong pake itu umpama. Dong parsís ke tukang garap kabón anggor tadi tu. Ais ju dong mulai ator siasat ko mau tangkap sang Dia. Ma dong ada eleng sang orang banya yang suka Yesus pung ajaran. Jadi dong pi jalan kasi tenga sang Dia sa.<bt>Those big/important people straight away understood that Yesus had aimed/targeted at them using that parable. They were exactly like those grape garden share-croppers. And so they started to make strategy/plot to capture/arrest Him. But they were afraid of the many people who liked Yesus' teaching. So (consequently) they just went away leaving Him be. [EXEG: Implicit-explicit: explicate how he had targetted them with this story. From UNS confusion. See TN, NET note, CONNOT, TRT.] [EXEG: Implicit-explicit: explicate why they feared the crowd. From UNS confusion. Explicit elsewhere in the gospels. See TN.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ator siasat ko tangkap = cari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">ator siasat ko tangkap = cari akal, susun rencana, strategi ; ser = aim, target, naksir</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang mau hiki sang Tuhan Yesus deng pake so'al bayar bea<bt>People want to trap Lord Yesus with a problem about paying tax</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bea = balasteng (Du - archaic),"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">bea = balasteng (Du - archaic), pajak</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 22:15-22; Lukas 20:20-26)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais itu, orang Yahudi pung orang bésar dong suru barapa orang Farisi, deng orang dari Herodes pung partei pi baso'al deng Yesus, ko mau hiki sang Dia.<bt>After that, the Yahudi big/important people ordered several Farisi people, with people from Herodes' party to go discuss/debate/take issue with Yesus, wanting to trap Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="balasteng = tax (archaic); hiki ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">balasteng = tax (archaic); hiki = jerat, trap; so'al ini maju kana, mondor kana</Message></Annotation><v n="14" />Ais dong datang, ju baso'al deng Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Botong samua tau kalo Bapa pung hati lurus, deng sonde tau putar-balek. Bapa lia orang pung hati sa. Bapa ju kasi tau Tuhan Allah pung mau deng tarús-taráng, tagal Bapa sonde pandang muka. Naa! Sakarang botong mau tanya satu hal. Iko kotong pung atoran agama Yahudi, kira-kira kotong ni musti bayar bea kasi sang pamarenta Roma pung raja bésar,<bt>Then they came and took issue with Him saying, &lt;&lt;Father Teacher! We-inc all know that Father's liver is straight, and don't know how to lie. You just looks at people's livers. You also tell/explain God's will frankly/straight, because You don't view faces/discriminate. Naa! [+shift to main point] Now we-inc want to ask one thing. According to the teaching/s of our Yahudi religion, should we probably pay tax to the Roma government's big/important king,</bt><note reference="12:14" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Orang Roma pung raja bésar, dong pange &lt;keser&gt;.<bt>The Roma people's big/important king, they call &lt;Keser&gt;.</bt></note>ko sonde?&gt;&gt;<bt>or not?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pandang bulu (BI) = pandang muka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">pandang bulu (BI) = pandang muka (KM; discriminate, differentiate, prejudiced, react differently on basis of curliness of body-hair/facial features); balasteng = tax (Du); pandang muka; putar-balek = tipu daya, omong kosong; first yang is complementiser like 'bahwa'; angka nae = praise, talk him up</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deng sonde ame pusing deng orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">deng sonde ame pusing deng orang laen pung pendapat. Bapa kasi ajaran deng tarús trang tentang Tuhan Allah pung mau dari manusia, sebab Bapa sonde pandang bulu. bayar balasteng kasi sang Keser</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Ma Yesus su tau dong mau pancing sang Dia, ko Dia omong malawan pamarenta Roma. Ju Yesus manyao deng karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko bosong mau hiki sang Beta deng itu so'al! Coba kasi lia sang Beta doi perak satu dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus knew they wanted to bait Him, so that (purpose) He would talk against the Roma govt. Then Yesus responded/anwered them strong/harsh/forcefully saying, &lt;&lt;Why are you-pl trying to trap Me that problem/issue! Show Me a silver money (imperative)!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doi perak = coin; susun so'al"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">doi perak = coin; susun so'al</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus su tau memang dong pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Yesus su tau memang dong pung hati munafik putar balek. Ju Dia manyao, bilang,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\HK00166C.tif" rtfFormat="width:7.0cm;TextWrapping:none">Pamarenta Roma pung doi perak<bt>Roma government's silver money</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais dong sorong kasi sang Dia doi perak satu. Ju Yesus ame ko pareksa itu doi. Ais Dia tanya sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini gambar ni, sapa pung muka? Deng ini sapa pung nama?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they extended giving Him a silver money. And Yesus took and inspected that coin. Then He asked them saying, &lt;&lt;This picture here, is whose face? And this is whose name?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais dong manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu pamarenta Roma pung raja bésar!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they answered saying, &lt;&lt;That's the Roma govt's big/important king!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Ais Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa! Kalo bagitu, bosong pi kasi sang pamarenta apa yang pamarenta pung hak. Deng kasi sang Tuhan Allah apa yang Tuhan Allah pung hak.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Naa! If it's like that, you-pl go give to the govt what the govt has rights.to. And give to God what God has rights to.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dengar Dia manyao bagitu, ju dong samua taheran-heran, ko Dia bilang batúl na. Andia ko dong sonde bisa hiki ame sang Dia.<bt>Hearing Him answer like that, they were all amazed, for He had obviously answered correctly [+emphatic]. That is why they could not (successfully-svc) trap Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">So'al orang mati idop kambali, deng orang bakawin di sorga, ko sonde?<bt>The issue of dead people living again, and people marrying in heaven, or not?</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 22:23-33; Lukas 20:27-40)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ada satu partei agama laen, yang orang subu bilang, partei Saduki. Dong ajar bilang, orang mati sonde bisa idop kambali. Satu kali, ada barapa orang Saduki ju datang mau hiki sang Yesus. Dong omong deng Yesus bilang,<bt>There was another religious party, which people called the Saduki party. They taught that dead people cannot live again. One time, there were several Saduki people who came to trap Yesus. They spoke with Yesus saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis itu, ada barapa orang dari"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Abis itu, ada barapa orang dari partei laen ju datang mau hiki sang Yesus. (Dong ini dari partei Saduki yang ajar bilang orang mati sonde bisa idop kambali).</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-07-18 01:22:47Z">Dong omong deng Yesus bilang,</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 23:8</note><v n="19" />&lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Ba'i Musa ada tulis kasi sang kotong, ini adat bilang: kalo ada satu laki-laki mati kasi tenga dia pung bini, ma sonde ada ana, na, itu laki-laki pung adi musti kawin ame itu janda, ko biar kasi turunan sang dia pung kaka yang su mati tu.<bt>&lt;&lt;Father Teacher! Forefather Musa wrote for us-inc, this custom/tradition saying: if/when a male dies leaving behind his wife, but there is no child, na, that male's younger sibling must marry that widow, so that there be descendants for that elder sibling of his who died. [EXEG: in Gk, quote margin is in vs. 18.]</bt><note reference="12:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 25:5</note><v n="20" />Memang Musa ajar bagitu. Ma botong ada mau tanya bagini: ada tuju laki-laki basodara. Yang partama kawin lebe dolo. Ais dia mati, deng sonde ada ana.<bt>Musa actually did teach like that. But we-exc want to ask like this: there are seven male siblings. The first1 marries first2. Then he dies, and has no child.</bt><v n="21" />Ju dia pung adi yang iko sang dia, kawin bale itu janda. Sonde lama dia ju mati, deng sonde ada ana. Bagitu ju deng adi yang nomer tiga. Dia kawin deng itu janda, ma dia mati, ju sonde ada ana.<bt>Then his younger sibling that follows him, marries that widow. Not long/soon he also dies, having no child. Like that also with younger sibling number three. He marries that widow, but he dies, and has no child.</bt><v n="22" />Bagitu tarús-tarús sampe adi bungsu ju mati. Ais ju itu janda mati.<bt>Like that continuing-continuing until younger sibling youngest child also dies. And then that widow dies.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Naa! Sakarang botong mau tanya bagini: itu parampuan su parná kawin deng tuju laki-laki! Ma kalo dunya kiamat ko Tuhan kasi idop kambali orang mati dong, nanti itu parampuan jadi sapa pung bini dari itu tuju orang?&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [+shift to summary/conclusion]! Now we want to ask like this: that woman has already been married with 7 males! But at the end of the world when the Lord makes alive again dead people, that woman will be whose wife from those 7 people?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ais Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bosong batanya bagitu, dia pung arti, bosong sonde mangarti batúl Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi pung isi. Deng bosong ju sonde mangarti Tuhan Allah pung kuasa. Jadi bosong ni su sala batúl!<bt>Then Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;If you-pl ask like that, it means you do not truly understand the contents of God's Holy/Clean Writings. And you also do not understand God's power/authority. So (consequently) you here are really wrong!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Bosong kaliru mo mati!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">"Bosong kaliru mo mati!</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Dengar, é! Bagini: di sorga, sonde ada yang kawin. Samua orang mati yang Tuhan kasi idop kambali, sonde ada yang kawin lai. Bagitu ju Tuhan Allah pung ana bua di sorga sonde kawin.<bt>Listen, é! It's like this: in heaven, there is no-one that marry. All dead people whom the Lord makes alive again, there is no-one that marries again/anymore. It's like that also for *angels (God's underlings in heaven) don't marry.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="malinkan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">malinkan</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dong sonde mungkin kawin ulang lai,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">dong sonde mungkin kawin ulang lai, malinkan dong dong samua</Message></Annotation><v n="26" />Ais, Beta ju kasi tau so'al orang mati dong idop kambali, ko sonde. Ba'i Musa tulis so'al pohon kici yang tabakar ma sonde angus tu. Bosong inga itu carita, ko sonde? Waktu api manyala di itu pohon, Tuhan Allah kasi tau sang Musa bilang, &lt;Beta ni, lu pung ba'i-ba'i dong pung Tuhan Allah. Andia ba'i Abraham, ba'i Isak, deng ba'i Yakob. Dong samua sémba tarús sang Beta sampe sakarang.&gt;<bt>Then I'll tell/explain to you the problem of dead people living again, or not. Forefather Musa wrote about that small tree/bush that burned2 (with fire) but didn't burn2 up. Do you remember that story, or not? When the fire was flaming/shining in that plant, God told Musa saying, &lt;I here am your-sg the God of your forefathers. That is forefather Abraham, forefather Isak, and forefather Yakob. They all continually worship Me until now.&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Mangkali bosong balóm mangarti carita pohon"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Mangkali bosong balóm mangarti carita pohon kici yang tabakar ma sonde angus tu, di ba'i Musa pung tulisan. Itu carita bilang, Tuhan Allah kasi tau sang Musa bilang, &lt;Beta ni lu pung ba'i-ba'i dong pung Tuhan Allah. Andia Ba'i Abraham, Ba'i Isak, deng Ba'i Yakob. Dong samua sémba tarús sang Beta sampe sakarang.&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 3:6</note><v n="27" />Naa! Kotong tau bilang, itu ba'i-ba'i dong su lama mati. Ma tagal Tuhan Allah su bilang Dia masi jadi dong pung Tuhan, andia ko kotong tau bilang, dong su idop kambali. Jadi biar orang su mati, ju dong idop kambali. Memang orang idop yang sémba sang Tuhan Allah, bukan orang mati, to? Jadi kalo bosong pegang tarús itu ajaran bilang, orang mati sonde idop kambali, bosong memang su talalu sala tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa [+shift]! We-inc know that those forefathers were already long dead. But because God had already said He still is their Lord/God2, that is why we know that they are alive again. So (consequently), even if people have died, they live again. Actually it's living people that worship God, not dead people, to [+tag, expecting confirmation]? So (consequently) if you keep holding that teaching saying, dead people don't live again, you really are extremely wrong!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Sayang sang Tuhan deng sayang sang orang<bt>Love the Lord and love people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 22:34-40; Lukas 10:25-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Itu waktu, ada satu guru agama yang iko dengar Yesus dudu ba'omong deng orang dari partei Saduki dong. Itu guru agama pikir bilang, Yesus su manyao dong pung so'al tu deng bae. Ais dia tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Beta mau tanya bagini: kotong pung adat pung atoran, deng agama pung parenta dong, talalu banya. Dari samua parenta yang datang dari ba'i Musa, yang mana yang paling pantíng?&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, there was a religion teacher who participated hearing Yesus sit talking with the people from the Saduki party. That religion teacher thought that Yesus had answered their problem well. Then he asked Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Father! I want to ask like this: our-inc customary law rules, and religion's commands, are very many. From all the commands that come from forefather Musa, which is/are the most important?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01744b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;textWrapping:none" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Parenta yang paling pantíng dalam Tuhan pung Tulisan Barisi tu, bilang bagini:<bt>Yesus answered/responded saying, &lt;&lt;The command that is the most important in God's Scriptures, says like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Samua orang di Isra'el! Bosong dengar bae-bae!<bt>&lt;All people in Israel! You-pl listen carefully!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">Tuhan Allah tu, memang kotong pung Tuhan,<bt>The Lord God1, is truly our-inc Lord/God2,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng yang hak parenta sang kotong!<bt>and the one who has the say-so/ordering rights over us-inc!</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Sonde ada yang laen lai, cuma Dia sandiri sa!<bt>There is none other, only just He himself!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Parenta yang pertama,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Parenta yang pertama, dia pung bunyi bilang, &lt;&lt;Hei orang Isra'el samua! Dengar! Kotong pung Tuhan Allah itu Tuhan yang esa.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="30" />Jadi bosong musti sayang sang Dia <span class="Italic">lebe</span> dari samua.<bt>So (consequently) you-pl must love Him <span class="Italic">more</span> than all/everything.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">Tagal itu, bosong musti salalu rindu sang Dia,<bt>Because of that, you must always yearn affectionately for Him,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rindu = love, perhaps implies physical"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">rindu = love, perhaps implies physical separation, but also implies a strong existing relationship that yearns.affectionately, always mindful</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">mangarti sang Dia,<bt>understand/know Him,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng karjá karás ko iko Dia pung mau.&gt;<bt>and work hard to follow/obey His will.&gt; [EXEG: Don't force the 4 Gk/Hebrew categories into local RL worldview. Here we have 1) broad all-encompassing umbrella; followed by more specific 2) feelings, 3) mind, 4) effort. We have repeatedly tested the TB rendering to be incomprehensible to seminary trained Indonesians. This has been tested as much more transparent, insightful, and thought provoking. The point of the Gk/Heb categories is “all aspects of your being”.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong musti cinta sang Tuhan Allah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Bosong musti cinta sang Tuhan Allah deng sepenu hati, deng bosong pung jiwa, deng bosong pung pintar deng bosong pung kekuatan.&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:29-30" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 6:4-5</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Deng parenta yang kadua bilang bagini:<bt>And the second command says like this:</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Lu musti sayang orang laen dong, sama ke lu sayang lu pung diri sandiri.&gt;<bt>&lt;You-sg must love other people, like you love your very own self.&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ov = sayang lu pung diri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">ov = sayang lu pung diri badan (Sabu group)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Parenta kedua: 'Cinta manusia laen dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Parenta kedua: 'Cinta manusia laen dong sama ke lu cinta lu pung diri sandiri.&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ini dua parenta yang paling pantíng. Sonde ada parenta laen lai yang lebe pantíng dari ini dua parenta.&gt;&gt;<bt>These are the two commands which are the most important. There are no other commands which are more important that these two commands.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="12:31" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 19:18</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ais, itu guru agama omong lai sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang! Yang Papa bilang tu, batúl. Tuhan Allah yang hak parenta sang kotong, deng sonde ada Tuhan laen lai.<bt>Then that religion teacher spoke again to Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;True! That which Father has said is correct. God is the one with say-so/ordering rights over us-inc, and there is no other Lord/God2.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais itu guru agama bilang lai"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Ais itu guru agama bilang lai sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Papa manyao batúl ó! Memang yang Papa bilang itu batúl: Tuhan itu Allah yang esa, deng sonde ada Allah laen lai.</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 4:35</note><v n="33" />Kotong musti sayang sang Dia lebe dari samua, sampe kotong salalu rindu sang Dia, mangarti sang Dia, deng karjá karás ko iko Dia pung mau. Deng kotong ju musti sayang orang laen, sama ke kotong sayang kotong pung diri badan. Itu, Tuhan lebe sanáng, daripada kotong cuma iko atoran agama sa. Itu lebe bae daripada kalo kotong cuma bakar binatang korban, ko, kasi barang laen sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>We-inc must love Him more than all/everything, to the point that we-inc always desire/yearn for Him, understand/know him, and work hard to follow/obey His will. And we must love other people, like we love our own body. That, the Lord loves more, than if we only just follow religious regulations. That is better than if we just burn animal sacrifices or, give other things to Him.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dan manusia musti cinta sang Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Dan manusia musti cinta sang Tuhan deng dia pung hati samua, deng dia pung kepintaran samua, deng dia pung kuat samua. Deng dia musti cinta sang manusia laen dong sama ke dia cinta dia pung diri sandiri. Itu lebe bae dari pi bawa persembahan korban yang bakar di atas mesba, deng korban-korban macam-macam laen dong kasi sang Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:33" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Hosea 6:6</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Dengar dia manyao bagitu, ju Yesus pikir bilang, itu guru agama su mangarti deng bae. Ais Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu su amper jadi Tuhan Allah pung orang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing him answer like that, Yesus thought that that religion teacher understood well. So Yesus said, &lt;&lt;You-sg have almost/nearly become God's person.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus pikir, bilang, itu guru agama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Yesus pikir, bilang, itu guru agama su manyao deng bae batúl. Ju Yesus bilang sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu su amper jadi Yuhan Allah pung anggota jemaat.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais itu, sonde ada orang laen lai yang barani baso'al deng Yesus, ko sonde ada orang yang ontong sang Dia na.<bt>After that, there were no other people who dared take issue/debate with Yesus, because there was no person who could conquer/beat/overcome Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis itu, dari orang laen dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Abis itu, dari orang laen dong di Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat itu, dong lia bilang sonde ada yang dapa ontong sang Yesus. Jadi sonde ada lai satu orang yang barani baso'al deng Yesus lai. Abis itu, samua ju su sonde ada lai satu orang yang barani baso'al deng Yesus.<span class="Italic">(34)</span></Message></Annotation><note reference="12:28-34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 10:25-28</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Kristus itu, memang raja Daud pung turunan, ma Dia ju jadi raja Daud pung Bos<bt>That Kristus, is truly king Daud's descendant, but He is also king Daud's Bos/master</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 22:41-46; Lukas 20:41-44)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ais itu, Yesus masi ajar orang di Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Ju Dia so'al sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Iko bosong pung pikiran, karmana? Guru agama dong ajar so'al Kristus tu, yang Tuhan Allah su tunju dari dolu-kala. Iko dong, Dia cuma jadi raja Daud pung turunan sa. Ma itu sonde batúl.<bt>After that, Yesus still taught people at the *Temple. Then he took issue/debated with them saying, &lt;&lt;According to your-pl thinking, how is it? The religion teachers teach about Kristus, whom God has designated from long ago. According to them, He is only just king Daud's descendant. But that is not true.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dolu-kala emphasizes the temporal distance more"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">dolu-kala emphasizes the temporal distance more unambiguously than dolu-dolu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu Dia ada ajar jemaat dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Waktu Dia ada ajar jemaat dong di Bait Allah, Yesus angka soal bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana ko guru-guru agama dong ajar bilang Juruslamat itu Daud pung turunan?</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Tagal dolu Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi su pake Daud ko tulis bilang,<bt>Because long ago God's *Holy Spirit used Daud to write saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Padahal Daud sandiri - iko Tuhan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Padahal Daud sandiri - iko Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi pung kasi tau sang dia -, omong, bilang,</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Tuhan Allah su kasi tau sang beta pung bos bilang,<bt>&lt;God1 has told my bos saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="'Tuhan Allah kasi tau sang beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">'Tuhan Allah kasi tau sang beta pung Tuhan:</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">&lt;&lt;Mari ko dudu di ini tampa terhormat di Beta pung sablá kanan.<bt>&lt;&lt;Come to sit in this most honoured place at my right hand.</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 3" usfm="q3">Nanti Beta bekin sang lu pung musu dong, sampe dong ta'alok sang lu.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>I will make your enemies, to the point that they bow/surrender to you.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="&quot;Dudu di Beta pung sablá kanan,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">"Dudu di Beta pung sablá kanan, sampe Beta bekin pata Lu pung musu-musu dong samua ko dong tondo taalok sang Lu.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bow heads + under feet ;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">bow heads + under feet ; bekin pata = ancor dong pung kekuatan; tondo ta'alok = takhluk, menyerah, kalah (Ena knows, Ina doesn't)</Message></Annotation><note reference="12:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 110:1</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37a" />Dari itu kotong dapa tau bilang, raja Daud sandiri pange sang Kristus tu bilang, &lt;Bos&gt;. Dia pung arti, kalo orang bilang Kristus tu, cuma raja Daud pung turunan sa, itu balóm cukup! Tagal Dia ju jadi raja Daud pung Bos yang hak parenta sang dia na!&gt;&gt;<bt>From that we-inc know that king Daud himself called Kristus, saying &lt;Bos&gt;. That means if people say that Kristus is only just king Daud's descendant, that is not enough! Because He is also king Daud's Bos who has the say-so/ordering rights over him [+obvious]!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi kalo Daud pange sang Juruslamat"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Jadi kalo Daud pange sang Juruslamat bilang 'Tuhan", na karmana ko dia itu Daud pung turunan?&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus bilang ati-ati deng guru agama dong pung putar-balek<bt>Lord Yesus says be careful with the religion teachers' deception/deviousness</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 23:1-36; Lukas 20:45-47)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37b" />Waktu Yesus omong bagitu tadi, ju orang banya dong talalu suka dengar sang Dia.<bt>When Yesus spoke like he just did, many people liked very much to hear Him.</bt><v n="38" />Ais Dia kasi tau lai sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong musti ati-ati deng guru agama dong. Dong suka pasiar pake dong pung baju panjang raroso pi katumu banya orang, ko biar orang lia sang dong bilang, &lt;We! Dong tu, orang bésar, ó!&gt;<bt>Then He told/explained further/again to them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl must be careful with religion teachers. They like to strut around [public places outside the home] wearing their long robes that drag on the ground to go meet many people, so that people will see them saying, &lt;We [+attention]! Those ones there are really big/important people, ó!&gt; [NOTE: the longer the robe = the higher the social status.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="raroso = till drags on the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">raroso = till drags on the ground (simbol sombong, kemewahan); opposite of wearing short to work</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia omong kasi sang dong bilang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Dia omong kasi sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong musti hati-hati deng guru-guru agama dong. Dong suka bajalan pake juba pajang raroso di jalan deng dong suka orang dong hormat sang dong di pasar-pasar.</Message></Annotation><v n="39" />Kalo dong maso pi ruma sambayang, ko, dong iko pesta, dong salalu cari tampa dudu yang paling bagus, ko biar banya orang lia sang dong.<bt>If/when they enter a worship house, or they attend a party/feast, they always seek the best sitting place, so that many people will see them.</bt><v n="40" />Ma ati-ati, ó! Te dong ju maen putar-balek sang janda dong, ko rampas ame dong pung ruma samua. Ma di muka banya orang, dong tutu dong pung jahat tu, deng badiri sambayang lama-lama. Dong mau ko orang bilang dong pung hati barisi. Ma nanti Tuhan Allah kasi hukum paling barát sang dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>But be careful, ó! Cuz they perpetually lie to/deceive widows, to steal/rob all their houses. But in front of many people, they cover that evil of theirs, and stand praying a long time. They want for people to say they have clean/holy livers. But later God will give very heavy/severe punishment to them.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="duda = male janda; ati-ati"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">duda = male janda; ati-ati</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Janda kasian kasi maso doi kolekte yang paling bésar<bt>A pitiful/poor widow puts in collection money that is the biggest</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 21:1-4)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ais itu, Yesus pi dudu bamangada deng peti derma di Tuhan pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Dia lia orang dong datang kasi maso dong pung doi kolekte pi dalam itu peti. Dia lia orang kaya dong ju datang kasi maso dong pung doi bam-banya di situ.<bt>After that, Yesus went to sit facing the collection box in the *Temple. He saw various people come put their collection money in that box. He saw rich people also come put large amounts of their money there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="peti derma = kolekte"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">peti derma = kolekte</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Ais ada satu janda kasian ju datang iko sambayang. Dia kasi maso doi dua sen di itu peti. Itu doi pung harga paling kici.<bt>Then there was a poor/pitiful widow also come to worship. She put 2 sen money/coin in that box. That money value is the very smallest.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doi rimis = setenga cen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">doi rimis = setenga cen</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Doi rimis itu doi satenga sen"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Doi rimis itu doi satenga sen rece yang dia pung harga paling kici.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Ais Yesus gape Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong lia bae-bae sang itu janda kasian tu. Dia kasi maso doi dua sen sa, ma dia su kasi lebe dari samua orang.<bt>Then Yesus hand motioned to summon His disciples saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl look carefully at that poor/pitiful widow there. She has only put in 2 sen money, but she has given more than everyone.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="gape = hand-motion to come"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">gape = hand-motion to come</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus gape Dia pung ana murid"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Yesus gape Dia pung ana murid dong abis kusu-kusu deng dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong perhatikan bae-bae. Ini janda miskin ini, su kasi maso pi dalam itu peti lebe banya dari orang-orang laen dong pung kolekte samua.</Message></Annotation><v n="44" />Itu orang laen dong samua kasi maso kolekte dari dong pung doi sisa. Ma ini janda ni, dia su kasi abis dia pung doi samua sang Tuhan Allah.&gt;&gt;<bt>All those other people put in collection from their extra/leftover money. But this widow here, she has given away all her money to God.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="doi rece ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">doi rece =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma ini janda, dia su kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Ma ini janda, dia su kasi samua yang dia punya, padahal dia parlú itu doi rece buat dia pung idop hari-hari.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau memang, Ruma Sambayang Pusat pung rubu<bt>Lord Yesus *prophesies (tells beforehand), the *Temple's destruction</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:1-2; Lukas 21:5-6)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="13" />
      <v n="1" />Ais itu, Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dong mau pi kasi tenga Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Waktu dong kaluar, Dia pung ana bua satu kasi tunju itu Ruma Sambayang, ju bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa, é! Coba Papa lia ini dolo! Ini Ruma pung bagus lai! Dong susun dia pung batu bésar dong talalu bagus, é!&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus and His *disciples were about to leave the *Temple. While they were exiting, one of His disciples pointed to that Worship House, and said, &lt;&lt;Father, é! Have a look at this [+idiomatic]! They really stacked/arranged these rocks together really well/beautifully!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu Yesus kaluar dari Bait Allah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Waktu Yesus kaluar dari Bait Allah ju Dia pung ana murid satu omong, bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru! Coba buang mata pi di Yerusalem pung bangunan dong. Coba lia dia pung batu-batu dong. Pung bagus bukan maen.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="2" />Ma Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini Ruma memang bagus! Ma sonde lama lai, te dong kasi rubu abis ini batu-batu samua.&gt;&gt;<bt>But Yesus answered/responded saying, &lt;&lt;This House is truly nice/beautiful! But not much longer/soon, they will completely knock down all these stones.&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: non-referential ‘they’.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Hari kiamat pung tanda-tanda<bt>Signs of the final day/s /end times</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:3-14; Lukas 21:7-19)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ais ju Yesus dong pi gunung Saitun, ko dudu di tampa yang bamangada deng Ruma Sambayang Pusat. Ais Dia pung ana bua ampa orang datang ko dong ba'omong sandiri deng Dia. Andia Petrus, Yakobis, Yohanis, deng Anderias.<bt>Then Yesus (collective) went to Saitun mountain, to sit at a place that faced the *Temple. Then four of His *disciples came to talk alone with Him. That is, Petrus, Yakobis, Yohanis, and Anderias.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangada = face"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">mangada = face</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis ju Yesus pi di Bukit"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Abis ju Yesus pi di Bukit Zaitun ko dudu di situ, di tampa yang baku mangada deng Bait Allah. Ju Petrus, Yakobis, Yohanis deng Andreas datang ba'omong pribadi deng Dia.</Message></Annotation><v n="4" />Dong tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Coba kasi tau ulang Papa pung omong tadi tu. Kapan tempo datang dia pung waktu tu? Deng dia pung tanda-tanda tu, karmana?&gt;&gt;<bt>They asked saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Please explain again what you were talking about earlier. When will its time come? And its signs, how will they be?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ais Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Asal bosong jaga bae-bae, ó! Ko bosong jang kaná tipu.<bt>Then Yesus answered saying, &lt;&lt;As long as/the important thing is you-pl watch out/guard carefully, ó! So that you don't get decieved.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Asal bosong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Ju Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Asal bosong buka bosong pung mata lebar-lebar, ko bosong jang kaná tipu.</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Te nanti ada macam-macam orang yang datang puku dada bilang, &lt;Beta ni, Kristus, andia Orang yang Tuhan Allah su janji memang dari dolu&gt;. Ais dong ju tipu banya orang.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) later there will be all sorts of people who come hitting their chests saying, &lt;I here am Kristus, that is the Person who God promised beforehand from long ago.&gt; So/then they will deceive many people.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nanti banya orang datang bawa-bawa Beta"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Nanti banya orang datang bawa-bawa Beta pung nama ko omong, bilang, &lt;Beta ni dia ini!&gt; abis dong tipu banya orang.</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Kalo bosong lia orang baparáng, ko, bosong dengar isu bilang, ada paráng di mana-mana, na, bosong sonde usa taku. Te macam bagitu tu musti jadi dolo, ma hari kiamat balóm sampe.<bt>If/when you see people warring, or you hear rumours saying, there is war all over the place/in many places, na, you-pl don't need to be afraid. Cuz (elaboration) various things like that have to happen first, but the final day/s have not yet arrived.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalo bosong dengar bunyi orang dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">kalo bosong dengar bunyi orang dong baku tempur deng dengar kabar-kabar prang di mana-mana, bosong sonde usa taku. Itu samua musti jadi ma bukan berarti kiamat su mau datang.</Message></Annotation><v n="8" />Nanti satu suku baparáng lawan laen suku. Satu negara baparáng lawan laen negara. Ada tana goyang di mana-mana. Musim lapar dong ju hebat mati pung! Ini samua jadi tanda-tanda, sama ke parampuan yang baru mulai saki mau barana.<bt>Later one tribe/clan will war against another tribe/clan. One nation will war against another nation. There will be earthquakes all over the place. And hunger seasons are extremely severe! These all are signs, like a woman who just begins to be in pain about to give birth.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu samua baru dia pung ujung-ujung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Itu samua baru dia pung ujung-ujung sa, sama ke parampuan yang saki mau barana.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Jadi bosong musti jaga bae-bae, é! Te nanti dong datang tangkap sang bosong ko hela bawa pi pangadilan agama. Deng dong papoko sang bosong dalam ruma sambayang dong. Dong ika bawa sang bosong pi orang yang pegang kuasa, tagal bosong iko sang Beta. Ma itu ju jadi salák ko bosong kasi tau sang dong so'al Beta.<bt>So (consequently) you must guard/watch out carefully, é! Cuz (elaboration) later they will come catch/capture/arrest you to drag take you to the religious court. And they will beat (repeatedly) you in various worship houses. And they will tie carry you to people who hold authority, because you follow/obey Me. But that also becomes space/time/opportunity for you to tell them about Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="papoko = rufuk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">papoko = rufuk</Message></Annotation><v n="10" />Te Tuhan pung orang musti pi kasi tau lebe dolo Beta pung Carita Bae sang samua suku di ini dunya, baru hari kiamat sampe.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) God2's/Lord's people must first tell My *Good Story to all tribes in this world, only then will the final day arrive.</bt><v n="11" />Inga, ó! Kalo dong ika bawa sang bosong pi pangadilan, bosong sonde usa taku bilang, &lt;Nanti beta mau ba'omong bilang apa? Ko, beta manyao bilang apa?&gt; Kalo dia pung waktu su sampe bagitu, bosong omong iko sa, apa yang Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi kasi tau sang bosong.<bt>Remember, ó! If they tie carry you to court, you don't need to be afraid saying, &lt;What will I say? Or what will I answer?&gt; If/when that time has arrived, you just talk according to what God's *Holy Spirit tells you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Apa yang bosong omong, itu bukan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Apa yang bosong omong, itu bukan bosong png bahasa sandiri, tapi Tuhan Allah pung Roh yang Barisi pung omongan.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:9-11" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:17-20, Lukas 12:11-12</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Dalam satu ruma, kalo ada orang yang parcaya sang Beta, nanti dia pung sodara sandiri cari jalan ko bunu sang dia. Ais kalo ana yang parcaya, nanti dia pung papa sandiri bunu sang dia. Ju kalo ada mama deng papa yang parcaya sang Beta, nanti dong pung ana sandiri yang bunu sang dong.<bt>In one house, if there is a person who believes in Me, his own siblings will seek/look for a way to kill him. Then if it's a child who believes, his own father will kill him. And if there is a father and mother who believe, his own child/ren will kill him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang dong nanti beki kianat sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Orang dong nanti beki kianat sang dong pung sudara sandiri ko biar dong bunu mati sang dia. Nati yang bagitu ju jadi deng papa deng dia ping ana sandiri. Ana-ana dong nanti jadi kapala batu ko lawan dong pung papa deng mama, abis dong pi sarahkan sang dong ko biar bunu bekin mati sang dong</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Jadi nanti orang dong binci mati sang bosong, tagal bosong parcaya sang Beta. Ma sapa yang batahan sampe abis, pasti Tuhan Allah kasi salamat sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) later people will (strongly) hate you, because you believe in Me. But whoever endures to the end, surely God will give salvation to him.&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="13:13" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 10:22</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Bajaga bae-bae, te hari kiamat su mau deka! [\s2]<bt>Watch carefully, cuz the final day is near! [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:15-28; Lukas 21:20-24)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Yesus omong tarús bilang, &lt;&lt;Satu orang yang jahat mati pung nanti datang. Dia maso pi badiri di tampa pamali di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat yang sonde pantas buat dia, sampe dia bekin noju itu tampa. Andia ko Tuhan Allah bale balakang kasi tenga itu tampa. Kalo bosong su lia bagitu, ati-ati, ó! (Sapa yang baca ni, ju musti ati-ati!) Itu jadi tanda bilang, hari-hari susa su sampe di muka pintu. Kalo su lia bagitu, orang di propinsi Yudea bangun lari pi gunung suda.<bt>Yesus continued talking saying, &lt;&lt;An extremely evil person will come. He will enter go stand in the place that is taboo/sacred in God's *Temple, which is not appropriate for him, to the point that he makes that place repulsive/defiled. That is why God will turn his back leaving/abandoning that place. If/when you see like that, be careful, ó! (Whoever reads this, must also be careful!) That is a sign that difficult days are just in front of the door. If/when you see like that, people in Yudea province get up and run to the mountains (imperative).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pamali = karamat, orang sonde bole"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">pamali = karamat, orang sonde bole pigi; noju = kotor (ritually), defiled</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:14" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 9:27, 11:31, 12:11</note><v n="15" />Deng musti lari capát-capát, ko biar jang calaka. Kalo ada yang su kaluar dari ruma, jang pulang pi ame barang lai.<bt>And they must run fast, so that they don't be overcome by misfortune. If there is any who have already come out/left their house, don't return home to get any more things.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang yang ada di atas atap"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Orang yang ada di atas atap ruma jang turun deng jang maso pi dalam ruma ko mau ame barang.</Message></Annotation><v n="16" />Ju orang yang ada di kabón, jang kambali ko ame kaen panas lai. Ma lari tarús sa!<bt>And people who are in the gardens/fields, don't return again to get blankets. But just keep on running!</bt><note reference="13:15-16" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 17:31</note><v n="17" />Yang paling kasian, parampuan yang ada dudu parú, deng mama-mama yang ada kasi susu ana mera. Ko dong sonde bisa lari capát na.<bt>The most pitiful people are woman who are pregnant and mothers who are nursing newborns. For they obviously can't run fast.</bt><v n="18" />Jadi lebe bae bosong sambayang ko minta hal jahat tu jang jato pas deng musim ujan.<bt>So (consequently) it's better that you-pl pray to request that those evil things don't happen in/during the rainy season. [EXEG: functional substitute for winter.]</bt><v n="19" />Te itu hari talalu susa mau mati! Mulai dari Tuhan Allah bekin ini dunya sampe sakarang, orang balóm parná lia susa bésar macam ke bagitu. Deng nanti orang ju sonde lia ulang susa macam bagitu lai.<bt>Cuz (elaboration) those days will be very extremely difficult. Starting from God made this world until now, people (generic) have never yet seen difficulty as big/severe as that. And later/future people will also never again see difficulty of that type.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu hari-hari yang bekin ngeri itu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Itu hari-hari yang bekin ngeri itu nanti bawa datang susa duka yang bésar mo mati, yang balum pernah jadi, mulai dari Tuhan Allah bekin ini dunya sampe sakarang, deng itu kejadian nanti sonde pernah jadi ulang lai.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 12:1, Dunya Model Baru 7:14</note><v n="20" />Kalo Tuhan sonde kasi pende itu hari, nanti sonde ada satu orang ju yang bisa batahan idop. Ma tagal Tuhan Allah sayang Dia pung orang yang Dia su pili dong, andia ko Dia kasi pende itu hari-hari susa dong.<bt>If the God2/Lord does not shorten those days, there will not be a single person who can endure living. But because God loves His people whom He chose, that is why He shortens those days of difficulty.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Andekata Tuhan Allah sonde bekin pende"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Andekata Tuhan Allah sonde bekin pende dia pung waktu, nanti sonde ada satu orang lai yang bisa salamat. Ma Tuhan ingat Dia pung jemaat, jadi Dia bekin pende dia pung hari.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Nanti kalo itu hari su sampe, bosong dengar orang dong bilang, &lt;Lia dolo! Kristus ada di sini!&gt; Ma orang laen bilang, &lt;Kristus ada di sana!&gt; Ma bosong jang dengar, é!<bt>Later if/when those days arrive, you-pl will hear people say, &lt;Look! Kristus is here!&gt; But other people say, &lt;Kristus is there!&gt; But don't you-pl listen, é!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu waktu kalo bosong dengar ada"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Itu waktu kalo bosong dengar ada orang yang bilang sang bosong, bilang: "Mari te Juruslamat ada di sini!&gt; atau 'Lia te Dia ada di situ!&gt; - bosong jang parcaya.</Message></Annotation><v n="22" />Te nanti ada orang kaluar ko puku dada bilang, &lt;Beta ni, Kristus!&gt; Yang laen lai bilang, &lt;Beta ni, Tuhan Allah pung jubir.&gt; Nanti dong bekin tanda heran macam-macam pake setan pung kuasa ko putar-balek orang. Dong coba-coba ko Tuhan Allah pung orang dong ju kaná tipu!<bt>Cuz (elaboration) there will be people coming out beating their chests saying, &lt;I here, Kristus!&gt; Another will say, &lt;I here, God's *prophet (spokesperson).&gt; Later they will do all sorts of *miracles using the power of evil spirits to deceive people. They try their best so that God's people will also get deceived!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sebab juruslamat-juruslamat palsu deng nabi-nabi palsu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Sebab juruslamat-juruslamat palsu deng nabi-nabi palsu dong su muncul datang itu. Nanti dong bekin mujizat macam-macam deng tanda-tanda ajaibrupa-rupa ko tipudaya orang-orang dong samua, termasok Tuhan Allah pung jemaat dong juga.</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Ma bosong musti jaga bae-bae, é! Itu hari-hari susa dong balóm sampe, ma Beta su kasi inga memang sang bosong, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>But you must guard/watch carefully! Those difficult days have not yet arrived, but I have reminded you about them beforehand.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Manusia Tulen pung datang [\s2]<bt>The coming of the Ideal/Prototype Human [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:29-31; Lukas 21:25-28)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="24" />Ais Yesus sambung lai ko kasi tau Dia pung ana bua dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo itu hari-hari susa dong su abis,<bt>Then Yesus continued on to explain to His *disciples saying, &lt;&lt;If/when those difficult days are over,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Nanti matahari jadi galáp,<bt>The sun will become dark,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">bulan ju su sonde taráng lai.<bt>the moon also will no longer shine.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis itu susa duka yang bésar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Abis itu susa duka yang bésar pung hari dong, nanti matahari jadi glap deng bulan ju sonde ada pung sinar lai.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 13:10, Yeskial 32:7, Yoel 2:10, 31, 3:15, Dunya Model Baru 6:12</note></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">
      <v n="25" />Bintang-bintang bajato dari langit,<bt>Stars will be falling from the sky,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">deng kuasa di langit dong jadi harba-biruk.&gt;<bt>and powers in the sky will become chaotic.&gt; [CHECK: what would be some examples be of &lt;powers in the sky&gt;?]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="harba-biruk = kaco-balo (BI = haru-biru)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">harba-biruk = kaco-balo (BI = haru-biru) = kocar-kacir = tagoyang pi datang</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bintang-bintang dong bajato dari langit, deng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Bintang-bintang dong bajato dari langit, deng yang pegang samua kuasa di langit dong samua mulai jadi kaco balo. // Deng samua kuasa di langit jadi harba-biruk.&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:25" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 34:4, Yoel 2:10, Dunya Model Baru 6:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ais itu, baru samua orang dapa lia sang Beta, Manusia Tulen ni. Nanti Beta datang di awan dari langit. Deng samua orang dapa lia Beta pung kuasa, deng Beta pung hebat samua!<bt>After that, only then will all people see Me, this Ideal/Prototype Human. I will come in cloud from the sky. And all people will see My power and all My amazingness! [EXEG: Gk ‘glory’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu waktu nanti ana Manusia muncul"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Itu waktu nanti ana Manusia muncul datang tabungkus deng awan, deng pegang bawa Dia pung kuasa bésar, langkáp deng dia pung tanda-tanda kebesaran samua.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:26" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:13, Dunya Model Baru 1:7</note><v n="27" />Ais Beta parenta Tuhan Allah pung ana bua di sorga, ko pi kumpul samua orang yang Beta su pili dari dunya pung ujung-ujung, dari matahari nae sampe matahari turun; dari utara sampe salatan.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then I will order God's underlings in heaven (*angels), to go gather all the people that I have chosen from the ends of the earth, from east until west, from north until south.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Nanti Dia kirim malikat-malikat dong turun"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Nanti Dia kirim malikat-malikat dong turun datang ko kumpul ame Dia pung jemaat yang Dia su pili ame sang dong dari Timur deng Barat, dari utara deng Selatan, dari dunya pung ujung-ujung sampe di langit pung ujung-ujung.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Hari-hari susa jadi tanda Tuhan Yesus pung datang [\s2]<bt>The days of difficulty will be a sign of Lord Yesus' coming [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:32-35; Lukas 21:29-33)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Yesus sambung Dia pung omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta ame umpama dari pohon. Kalo dia pung daon mulai kuning, itu tanda bilang, musim panas su deka-deka datang.<bt>Yesus continued speaking saying, &lt;&lt;I take a parable/example from a tree. If/when its leaves begin turning yellow, that is sign says hot season is soon to come. [EXEG: functional local substitute. Gk is locked into the fig tree.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="umpama = contoh;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">umpama = contoh;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong ame ajaran dari pohon ara."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Bosong ame ajaran dari pohon ara. kalo dia pung cabang alus dong pung warna su ijo deng dia pung kayu su lembut, deng dia pung daon muda su mulai kaluar, bosong tau, bilang, musim panas su deka-deka datang.</Message></Annotation><v n="29" />Bagitu ju, kalo bosong su lia hari-hari susa datang, sama ke yang Beta su kasi tau tadi tu, itu tanda bilang, Beta su deka-deka datang.<bt>Like that also, if/when you-pl see the difficult days arrive, like what I just told you, that sign/s says that I am soon to come.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bagitu juga kalo bosong dapa lia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Bagitu juga kalo bosong dapa lia ame itu hal dong jadi, bosong tau memang bilang dia pung hari su talalu deka.</Message></Annotation><v n="30" />Sakarang dengar bae-bae! Dari samua orang yang idop sakarang ni, nanti ada yang balóm mati, te itu hari-hari susa dong su datang.<bt>Now listen carefully! From (among) all people who live now, later there are those who won't yet die, yet those difficult days will have arrived.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="comma after te OK by UNS's"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">comma after te OK by UNS's</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong tau memang! Itu peristiwa dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Bosong tau memang! Itu peristiwa dong nanti jadi dahulu dari orang-orang yang sakarang masi idop dong mati samua.</Message></Annotation><v n="31" />Biar langit deng bumi su ilang, ma Beta pung omong ni batahan sonde abis-abis.&gt;&gt;<bt>Even if/though the sky and earth disappear, nevertheless this talking/words of Mine will endure without ever finishing/ceasing.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Biar langit ilang pi parsetan, ma"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Biar langit ilang pi parsetan, ma Beta kung kata-kata ini laku sampe dunya kiamat.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus pung waktu datang tu, rahasia [\s2]<bt>The time of Lord Yesus' coming, is a secret [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 24:36-44)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Yesus omong tamba bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde ada satu orang yang tau kapan Beta pung hari deng jam datang kambali. Tuhan Allah pung ana bua di sorga, ju sonde tau. Beta sandiri, ju sonde tau. Cuma Beta pung Papa sa yang tau.<bt>Yesus added saying, &lt;&lt;There is not one person who knows when is My day and hour to come again. God's *angels also don't know. I myself, also don't know. Only just My Father is the one who knows.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Biar bagitu juga, sonde ada satu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Biar bagitu juga, sonde ada satu orang yang tau parsís dia hari deng dia pung jam. Sedang malikat-malikat di sorga dong ju sonde tau. Deng itu ana ju sonde tau juga. Kecuali Bapa sa yang tau.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:32" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 24:36</note><v n="33" />Tagal itu, bosong musti bajaga bae-bae, tagal bosong sonde tau kapan dia pung waktu.<bt>Because of that, you-pl must watch/guard carefully, because you do not know when it's time is.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Jadi bosong musti bajaga deng waspada,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Jadi bosong musti bajaga deng waspada, te bosong sonde tau dia pung waktu jato kaná kapan.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="34" />Sonde lama lai Beta su pi kasi tenga sang bosong, ma nanti Beta datang kambali. Sama ke tuan ruma yang jalan kasi tenga dia pung ruma ko pi tampa jao. Dia suru dia pung ana bua dong ko urus bae-bae itu ruma. Deng dia bagi kasi dong satu-satu deng dia pung karjá. Dia parenta tukang jaga pintu ko bajaga bae-bae, sampe dia pulang.<bt>Not much longer/soon I will leave you, but [+contrary to expectation] then I will come again. Just like a house owner/master [EXEG: Context: vs.35] who goes leaving his house to go to a far place. He tells his underlings to take good care of (managing) that house. And he divides work for each one of them. He orders the watcher-of-the-door to guard carefully, until he returns home.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia pung ibarat sama ke ada"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Dia pung ibarat sama ke ada orang yang jalan kasi tenga dia png ruma ko pi di satu tampa yang jao. Dia suru dia pung pelayan-pelayan dong ko urus dia pung ruma, deng bagi kasi sang dong satu-satu deng dia pung kerja. Dia kasi parenta sang tukang jaga pintu ko bajaga bae-bae.</Message></Annotation><note reference="13:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 12:36-38</note><v n="35" />Bosong ju musti bajaga siang-malam, tagal bosong sonde tau kapan tuan ruma pulang. Pulang sore ko, tenga malam ko, siang ko, waktu matahari nae ko. Bosong sonde tau kapan.<bt>You-pl also must watch/guard day-night (=constantly), because you do not know when the house owner returns home. (Whether he) returns home afternoon or, middle of the night or, noon or, when the sun is coming up or [Gram: open disjunction]. You-pl don't know when.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="open disjunction OK"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">open disjunction OK</Message></Annotation><v n="36" />Jang sampe dia datang takuju, te dapa bosong ada tidor masanggorok.<bt>Don't let it be that he comes unexpectedly, cuz/yet (elaboration) you are sleeping snoring.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="masanggorok = snoring; tidor malengga kea"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">masanggorok = snoring; tidor malengga kea = penyu (sleeping like an upside-down turtle)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Jadi apa yang Beta kasi tau sang bosong ni, Beta ju kasi tau samua orang laen bilang, &lt;Bosong musti bajaga bae-bae ko sambut Beta pung datang.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>So (consequently) what I am telling you here, I also tell to all other people saying, &lt;You-pl must watch/guard carefully to greet/celebrate My arrival.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">[Sampe di situ, Tuhan Yesus barenti ba'omong deng Dia pung ana bua dong di gunung Saitun.]<bt>[This is the end (to that point) Lord Yesus stopped talking with his *disciples on Saitun mountain.] [DISCOURSE: high level closure indicating major shift, engineered by consultant from UNS responses.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Orang bésar dong cari akal ko mau tangkap sang Tuhan Yesus deng diam-diam<bt>The big/important people make a plan to capture the Lord Yesus quietly</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:1-5; Lukas 22:1-2; Yohanis 11:45-53)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="14" />
      <v n="1-2" />Ais itu, kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos deng guru agama dong masi bacari akal ko mau tangkap sang Yesus deng diam-diam. Ko dong mau bunu sang Dia na. Ma dong ator siasat bilang, &lt;&lt;Tahan dolo! Kotong jang tangkap sang Dia capát-capát, tagal hari-hari bae su deka. Jang sampe orang banya dong nanti mangamok.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, the *chief priests and *religious teachers still were seeking together a plan to capture/arrest Yesus quietly. Their true purpose was so they could kill him [+idiomatic]. But they strategized/plotted saying, &lt;&lt;Wait! Let's not capture/arrest Him too quickly, because the holidays are near. Don't let it be that the crowds go berserk/riot.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="huru-hara = ribut; mangamok"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">huru-hara = ribut; mangamok</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong ba'omong bagitu, tagal masi dua hari lai, orang Yahudi dong pung hari-hari bae, yang dong kasi nama &lt;Hari Paska&gt; deng &lt;Pesta Roti Sonde Pake Ragi&gt;. Deng itu hari-hari bae, dong inga tempo dolu, waktu dong pung nene-moyang kaluar dari negrí Masir.<bt>They spoke like that to each other, because in two more days, the Yahudi people's holidays, which they called &lt;Paska Day&gt; and &lt;The Feast of Bread without Bread Seed/Yeast.&gt; With those holidays, they remembered the earlier times, when their ancestors left the country of Masir. [EXEG: implicit-explicit, background because of natural UNS questions. Without the background info, the readers were distracted with skewed focus.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mur = dregs of palmwine used"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">mur = dregs of palmwine used as leavening; bibit roti</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Hari Paskah deng Perayaan Roti Sonde"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Hari Paskah deng Perayaan Roti Sonde Pake Mur tenga dua hari lai. Imam-imam kapala deng guru-guru agama dong ada bacari akal karmana ko mau tangka sang Yesus diam-diam ko mau bunu bekin mayi sang Dia. Dong ba'omong, bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong jang tangkap sang Dia kaná deng hari raya te nanti orang dong bekin huru hara.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:1" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 12:1-27</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Parampuan po'a minya wangi yang mahal kasi sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>A women who poured expensive fragrant oil onto the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:6-13; Yohanis 12:1-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Di kampong Betania, ada satu orang nama Simon. Dolu orang noju sang dia, tagal dia kaná panyaki kusta. Ma sakarang dia su bae.<bt>In the village of Betania, there was a person named Simon. Before/previously people were grossed out/repulsed by/at him, because he had leprosy. But now he was healed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ais itu ju, waktu itu hari-hari bae balóm datang, Yesus dong ada pi makan di Simon pung ruma. Waktu dong makan, ada satu parampuan datang katumu sang Yesus. Dia ada pegang satu botol yang dong bekin dari batu. Dia pung isi, minya wangi asli yang mahal mati pung.<bt>And so after that, when those holidays had not yet come (=before they happened), Yesus (collective) went and ate at Simon's house. While they ate, a woman came to meet Yesus. She was holding a bottle which was made of stone (which they made: non-referential). Its contents were original/pure fragrant oil which was very expensive.</bt><note reference="14:3-5" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Itu minya wangi pung harga, sama ke satu tukang pung gaji satu taon. Alkitab Bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, itu minya pung harga 300 <span class="Italic">&lt;denari&gt;,</span> deng minya pung nama <span class="Italic">&lt;nardos&gt;,</span> yang dolu orang bekin dari akar wangi. Alkitab Bahasa Indonesia bilang &lt;narwastu&gt;. Deng itu botol, dong bekin dari batu yang orang bisa pahat. Itu botol pung harga ju mahal. Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, itu botol dong bekin dari batu yang dia pung nama <span class="Italic">&lt;alabastros&gt;</span>. Alkitab Bahasa Indonesia bilang itu batu pung nama &lt;batu pualam&gt;. Lia ju di Lukas 7:37-38.<bt>That fragrant oil's price, is equivalent to a craftsman's wage for one year. The Yunani language Bible says that oil's price is 300 <span class="Italic">&lt;denari</span>&gt;, and oil's name <span class="Italic">&lt;nardos</span>&gt;, which people used to make from fragrant roots. The Indonesian Bible says &lt;narwastu&gt;. And that bottle, they made from stone that could be carved. That bottle's price was also expensive. The Yunani language Bible says that bottle they made it out of a stone with its name <span class="Italic">&lt;alabastros</span>&gt;. The Indonesian Bible says that stone's name is &lt;batu pualam&gt;. Also see in Lukas 7:37-38.</bt></note>Ais, itu parampuan puku bekin pata itu botol pung tutu. Ju dia po'a kasi malele palán-palán itu minya di Yesus pung kapala, ko jadi tanda dia kasi hormat sang Yesus.<bt>Then that woman hit making broke that bottle's cover. And she poured letting drip slowly that oil on Yesus' head, to be a sign that she showed respect to Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="po'a = pour out ; bubu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">po'a = pour out ; bubu = pour into another container; tuang = pour slowly</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu Yesus ada di Betania, di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Waktu Yesus ada di Betania, di Simon yang dolu bapanyaki kusta pung ruma, ada satu parampuan datang katumu sang Dia. Itu parampuan ada bawa minya wangi yang paling mahal, bekin dari akar wangi, nama minya narwastu di botol pualam satu. Waktu Yesus ada dudu makan ju itu parampuan bekin pica itu botol pung tutu, abis po'a itu minya pi di Yesus pung kapala.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ma ada barapa orang laen yang iko makan di situ ju. Waktu dong lia itu parampuan bekin bagitu, ju dong mara, ko dong ba'omong sombong bilang, &lt;&lt;Hmm! Parampuan apa ni, ko dia pi buang parcuma itu minya wangi yang mahal mati pung!<bt>But there were several other people who also were eating there. When they saw that woman do like that, then they got angry and so they spoke arrogantly saying, &lt;&lt;Hmm! [+critical] What kind of woman is this, so that she throws.away unnecessarily that fragrant oil that is very expensive! [RQ: not a true question, but a criticism.]</bt><v n="5" />Lebe bae dia jual itu minya sa! Ko pi bagi dia pung doi yang banya, kasi sang orang malarat dong! Te itu minya wangi pung harga, sama ke satu orang pung gaji satu taon.&gt;&gt; Ju dong togor karás sang dia.<bt>It would be better if she just sold that oil! For the purpose of going to give so much money from it to the poor/unfortunate people! Cuz (elaboration) that fragrant oil's price/value, is equivalent to a person's wage for one year.&gt;&gt; And they scolded her strongly/harshly.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="miskin &gt; kasian &gt; malarat &gt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">miskin &gt; kasian &gt; malarat &gt; maleset / kere (Jawa)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Itu minya bisa jual deng harga"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Itu minya bisa jual deng harga lebe dari tiga ratus doi perak, deng dia pung doi bisa kasi sang orang-orang miskin dong!&gt;&gt; Jadi dong mara sang itu parampuan.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Ma Yesus balas bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong sonde usa bekin susa ini parampuan! Kasi tenga pi sang dia sa! Beta sanáng, tagal dia su po'a ini minya wangi di Beta pung badan.<bt>But Yesus replied/responded saying, &lt;&lt;You don't need to make things difficult for this woman! Just leave her alone! I am happy, because she has poured this fragrant oil on My body.</bt><v n="7" />Orang kasian dong salalu ada deng bosong. Jadi bosong bisa tolong sang dong kapan sa. Ma kalo Beta, sonde lama lai, te Beta su sonde ada sama-sama deng bosong.<bt>The poor/pitiful people will always be with you-pl. So (consequently) you can help them whenever/at any time. But as for Me, not much longer, I will no longer be together with you.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Orang miskin dong masi salalu ada"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Orang miskin dong masi salalu ada di bosong pung teng-tenga, jadi kapan sa bosong bisa tolong sang dong. Ma Beta su sonde bisa tenga deng bosong trus-trus.</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Carita Ulang so'al Jalan Idop 15:11</note><v n="8" />Beta pung idop su sonde lama lai. Deng ini parampuan po'a ini minya tadi, dia su sadia Beta pung badan lebe dolo, sama ke dia kasi rampe memang Beta pung mayat.<bt>My life is not much longer/will soon end. With/By this woman pouring this oil earlier, she has prepared My body ahead of time, like she is actually putting perfume/flowers beforehand on My corpse.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rampe = flowers and spices thrown"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">rampe = flowers and spices thrown on grave for burial (daun pandan)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ini parampuan su bekin apa yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Ini parampuan su bekin apa yang dia bisa bekin kasi sang Beta. Dia su siram memang dia pung rampe kasi di Beta pung kubur.</Message></Annotation><v n="9" />Inga bae-bae, ó! Di mana sa Tuhan Allah pung Carita Bae tasiar kuliling ini dunya, dong ju pasti carita ini parampuan pung bae! Ko biar samua orang inga sang dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember this well, ó! Whereever God's *Good Story is spread all all around this world, they will surely also tell about this woman's goodness! So that all people remember her.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Inga bae-bae ó! Nanti kalo orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Inga bae-bae ó! Nanti kalo orang pi kasi tau Tuhan Allah pung Carita Bae kuliling ini dunya, dong ju pasti carita bilang apa yang ini parampuan beking sang Beta itu, memang bae. Biar deng ini carita, samua orang inga sang dia." long sentence Di mana sa Tuhan Allah pung Carita Bae tasiar kuliling ini dunya, dong ju pasti carita ini parampuan pung bae! Ko biar samua orang inga sang dia.&gt;&gt;<span class="Italic">(9) (9) </span>Bosong parcaya é! Kuliling ini dunya, di mana sa, asal ada orang dong bawa Tuhan Allah pung Injil, dong pasti carita tentang ini parampuan pung perbuatan ini sama ke satu kenangan kasi sang Beta.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Yudas basakongkol ko mau jual Tuhan Yesus<bt>Yudas plots/schemes to *betray/sell the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:14-16; Lukas 22:3-6)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="10" />Ais ju ada satu dari Yesus pung ana bua dua blas orang tu, nama Yudas Iskariot. Dia kaluar pi cari kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos, ko mau jual buang sang Yesus kasi dong. Sampe di dong, ju dia kasi tau dia pung maksud.<bt>After that, there was one of the twelve disciples of Yesus, named Yudas Iskariot. He went out going to find the *chief priests, to sell throwing away (*betray) Yesus to them. Arriving at them, he told them his intention/plan. [DISCOURSE: Last sentence required by RL discourse to transition from irrealis plan in vs. 10 to reaction/response in vs. 11.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="basakongkol = sepakat, berunding, berencana; bapár"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">basakongkol = sepakat, berunding, berencana; bapár = satu partei; kawan satu kaki = kawan akrab ; maen balakang = do behind s.o. back</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis ju, satu dari itu ana"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Abis ju, satu dari itu ana murid dua blas orang, yang dia pung nama Yudas, pi di imam-iman kapala ko mau bekin kianat sang Yesus deng dong.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Waktu bos-bos dong dengar Yudas pung omong bagitu, ju dong sanáng mau mati. Ju dong janji bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo lu mau jual Yesus kasi sang botong, pasti botong bayar.&gt;&gt; Ais Yudas kaluar, ju dia mulai cari akal ko mau kasi Yesus pi sang dong.<bt>When those bosses heard Yudas' talk like that, then they were very extremely happy. And they promised saying, &lt;&lt;If/when you sell Yesus to us, surely we-exc will pay.&gt;&gt; Then Yudas went out, and he began to seek an idea (negative scheming overtones) to give Yesus to them.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="botong = 1pe ; kotong ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">botong = 1pe ; kotong = 1pi; cari akal is more negatively valued than ator siasat (which can be neutral)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus makan pesta Paska deng Dia pung ana bua dong<bt>Lord Yesus eats Paska/Passover feast with His *disciples</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:17-25; Lukas 22:7-14, 21-23; Yohanis 13:21-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Itu hari jato di hari partama dari orang Yahudi pung hari-hari bae. Jadi di itu hari, dong biasa bakar roti yang sonde pake bibit roti, deng dong ju horo domba. Ais ju Yesus pung ana bua dong datang tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Ini hari ni, kotong pung hari bae Paska. Jadi Papa mau botong pi sadia tampa pesta Paska di mana?&gt;&gt;<bt>That day fell on the first day of the Yahudi people's holidays (plural). So (consequently) on that day, they usually bake bread that does not use bread seed/yeast, and they also cut/slaughtered a sheep. So/then Yesus' disciples came asking Him saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Today is our Paska/Passover holiday. So (consequently) where do You want us to go prepare the place for the Paska feast?&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Festival of Unleavened Bread runs 7 days, and overlaps with Passover (1st or 2nd day depending on how counted). “the first day” here probably means “before 6pm (when the next day [Passover] started)”. “Passover lamb” is generic, so NIV “customarily sacrificed (ritually slaughtered)”. See TH, TN.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** restructured to get background-foreground info"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">*** restructured to get background-foreground info right -- July 2005 (Sabu)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis itu, Yesus pung ana bua"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Abis itu, Yesus pung ana bua dong datang tanya sang Dia, bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Ini hari ni, kotong pung hari bae Paska. Jadi, Papa mau botong pi sadia tampa pesta Paska di mana?&gt;&gt; Te itu hari, hari partama dari orang Yahudi pung hari-hari bae. Itu hari, dong biasa bakar roti yang sonde pake bibit roti, deng dong ju potong domba. Bagitu orang Yahudi dong maso hari pertama Perayaan Roti Yang Sonde Pake Ragi, waktu dong potong domba Paskah, Yesus pung ana murid dong datang tanya sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa mau ko kotong siap makanan Paskah kasi sang Bapa di mana?&gt;&gt;<span class="Italic">(12)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ais Yesus suru Dia pung ana bua dua orang bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pi lebe dolo di kota. Di sana, nanti bosong katumu deng satu laki-laki yang ada masa'a aer di satu kumbang kici. Bosong pi iko sang dia sa.<bt>So/then Yesus ordered two of His *disciples saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl go on ahead to the city. There (yonder) you will meet a male who is shoulder carrying water in a little clay jar. You just go follow him. [BACKGROUND: carrying water was normally women's work, so this would have stood out as unusual or noticable.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="masa'a = shoulder-carry (UNS jelas 'bawa',"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">masa'a = shoulder-carry (UNS jelas 'bawa', ma dia pung cara sonde jelas); kumbang = clay water jug</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-08-13 01:28:18Z" /></Annotation><v n="14" />Nanti kalo dia maso pi ruma mana, na, bosong pi iko sang dia di situ. Ais bosong kasi tau sang itu tuan ruma bilang, &lt;Bapa! Botong pung Bapa Guru ada minta satu tampa, ko Dia mau pake bekin pesta Paska deng Dia pung ana bua dong.&gt;<bt>Later whichever house he enters, na, you-pl go follow him there. Then you tell that house owner saying, &lt;Father! Our-exc Teacher is requesting a place, so that He can use it to make the Paska/Passover feast with his disciples.&gt;</bt><v n="15" />Ais nanti itu orang kasi tunju satu kamar luas di lante atas. Dia su sadia langkáp itu kamar. Cuma tenga bosong dua pi ko sadia makan di situ sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that person will show a wide/broad room on the upstairs floor. He already completely prepared/furnished that room. The only thing left is for you two to go prepare the food there.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais dong dua jalan pi kota. Di sana dong dapa katumu deng samua yang Yesus su kasi tau memang sang dong. Ju dong sadia samua, ko Yesus dong makan pesta Paska di situ. Ais dong dua pi pange sang Yesus dong.<bt>Then they two went to the city. There they met with/encountered all that Yesus had already explained beforehand to them. And they prepared everything for Yesus (collective) to eat the Paska/Passover feast there. Then the two of them went and summoned Yesus (coll). [EXEG/DISCOURSE: Maths: vs. 16: 2 of the 12 go prepare the place. vs. 17: Jesus comes with the 12 (which includes the 2 in 16). So for RL discourse we need to have them go back and summon Jesus (collective). No disputes from commentaries.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju itu ana murid dong jalan"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Ju itu ana murid dong jalan pi di kota. Di sana dong katumu deng samua yang Yesus su bilang memang sang dong. Jadi dong sadia makanan Paskah di situ.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="17" />Waktu matahari su mulai tanggalám, ju Yesus deng Dia pung ana bua dua blas orang dong pi di situ.<bt>When the sun was beginning to go down/drown, then Yesus and his 12 disciples went there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Malam turun ju Yesus deng Dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Malam turun ju Yesus deng Dia pung ana murid dong datang di situ.</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ais dong dudu ko makan sama-sama. Waktu dong ada makan, Yesus ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dengar, é! Ada satu orang dari bosong yang nanti jual Beta kasi pi orang laen dong.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they sat to eat together. When/while they were eating, Yesus spoke saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl listen, é! There's one of/from you who will later sell/betray Me to other/foreign people.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu dong dudu makan, Yesus omong,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Waktu dong dudu makan, Yesus omong, bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dengar é! Ada satu orang dari bosong samua, yang ada dudu makan sama-sama deng Beta, yang nati bekin kianat sang Beta.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:18" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 41:10</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Dengar bagitu, ju dong pung hati rasa tar enak. Tarús dong satu-satu tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu orang yang Papa omong tu, bukan beta, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>Hearing that, then their hearts felt not good/felt troubled. Then each one of them asked Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;That person that Father/You were talking about, is not me, to? [+tag: expecting affirmative response]&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong dengar Dia bilang bagitu ju"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Dong dengar Dia bilang bagitu ju dong samua pung hati sedih. tarús dong satu-satu datang tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa sonde maksud bilang itu orang andia beta, bukan?&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Orang yang colo dia pung roti pi dalam ini mangko sama-sama deng Beta, dia tu yang nanti jual buang sang Beta.<bt>Yesus answered/responded saying, &lt;&lt;The person who dips his bread in this bowl together with Me, he is the one who will sell off/betray Me.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deta garam = dip in salt;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">deta garam = dip in salt; colo = dip in liquid; andia dia itu = stressed focus construction</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia itu sala"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia itu sala satu dari bosong dua blas orang, yang ada makan sama-sama deng Beta satu piring.</Message></Annotation><v n="21" />Inga, é! Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, musti mati sama ke dong su tulis memang dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi. Ma awas! Itu orang yang mau jual Beta tu, nanti dia pikol dia pung calaka! Ada lebe bae kalo dia pung mama sonde barana ame sang dia!&gt;&gt;<bt>Remember, é! I, the *Ideal/Prototype Human, must die just like what was written beforehand in God's *Scriptures. But be careful! That person who will sell/betray Me, he will shoulder carry/bear his misfortune! It would be better if his mother didn't give birth to him!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau bilang, itu roti deng aer anggor jadi tanda ko kotong inga sang Dia [\s2]<bt>The Lord Yesus explains saying that bread and grape liquid are signs to remember Him [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:26-30; Lukas 22:14-20; 1 Korintus 11:23-25)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="22" />Waktu dong masi makan, ju Yesus angka ame roti satu balok, ko minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Ais Dia bekin pica-pica itu roti, ju sorong kasi sang Dia pung ana bua dong. Ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini roti, Beta pung badan. Ame ko makan suda.&gt;&gt;<bt>When they were still eating, Yesus picked up a bread loaf, and gave thanks to God. Then He broke-broke that bread (into little pieces), and extended it to His *disciples. And He said, &lt;&lt;This bread is My body. Take it to eat [+mild imperative].&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Sementara dong makan (check);"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Sementara dong makan (check);</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu dong makan, Yesus angka ame"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Waktu dong makan, Yesus angka ame roti ko ucap doa sukur sang Tuhan Allah. Abis Dia bekin pica-pica itu roti deng Dia pung tangan, ko sorong kasi sang Dia pung ana murid dong, deng bilang bagini, &lt;&lt;Ame ko makan te ini Beta pung badan.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01803b.tif" rtfFormat="width:10.0cm;textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="23" />Ais itu, Dia angka ame galás yang ada isi bua anggor pung aer. Dia ju minta tarima kasi sang Tuhan Allah. Ais Dia sorong kasi itu galás pi Dia pung ana bua ko dong samua minum.<bt>After that, He picked up a glass that was filled with grape fruit's liquid. And He also gave thanks to *God. Then He extended that glass to His *disciples for them all to drink. [EXEG: In the NT, Gk ‘wine’ tends to be mildly alcoholic (low percentage, depending on season) and used for daily drink and quenching thirst. In eastern Indonesia “anggur” is only bottled, is a type of fortified wine or brandy with high alcoholic percentage, and is only used to get drunk or serve communion. So it is a different class of alcoholic drink than what is intended. This is our tested strategy to get past the baggage.]</bt><v n="24" />Ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini anggor, Beta pung dara. Dia nanti tatumpa ko kasi salamat banya orang. Ini dara jadi bukti ko kasi inga bilang, apa yang Tuhan Allah su janji, memang sakarang ni su jadi. Naa, ame ko minum suda.<bt>And He said, &lt;&lt;This grape/wine is My blood. It will be spilled out in order to *save/rescue many people. This blood is the evidence to remind (you/people) that, that which God has promised, actually now has already happened/come into being. Naa, take and drink [+mild imperative].</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tampias = splashed; tumpa untuk maksud"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">tampias = splashed; tumpa untuk maksud tertentu</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ada pake bekin resmi Tuhan Allah"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">ada pake bekin resmi Tuhan Allah pung janji, dara yang tatumpa kasi banya orang.</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 24:8, Yeremia 31:31-34</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="25" />Dengar bae-bae dolo! Mulai dari ini malam, Beta su sonde minum bua anggor pung aer lai. Sampe Beta dudu parenta sama-sama deng Beta pung Bapa di sorga, baru Beta minum lai.&gt;&gt;<bt>Listen carefully! Starting from this night, I will no longer drink grape fruit's liquid any more. Until I sit ruling together with My Father in heaven, only then will I drink it again.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="@@ added pargraph July 2005 (Sabu)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">@@ added pargraph July 2005 (Sabu)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bosong parcaya sang Beta. Beta su"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Bosong parcaya sang Beta. Beta su sonde minum lai ini anggor, sampe Beta dapa minum anggor baru di Bapa pung ruma di sorga.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="26" />Ais ju dong manyanyi satu lagu ko puji sang Tuhan Allah. Tarús dong kaluar malam ko pi gunung Saitun.<bt>After that, they sang a song to praise God. Then they went out at/by night to go to Saitun mountain. [NOTE: Singing a hymn from the Psalms is the very last step in the Jewish Passover Seder/Liturgy. They can choose from about 5 different psalms.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tau lebe dolo bilang, Petrus nanti manyangkal sang Dia<bt>Lord Yesus reveals ahead of time that Petrus will deny (knowing) Him</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:31-35; Lukas 22:31-34; Yohanis 13:36-38)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="27" />Waktu dong bajalan tu, Yesus kasi tau memang bilang, &lt;&lt;Nanti sabantar malam ni, bosong samua lari kasi tenga sang Beta. Itu sama ke dong su tulis memang dalam Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi bilang,<bt>When/while they were walking, Yesus revealed beforehand saying, &lt;&lt;Later on tonight, you all will run away leaving Me. That is like what they have written beforehand in God's *Scriptures saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="manyangkal = ingkar (janji), sonde mangaku;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">manyangkal = ingkar (janji), sonde mangaku;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 1" usfm="q1">&lt;Nanti Tuhan Allah bekin mati gambala,<bt>&lt;God will kill the shepherd, [EXEG: Gk ‘strike down’ here = ‘kill, slay, mortal blow’. LN, BAGD, TH, TN.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="strike the shepherd"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">strike the shepherd</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Line 2" usfm="q2">ais dia pung domba dong lari batasiram.&gt;<bt>and his sheep will run scattering (all over the place).&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tasiram = scattered, cerai-berei"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">tasiram = scattered, cerai-berei</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="'Beta, Tuhan Allah nanti bunu bekin"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">'Beta, Tuhan Allah nanti bunu bekin mati dia pung gembala deng dia pung domba-domba dong nanti lari tasiar pi mana-mana.</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:27" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Sakaria 13:7</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="28" />Beta memang mati. Ma nanti kalo Beta su idop kambali, Beta pi lebe dolo dari bosong di propinsi Galilea.&gt;&gt;<bt>I am truly going to die. But later when I live again/come back to life, I will go ahead of you-pl to propinsi Galilea.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Tapi sesudah Beta idop kombali, nanti"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Tapi sesudah Beta idop kombali, nanti Beta barangkat lebe dolo dari bosong pi di Galilea.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 28:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Ais ju Petrus protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa! Biar orang laen dong samua lari kasi tenga sang Papa, ma beta sonde akan!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Petrus protested saying, &lt;&lt;Father! Even if all the other people run leaving Father/You, nevertheless I (definitely) will not!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="protes ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">protes =</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="30" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Pe'u! Inga, é! Ini malam, ayam balóm kokore'o dua kali, ma lu su omong tiga kali bilang, lu sonde kanál sang Beta!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered/responded saying, &lt;&lt;Pe'u (Peter nickname—affectionate)! Remember, é! This night, the chicken will not yet crow two times, but you-sg will already say three times that you do not know Me!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kokore'o = cock crows ; manyangkal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">kokore'o = cock crows ; manyangkal buang =</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus bilang sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Petrus!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Yesus bilang sang dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Petrus! Ingat é! Ini malam, lebe dolo dari ayam kokore'o dua kali, lu su menyangkal buang sang Beta sampe tiga kali.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Ma Petrus manyao karás bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde, Papa! Kalo Papa mati, beta ju iko mati sama-sama. Ma beta sonde akan lari kasi tenga sang Papa, deng sonde manyangkal sang Papa!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petrus answered/responded strongly/forcefully/loudly saying, &lt;&lt;No, Father! If Father/You die, I also follow/participate in dying together. But I will not run leaving behind/abandon Father/You and won't deny (knowing) Father/You!&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: RL patterns, fleshed out from context.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju Petrus manyao deng suara tegas"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Ju Petrus manyao deng suara tegas bilang, &lt;&lt;Biar beta musti mati sama-sama deng Bapa, ma beta sonde akan menyangkal sang Bapa!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Petrus pung tamán laen dong ju satu-satu bilang bagitu.<bt>Petrus' other friends also each said like that.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus sambayang di kabón Getsemani<bt>The Lord Yesus prays in the Getsemani garden/orchard</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:36-46; Lukas 22:39-46)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="32" />Ais itu, Yesus dong jalan tarús sampe di satu kabón di gunung Saitun, nama &lt;Getsemani&gt;. Ju Yesus kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong dudu tunggu di sini, é. Beta mau pi sambayang di sana.&gt;&gt;<bt>After that, Yesus (collective) walked on to a garden/orchard/grove on Saitun mountain, named ‘Getsemani’. And Yesus told them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl sit waiting here, é! I 'm going to go pray over there/yonder.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong samua jalan sampe di satu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Dong samua jalan sampe di satu tampa nama Getsemani. Yesus bilang Dia pung ana murid dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong tunggu di sini. Beta mau pi berdoa sabantar sa!&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ju Yesus pange bawa sang Petrus, Yakobis, deng Yohanis, ko pi sama-sama deng Dia. Mulai dari itu waktu, ju Dia pung hati rasa susa deng sonde tanáng.<bt>And Yesus called taking Petrus, Yakobis, and Yohanis, to go together with Him. Beginning from that time, then His liver felt troubled/disturbed and was not calm.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tado / tanáng"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">tado / tanáng</Message></Annotation><v n="34" />Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung hati susa mau mati! Beta rasa tingka ke Beta su mau mati sa. Bosong dudu bajaga di sini dolo.&gt;&gt;<bt>He told them saying, &lt;&lt;My liver is extremely troubled! I feel like I am going to/about to die. You-pl sit guarding here for now.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mete = stay awake to watch"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">mete = stay awake to watch (dead body); tingka ke = seperti, seolah-olah</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Dia kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung hati susa mo mati. Beta rasa tingka ke Beta su mau mati sa. Bosong dudu tenga di sini deng buka bosong pung mata lebar-lebar / jang tidor.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01810b.tif" rtfFormat="width:9.0cm;textWrapping:none;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35-36" />Ais Dia maju lebe jao sadiki, ju Dia tikam lutut di tana ko sambayang bilang, &lt;&lt;Papa manis! Kalo Papa satuju, na, Beta sonde usa tanggong itu sangsara sampe mati macam bagini. Beta su tau memang bilang, sonde ada yang Papa sonde bisa bekin. Jadi kalo bole, na, Papa angka buang jao-jao ini sangsara dari Beta. Ma jang iko Beta pung mau; biar iko Papa pung mau sa.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then He went on a little bit further, and He knelt on the earth to pray saying, &lt;&lt;Dear/sweet Papa/Father! If Father/You agree, na, I don't need to carry/bear this suffering to the point of death like this. I know for sure that, there is nothing You cannot do. So (consequently) if it's possible, na, lift away far-far this suffering from Me. But don't follow My will; just only follow Your will.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Papa bo'i (Rote (sayang); tikam lutut"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Papa bo'i (Rote (sayang); tikam lutut = metaphor for earnest, strive, berjuang sungguh-sungguh; Islam cium tana; jang tako, beta pasang kaki (really will do it); ator kuda-kuda = ator siasat</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus maju lebe jao sadiki ju"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Yesus maju lebe jao sadiki ju Dia jato tikam lutut di tana ko berdoa. Di dalam Diapung doa, Dia minta ko kalo bisa na Dia sonde usa pikol itu sangsara. Papa, sio! Beta su tau memang bilang sonde ada satu hal yang mustahil kasi sang Bapa. kalo bisa na Bapa jang kasi pikol ini sangsara kasi sang Beta. Tapi jang iko Beta pung mau. Biar Bapa pung mau sa yang jadi.&gt;&gt;<span class="Italic">(35)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Ais ju Dia kambali pi Dia pung ana bua tiga orang tu, ma dong ada tidor sonu. Ais Dia kasi bangun sang dong, ju Dia omong sang Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;He, Pe'u!<bt>After that, He returned to those three disciples of His, but they were sleeping soundly. Then He woke them up, and He said to Petrus saying, &lt;&lt;He! Pe'u! [+affectionate nickname: Pete]</bt><note reference="14:37" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Alkitab bahasa Yunani tulis bilang, &lt;Simon&gt; di sini. Simon tu, Petrus pung nama laen.<bt>The Greek language Bible writes saying &lt;Simon&gt; here. Simon is Petrus' other name.</bt></note>Lu tidor, ko? Beta di situ cuma sabantar sa, ma bosong sonde bisa bajaga sadiki ju!<bt>You're sleeping, ko? [+confirmative tag] I'm over there just a short/brief time, but you-pl can't even watch a little bit! [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk /houra/ can be translated here as ‘one hour’ OR ‘a little while’; TH, TRT, LN; since clocks weren't invented until centuries later, it should be a vague time word, not a precise time word. Watch out for anachronisms in your translation. Something like Tetun Dili /oras ida/ is a good match for the Gk.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mete = ; mata su puruk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">mete = ; mata su puruk = mata barát</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis ju, Dia kombali ma Dia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Abis ju, Dia kombali ma Dia dapa katumu sang dong tiga orang ada tidor sonu. Dia bilang sang Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;He, Petrus. Lu tidor na? Lu sonde bisa mete kasi Beta satu jam juga?&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><v n="38" />Goso bekin taráng lu pung mata dolo. Ais bangun ko bajaga deng Beta! Bosong pung hati memang mau bekin yang bae, cuma bosong pung badan sonde kuat. Jadi lebe bae bosong sambayang, ko kalo kaná coba'an, bosong sonde kala.&gt;&gt;<bt>Rub making clear your-sg eyes (imperative). Then get up to guard/watch with Me! Your-p livers really want to do what is good, only your bodies are not strong. So (consequently) it would be better that you pray, so that if you are affected/overcome by testing/temptation, you don't get defeated.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk word covers both 1) testing one's character, and 2) tempting to sin. Try to cover both if possible, not just the second.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis Yesus omong kasi sang dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Abis Yesus omong kasi sang dong tiga orang bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong bangun ko mete deng Beta. Bosong iko berdoa ko biar bosong sonde kaná coba'an. Memang hati ada mau bekin yang bae ma badan sonde kuat pikol.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">1 Korintus 10:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Ais Yesus pi sambayang satu kali lai. Dia minta ulang sang Tuhan, ko jang kasi tenga Dia pikol itu sangsara.<bt>Then Yesus went to pray another time. He requested again to the Lord, that He not leave/allow Him to shoulder carry/experience that suffering.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis Yesus pi ko berdoa satu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Abis Yesus pi ko berdoa satu kali lai. Dia omong lai kata-kata yang sama ke Dia pung doa tadi.</Message></Annotation><v n="40" />Ais Dia datang kambali di Dia pung ana bua tiga orang tu. Ma dong su tidor ulang lai, te dong pung mata barát mau mati. Ais Dia kasi bangun ulang sang dong, ma dong sonde tau mau manyao bilang apa sang Dia.<bt>Then He came back to those three disciples of His. But they were sleeping again, cuz (elaboration) their eyes were extremely heavy. Then He woke them up again, but they didn't know what to respond saying to Him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mangantok; mata su puruk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">mangantok; mata su puruk</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bagitu Dia datang kombali, Dia dapa"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Bagitu Dia datang kombali, Dia dapa sang dong su tidor ulang lai, te dong sonde bisa tahan dong pung manganto. Ais Dia kasi bangun ulang sang dong, ma dong sonde tau manyao apa-apa sang Yesus.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="41" />Ais itu, Yesus kasi tenga sang dong ko pi sambayang yang katiga kali. Ais ju Dia kambali ko kasi bangun sang dong. Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong masi tidor lai, ko? Cukup suda! Bangun! Te orang yang mau jual sang Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, su deka. Sakarang dong su mau tangkap sang Beta, ko kasi pi orang jahat dong pung tangan.<bt>After that, Yesus left them to go pray a third time. Then He came back to wake them up. He said, &lt;&lt;You're sleeping again, ko? [+confirmative tag] Enough already! Get up! Cuz (elaboration) the person who wants to sell/betray Me, the *Ideal/Prototype Human here, is already near. Now they already want to capture/arrest Me, to give me to the hands of evil people. [NOTE to daughter translations: Check that this is not a Hebraism or literalism in your language.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bagitu Yesus kombali lai kali yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Bagitu Yesus kombali lai kali yang katiga, ju Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong masi mau tidor, ko? Masi mau istirahat tarús? Cukup suda! Bangun, te dia pung waktu su sampe. Orang yang mau serakan sang ana Manusia pi di orang berdosa dong pung tangan su datang.</Message></Annotation><v n="42" />Bangun su! Buka bosong pung mata ko lia coba pi sana dolo! Orang yang mau jual buang sang Beta tu, su datang. Mari ko kotong pi katumu sang dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>Come on, get up! Open your-pl eyes and look over there! That person who is going to sell/betray Me has arrived. Let's (inc) go meet them!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kaná tangkap<bt>The Lord Yesus is arrested/captured</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:47-56; Lukas 22:47-53; Yohanis 18:3-12)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="43" />Waktu Yesus masi ba'omong bagitu, ju takuju sa, Yudas su datang deng orang bam-banya. Dong datang deng bawa kalewang kudung deng kayu kudung, ko mau tangkap sang Yesus. Dong bekin bagitu, iko parenta dari bos-bos Yahudi dong. Dong tu, andia kapala agama dong pung bos-bos, guru agama dong, deng tua-tua adat.<bt>When Yesus was still talking like that, suddenly Yudas came with many people. They came carrying short fighting-swords and clubs, to capture/arrest Yesus. They did like that, following the command from the Yahudi bosses/leaders. Those were, the *chief priests, the religion teachers, and traditional elders.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalewang = pedang, sword; kayu kudung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">kalewang = pedang, sword; kayu kudung = clubs, night sticks</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Waktu Yesus masi omong te Yudas,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Waktu Yesus masi omong te Yudas, satu dari Dia pung ana murid yang dua blas orang itu, muncul datang. Orang dong banya yang datang iko sang dia. Ada yang bawa kalewang deng ada yang bawa kayu kudung.Imam-imam kapala, guru-guru agama deng orang Yahudi pung pamimpin yang kirim sang dong datang.</Message></Annotation><v n="44" />Yudas su kasi sein memang sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong lia bae-bae! Beta ciom sang sapa, na, bosong tangkap ame sang Dia suda! Andia Dia tu, orang yang bosong cari!&gt;&gt;<bt>Yudas had already given a code/sign to them beforehand saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl look carefully. Whomever I kiss, you capture/arrest Him (imperative)! That will be Him there, the person whom you-pl seek!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Si Pengkianat itu su kasi sein"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Si Pengkianat itu su kasi sein memang sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong lia bae-bae. Beta ciom sapa na bosong tangkap ame sang Dia suda te Dia pung orang andia Dia. Ika bawa sang Dia suda.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi sein = give a sign"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">kasi sein = give a sign (Du loan)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01812b.tif" rtfFormat="width:9.0cm;verticalPosition:bottom">Yudas kasi sein, deng ciom sang Yesus<bt>Yudas gives a sign, and kisses Yesus</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Jadi waktu Yudas dong sampe di situ, ju dia langsung mangada sang Yesus. Ais dia togor bilang, &lt;&lt;Bapa Guru!&gt;&gt; Ju Yudas paló-ciom ame sang Dia.<bt>So (consequently) when Yudas (collective) arrived there, then he straight away went in front of Yesus. Then he greeted saying, “Teacher!” Then Yudas hugged-kissed Him. [EXEG: Gk is just kiss. Timor lgs treat it as a complex action. Primary sense of word for ‘kiss’ is ‘sniff/smell’, so this complex action forces the ‘kiss’ reading.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="togor = 1) scold, forbid, rebuke,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">togor = 1) scold, forbid, rebuke, tegur, 2) greet, sapa togor = greet; palo = peluk<span class="Italic">(45)</span></Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bagitu Yudas pung datang sampe ju"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Bagitu Yudas pung datang sampe ju dia langsung mangada sang Yesus abis dia omong, bilang. "Bapa Guru!&gt;&gt; Abis dia palo ciom sang Dia.</Message></Annotation><v n="46" />Tarús orang banya dong maju datang, ko tangkap sang Yesus.<bt>Then those many people come forward, to capture/arrest Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju itu orang-orang yang datang samaa-sama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Ju itu orang-orang yang datang samaa-sama deng Yudas maju ko tangkap ame sang Yesus abis dong pasang rante pi di Dia pung tangan.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Ma Yesus pung orang satu cabu ame dia pung parang kudung ko seruk bekin putus satu orang pung daon talinga. Itu orang yang luka tu, kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar pung orang suru-suru.<bt>But one of Yesus' people pulled out/unsheathed his short machete to slash off/separating a person's (outer) ear. That person who was wounded there, was a servant of the *high priest (big boss of the Yahudi priests).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="parang kudung = short machete; seruk"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">parang kudung = short machete; seruk = slash at; raja pung hamba;</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma ada satu orang yang badiri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Ma ada satu orang yang badiri deka-deka di situ cabu ame dia pung parang kudung ko seruk bekin putus imam bésar pung hamba pung daon talinga satu</Message></Annotation><v n="48" />Ais Yesus omong deng itu orang dong yang datang tangkap sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana? Bosong kira Beta ni orang jahat, ko? Jadi bosong datang tangkap sang Beta deng bawa kalewang deng kayu kudung?<bt>Then Yesus talked with those people who came to capture/arrest Him saying, &lt;&lt;How is it? Do you-pl think I here am an evil person, ko? [+confirmative tag] So (consequently) you come capture/arrest Me with fighting swords and wood clubs?</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus togor itu orang-orang yang datang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Yesus togor itu orang-orang yang datang tangkap sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong pikir Beta ni penjahat ko? Sampe bosong datang tangkap sang Beta deng pegang bawa kalewang deng kayu kudung</Message></Annotation><v n="49" />Tiap hari Beta ajar sang bosong di Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ma sonde ada satu orang yang datang tangkap sang Beta. Mari tangkap sang Beta suda! Te ini su tulis memang dari dolu di Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan Barisi.&gt;&gt;<bt>Every day I taught you-pl in God's *Temple, but there was not one person who came to capture/arrest Me. Come capture/arrest Me (imperative)! Cuz (elaboration) this is already written beforehand in God's Scriptures.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="saban = stok lama; tiap ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">saban = stok lama; tiap = stok baru (both known)</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Saban hari Beta badiri ajar sang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Saban hari Beta badiri ajar sang bosong samua di Bait Allah, ma sonde ada satu orang yang datang tangkap sang Beta. Tapi supaya samua bisa jadi iko apa yang su tulis menmang dalam Alkitab, na bosong mari ika sang Beta suda.</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:49" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 19:47, 21:37</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="50" />Yesus pung ana bua dong taku mau mati. Ju dong bangun lari kasi tenga sang Dia sandiri sa.<bt>Yesus' disciples were scared to death. So they fled leaving Him just himself.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ana murid dong samua bangun bongkar"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">ana murid dong samua bangun bongkar ko lari kasi tenga sang Yesus</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="51" />Di situ ju, ada satu orang muda yang iko-iko Yesus pung balakang. Dia ada bungkus badan deng kaen sapotong. Itu orang dong ju mau tangkap sang dia.<bt>There also, there was a young person who followed along behind Yesus. He had wrapped his body with a piece of cloth. Those people also wanted to catch/arrest him.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ada satu orang muda, yang cuma"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Ada satu orang muda, yang cuma pake kaen sapotong di dia pung badan, pi iko sang Yesus. Itu orang-orang dong mau tangkap sang dia</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-08-19 04:17:16Z">.</Message></Annotation><v n="52" />Ma dong dapa pegang dia pung kaen sa. Ais dia lari pulang deng talanjang sa, ko dia su taku mau mati na.<bt>But they could only just grab his cloth. So he ran home naked, cuz (elaboration) he was scared to death. [+obvious, emphatic]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ma dia lapás buang dia pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">ma dia lapás buang dia pung kaen, abis dia lari talanjang sa kasi tenga sang dong.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong bawa sang Tuhan Yesus pi pangadilan agama<bt>They take the Lord Yesus to the religious court</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:57-68; Lukas 22:54-55, 63-71; Yohanis 18:13-14, 19-24)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="53" />Ais itu, dong pegang bawa sang Yesus pi kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar pung ruma. Di situ, orang bésar dong su bakumpul. Andia, kapala agama dong pung bos-bos, guru agama dong, deng tua-tua adat.<bt>After that, they took Yesus to the house of the *high priest. There, big-big (important) people had already gathered. That is, the *chief priests, the *religion teachers, and the *traditional elders.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kapala besar = 1) sombong, 2)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">kapala besar = 1) sombong, 2) suka malawan, rebellious, kapala batu</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="54" />Waktu dong pegang bawa sang Yesus tu, Petrus ju ada iko sambunyi-sambunyi dari balakang, sampe di kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar pung ruma. Dia ju maso di kintal, ko iko dudu panggang api sama-sama deng orang jaga yang ada di situ.<bt>When they were taking Yesus there, Petrus also went following hidden from behind, all the way to the house of the *high priest. He also went into the yard, to participate sitting warming at the fire together with guards who were there.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="beking angat dia pung badan deka"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">beking angat dia pung badan deka api unggun, angat = hangat, warm; api unggun = bonfire ; ***added "guards"</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hupjretwn: underling, servant, helper &quot;in all"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z" status="Information">hupjretwn: underling, servant, helper "in all probability here the temple guard"</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="55" />Di dalam itu ruma, kapala agama dong pung bos-bos ada ba'omong deng orang-orang yang dudu di pangadilan agama. Dong samua cari bukti ko mau kasi sala sang Yesus, tagal dong mau hukum mati sang Dia. Ma dong sonde dapa bukti apa-apa.<bt>Inside that house, the *chief priests were talking with the people who sat on the *religious court. They all sought evidence/proof to accuse Yesus, because they wanted to sentence Him to death. But they could not get any evidence at all. [NOTE to daughter translations: Avoid the misleading impression that this was at the LOCATION of court; this is only with the PEOPLE who have authority in that court.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Imam-imam Kapala deng Mahkamah Agama pung"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Imam-imam Kapala deng Mahkamah Agama pung anggita dong samua ada cari-cari bukti ko dapa Yesus pung sala ko biar dong busa kasi jato hukuman mati sang Dia. Ma dong sonde dapa satu bukti apa juga.</Message></Annotation><v n="56" />Ju dong pange ame banya saksi ko mau kasi jato sang Yesus. Ma dong pung omong tu, sonde bacocok satu deng satu.<bt>And they called many witnesses (loan) to make Yesus fall (socially, morally, politically). But that talking of theirs (=what they said), it didn't match up with each other.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Dong pange ame barapa orang ko"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Dong pange ame barapa orang ko kasi kesaksian palsu malawan sang Yesus, ma dong pung kesaksian dong sonde bacocok satu deng satu.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="57" />Ais ada barapa saksi lai yang bangun badiri ko omong putar-balek bilang,<bt>Then there were several other witnesses who stood up to speak lies/deception saying,</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Abis ada saksi barapa orang yang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Abis ada saksi barapa orang yang bangun badiri ko kasi kesaksian palsu bilang</Message></Annotation><v n="58" />&lt;&lt;Botong ada dengar ini orang omong bilang, &lt;Nanti Beta kasi rubu Ruma Sambayang Pusat yang manusia kasi bangun deng tangan. Ais tiga hari lai, nanti Beta kasi bangun ulang itu Ruma, ma sonde pake manusia pung tangan.&gt;&gt;&gt;<bt>&lt;&lt;We-exc have heard this person talk saying, &lt;I will destroy this Temple that humans have build with hands. Then three days later, I will rebuild that House again, but not using human hands.&gt;&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="*** humans"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">*** humans</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:58" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yohanis 2:19</note><v n="59" />Ma dong pung omong tu, sonde bacocok satu deng satu.<bt>But that talking of theirs (=what they said), didn't match up with each other.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="60" />Ais kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar tu, bangun badiri di muka samua orang yang dudu di itu pangadilan. Ju dia tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Banya orang su kalák sang Lu. Ma akurang ko Lu diam sa?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that *high priest, stood up in front of all the people who sat on that court. And he asked Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;Many people have accused You-sg. But why are You just quiet?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju Imam Bésar bangun badiri di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Ju Imam Bésar bangun badiri di Mahkamah Agama pung muka, ko dia tanya sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko Lu sonde jawab ini orang dong pung tuduhan satu juga?</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kalák = gugat, lapor, dakwa, omong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">kalák = gugat, lapor, dakwa, omong kasi sala</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="61" />Yesus sonde omong sadiki ju. Ais kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar tanya ulang sang Dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Coba Lu kasi tau dolo! Apa memang Lu ni, batúl-batúl Kristus, Tuhan Allah pung Ana yang Dia su janji dari dolu tu?&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus didn't even talk a little bit. Then the high priest asked again to Him saying, &lt;&lt;You should talk (to us)! Really are You here, truly the Kristus, that *Child of God whom He promised from before?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ma Yesus diam sa. Tia sonde"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Ma Yesus diam sa. Tia sonde jawab satu kata juga. Abis ju itu Imam Bésar tanya ulang sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Coba Lu kasi tau, Lu ni, Juruslamat, Tuhan Allah yang maha tinggi pung ana ko?</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="62" />Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Memang batúl. Dia tu, andia Beta ni. Nanti bosong samua dapa lia Beta, Manusia Tulen ni, dudu di sorga di Tuhan Allah pung sablá kanan. Dia yang pung kuasa paling hebat! Nanti Beta deng Dia sama-sama pegang parenta! Ais itu, nanti Beta turun datang dari sorga deng awan.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus answered/responded saying, &lt;&lt;It's really true. That Him, is Me here (=I am He). Later you-pl will all see Me, the *Ideal/Prototype Human here, sitting in heaven at God's right hand. He's the one whose power is extremely amazing! Later I and Him will rule together! After that, I will come down again from heaven with a cloud.&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk is NOT ‘glory’ here.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu Dia Beta!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Yesus manyao, bilang, &lt;&lt;Itu Dia Beta! Nanti bosong samua dapa lia ana Manusia duru di Dia pung Bapa pung sablá kanan deng nanti Dia turun datang dari langit.&gt;&gt;</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:62" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Daniel 7:13</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="63" />Dengar Yesus omong bagitu, ju kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar mara mau mati, sampe dia ru'i bekin tarobe dia pung baju panjang. Ais dia batarea kasi tau samua orang yang dudu di pangadilan tu bilang, &lt;&lt;Kotong sonde parlú saksi lai!<bt>Hearing Yesus talk like that, then the high priest was extremely angry, to the point that he forcefully ripped up his long robe. Then he shouted telling all the people who sat on that court saying, &lt;&lt;We-inc don't need any more witnesses!</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="robe = robek; ru'i = sentak,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">robe = robek; ru'i = sentak, rip forcefully</Message></Annotation><v n="64" />Bosong su dengar deng bosong pung talinga sandiri, Dia sandiri yang omong bagitu, to? Dia su angka diri jadi Tuhan Allah pung Ana. Ini hojat barát! Iko atoran agama, kalo ada orang bekin diri sama deng Tuhan Allah, itu orang musti mati! Jadi sakarang, bosong mau putus bilang apa?&gt;&gt;<bt>You-pl have heard with your very own ears, He himself is the one who spoke like that, to? [+tag, expecting affirmation] He has raised himself to be/become God's Child. This is heavy/severe blasphemy/slander! According to the religious regulations, if a person makes himself to be the same as God2/the Lord, that person must die! So (consequently) now, what do you-pl want to decide?&gt;&gt; [STYLE: ‘decide’ here is the wording for a formal decision by an authority such as a judge or government.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hojat = fitnah, menghujat, menghina, mengjelekkan,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">hojat = fitnah, menghujat, menghina, mengjelekkan, kasi jato Tuhan Allah pung nama</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dong samua putus bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang memang batúl sala! Jadi dia musti kaná hukum mati!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they all decided saying, &lt;&lt;This person is really truly wrong! So (consequently) he must get the death punishment!&gt;&gt;</bt><note reference="14:64" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kapala Agama dong pung Atoran 24:16</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="65" />Ais barapa orang maju ko sumbur luda sang Yesus. Dong tutu ame Dia pung mata, ju dong papoko sang Dia. Ais dong suru bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo Lu jadi Tuhan pung jubir, na, coba Lu rai. Sapa yang falungku sang Lu?&gt;&gt; Ais dong parenta orang yang jaga Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ko dong datang bawa sang Yesus. Dong bawa sang Dia pi, ju dong tampeleng barmaen sang Dia.<bt>Then several people came forward to spit at Yesus. They covered His eyes, and beat/repeatedly hit Him. Then they ordered saying, &lt;&lt;If you are God's spokesman/prophet, try to discern/divine. Who punched/socked You (with fist)?&gt;&gt; Then they ordered the people who guard the Temple to come take Yesus. They took Him away, and they slapped Him around.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maspurak = spit (Rote) ; sumbur"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">maspurak = spit (Rote) ; sumbur luda = spit at ; sumbur obat = ; tampeleng ; bola-bale; rai coba = coba kasi tau; rai = figure out, discern, terka; hela bawa has implications of resistance; falungku = sock w/fist ***added "prophesy" more explicitly</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ais barapa orang maju ko sumbur"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Ais barapa orang maju ko sumbur luda sang Yesus. Dong tutu ame Dia pung mata, ju dong papoko sang Dia. Ais dong tanya, bilang, &lt;&lt;Coba Lu rai. Sapa yang falungku sang Lu?&gt;&gt; Ais dong parenta orang yang jaga Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ko dong datang bawa sang Yesus. Dong bawa sang Dia pi, ju dong tampeleng barmaen sang Dia. Ju barapa orang maju ko maspurak luda sang Yesus, abis dong tutu ame Dia pung muka, ko dong mulai papoko sang Dia. Ju dong omong, bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu rai coba bilang sapa yang falungku sang Lu?&gt;&gt; Pengawal-pengawal dong ju maju datang ko tampeleng barmaen bola-bale sang Dia.<span class="Italic">(65)</span></Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Petrus omong tiga kali bilang, dia sonde kanál sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Petrus says three times, that he does not know the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 26:69-75; Lukas 22:56-62; Yohanis 18:15-18, 25-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="66-67" />Itu waktu, Petrus masi iko dudu di kintal. Ais kapala agama Yahudi pung bos bésar pung hamba parampuan satu datang lia sang dia ada panggang api. Dia lia bae-bae Petrus pung muka, ais dia omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tadi lu ju ada iko sama-sama deng Yesus, itu orang Nasaret, to? Batúl, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>At that time, Petrus was still following sitting in the yard. Then a female house servant/maid of the *high priest came seeing him warming by the fire. She looked closely at Petrus' face, then she spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Earlier you-sg also were following together with Yesus, that Nasaret person, to? [+tag, expecting affirmation] Yes, right?&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="manyangkal = sonde kanal; babu ="><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">manyangkal = sonde kanal; babu = tukang jaga ana, tukang karjá di dapur; lu babu beta pung ana (derogatory); jongos maloi bae-bae = teliti; inti bae-bae = perhatikan; maloi-maloi</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="68" />Ma Petrus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Sonde! Akurang ko lu tanya bagitu! Beta sonde kanál sang Dia.&gt;&gt; Ais Petrus kaluar ko pi badiri di muka pintu maso. [Pas itu waktu ju, ayam kokore'o.]<bt>But Petrus answered/responded saying, &lt;&lt;No! Why are you-sg asking like that! I don't know Him.&gt;&gt; Then Petrus went out to stand by the front gate. [Exactly at that time, then the/a chicken crowed.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pintu hek = gateway to the"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">pintu hek = gateway to the outside (UNS, Ena knows, Yanto doesn't; Sabu = toka) *** brackets and ftn added (2009)</Message></Annotation><note reference="14:68" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani saparu sonde tulis kalimat dalam kurung ni.<bt>Some Yunani language writings do not have this sentence in brackets.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="69" />Ais, itu hamba dapa lia ulang sang Petrus. Ju dia kasi tau orang-orang yang ada di situ bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia ni, satu dari itu orang dong!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then that helper/maid saw Petrus again. And she told the people who were there saying, &lt;&lt;This one here is one of those people!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pambantu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">pambantu</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-08-19 04:38:07Z" /></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="70" />Ju Petrus protes bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu gila mangkali! Beta sonde kanál itu Orang, ma!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Petrus protested saying, &lt;&lt;You're probably crazy! I don't know that Person! [+modal of protest/objection]&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="protes ; ma (tag)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">protes ; ma (tag)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Sonde lama lai, satu orang laen yang ada di situ omong lai sang Petrus bilang, &lt;&lt;Heh! Lu masi mau putar-balek lai bilang, lu sonde sama-sama deng itu orang dong! Weh! Bosong samua, orang Galilea, to?&gt;&gt;<bt>Not long later/soon, another person who was there spoke again to Petrus saying, &lt;&lt;Heh! [+attention, critical] You-sg are still lying/deceiving saying you weren't together with those people! Weh [+negative element]! All of you-pl are Galilea people, to?&gt;&gt; [+tag, expecting affirmation]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="71" />Ma Petrus malawan lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Beta sumpa! Beta sonde kanál itu Orang!&gt;&gt;<bt>But Petrus opposed again saying, &lt;&lt;Weh! [+negative element] I swear an oath! I don't know that Person!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Gk term here is fairly strong, invoking divine punishment if not true or not fulfilled. We have fleshed this out in other gospels.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="NOTE: Gk also has curse, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">NOTE: Gk also has curse, but putting both in here seems heavy</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="72" />Pas dia omong bagitu, ju ayam kokore'o dua kali. Ju Petrus inga ame Yesus pung bahasa tadi bilang, &lt;&lt;Ayam balóm kokore'o dua kali, ma lu su manyangkal sang Beta tiga kali.&gt;&gt;<bt>Exactly when he spoke like that, then a chicken crowed two times. And Petrus remembered Yesus' words earlier saying, &lt;&lt;The chicken won't yet have crowed two times, but you-sg will have already denied Me three times.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: make a reasonable match with 14:30]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Inga ame bagitu, ju Petrus manangis makarereu.<bt>Remembering like that, then Petrus cried deeply/in grief.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="maskakeduk. = terisak-isak, weep, with sobs,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">maskakeduk. = terisak-isak, weep, with sobs, taking repeated breaths; makareu/makarereu = weep loudly, long wail</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deng manangis maskakeduk."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">deng manangis maskakeduk.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong ame bawa sang Tuhan Yesus pi mangada sang gubernor Pilatus<bt>They take the Lord Yesus to face gubernor Pilatus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:1-2, 11-14; Lukas 23:1-5; Yohanis 18:28-38)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="15" />
      <v n="1" />Papagi sakali, samua orang di pangadilan tu, basakongkol ko mau bekin mati sang Yesus. Ais dong ika bawa sang Dia pi mangada sang gubernor Pilatus.<bt>Very early (the next) morning, all the people in that court, they plotted to kill Yesus dead. Then they tied/bound bringing Him to face gubernor Pilatus. [DISCOURSE (referent tracking): the four groups are undertranslated here, because the style is too heavy in the RL, and the info is retrievable from last section.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="barunding ; sakongkol = plot evil"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">barunding ; sakongkol = plot evil</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="barunding kilat sa. Ju dong ika"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">barunding kilat sa. Ju dong ika ame sang Yesus deng rante, abis</Message></Annotation><v n="2" />Waktu dong sampe di gubernor, dia so'al sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana? Batúl Lu ni, orang Yahudi pung Raja, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>When they arrived at the gubernor, he took issue with Yesus saying, &lt;&lt;How about it? Is it true that You here are the King of the Yahudi people, ko?&gt;&gt; [+confirmative tag]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Batúl. Pak gub su omong batúl tu.&gt;&gt;<bt>Yesus replied saying, &lt;&lt;True! Pak/Mr gub is speaking true there.&gt;&gt; [STYLE: appropriate vocative to govt authority.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="3" />Ais kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos ba'omong deng gubernor bilang, &lt;&lt;Ini orang su bekin sala sonde sadiki!&gt;&gt; Ju dong kasi tau Dia pung sala-sala dong, satu-satu.<bt>Then the *chief priests talked with the gubernor saying, &lt;&lt;This person has done wrongs which are not few!&gt;&gt; And they told His sins, one by one. [STYLE: understatement: ‘not a few’ = many]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="4" />Ais gubernor tanya ulang sang Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Lu sonde dengar dong pung omong tu? Dong su kasi sala bam-banya sang Lu. Coba Lu balas dolo!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the gubernor asked Yesus again saying, &lt;&lt;Don't You-sg hear wht they are saying? They are making many accusations against You. You should try and respond!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="5" />Ma Yesus sonde manyao apa-apa, sampe itu gubernor taheran-heran.<bt>But Yesus did not respond anything at all, to the point that the gubernor was amazed.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Gubernor Pilatus putus hukuman mati sang Tuhan Yesus [\s2]<bt>Gubernor Pilatus decides a death sentence/punishment for the Lord Yesus [\s2]</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:15-26; Lukas 23:13-25; Yohanis 18:39-19:16)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="6" />Tiap taon, kalo orang Yahudi dong bekin pesta Paska, orang banya dong biasa pili satu orang bui, ko gubernor kasi lapás sang dia.<bt>Each year, if/when the Yahudi people were making the Paska/Passover feast, many people usually chose one jail person, so that the governor would free him.</bt><v n="7" />Itu waktu, ada satu orang bui, nama Barabas. Dolu dong tangkap sang dia deng dia pung tamán dong, tagal dia malawan pamarenta Roma, deng dia ju bunu orang.<bt>That time, there was a jail person named Barabas. Previously they had captured/arrested him and his friends/companions, because he opposed/rebelled against the Roma government, and he also killed person/s (generic). [EXEG: Fee &amp; Strauss 2007]</bt><v n="8" />Tagal itu pesta Paska su deka-deka, andia ko banya orang pi gubernor Pilatus ko batarea bilang, &lt;&lt;Pak gubernor! Hari Paska su datang! Kalo bisa, na, pak gub tolong kasi lapás satu orang bui sama ke biasa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Because the Paska feast was very near, that is why many people came to gubernor Pilatus to shout out saying, &lt;&lt;Pak/Mr gubernor! Paska day is here! If possible, na, pak/Mr gub please free a jail person like usual/normal/customarily do!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deka-deka = fast approaching"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">deka-deka = fast approaching</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Ais gubernor manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Naa! Beta mau kasi lapás sang sapa? Karmana kalo beta lapás bosong orang Yahudi pung Raja ni? Bosong satuju, ko?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the gubernor responded saying, &lt;&lt;Naa! Whom should I free? How.about I free this Raja of the Yahudi people? You-pl agree, right?&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="10" />Gubernor omong bagitu, padahal dia su tau kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos ada bawa sang Yesus kasi dia, tagal dong ada binci talalu sang Yesus.<bt>The Gubernor spoke like that, however he already knew that the chief priests had brought Yesus to him, because they hated Yesus excessively.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="padahal"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">padahal</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kasi sang dia karna dong iri"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">kasi sang dia karna dong iri hati.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="11" />Ma itu bos-bos agama tusu-tusu itu orang banya dong, ko dong samua minta sang gubernor bilang, &lt;&lt;Botong sonde mau sang Dia! Kasi lapás sang Barabas sa!&gt;&gt;<bt>But those religion bosses/leaders kept poking/inciting (to persuade negatively) that crowd, so that they all request the gubernor saying, &lt;&lt;We-exc don't want Him! Just free Barabas!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="hasut = goso-goso beking panas orang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">hasut = goso-goso beking panas orang pung hati ; buju = persuade; tusu-tusu = poke to persuade neg. (Rote = tusu-hai [hai = ikan pari pung ekor])</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais gubernor tanya ulang bilang, &lt;&lt;Kalo bagitu, beta musti bekin apa sang Yesus, yang dong pange sang Dia, &lt;Raja orang Yahudi&gt; ni?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the gubernor asked again saying, &lt;&lt;If that's the case, what must I do with this Yesus, whom they call Him, &lt;Raja of the Yahudi people&gt;?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="13" />Ju dong samua batarea rame-rame bilang, &lt;&lt;Bekin mati sang Dia sa! Paku Dia di kayu palang!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they all shouted out enthusiastically saying, &lt;&lt;Just kill him! Nail him on a *cross!&gt;&gt; [KT: the Gk term, like the English indicates crossed pieces of wood. Avoid meaningless religious terms like Arabic or Portuguese loans that don't convey any meaning or description. The Gk does.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kayu salib = shape widely known,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">kayu salib = shape widely known, children know from graves</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais gubernor tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Ko Dia pung sala apa? Beta su pareksa sang Dia, ma beta sonde dapa Dia pung sala apa-apa!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then the gubernor asked saying, &lt;&lt;[+protest, objection] what is His wrong? I have examined Him, but I can't find any wrongs of His at all.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="this ko is Q particle implying"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">this ko is Q particle implying protest (?)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma dong samua batarea lebe karás lai bilang, &lt;&lt;Bekin mati sang Dia! Paku Dia di kayu palang suda!&gt;&gt;<bt>But they all yelled even louder saying, &lt;&lt;Kill Him dead! Nail Him on a cross (imperative)!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="kayu palang = cross bar/beam, but"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">kayu palang = cross bar/beam, but also used for roadblock</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Tagal gubernor mau bekin sanáng orang banya dong pung hati, andia ko dia lapás sang Barabas, iko dong pung mau. Ais dia parenta orang jaga dong, ko pi firuk sang Yesus pake cambuk.<bt>Because the gubernor wanted to make the crowd's livers' happy, that is why he freed Barabas, according to their will. Then he ordered his guard people, so that they whipped Yesus with a whip.</bt><note reference="15:15" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tantara Roma dong pake cambuk yang bekin dari tali kulit binatang barapa urat. Ais dong ika tulang tajam, ko, tima tajam di tali pung ujung-ujung. Kalo firuk ulang-ulang pake itu cambuk, kulit dong takupas buang.<bt>The Roma soldiers used a whip that was made from several strips of skin/leather rope. Then they tied sharp bones or sharp lead on the ends of the ropes. If/when whipped over and over using that whip, skin can be peeled off/away.</bt></note>Firuk abis, ju tantara dong ame bawa sang Yesus, ko mau pi paku bekin mati sang Dia di kayu palang.<bt>After they were finished whipping, then the soldiers took Yesus to go kill Him on a cross. [GRAMM: it is important that this is irrealis purpose here, since they don't actually crucify him until starting at 15:33]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="need picture of cambuk??"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">need picture of cambuk??</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tantara dong hantam barmaen sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>Soldiers repeatedly do.bad.things to the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:27-31; Yohanis 19:2-3)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="16" />Ais itu, tantara dong hela bawa sang Yesus di dong pung kintal bésar.<bt>After that, the soldiers pulled bringing Yesus to their big yard.</bt><note reference="15:16" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tantara dong pung tampa tu, dong pange dalam bahasa Latin bilang, <span class="Italic">praetorium.</span> Itu tantara dong pung tampa sandiri di kompleks ruma jabatan.<bt>That place of the soldiers, they called in the Latin language saying <span class="Italic">praetorium</span>. It is the army's own place in the complex of the official (governor's) house.</bt></note>Di situ dong pange ame dong pung tamán satu batalyon.<bt>There they called their friends from one batalyon (loan: +/- 750 people). [EXEG: Roman ‘cohort’ was around 400-600 men. Avoid the impression there were 2 men and a few of their mates. The impression is of public humiliation—as happens with many armies of occupation.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="cohort = 400-600 men; BI regu"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">cohort = 400-600 men; BI regu = 9-10; platon/peleton = (3+ regu), +/- 35 orang; kompi = (4+ platon), +/- 150 orang; batalyon/batalion = (5 kompi) +/- 750 orang; brigade/brigif (brigade infantri) = (+/- 5 batalion) +/- 3750 orang; divisi = (+/- 5 brigif), +/- 18750 orang;</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-08-19 07:36:41Z" /></Annotation><v n="17" />Ju dong kasi pake sang Yesus satu baju panjang warna ungu sama ke raja dong biasa pake. Ais dong ame pohon baduri pung takis ko mala'e bekin topi. Ju dong tendes itu topi baduri pi Yesus pung kapala, ko maen-maen bekin sama ke dong mau angka raja baru pake topi jabatan.<bt>Then they made Yesus wear a long purple robe like kings usually wear. Then they took a thorn tree/bush small branches to braid/twist to make a hat. Then they mashed down that thorn hat on Yesus' head, to pretend like they were elevating/installing a new king using an official hat. [EXEG: Mark says ‘purple’; Matthew says ‘scarlet’. Preserve the differences. Many think it was probably between the two colours.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mala'e = anyam, braid (hair); takis"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">mala'e = anyam, braid (hair); takis = small branch cabang kici-kici; piru = headcloth (ifutin)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <fig path="HK-LB\LB00321C.tif" rtfFormat="width:6.0cm;textWrapping:around:horizontalPosition:left" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="18" />Ju dong samua kasi hormat maen-maen sang Dia, deng bilang, &lt;&lt;Tabe raja orang Yahudi!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then they all pretended to honour Him, and said, &lt;&lt;Honour to the king of the Yahudi people!&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tabe = tabea, hormat, salam (kirim"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">tabe = tabea, hormat, salam (kirim tabe sang dia)</Message></Annotation><v n="19" />Ju dong sangaja tondo kasi hormat di Yesus pung muka. Ais dong sumbur luda ulang-ulang di Dia pung muka. Ais dong kadeluk ulang-ulang sang Dia deng kayu.<bt>And they mockingly/teasingly bowed to show honour in front of Yesus' face. Then they spit repeatedly at/on His face. Then they beat Him on the head repeatedly with wood.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sumbur = spit; hungga = lempar;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">sumbur = spit; hungga = lempar; kadeluk = hit/beat on head</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju dong hungga Dia pung kapala"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Ju dong hungga Dia pung kapala pake tongkat,</Message></Annotation><v n="20" />Dong barmaen abis sang Dia, ju dong buka buang itu baju panjang. Ju dong kasi pake ulang Dia pung pakean. Ais ju dong bawa sang Dia pi kaluar kota Yerusalem, ko pi paku tagantong sang Dia di kayu palang sampe mati.<bt>They finished playing with/mocking Him, then they took off/away that long robe. And they made Him wear His clothes again. Then they took Him to go outside Yerusalem city, to go nail hanging Him from a *cross until dead. [NOTE to daughter translations: irrealis /ko/ is essential here. This is intent. He is not nailed and killed until next two sections.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong paku sang Tuhan Yesus di kayu palang<bt>They nail the Lord Yesus on the *cross</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:32-44; Lukas 23:26-43; Yohanis 19:17-27)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="21" />Waktu dong jalan kaluar dari Yerusalem, di tenga jalan dong katumu satu orang dari kota Kirene. Dia pung nama Simon. Dia tu, Aleksander deng Rufus pung bapa. Dia baru mau maso pi Yerusalem, ma tantara dong pegang ame sang dia, ko paksa pikol Yesus pung kayu palang.<bt>When they were walking leaving Yerusalem, in the middle of the road/journey they met a person from Kirene city. His name was Simon. He was Aleksander and Rufus' father. He was just entering Yerusalem, but the soldiers grabbed him, to force him to shoulder carry Yesus' cross. [DISCOURSE: Gk use of A and R indicates these two are known to Mark's audience.]</bt><note reference="15:21" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Roma 16:13</note><v n="22" />Dong hela bawa sang Yesus sampe di satu tampa, nama Golgota. (Dia pung arti bilang, &lt;tampa tulang kapala&gt;.)<bt>They pulled bringing Yesus to a place, named Golgota. (Its meaning saying, &lt;head bone place&gt;.) [EXEG: Note that hymns call it a ‘hill’, but scripture doesn't. Avoid reading that into the text.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="tulang kapala = tengkorak;"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">tulang kapala = tengkorak;</Message></Annotation><v n="23" />Di situ, dong mau kasi minum sang Yesus anggor asam yang su campor deng obat, ko biar Dia bisa tahan saki. Ma Yesus sonde mau minum.<bt>There they wanted to give Yesus a drink of sour grape/wine that was mixed with medicine, so that He could stand the pain. But Yesus did not want to drink it. [EXEG: Gk ‘myrrhed wine’ for ‘stupefying’, see LN, TN, TH, TRT, CONNOT]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="can't use BI mur here cause"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">can't use BI mur here cause mur means dregs/ampas of laru</Message></Annotation><v n="24-25" />Ais dong paku malenggang sang Yesus di kayu palang. Ju dong kasi badiri itu kayu palang, kira-kira jam sambilan pagi. Ju tantara dong hela lot ko mau tau sapa yang dapa Yesus pung pakean.<bt>Then they nailed belly-up/spread-eagled Yesus on the cross. Then they made that cross stand up, approximately nine o'clock in the morning. Then the soldiers drew lots in order to know/find out who would get Yesus' clothes. [EXEG: ‘spread-eagled’ not required, but helpful for people who don't know much about crucifixion. How would your language talk about ‘9 o'clock’? Be as precise as their system allows, to help the apologists in years to come. KT: ‘cast lots’, ‘draw lots’, or functional equivalent. It occurs in several books and contexts, for seeing who gets something.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="paku malenggang = belly-up, spread-eagled \ant"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">paku malenggang = belly-up, spread-eagled \ant = matono = srpead out face down (\va mantono); buang undi = (BI) banya cara, e.g. doi toss coin to see if it comes up heads or tails, tulang, batu, kayu, make a mark, see who tooses closest; buang lot = cast lots / hela lot = draw straws ; onde-onde = (kue)</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:24" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 22:19</note><v n="26" />Ais dong tulis di satu papan, ko paku di Yesus pung atas kapala bilang,<bt>Then they wrote on a board, and nailed it above Yesus' head saying,</bt></p>
    <p class="Line Centered" usfm="qc">
      <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Ini, orang Yahudi pung Raja&gt;&gt;</span>
      <bt>&lt;&lt;This is the Yahudi people's King&gt;&gt;</bt>
    </p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Dong pake itu alasan ko hukum sang Yesus.<bt>They used that basis/reason to sentence/punish Yesus. [EXEG: ‘charge against him’; purpose of board explicated because of UNS confusion.]</bt><v n="27" />Di situ, dong ju paku kasi mati dua orang parampok. Satu di Yesus pung sablá kanan; satu di Dia pung sablá kiri.<bt>There, they also nailed to death two robbers. One on Yesus' right side; one on His left side.</bt><v n="28" />[Deng bagitu dong iko apa yang su tulis memang di Tuhan Allah pung Tulisan bilang, &lt;&lt;Dong bekin sang Dia sama ke orang jahat.&gt;&gt;]<bt>[In that way they followed/were in accord with what was already written in God's Writings saying, &lt;&lt;They made Him like an evil person.&gt;&gt;] [NOTE to daughter translations: if possible, make this come out more towards ‘criminal, lawless’, and less towards ‘sinner’ to better reflect the Gk.]</bt><note reference="15:28" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling tua dong, sonde tulis ini ayat 28.<bt>The oldest Yunani language writings do not write this verse 28.</bt></note><note reference="15:28" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Yesaya 53:12</note></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01836b.tif" rtfFormat="width:11.0cm;verticalPosition:top" />
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="29" />Samua orang yang jalan lewat di situ lia Yesus tagantong di itu kayu palang. Ju dong goyang-goyang kapala ko olok bekin malu Yesus bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoi! Lu bilang Lu bisa kasi rubu Tuhan Allah pung Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ais kasi bangun ulang dalam tempo tiga hari, to?<bt>All the people who walked by there saw Yesus hanging on that cross. And they shook their heads to mock/ridicule make Yesus embarrassed/ashamed saying, &lt;&lt;Hoi! [+critical] You-sg said You can destroy God's *Temple, then rebuild it again in three days time, to? [+tag, expecting affirmation] [NOTE to daughter translations: make sure this ‘hang’ matches what they did nailed on crosses, and doesn't evoke ‘hung suspended with a rope by the neck’.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="putar muka = look away; goyang"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">putar muka = look away; goyang kapala ; olok = ejek, ridicule, tease, spite</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:29" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 22:8, 109:25, Markus 14:58, Yohanis 2:19</note><v n="30" />Coba Lu turun dari itu kayu palang, ko kasi lapás Lu pung diri suda! Kalo bagitu, baru botong parcaya memang Lu ni, Tuhan Allah pung Ana.&gt;&gt;<bt>Try to get down from that cross, to free yourself (imperative)! If its like that, only then we-exc will really believe You-sg here are God's Child.&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="31" />Kapala agama Yahudi dong pung bos-bos deng guru agama dong ju olok sang Yesus, deng ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia su kasi salamat orang laen, ma sonde bisa kasi salamat Dia pung diri sandiri!<bt>The chief priests and religious teachers also mocked/ridiculed Yesus, and spoke (recip/among themselves/to each other) saying, &lt;&lt;He has *saved/rescued other people, but He can't save his own self!</bt><v n="32" />Dia bilang Dia pung diri, &lt;Kristus&gt;, andia Orang yang Tuhan Allah su janji memang dari dolu. Orang laen bilang, Dia ni orang Isra'el pung Raja. Kalo batúl bagitu, na, biar Dia turun dari kayu palang ko kotong lia dolo. Bagitu, baru kotong bisa parcaya sang Dia.&gt;&gt;<bt>He called Himself &lt;Kristus&gt;, that is the person whom God has promised beforehand from long ago. Others say, He here is the King of the Isra'el people. If it's truly like that, na, let Him get down from that *cross so that we-inc can see. [If] Like that only then we can believe in Him.&gt;&gt;</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="subu = sebut, kasi nama, rafer"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">subu = sebut, kasi nama, rafer</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Itu dua orang yang tagantong sama-sama deng Yesus di kayu palang, ju iko olok sang Dia.<bt>Those two people that were hanging together with Yesus on the cross, also followed/participated in mocking/ridiculing Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus mati<bt>Lord Yesus dies</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:45-56; Lukas 23:44-49; Yohanis 19:28-30)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="33" />Ais itu, galáp gulita tutu ame itu tampa dari tenga hari sampe jam tiga sore.<bt>After that, deep darkness covered that place from mid day to 3 o'clock in the afternoon. [NOTE to daughter translations: use the closest and most precise way of talking about 3pm, but it needs to be natural.]</bt><v n="34" />Pas jam tiga sore ju, Yesus batarea pake bahasa Aram bilang, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Eloi! Eloi! Lema sabaktani?&gt;&gt;</span> (Dia pung arti bilang, &lt;&lt;Beta pung Tuhan! Beta pung Allah, é! Akurang ko Papa bale balakang kasi tenga sang Beta bagini?&gt;&gt;)<bt>Exactly at three o'clock in the afternoon, then Yesus yelled in their Aram language saying, <span class="Italic">&lt;&lt;Eloi! Eloi! Lema sabaktani?&gt;&gt;</span> (It's meaning saying, &lt;&lt;My Lord! My God, é! Why is Father/You turning your back abandoning Me like this?&gt;&gt;) [NOTE to daughter translations: the Aramaic phrase that most people have memorised (from the Textus Receptus?) has the vowels wrong, according to the Gk transcription in Mark and Matthew.]</bt><note reference="15:34" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 22:2</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="35" />Ada barapa orang deka-deka di situ dengar Yesus pung suara tu. Ju dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Hoi! Bosong dengar dolo. Dia ada pange sang Elia, Tuhan pung jubir dolu tu!&gt;&gt;<bt>There were several people close by there hearing that voice of Yesus'. Then they said, &lt;&lt;Hoi! You-pl listen! He's calling Elia, that *prophet/spokesperson of the Lord's from long ago!&gt;&gt;</bt><v n="36" />Ais satu orang lari-lari pi ame lumut ko calóp maso pi dalam anggor asam. Ju dia tusu itu lumut deng ujung tongkat, ju sorong pi Yesus pung bibir ko Dia isap. Ais, itu orang omong bilang, &lt;&lt;Tunggu ko kotong lia coba! Sapa tau nanti Elia datang ko kasi turun sang Dia dari itu kayu palang.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then one person ran to get moss to dip it in sour grape/wine. Then he speared that moss on the end of a stick, and extended it to Yesus' lips so that He could suck. Then that person spoke saying, &lt;&lt;Wait so we'll see! Who knows maybe Elia will come to get Him down from that cross.&gt;&gt; [NOTE to daughter translations: Gk. is ‘sea sponge’, not moss. Use the sponge term if you have one. KM UNS's didn't know the rare term for sponge.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="bunga karang = sponge, coral (various)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">bunga karang = sponge, coral (various) and in BI translations, but UNS not know; lumut = moss</Message></Annotation><note reference="15:36" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lagu Puji dong 69:22</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="37" />Ais Yesus batarea ulang lai, ju Dia mati.<bt>After that Yesus yelled again, then He died.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="38" />Di Ruma Sambayang Pusat, ada satu gorden bésar tagantong ko pele Tuhan Allah pung Kamar Paling Barisi. Parsís Yesus pung putus napas, ju itu gorden tarabe putus bagi dua, dari atas sampe bawa.<bt>In the *Temple, there was a big curtain hanging to block off God's *Most Clean/Holy Room. Exactly when Yesus died [euphemism: his stopping of breath, tested with UNSs], then that curtain ripped separating dividing into two, from the top to the bottom.</bt><note reference="15:38" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Kaluar dari Masir 26:31-33</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="39" />Di Golgota, ada satu komandán jaga yang badiri deka Yesus pung kayu palang. Waktu dia lia Yesus pung mati, dia takuju. Ais dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Ini Orang ni, memang batúl-batúl Tuhan Allah pung Ana, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>At Golgota, there was a commander guard who stood near Yesus' cross. When he saw Yesus' death, he was startled/amazed. Then he said, &lt;&lt;Awii [+amazement]! This Person here, really was truly God's Child, ó!&gt;&gt; [EXEG: Shift in location made explicit.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="He'ela! = INTERJ orang dapa lia"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">He'ela! = INTERJ orang dapa lia kita beking tara bae. Gotcha! ; Awii =signals kagum, impressed</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-08-19 23:28:30Z" /></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="40-41" />Deng ada parampuan barapa orang yang iko lia Yesus pung mati dari jao. Dong tu, yang dolu layani sang Yesus dong di Galilea. Andia, Salome, Maria dari negrí Magdala, deng Maria yang satu lai (andia Yakobis muda deng Yoses<bt>And there were several women who followed watching Yesus' death from far. Those were the ones who had served Yesus previously in Galilea. That is, Salome, Maria from the village Magdala, and another Maria (that is young Yakobis' and Yoses</bt><note reference="15:40-41" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Ada tulisan bahasa Yunani saparu bilang &lt;Yoses pung mama&gt;, yang laen bilang &lt;Yosef pung mama&gt;.<bt>Some Yunani language writings say &lt;Yoses' mother&gt;, others say &lt;Yosef's mother&gt;.</bt></note>pung mama), deng banya parampuan laen dong yang iko datang di Yerusalem sama-sama deng Yesus.<bt>mother), and many other women who followed coming to Yerusalem together with Yesus. [NOTE to daughter translations: many people do not know that ‘Magdal-ena’ means ‘woman from Magdala’. ‘Magdal-eno’ would be ‘male from Magdala. For example ‘Mexic-ana’ is ‘female from Mexico’; ‘Mexic-ano’ is ‘male from Mexico’. ‘Americ-ana’ is ‘female from America’, etc.] [DISCOURSE: reordered background-foreground info more naturally.]</bt><note reference="15:40-41" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Lukas 8:2-3</note></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Dong kubur sang Tuhan Yesus<bt>They bury the Lord Yesus</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 27:57-61; Lukas 23:50-56; Yohanis 19:38-42)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="42-43" />Ais itu, ada satu orang cari jalan ko mau kasi turun Yesus pung mayat dari itu kayu palang. Itu orang pung nama Yusuf. Dia dari kota Arimatea. Deng dia ju anggota majelis di pangadilan agama Yahudi. Dia pung hati bae. Deng dia ada tunggu-tunggu Tuhan Allah pung parenta datang.<bt>After that, a person sought a way to take down Yesus' corpse from that cross. That person's name was Yusuf. He was from Arimatea city. And he was also a member elder in the Yahudi religion court. His liver was good (=he was a good man/man of good character). And he was waiting-waiting for the arrival of God's rule/governing. [DISCOURSE: 42-43 reordered to get background-foreground and chronology sorted right according to RL patterns.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="batunggu = ba here is DUR"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">batunggu = ba here is DUR</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-08-19 23:39:36Z" /></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Yesus pung mati tu, pas deng hari Jumat. Dia pung beso kaná deng orang Yahudi dong pung hari sambayang. Andia ko itu hari Jumat tu, Yusuf mau kasi turun lebe dolo Yesus pung mayat. Ais dia bekin barani dia pung hati, ko pi minta Yesus pung mayat di gubernor Pilatus.<bt>Yesus' death there, was exactly on Friday. It's tomorrow/next day would be the Yahudi people's worship day. That is why on that Friday, Yusuf wanted to first take down Yesus' corpse. So he made his heart brave, to go request Yesus' corpse from gubernor Pilatus. [BACKGROUND: Jewish Sabbath started at sundown on Friday evening.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Hari su mulai malam waktu Yusuf"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Hari su mulai malam waktu Yusuf</Message></Annotation><v n="44" />Waktu gubernor dengar Yusuf minta bagitu, ju dia heran. Ais dia bilang, &lt;&lt;Awii! Ko itu orang su mati bagitu capát! Beta kira sonde mungkin bagitu, ó!&gt;&gt;<bt>When the gubernor heard Yusuf's request like that, he was surprised. And he said, &lt;&lt;Awii! [+amazement] That person has died that quickly! [+inquiry] I didn't think it's probable like that, ó!&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: ‘Pilate wondered’ made into direct speech—processed and accepted by several consultants.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ju dia suru orang ko pi pange itu komandán, ko dia tanya bilang, &lt;&lt;Karmana, é? Yesus tu, su mati, ko balóm?&gt;&gt;<bt>Then he ordered a person to go call/summon that commander, to ask him saying, &lt;&lt;How is it? That Yesus is already dead, or not yet?&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="45" />Itu komandán manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Dia memang su mati dari tadi, bapa.&gt;&gt; Gubernor dengar bagitu, ju dia kasi isin sang Yusuf ko pi ame bawa Yesus pung mayat.<bt>That commander replied/responded saying, &lt;&lt;He really is dead from earlier, father/sir.&gt;&gt; When the gobernor heard that, he gave permission to Yusuf to go take Yesus' corpse.</bt></p>
    <fig path="cook\cnt\cn01847b.tif" rtfFormat="width:8.0cm;verticalPosition:bottom">Dong bawa Tuhan Yesus pung mayat pi dalam kubur<bt>They take the Lord Yesus' corpse into the grave</bt></fig>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="46" />Ais Yusuf pi béli kaen panjang yang mahal. Tarús dia pi di Golgota. Ju dia kasi turun Yesus pung mayat dari kayu palang. Dia ju bungkus bae-bae itu mayat deng itu kaen baru. Itu waktu, dong baru abis pahat ame satu kubur di gunung batu. Ju dong koko kasi maso Yesus pung mayat pi dalam itu lobang kubur. Tarús dong guling ame satu batu plat yang bésar, ko dong tutu bae-bae di itu kubur pung pintu. Ju Yusuf dong pulang.<bt>Then Yusuf went and bought a long expensive cloth [EXEG: NLT]. Then2 he went to Golgota. And he took down Yesus' corpse from the cross. He also wrapped carefully that corpse with that new cloth. At that time, they [non-referential] had recently finished chiseling a grave in a rock mountain. Then they carried entering Yesus' corpse into that grave hole. Then they rolled a big flat rock so they could close well that grave's door. Then Yusuf (collective) went home. [DISCOURSE: Last sentence implicit-explicit to get everybody sorted out. RL discourse.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="baru abis pahat ame satu kubur"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">baru abis pahat ame satu kubur ??</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2014-08-19 23:48:50Z">[</Message></Annotation><Annotation class="General" selectedText="deng kaen baru yang mahal."><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">deng kaen baru yang mahal.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="47" />Itu waktu, Maria dari Magdala deng Maria yang laen (andia Yoses pung mama), ju ada iko sampe di situ. Dong dua lia ko inga bae-bae itu tampa yang dong su taro Yesus pung mayat tu.<bt>At that time Maria from Magdala and the other Maria (that is Yoses' mother), also were following to there. They two looked to carefully remember that place where they put/placed that corpse of Yesus. [NOTE to daughter translations: some lgs distinguish between ‘bury (put a body down into soil)’ and ‘place (the body horizontally into a shelf in a rock hole’. CHECK yours carefully and don't mix them up.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus idop kambali!<bt>Lord Yesus lives again/comes back to life!</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 28:1-8; Lukas 24:1-12; Yohanis 20:1-10)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <c n="16" />
      <v n="1" />Dia pung beso, hari Sabtu, andia orang Yahudi dong pung hari sambayang. Waktu matahari su tanggalám, Maria dari negrí Magdala, Maria yang laen tu (andia Yakobis pung mama), deng Salome, pi béli minya wangi, ko beso dong mau pi siram di Yesus pung mayat, iko orang Yahudi dong pung adat.<bt>The next day was Saturday, that is the Yahudi people's day of prayer. After the sun had already set, Maria from Magdala, that other Maria (that is Yakobis' mother), and Salome, went to buy fragrant oil, in order that tomorrow/the following day they wanted to go sprinkle it on Yesus' corpse, according to the Yahudi people's tradition. [EXEG: Sat after sundown they could buy things because the Sabbath was over.]</bt><v n="2" />Ais hari Minggu papagi sakali, ju dong tiga pi di itu kubur.<bt>Then Sunday really early in the morning, they three went to that grave. [EXEG: Gk: about sunrise]</bt><v n="3-4" />Di tenga jalan dong ba'omong bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Nanti sapa yang bisa tolong kasi ondor itu batu bésar dari kubur pung pintu tu? Kotong tiga sa pasti sonde kuat, ko itu batu bésar mau mati na!&gt;&gt;<bt>In the middle of the road/journey they talked with each other saying, &lt;&lt;We! [+attention] Who can help reverse back that big rock from that grave's door? We three surely aren't strong enough, because that rock is extremely big!&gt;&gt; [+obvious]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="te itu batu pung besar lai!"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">te itu batu pung besar lai! (expressing wonder) vs. ko itu batu besar sakali na! (expressing statement of declaration)</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma sampe deng sampe di situ ju, dong dapa lia itu batu su taguling.<bt>But upon arrived there, they saw that rock was already rolled (back/away).</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="sapa yang bisa tolong geser kasi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">sapa yang bisa tolong geser kasi ondor itu batu bésar dari kubur pung pintu?&gt;&gt; ...dong dapa lia itu batu su taguling buang.</Message></Annotation><v n="5" />Ais dong maso pi dalam itu kubur. Ma dong takuju mau mati, tagal dong dapa lia satu orang muda ada dudu di dong pung sablá kanan, pake pakean puti mangkilat.<bt>Then they entered that grave. But they were extremely startled, because they saw a young person sitting on their right side, wearing shiny white clothes. [NOTE to daughter translations: Don't force the /puti mangkilat/ here. /Puti barisi/ is fine. Whatever your “maximum degree of white” is.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="pake pakian puti barisi"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">pake pakian puti barisi</Message></Annotation><v n="6" />Ju itu orang muda kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Bosong sonde usa taku! Beta tau bosong datang ko mau cari Yesus dari Nasaret, yang dong su kasi mati di kayu palang tu. Dia su sonde ada di sini lai, ko Dia su idop kambali na! Mari ko bosong lia sandiri itu tampa yang dong taro Dia pung mayat tu, su kosong.<bt>Then that young person told them saying, &lt;&lt;You-pl don't need to be afraid! I know you are coming to find Yesus from Nasaret, whom they killed on that cross. He is no longer here, because2 He already lives again! [+certain] Come, so that you can see for yourselves that place where they put that corpse of Yesus, it's empty.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="ko ... na =declaration of truth"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">ko ... na =declaration of truth</Message></Annotation><v n="7" />Naa, bosong pulang capát-capát suda! Pi kasi tau sang Petrus dong bilang, Yesus su idop kambali. Dia su jalan lebe dolo pi Galilea. Nanti dong katumu deng Yesus di sana, sama ke yang dolu Dia su kasi tau memang sang dong. Naa, bosong pulang suda!&gt;&gt;<bt>Naa, [+shift to important point] you-pl go home quickly (imperative). Go tell Petrus (collective) that Yesus lives again/is alive again/has come back to life. He has already go on ahead to Galilea. Later they will meet Yesus there, same as what He told them previously. Naa, you-pl go on home (imperative)!&gt;&gt; [KT: we translate the meaning, not the words. Gk here is ‘raised’. The 1st-2nd century heresy of Docetism held that Jesus did not really die, but merely ‘swooned’, and rose/got up again. Muslims continue to hold that belief. Equivalent words for ‘raise, get up’ in most RLs are restricted to living things, such as people or animals that faint, swoon, collapse, and then regain strength and ‘arise, get up’. But it would not naturally be used for something that was dead. Tertullian, other church fathers, and the main orthodox creeds made it clear that their view was that 1) Jesus really died, and 2) Jesus came back to life from his death. So do not use words that are normally associated only with living things. Make the underlying meaning explicit: Jesus came back to life. Then everything holds together and works. This is a recurring issue throughout the NT. Think of ‘raised’ as church jargon that evokes the intended meaning, but does not say the intended meaning.]</bt><note reference="16:7" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Mateos 26:32, Markus 14:28</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="8" />Waktu itu parampuan dong lia itu tampa kosong, dong takuju. Tarús dong lari kaluar. Ais dong pulang capát-capát. Dong sonde kasi tau sapa-sapa di jalan, tagal dong taku mau mati.<bt>When those women saw that empty place, they were startled. Then they ran out. Then they went home quickly. They didn't tell anyone on the road, because they were scared to death/terrified.</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">[Tuhan Yesus katumu deng Maria dari Magdala<bt>[Lord Yesus meets with Maria from Magdala</bt><note reference="16:9-20" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling tua deng yang paling bae abis di ayat 8. Markus pung Carita tutu deng dua cara: satu yang panjang (Markus 16:9-20), deng satu laen yang pende (Markus 16:9-10). Iko orang yang pintar dong, yang mangarti bae-bae Markus pung Carita ni, ini dua bagian ni dong tulis dari balakang. Dua-dua carita so'al Yesus idop kambali dari Dia pung mati, deng orang yang parcaya sang Yesus dong pung tugas.<bt>The oldest writings in the Yunani language, and those that are best, end at verse (loan) 8. Markus' Story closes in two ways: one which is long (Markus 16:9-20), and another which is short (Markus 16:9-10). According to the opinion of knowledgable people who know Markus' story very well (=expert), these two closings/endings were written afterward. Both of them tell of the resurrection of Yesus from His death, and the work/task of people who believe in Yesus.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 28:9-10; Yohanis 20:11-18)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Hari Minggu papagi tu, Yesus pi kasi tunju muka lebe dolo sang Maria dari Magdala, yang dolu Yesus parná usir tuju setan dari dia pung diri.<bt>Early that Sunday morning, Yesus revealed himself first to Maria from Magdala, whom previously Yesus had expeled seven evil spirits from her (self).</bt><v n="10" />Dia lia abis sang Yesus, tarús dia pulang ko pi kasi tau samua orang yang dolu iko sang Yesus. Dong masi bakumpul deng hati susa, deng dong pung aer mata jato inga Yesus pung mati tu.<bt>After she finished seeing Yesus, then2 she went home to tell all the people who previously had followed Yesus. They were still gathered with sad livers and their tears were falling remembering that death of Yesus.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mete stay awake for the dead,"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">mete stay awake for the dead, not associated with daytime, but OK here if early morning not yet gone home from mete.</Message></Annotation><v n="11" />Ais Maria kasi tau sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Akurang ko bosong masi susa? Sonde usa susa lai, te Yesus su idop kambali! Tadi ni, beta baru sa katumu sang Dia na!&gt;&gt;<bt>Then Maria told them saying, &lt;&lt;Why are you-pl still (in a state of) difficulty? It's no longer necessary, cuz (elaboration) Yesus already lives again. Just now/earlier, I just met with Him!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma dong samua manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Lu omong kosong!&gt;&gt;<bt>But they all answered/responded saying, &lt;&lt;Weh [+negative element, annoyance]! You-sg are lying (empty words)!&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: direct speech]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tunju muka sang dua orang lai<bt>The Lord Yesus reveals himself to two more people</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 24:13-35)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="12" />Ais itu, Yesus pung ana bua dua orang jalan pi satu kampong. Di tenga jalan ju, Yesus pi kasi tunju muka sang dong, ma Dia su jadi laen. Ma sonde lama, te dong ju kanál sang Dia.<bt>After that, two of Yesus' disciples were walking to a village. On the road/during the journey, Yesus went to reveal himself to them, but He was different/changed. But soon they recognised Him. [DISCOURSE: Last sentence required by RL discourse. Also discussed in commentaries.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="rupa = form, model (KM)"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">rupa = form, model (KM)</Message></Annotation><v n="13" />Ais dong dua pulang pi kasi tau dong pung tamán bilang, &lt;&lt;We! Bosong dengar dolo! Tadi ni, botong baru katumu deng Yesus di jalan!&gt;&gt;<bt>They they two went home to tell their friends/companions saying, &lt;&lt;We [+attention]! You-pl listen! Just now, we-exc just met with Yesus on the road!&gt;&gt;</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Ma dong pung tamán dong samua manyao bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Bosong jang omong kosong bagitu!&gt;&gt;<bt>But their friends all answered/responded saying, &lt;&lt;Weh [+negative element, annoyance]! You-pl don't lie like that!&gt;&gt; [DISCOURSE: direct speech]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus kasi tunju muka sang ana bua dong samua<bt>The Lord Yesus reveals himself to all his *disciples</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Mateos 28:16-20; Lukas 24:36-49; Yohanis 20:19-23; Utusan dong pung Carita 1:6-8)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="14" />Ais ju Yesus katumu deng Dia pung ana bua sablás orang, waktu dong ada dudu makan. Dia togor sang dong bilang, &lt;&lt;Weh! Bosong pung kapala batu lai! Orang su kasi tau sang bosong bilang, dong su lia sang Beta deng dong pung mata biji sandiri, ma bosong sonde mau parcaya! Bosong bilang, dong samua omong kosong! Naa! Sakarang ni, Beta sandiri su datang. Beta memang su mati, ma sakarang ni, Beta su idop kambali! Naa, bosong lia sandiri sa.<bt>After that, Yesus met with his eleven *disciples when/while they were eating. He scolded them saying, &lt;&lt;Weh [+negative element, annoyance]! You-pl are very stubborn! People have told you that they have seen Me with their very own eyeballs, but you won't believe! You say, they're all lying/talking nonsense! Naa [+shift, to conclusion]! Now, I myself have come. I really died, but now, I live again! Naa, you just see for yourselves. [DISCOURSE: made direct speech. See KT note at 16:7.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="mata biji = KM very own"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">mata biji = KM very own eyeballs (vs. BI biji mata 'pupils')</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="15" />Jadi sakarang bosong musti pi kuliling di ini dunya, ko pi kasi tau samua orang Beta pung Carita Bae ni.<bt>So (consequently) now you-pl must go all around this earth, to tell all people this Good Story of Mine. [DISCOURSE: local lgs don't have quote margins in middle of same speaker. Quote margins indicate change of speaker.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="dropped prep 'about' to zero"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">dropped prep 'about' to zero</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:15" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 1:8</note><v n="16" />Orang yang parcaya sang Beta, deng dapa sarani, nanti Tuhan Allah kasi salamat sang dia, ko dia dapa tenga tarús deng Tuhan Allah di sorga. Ma orang yang sonde parcaya, nanti dia kaná hukum, deng Tuhan tola buang sang dia ko tenga tarús di luar.<bt>The person who believes in Me, and gets *baptised, God will *save/rescue him, so that he can live continually with God in heaven. But the person who doesn't believe, he will get sentenced/punished, and the Lord with push/reject throw away him so that he stay continually outside (heaven). [EXEG: explicate fuller forms of KT.]</bt><v n="17" />Deng orang yang parcaya sang Beta, nanti dong bekin tanda heran macam-macam, ko samua orang tau bilang, dong pung kuasa tu, memang datang dari Tuhan. Umpama, nanti dong bisa usir setan-setan pake Beta pung nama. Nanti Tuhan Allah bekin dong bisa ba'omong pake bahasa laen yang dong sonde tau.<bt>And the people who believe in Me, they will do *miracles/amazing signs of all sorts, so that all people will know that power of theirs, truly comes from the Lord. For example, they will be able to expel *evil spirits using My name/reputation. Later God will make them able to speak using other languages that they don't know. [EXEG: Gk. ‘new tongues’ can be a) human lgs they don't yet know [as in Acts 2], or b) speaking in tongues/spiritual lgs [as in 1 Cor 14] Going literal here could be easily misleading = made up lgs.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="***Andia ko changed to umpama"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">***Andia ko changed to umpama</Message><Message author="Chuck Grimes" created="2015-07-18 08:22:31Z">[EXEG:</Message></Annotation><v n="18" />Ais kalo dong pegang ular baracon, ko, dong minum kaná racon, dong sonde kaná calaka. Ju kalo dong taro tangan ko sambayang sang orang saki, nanti itu orang jadi bae.&gt;&gt;<bt>Then if/when they hold poisonous snake, or they drink adversely poison, they will not experience/be overcome by misfortune. And if/when they put/place hands to pray for sick people, those people will become well/healed.&gt;&gt; [KT: ‘lay hands on’ has contact with the person, and is not restricted to the head. Some church traditions use a term that has the hands facing the person about 20cm away, but that does not reflect the meaning of the Gk.] [EXEG: ‘lay hands on’ is taken as iconic part-whole ‘lay hands on to pray for’ since these complex actions are almost always associated with each other in context of sick.]</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Ju kalo dong taro tangan di"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Ju kalo dong taro tangan di atas orang saki pung kapala, nanti itu orang jadi bae.</Message></Annotation></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">Tuhan Yesus ta'angka nae pi sorga<bt>Lord Yesus is taken ascending to heaven</bt></p>
    <p class="Parallel Passage Reference" usfm="r">(Lukas 24:50-53; Utusan dong pung Carita 1:9-11)</p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="19" />Ais ba'omong deng Dia pung ana bua dong, ju Tuhan Allah angka kasi nae sang Yesus pi sorga. Di situ Dia jadi Tuhan Allah pung tangan kanan, ko Dong dua dudu parenta sama-sama.<bt>After speaking with His *disciples, then *God lift raised/took him up Yesus to heaven. There He is God's right hand/assistant, so the two of them rule/govern together.</bt><Annotation class="General" selectedText="Bagitu Yesus abis omong deng dong"><Message author="Unknown Author" created="2009-10-01 23:43:34Z">Bagitu Yesus abis omong deng dong ju Dia ta'angka naek pi di sorga.</Message></Annotation><note reference="16:19" class="Note Cross Reference Paragraph" usfm="x">Utusan dong pung Carita 1:9-11</note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="20" />Ais ju Dia pung ana bua dong iko Dia pung parenta. Dong pi mana-mana ko kasi tau samua orang Yesus pung Carita Bae. Ju Tuhan Allah kasi kuasa sang dong, ko dong bekin samua tanda heran yang Yesus su kasi tau tu. Ais banya orang parcaya sang Yesus, te dong su tau bilang, Carita Bae tu, memang batúl.]<bt>Then His disciples followed/obeyed His command/s. They went all over the place/everywhere to tell all people, Yesus' *Good Story. And God gave them power/authority so that they could do all those *miracles/amazing signs that Yesus had told them. Then many people believed in Yesus, cuz (elaboration) they knew that that Good Story is really true.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Section Head" usfm="s1">[MARKUS PUNG TUTU CARITA, IKO TULISAN DOLU-DOLU YANG LAEN<bt>[THE END OF MARKUS' STORY, FOLLOWING ANOTHER ANCIENT WRITING/s</bt><note reference="16:9-10" class="Note General Paragraph" usfm="f">Tulisan bahasa Yunani yang paling tua deng yang paling bae abis di ayat 8. Markus pung Carita tutu deng dua cara: satu yang panjang (Markus 16:9-20), deng satu laen yang pende (Markus 16:9-10). Iko orang yang pintar dong, yang mangarti bae-bae Markus pung Carita ni, dua bagian ni dong tulis dari balakang. Dua-dua carita so'al Yesus idop kambali dari Dia pung mati, deng orang yang parcaya sang Yesus dong pung tugas.<bt>The oldest writings in the Yunani language, and those that are best, end at verse (loan) 8. Markus' Story closes/ends in two ways: one which is long (Markus 16:9-20), and another which is short (Markus 16:9-10). According to the opinion of knowledgable people who know Markus' story very well (=expert), these two closings/endings were written afterward. Both of them tell of Yesus coming back to life from His death, and the work/task of people who believe in Yesus.</bt></note></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">
      <v n="9" />Waktu itu parampuan tiga orang dong su sampe di Petrus dong, ju dong kasi tau di samua-samua, so'al itu orang muda yang ba'omong di kubur tadi.<bt>When those three women had arrived at Petrus (collective), then they told everyone about that young person who had talked in the grave earlier.</bt><v n="10" />Ais ju Yesus sandiri parenta Dia pung ana bua, ko dong pi kasi tau Dia pung Carita Bae ni di samua tampa, sampe di dunya pung ujung-ujung. Carita Bae ni kasi tunju jalan ko Tuhan Allah kasi salamat orang dong dari dong pung sala-sala, ko dong idop tarús deng Dia.<bt>After that, Yesus himself commanded His *disciples, that they go tell this *Good Story of His to all places, to the ends/tips of the world. This *Good Story shows the way for God to *save/rescue people from their wrongs/sins, so that they can live continually with Him.</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p">Carita Bae ni, memang batúl sakali. Andia ko dia batahan tarús, sampe sonde tau abis-abis.]<bt>This *Good Story, is really very true. That is why it endures continually, to the point that it never ends.]</bt></p>
    <p class="Paragraph" usfm="p" />
    <fig path="maps\bible\palestin.bmp" rtfFormat="width:10.5cm" />
  </book>
</bible>